{"_id":"3Bzu6J8HPb5kAnZa","name":"045. Sister light, sister dark","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"nEIZOAbBi8YZmJDe","sort":600000,"flags":{},"content":"<section><strong>Session</strong>: 045 Sister light, sister dark</section>\n<div><strong>Played</strong>: October 24, 2020 (2020-10-24)</div>\n<div><strong>Day</strong>: Day 12, through to little hours of Day 13</div>\n<div><strong>Level</strong>: 8</div>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<h1 id=\"sister-light-sister-dark\" data-line=\"20\">Recap</h1>\n<p>[not written yet]</p>\n<h1>Transcript</h1>\n<h2 data-line=\"24\">Explosion aftermath</h2>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p data-line=\"24\">Crates look like bench-shaped shipping skids and/or mario boxes.</p>\n</section>\n<p data-line=\"30\">Rosindra and Malenka made it under the water. 8 more rushed for the pool. They are all treading water under the surface except flick. Ash is swirling over and above, falling onto the surface of the water, and the flames have died out.</p>\n<p data-line=\"32\">At first, Flick smelled smoke, and can see that there was a brief burst of sunlight in the aethereal plane -- almost as if the atmosphere of the plane had been blown away--, and the grey haze is beginning to obscure the runlight again. She takes 2 points of radiant damage as the light shines on her, and a brief stining and burning remains as blisters appear on her flesh, like a 2nd degree sunburn.</p>\n<p data-line=\"34\">Flick's relationship with spirituality / religion. Her foster parents were the equivalent of Xmas and Eastern presbyterians. her schooling was not parochial. She didn't get the sense that there was a \"there there\" when it came to religion. Her sense of the divine is more druidic, like from Gonfalon, Shoemaker Byte, and others. But her parents didn't -- she doesn't worship Silvanus. Her sense of a higher power is going to bottom out in some kind of animation of natural forces rather than a deity with temples. The gods clearly exist, but she doesn't worship them. (Silvanus is a deity in the Forgotten realms, \"Summer Oak Tree\", ) The equivalent of knowing about as much as someone who went to Catholic school but wasn't a catholic at home. Gonfalon would have made knowing about the rituals and what he observed, but it's not in her heart, and she doesn't know a ton. She's not religiously educated. She doesn't have a sense of what the other gods are.</p>\n<p data-line=\"36\">To Jean-Luc, using an incendiary device seems out of character for the Gaol Maidens. Is it Yolindar, or have they changed? He expects them to try to kill him, but this seems out of character. JL is pretty sure this wasn't meant for him; when the GM have killed someone it was a clean assassination -- even teh fact that a bounty was put out for him is weird, and that it is for 10,000gp, stroked his ego at the time, but now that things have exploded, it doesn't quite add up. JL also recognizes that if they wanted to collect the bounty they wouldn't vamporize his body. (\"10,000gp is personal level hatred; this is just business\")</p>\n<p data-line=\"38\">However, the vaporization conclusion -- although those who are in the room look very injured, none of them have disappeared into ash; it was largely from the crates and fabrics. So, a loud bang, almost like a slafh bang or cuppe dgasoline set on fire.</p>\n<p data-line=\"40\">People still have third degree burns, but no one is dead.</p>\n<p data-line=\"42\">JL climbs out of the water to see if there's anyone he can help. Two close to Vengeance's seat took the brunt of the blast; they are unconscious. the other 6 are burned but sitting up. some are crying, or screaming. none have a readily available medical kit. JL approaches one and offers a drink from his bottle. \"here, this will steady your nerves a little\"</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"44\">\n<p data-line=\"44\">Charisma check.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"46\">A little dazed and in pain, they ask \"did you bring this upon us?\" JL: i don't think so. The GM wouldn't do this; if it was to collect the bounty, it wouldn't have been a bomb. i don't think this one was about me.</p>\n<p data-line=\"48\">person 1: you may be right; i saw it wasn't under your seat that it exploded. what do you know about that creepy hairless man you brought with you? JL looks at vengeance, who is slowly beginning to suffer from alopecia. the monastery was suppressing his natural testoterone production, which meant his hairloss, such as it would have been, was ameliorated, but in the absence of that adulteration he's beginning to experience male pattern baldness. vengeance: thinks to himself: i'm more like a reverse-sampson, though, in that the more hair i lose the stronger i get. drav looks around to help. of the other people who made it into the water, 3 are healers and attend to the worst hurt. drav puts a comforting hand on one of the other's shoulders. \"Drav is not built to heal\" she apologizes. nevertheless, just acquaintance with Carlos's healing arts (in RUfus's cart) drav manages to do some superficial wound management, using some of her spell components as poultices.</p>\n<p data-line=\"53\">flick, distracted by the weirdness of the sunburn, once the spell wears off, she drops back into the material plane. after a minute. (to everyone else, flick had disappeared) reappearing, it looks like flick's hand was charred from the explosion.</p>\n<p data-line=\"55\">Rosindra, having escaped into the pool, comes up to JL. \"See what I mean, the Gaol Maidens are ruthless and will do anything to execute a bounty. we can't just hit at their HQ hoping it distracts them. we have to strike back everywhere, posted people on every port.\"</p>\n<p data-line=\"57\">JL: i don't disagree with you about the ruthlessness of the GM, but this doesn't feel like them, not that they don't deserve a bloody nose. i think we also need to expand the suspect pool.</p>\n<p data-line=\"59\">Rosindra: we don't have any other enemies in town. as far as I know we're the only game. JL: (no sense that this is a magical device? [arcana check: 17. ] looking around at the cave walls, the pitting is oddly reminiscent of that on the bracers of the burrowlings. )</p>\n<p data-line=\"62\">vengeance: i told you we should have had that armor made. flick: yeah it protected the burrowlings so effectively.</p>\n<p data-line=\"65\">JL insight -- and vengauns (\"venny\") see, in these folk, an attitude like that of when he first participated in a criminal lifestyle. they are almost faking it until they make it. they might not have experienced any deaths of their guild members so far. vengans noticed something similar.</p>\n<p data-line=\"67\">flick is absorbed with her own issues. [charisma saving throw, not late] feels compelled to get out of the ethereal plane ASAP. she has the presence of mind not to pop out on top of someone; once she's in an open space she reaches out and yanks like whipping around a flagpole on a skateboard, and drops to her knees (almost like the planes are rotating in opposite directions.) to an outside observer it's like she emerged from around a corner.</p>\n<p data-line=\"69\">Between a loud flashy explosion, a 10,000gp bounty that traveled farther than it should to a secret meeting location, and a suspicion about these people, he feels like he's being wound up to take out the gaol maidens.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"71\">\n<p data-line=\"71\">14 insight.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"73\">That's a possibility. It's also a possibility that whoever did this didn't fully understand the consequences of whatever they were setting up. JL is now significantly distrustful. But he still wants to take out the Gaol Maidens, since they are his enemy. He asks Rosindra if she has any leads on where the Gaol Maidens are.</p>\n<p data-line=\"75\">Rosindra: Of course I do, I wouldn't have asked you to go attack their HQ if I didn't have some kind of plan. I know they are stationed in one of the sandstone coves in the estuary. I can provide you wtih a map with landmarks.</p>\n<p data-line=\"77\">JL: (snidely) I guess I'm lucky that that map didn't get burned up. Rosindra: well i have it on my person and I made it into the water, and it's in this sealed tube ! JL: If you give me the map, I'll make sure they Rosindra: Is it just you four? JL: do you think we'll need more than that. I guess we could leave the monk at home.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"83\">\n<p data-line=\"83\">Performance check. 6. womp womp.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"85\">Rosindra seems to be distracted by other things; the trackers said there was a dozen or half a dozen people. JL [sadie was barking] Rosindra: you have until tomorrow evening, when we're expecting the next ships</p>\n<p data-line=\"89\">Flick: I have seen the natural ways you can keep a conflagration in a bottle, and this was not that. I went somewhere where nothing on this plane should be able to touch me , but some kind of terrible heat from that flare found me in the ether. JL: is it possible, flick, that you \"brought the heat\" with you when you ported? Flick: good ... question. and she falls into thought. \"I take my clothes with me, and what I'm carrying. one time i pulled aphelia. JL: it may be worth checking back with the dwarves at the library flick: if i did it just as it was exploding, maybe some of the principle carried the heat with it.</p>\n<p data-line=\"95\">Meanwhile Malenka approaches Flick. She looks at her and Jean-Luc. \"I didn't know that you had an upir with you.\" chhaaaaaaa! Flick: I'm not one of those, mam. Malenka looks at your burns. \"These aren't from the blast, as you can see -- flicks burnsn look like blisters, whereas the others are singed.\" JL looks at Vengeance to see if he caused it in some way. V: On the whole, I've been quite impressed with the show. It's a great way to welcome people. At the monastery, it wasn't a party unless at least 6 people ended up badly burned. and 19 need to be unconscious. we have never reached that number Malenka: Were these search parties, where those you ended up hunting were burned? Vengeance: This would be your average tea party Malenka: Because the tea was so hot? Vengeance and Malenka talk about ligatures and ligation.</p>\n<p data-line=\"106\">Drav inspects the residue on the cave walls. When she was in the Ten-Axe archives, she came across materials illustrating zinc mining. she sees indications of a zinc ore [alloy] with a metal that she's never seen before. it looks like it might have been this material that produced the flame.</p>\n<p data-line=\"110\">JL could probably connect that with the pitting on the bracers. He keeps that to himself. JL: given the danger, i think we should part ways. we'll head to the gaol maidens, you shouold get to a safehouse, and you can contact us after tomorrow night, Rosindra: yes, i'll be able to find you at the majesty's pelt JL: if nothing else, the GMs have shown an unwillingness to engage us in public. Rosindra: Pelaria be with you.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"116\">\n<p data-line=\"116\">Insight check for JL. calc 20</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"118\">It sounds like Rosindra almost catches herself saying that, but keeps going with it anyway.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"120\">\n<p data-line=\"120\">Religion checks, V with adv. Drav 24 (she's been hanging out with Carlos)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"122\">Flick isn't paying attention, and is still trying to puzzle out why Malenka thinks she's a vampire. so she doesn't hear any of this exchange.</p>\n<p data-line=\"124\">When Vengeance hears the name of the goddess Pelaria, it brings to mind an event when he was brought to the Monastery (when he was 200, 100 years ago).</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"126\">\n<p data-line=\"126\">Galen though V was born in the monastery, but he ran away from his parents because he didn't want to fish, and the monastery was the only place that would take him in. He still feels the lack of approval from his father in never having learned to fish well. And his father is dead. Vengeance isn't sure who is an elf and who's a human. maybe there will be a quest to find his real mother. but he's always been told he's a half elf and has pointy ears and he believed it. he was raised by people who weren't his birth parents.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"128\">There were plenty of literary magazines in Kriopolis, but none would accept JL's emo poetry. He went to a stem-focused shool, though, -- which is why he's so good at picking locks.</p>\n<p data-line=\"130\">100 years ago when V entered the monastery -- there was a , by that time old man, who went by the name of Ienezer. There was a big kurfuffle the day he left the monastery, declaring that he was a believer in Pelaria, and that he would do all he could to spread her gospel, and that he was renouncing the monks and their way of life forever, particularly their asceticism, and wanted to aim for a big city.</p>\n<p data-line=\"132\">Drav knows Pelaria as an urban diety; counterposed to the pastoral and the field. she stands for civil justice and virtue and morality. in these latter years, her followers can come across as hippocrites because of a Judge Dredd situation. Her followers have a strong hold on some large urban centers, esp. on the southwest of Ys.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"134\">\n<p data-line=\"134\">Her portfolio involves starbucks, multiuse districting, and gerrymandering.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"136\">The districts in her cities look like fizzlecysts. It's called Fizzlecysting here. Drav also somehow has an indepth knowledge of fizzlecysting ? she knows that it's being used in kribopolis to allocate more power to pelaria followers.</p>\n<p data-line=\"138\">Drav knows that the head of the Pelarian religion is Ibon sufla Ibogaine. if Drav talks to Vengeance, she'll recognize an abbreviation of Ibonezer into Ibon.</p>\n<p data-line=\"140\">Flick gets a drum sting for her bomb pun from a dying man. All the Pelaria stuff goes over her head, but she does watch the pantomime between Rosindra , and looks at the suspiciously treasure-map-like map. She feels like they are being played for saps. Something doesn't smell right, and it's not the burning flesh of the people we just met.</p>\n<p data-line=\"142\">Flick: (to JL) I know you want to fuck up the GMs anyway, but we need to do this on our own terms. I wouldn't follow any of the advice we just got from them. JL: I agree 100%, but we may be in \"the enemy of my enemy\" type situation. Flick: Rosindra or someone already tried to kill us and ended up killing more of her own people than us, so ... she and JL are in tinfoil hat territory territory, believing Rosindra has manufactured all of this to wind them up. JL agrees, but believes that it could nevertheless be a good thing. Flick: what objective evidence do we have that they even&nbsp;are&nbsp;the Hat Baskets JL: why do you think they are working for someone else?</p>\n<p data-line=\"149\">Vengeance: I'd really like a verm-inx right about now. Or maybe that can be a fake name for myself?</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"151\">\n<p data-line=\"151\">History checks, Flick gets a nat 20, and V scores high as well</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"153\">Flick and Vengeance both shout out: Vernix! Vernix is the last name of a very wealthy family in the Cressida area; they all of a sudden remembered Alphonse mentioning a Tishara.&nbsp;Tishara Vernix&nbsp;is the heir apparent to the Vernix fortune. If she's involved with the Hat Baskets it's likely that this is a vanity project of hers. This would make sense with it being called the 'Hat Baskets,' with all these twee contrivances -- from the outside they look like thieves activities, but they are the superficial trappings. Like a poorly researched detective novel. This Tishara is not in the meeting, however.</p>\n<p data-line=\"155\">Flick: Something needs shooting, so let's do what we came here to do. JL: I very much want to visit the GM for whatever reason. I need to figure out who they are and what they know.</p>\n<h2 id=\"a-portal-puzzle\" data-line=\"158\">A portal puzzle</h2>\n<p data-line=\"160\">Rosindra distractedly points them to a tunnel leading out. It's lit by a phosphorescent moss arranged in spirals along the walls. Some bryologist has taken their care with it. A couple hundred feet in, and see a figure blocking the way forward.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"162\">\n<p data-line=\"162\">Perception checks ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"164\">V recognizes this from the&nbsp;Origin of monsters, and Flick from her past, a nearly spherical feline zorbon completely blocking the corridor. It's mostly a ball; they can't see any arms, and there are tiny leathering toes at the bottom, and almost a beaklike mouth sitting just above the crossed ears, which fold down over its bodies.</p>\n<p data-line=\"166\">Flick hails it, and it opens its mouth so that it is coterminous with the corridor walls. Inside they see only darkness.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"168\">\n<p data-line=\"168\">Arcana checks, Drav gets a 23 and the others do very well.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"170\">They all know there is a certain trick involved here. Zorbon like this are used to seal off an entranceway. It's particularly fitting for someone who's M.O. is twee chotckies and gadgets. The opening now shows onto the street above.</p>\n<p data-line=\"172\">Flick detects that this is a portal, but not a planar portal. More like misty step in a zorbo. She rolls her eyes at the affectation and steps into it. Flick steps out, into the tunnel, again. She can see ahead of her the backs of Drav, V, and JL looking at the portal.</p>\n<p data-line=\"174\">She runs back up: Ok, that didn't work! JL has heard of similar setups. He walks backwards through the mouth. He disappears and appears again up on the street above. He is visible inside the portal.</p>\n<p data-line=\"177\">Flick: That's why you get the big bucks. JL thinks it's a bit like having your password be password.</p>\n<p data-line=\"180\">They all make their way up to street level. JL: the more I think about it, the less I think anything here has to do with me. I know the GMs are bad news, and it's worse investigating them.</p>\n<p data-line=\"183\">V dives through head first</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"185\">\n<p data-line=\"185\">Athletics check</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"187\">He falls from the top of the tunnel onto the floor, taking 5 points of bludgeoning damage from the fall against redundant flagstone forming a path. He tries sticking his arm, then his leg backwards. His then does a somersault, ending up at street level in zorbo drool.</p>\n<p data-line=\"189\">V: I'd always wanted a Zorbo for Monklemass.</p>\n<h2 id=\"midnight-streetwalkers\" data-line=\"191\">To the seacoves</h2>\n<p data-line=\"193\">JL thinks there's no way to explain what they are doing here, given that it's night time. They head north, passing by Melford's forge. There is a series of hills leading past the extant city walls. There's a guard tower which sits next to the riverrine road coming into town. There are no \"walls\" around town, only the ones adjacent to the guardhouses.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"195\">\n<p data-line=\"195\">Stealth checks. Drav gets a 6.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"197\">JL stares at everyone for not being stealthy as him, who's spent his life sneaking around warehouses. They're still 1/5 of a mile away from the tower, -- and it doesn't even seem like they are guards, but more town ambassadors. They look like they are townspeople; there are torches in sconces. It's a 60-foot stone tower. There are some milling around at ground level, there's a stable for refreshing horses. It's more of a convenience.</p>\n<p data-line=\"199\">JL thinks they need to go another mile north of the guardhouse. The river has established a straight course, bu there are still coves carved out of the sandstone. There are notable, old oak trees -- one of the trees has been carved by lightning and is nude on the right. The map points to coves on the alternate side of the river; it looks to be almost 500 feet across at this point. The river moves fairly swiftly, but bright moonlight illuminates the scene. The water level is 100 feet below.</p>\n<p data-line=\"201\">The map indicates a bridge 3 miles north of the crossing point. The Old Five Clan Road is crossed by a double bridge. A mile north of where they are it's only 300 feet wide.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"203\">\n<p data-line=\"203\">We try to figure out the limits of Flick's gloves of climbing and swimming. The DM will have to look this up later, w/r/t checks made during swimming.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"205\">Flick pulls out a bag of crushed, roasted thyme mixed with powdered quartz, whispers Gerd's name, and tosses the contents into the air.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"207\">\n<p data-line=\"207\">For reasons not entirely clear to Flick, Gerd has been manifesting as innocuous versions as things she's afraid of. He looks like a Kawaii peryton, with big anime eyes the size of a halfling, a fly speed of 60 feet and a strength of 18.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"209\">Flick greets Gerd politely and asks her to drop them on the opposite bank, above the visible lights. Gerd is looking a little more scaly or reptilian than a purely peryton-anime appearance. Flick ruminates that she doesn't understand Gerd's 'deal' very well.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"211\">\n<p data-line=\"211\">An intelligence check confirms this.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"213\">Gerd flies each of them across the river, taking just over a minute or two for each one, depositing Flick first. That side is more devoid of vegeation; there is scurb where the hills meet the river, and she can see the expanse of the sand flats reflecting moonlight, some areas sparkling. It's possible to see large quarries opened up further north and farther down the coast, with the occasional mind entrance closer.</p>\n<p data-line=\"215\">[2:00]</p>\n<p data-line=\"217\">Flick tries to spot any odd assortments of artificial light complementing the soft, pulsing orange glow being emitted from the cove.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"219\">\n<p data-line=\"219\">The DM realizes at this point that, if the cave was visibly glowing from the opposite bank, then he should not have imposed darkness rules on those entering the cave; although, as it would only affect a single perception check, he doesn't feel too bad.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"221\">Drav was able to learn about the sea cove formations while in the Ten-Axe archives. There are a few primary adits into the zinc mines. There's one mine entrance which probably leads down to this specific cove, but she can't be sure that they connect, as alot of the zinc is towards the top of the hills and the mines are relatively shallow. Drav is pretty sure they will have to belay or otherwise drop down to the level of the coves. Even dwarven survival checks would be difficult in the mines.</p>\n<p data-line=\"223\">Flick: I was hoping to encounter a stronghold, so this is a little more decentralized than I would have liked.</p>\n<p data-line=\"225\">JL walks back and forth along the shore to triangulate the horizontal position of the cove. It's not the approach he would love to take, but with the element of surprise it's not a terrible idea.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"227\">\n<p data-line=\"227\">A group survival check later ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"229\">Drav, smashing her strong fists together, works with the nimblefooted flick to pinpoint the position. By climbing down another 50 or 60 feet they could access the coves. Flick produces her rope of climbing, which knots itself up and drops down.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"231\">\n<p data-line=\"231\">Flick makes an arcana check kh.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"233\">While Flick tries to recollect the code word, the rope begins to rise into the air. She gives it play; once the rope is fully taught she looks up at the end of the rope, wondering if something has appeared there.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"235\">\n<p data-line=\"235\">A perception check with advantage later ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"237\">Flick thinks she notices a circular disturbance in the star field; almost like looking at the stars through a semi-opaque filter ('through a glass darkly').</p>\n<p data-line=\"239\">Flick: Does anyone else see this?</p>\n<p data-line=\"239\">JL: This is not my wheelhouse.</p>\n<p data-line=\"239\">Vengeance is distracted by the BDS&amp;M potential of the rope.</p>\n<p data-line=\"239\">Drav recognizes this as the spell Rope Trick encoded into the rope. It doesn't look 'activated' yet.</p>\n<p data-line=\"244\">Flick: Drav what was the last word I said before it started doing that Drav: ... 'dangit' ??</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"247\">\n<p data-line=\"247\">Drav is happy to help.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"249\">Vengeance: (pretending to be Drav): 'I'm not your secretary, Flick'</p>\n<p data-line=\"251\">Flick 'cancels' the spell without using it, and the rope assumes its orientation hanging down to the caves. Climbing down the rope, the cove opens out into a mouth, and she can see gently pulsing light far ahead of her in the cove, almost in the rhythm of breathing or a heart beating. Flick puts her back up against the wall and tugs the rope to let them know she's arrived.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"253\">\n<p data-line=\"253\">A stealth check ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"255\">Flick is silent as a clam as she attains the surface.&nbsp;JL follows as Flick adopts a forward position and nocks and arrow. With Flick as a beachhead, they are all able to alight silently. Vengeance tries to fashion his magic weeds into a balaclava for the 'heist.' There is only one eyehole (for both eyes).</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"257\">\n<p data-line=\"257\">V makes a sanity check</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"259\">He's unwittingly modelling this mask based on a monster in one of the bestiaries at the monastery (The origin of monsters, bequeathed to the reclusery upon the untimtely death of the reclusive ecclesiastical patron Wengrow Fassiltrim). A kind of cyclops, its single eyehole listed to one side, and its skull, pictured in the bestiary, was decorated with runes and etchings that no one could interpret. He feels his hands recreating the shape of that skull, and then the pure beauty of the coves brings him back to the natural world.</p>\n<p data-line=\"261\">Flick whispers 'wrap it up' to the rope, which unfastens itself, falls and winds itself up into a basketlike spiral over a period of half a minute.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"263\">\n<p data-line=\"263\">This happens at 10 feet per round.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"265\">A fairly regular path leads its way back, winding between granite columns let after the sandstone weathering and eroding around them.</p>\n<p data-line=\"267\">V put far too much material around the ears of his balaclava. The rest of them can hear the sounds of metal and rock emanating from the lit area. It sounds like tinkering or mining. JL approaches stealthily. Flick hangs back.</p>\n<h2 data-line=\"265\">Finally, a fight!</h2>\n<blockquote data-line=\"269\">\n<p data-line=\"269\">JL makes a stealth check. But it's not good enough ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"271\">JL sees, as he's creeping forward towards the light, a glint of metal shoot out from behind one of the columns and slash onto the stone column next to him, releasing an arc of sparks. Flick has kept JL within his dark vision range; too late to warn JL, but she sees the unmistakable figure of another thief or rogue, who's thrust out at JL with a shortsword.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"273\">\n<p data-line=\"273\">DK is very excited to use the Overextended feature.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"275\">JL cannot be surprised. The water feature is a melting glacial stream coming down over the sandstone.</p>\n<p data-line=\"277\">JL sees the sword, he takes his dagger and stabs into the exposed armpit, carving out a knot of muscle, and gouts of blood start spouting from under his arm. V: No! It's like attacking someone in a haunted house. Like this is all just a Tashara-Vernix production. She's really good at making things look real! JL: You can't even see me right now! V: I just know you so well that I know how you're going to react. 'Another knee-jerk reaction from Jean-Luc...'</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"282\">\n<p data-line=\"282\">Gerd acts on Flick's initiative but just after her. And you'll notice that Natural Explorer no longer makes reference to a favored terrain.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"284\">Flick has her arrow knocked, advances 30 feet, sees this thief outfitted in studded leathers, and aims for center mass. She notices that there's the chance to hit JL because of the positions of the combatants.</p>\n<p data-line=\"286\">JL: Go for it anyway!</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"288\">\n<p data-line=\"288\">24 to hit, for 19 force damage.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"290\">The thief again manages to twist out of the way of the incoming bolt, taking only a portion of the effect of the force arrow. Flick realigns and tries to sharpshoot.</p>\n<blockquote data-line=\"292\">\n<p data-line=\"292\">13 misses.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-line=\"294\">The arrow hits the column, tinking off and deflecting onto the floor. Flick grits her teeth and grimaces.</p>\n<p data-line=\"296\">Gerd rushes up next to Flick. Gerd looks interested in what's happening beyond the corner of the tunnel; Flick thinks for a minute she sees in addition to the pulsing light the shadow of wings beating. Gerd dashes forward to 'put eyes around the corner' to give it line of sight. Not being telepathic, Gerd will have to communicate somehow.</p>\n<p data-line=\"296\">&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<div data-line=\"296\">--- do i have this in the right order?</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div data-line=\"296\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">venny has to get hawk hatchet boomerang from artificer</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">- could get an artificer of level 4 , who knows or has access to the \"bound weapon\" spell, to infuse magic and permanently bind the weapon to him</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">(good quest idea?)</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">venny stands, and tries to bounce the selfkiller off a column , or a wall ?</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">rube goldberg throw</div>\n<div data-line=\"296\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">the true power of the weapon is to lure other people into using it and killing themselves</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">he gets another attack</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">throws darts (i think he can spend ki points to not attack at disadvantage)</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">he misses so badly that it misses JL too. it joins the pile of self-killer, dart, flick's arrow.&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">the teflon don over here</div>\n<div data-line=\"296\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">JL</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">attempts to stab&nbsp; with both daggers (two-weapon fighting)</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">full length of blade go into him</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">he regrets not calling for help</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">JL attacks again&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">daggers feel great in his hands; he's christened both of them</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">(something that lets him two-weapon fight with the daggers )</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">DK&nbsp; stays near and doesn't risk the OA.</div>\n<div data-line=\"296\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">Scunner: It's those idiot hat baskets! get out here!</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">DK parries one of his thrusts with the shortsword, but still gets sliced&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">- you privileged piece of shit! why do you have to bother some honest to goodness thieves just trying to make a living. go crawl back to your daddy.</div>\n<div data-line=\"296\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">JL is offended that this guy doesn't immediately recognize him.</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">flick: we've gotten wrapped up in the vanity project of some affluent ne'er-do-well</div>\n<div data-line=\"296\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">Drav's turn. [trying to figure out cover]&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">she can hear scrambling in the back indicating people are going to come out</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">he does pass, and takes cold damage because of her evocation ability</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">so he does take 6 cold damage, but doesn't get disadvantage (Frostbite)</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">fingers freeze and icy droplets freeze</div>\n<div data-line=\"296\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">[end]</div>"}
{"_id":"3Ms2n6A3hYZdHFsg","name":"005. A warm sense of nostalgia for the wordplay of half-elves","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"GF8k0MkmV1DIfHvo","sort":300001,"flags":{},"content":"<div><strong>Session</strong>: &sect;005 A warm sense of nostalgia for the wordplay of half-elves</div>\n<div><strong>Played</strong>:&nbsp;November 16, 2019 (2019-11-16)</div>\n<div><strong>Day 2 (cont.)</strong></div>\n<div><strong>Level 1 &amp; 2</strong></div>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<h1 id=\"spanstylefontsize12ptfontfamilyproximanovasansserifcolorcc0000backgroundcolortransparentfontweightboldfontstylenormalfontvariantnormaltextdecorationnoneverticalalignbaselinewhitespaceprewraprecapspan\">Recap</h1>\n<p>Eager to assemble the full might of their peers, Joan and Flick returned to Marshbout to extricate Drav from her goetic studies and bring her to the field once again. They were companioned by one Lum Gorbelly, an untidy gnoll wearing a white skullcap which party obscured a large scar traversing his face. Flick confessed to a small crush on Thaz, which Lum, a moody fellow, ignored graciously. Travel to Marshbout was short and uninterrupted, except by occasional refrications and anxieties of the parasitic nature of Thubudder Farest. Just as Joan betrayed a worrisome inclination towards fulgurous snorts, fueled by Flick's relentless hot air, the two passed through the stout walls of Famasta Monastery, into its homey cobblestoned courtyard, and took a moment to admire the heavy slate roof and cracked grotesques weighing down the <em>sobor </em>(main monastic building) and set off nicely by the creamy stucco walls and stained glass windows. After perusing a plaque detailing the invention of the <em>metum apmetum</em>&nbsp;(roughly: magic stucco) which was required to stand up to Marshbout's humid climate, and an artistically unsuccessful, if technically impressive, fresco painted by Laeffarelle Floȝed the Fleam and depicting two (perhaps allegorical) philosophers of indeterminate identity, Flick and Joan proceeded to the scriptorium and library. There finding Drav, buried in books but sanguine to continue her worldly adventures, Flick attempted to purloin one of the Doodril Library's tomes put instead was handed a package of missionary pamphlets which Joan stuffed in Drav's haversack.</p>\n<p>The three amigos returned post haste to An Sr&aacute;idbhaile, but were interrupted&nbsp;en route&nbsp;by the domain of Thuridan, a firbolg who had escaped from the fey wild in order to provide a sanctuary for trollkin. Thuridan divulged that his tiny kingdom had, as of late, been the recipient of certain unwanted intrusions by short-lived 'grotesque canine' forms; the grumic&nbsp;(clotted) puddles into which the monsters collapsed were noxious, avoided by the trollkin, and had to be burned. Ultimately this proved of far less interest than Thuridan's past, of which it became known that he was over one-thousand years old and still suffering from scars and trauma inflicted on him as a youth during cultural rites of passage. He mentioned a group of druids living north in the forest who might know more about the doglike monsters, asked the group to look out for a ggouyl (ghoul) friend of his named Bathybius who had last been seen in the west marshes, and handed Drav a burvība (leaf containing the text of a spell).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Thuridan's <em>uspusta lieta</em> (magic travelling bubble) conveniently disgorged the trio near the gnoll village, where Flick soon admitted that the trail of the hodmandods had gone cold;&mdash; unlike, however, Carlos's infatuation with a 'gnoll princess' whom he suspected had been captured with ill-intent by gnomes or dwarves. Aiming to impress, Carlos donated his healing prowess to the gnolls still convalescing from that morning's attack. To his dismay, it became clear that whatever power hurt the gnolls would require more profound intervention.</p>\n<p>Ready to move on, but soured on and suspicious of the quest to locate Lupenna, Flick nevertheless led the group northeast, towards the Grey Tongue and Castle Karn, where the gentlest path led up to an abbey surrounded by hundreds of close-set wooden crosses set in the hardscrabble ground. Entering the refectory, Joan discovered a skitting homunculus whispering \"&hellip; they want &hellip;\" into her mind, and the brave adventurers pushed their way further into the space.</p>\n<p><strong>&mdash; Ludmilla Sperski</strong></p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Petal</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: A medically adept gnoll.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Grey Tongue</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: a steep highland bordering Thubudder Farrest.&nbsp;</span></p>\n</section>\n<h4 id=\"spanstylefontsize10ptfontfamilycalibrisansserifcolor000000backgroundcolortransparentfontweightboldfontstylenormalfontvariantnormaltextdecorationnoneverticalalignbaselinewhitespaceprewrapludmillasperskispan\"></h4>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h2>Transcript</h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">something &ldquo;triggered beta&rdquo; tavern</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-46525bff-7fff-fc6c-ab47-d79fde6bbcfc\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<h1 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Proxima Nova',sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">[0] starts in gnoll camp</span></h1>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<h1 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Proxima Nova',sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">[10] depart the gnoll camp</span></h1>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Carlos as a cleric might be able to contact deity.&nbsp;</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; fo