ith the fleshbear, i'm not that surprised<br />* i just think we should be heaping praise on lupenna. i want to hear about the other dimension<br />lupenna: there's not much to tell about it. i've been in many dimensions.&nbsp; how&nbsp; old are you (to flick?). 30 years? [i thought she was 40]<br />-- the figurine is gone (turned into ephphatha)<br />lupenna: i was trying to get back here. the last time i was here; with ymenestra's help, i was able to&nbsp;<br />lupenna: you've trapped VV ? this is too much happening all at once. are you sure your time hasn't been telescoped in any way?<br />is flick tripping balls because of the goodberries ?<br />what do goodberries look like&nbsp; \"&nbsp;<br />flick: they are plump, like a table grape, but rainbowish colored, and wrinkly but not in an offputting way. (so like willy wonka grapes)<br />* so now flick has to check her bloodsugar<br />* when ephphatha disappeared, as you cast goodberry, except with your perception, you thought it was just the clouding of your vision; each place you cast the goodberries, it's flickering back and forth; looks like your hand is teleporting where the berries were, and then your hand solidifies into yourhand<br />\"they call them fingers vut i've never seen them fing\" (simpsons) -- altho fingers do fing; \"Fangen\" is german for \"to grab\"<br />ephphatha says from beyond \"the more you learn\" from flick's palm<br />lupenna: you''ll still have to live a secret life; i wasn't able to kill tantegorisch, and he wants you dead<br />flick: \"what did i ever do to him? why am i involved in any of this? who are you again?\"<br />lupenna: tantegorisch was my father's source of magic.&nbsp;<br />there came a time when T sought to increase his powers by absorbing into himself all his and his client's progeny<br />flick so you are my mother?&nbsp; how old ARE you ? what am I to you?<br />you're my godchild;&nbsp;<br />isabella: i'm your aunt. my sister is your mother.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;(isabella's half-sister is flick's mother)<br />flick: my foster parents used to frighten me with stories of the Bella. and used to use it to frighten me to do my chores<br />isabella: many years ago i left my imprint on the world in myth, but since then i've been able to change my nature (Euhemurus) -- but it's come at a terrible price, and hasn't been fully successful in the case of my brother<br />my brother is full Oni&nbsp;<br />flick is not half ogre; i'm half elf; why i've been able to resist my birthright of cannibalism. both of flick's&nbsp;<br />flick walks over to the door -- as i pass carlos, i pull him into a big bearhug<br />carlos: \"you're ok, elf\" -- then flick walks out of the room<br />carlos collects tobolux<br />joan talks to lupenna about how flick might be half-ogre<br />tobolux is not responsive --&nbsp;<br />carlos: \"it's my genii; the genii's awesome\"<br />jake: i wonder if zach wants to kill the genii to make the battle more meaningful<br />jake: there was a roll to pull lupenna out that failed; it could have failed<br />carlos: if this goes past 2 more cycles, i can't help you guys<br />flick: radiation damage was brutal<br />paros: i was damaged once<br />carlos: what happens if i uncork the genii bottle<br />* would healing word help the genii ?&nbsp;<br />* religion check&nbsp;<br />* aule will do his best<br />* casts prayer of healing (ritual) at level 3&nbsp;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; * oh you can't actually cast this as a ritual, normally<br />flick: so the reason we have to skulk around, is because of this tantegorisch character ?&nbsp;<br />genii sucked back into bottle: \"goodbye friend, see you tomorrow?!\"<br />flick: this tantegorisch character is still looking for me / us?&nbsp;<br />lupenna: he's looking for anyone who's had something to do with his power; all of usu are invested in his power and rely on it<br />flick: is this the reason i can do that ? (plane-tweaks the bed poster)<br />[should have had isabella say : \"my bed!\"]<br />* a rotten goodberry falls out of a miniature portal that happens when flick shakes the bed<br />lupenna: no ,that's all you. Tantegorisch would love to get his hands on that kind of power; i could barely squeeze my way out of ephphatha, or whatever that plane calls itself<br />joan: is T in that plane, or our world?<br />L: i haven't been able to find him anywhere<br />flick: his whole thing is to make himself bigger by sucking the life out of everyone else. let's kill him then.<br />joan: we can't find him (i'm interjecting anyway)<br />flick: joan, our business has been concluded (breakup / subplot)<br />L: i've thought about the tactic, but T has mercenaries, but he can appear and disappear without warning; if he can get to you before you're powerful enough to get away, that's the problem;&nbsp;<br />carlos: i'm just petting the bottle!<br />joan: you're sending mixed messages<br />flick: how has he managed to not find us up until this point<br />lupenna: the banishment really did do its work, but i was able to get this far in towards his center of power means it's beginning to break down. i think that's what kept you out of his vision.<br />(maybe lupenna came back at 25 &acirc;&euro;&brvbar; years?)&nbsp;<br />joan: did you know it would do this?<br />lupenna: i was supposed to be a homing beacon , but because of the power you just showed me, it allows me to travel to where that person is; your interaction with the object must have allowed it to open into a wormhole. when i gave it to you, it wasn't just a eripat agaisnst T, but also against tomsething far more evil he sought to align himself with.&nbsp;<br />joan: don't give more creepy gifts&nbsp;<br />lupenna: not even these? i think you''ll like these<br />paros is interested in the boots<br />flick: \"i'm sorry i spoke harshly to you joan\"<br />joan: it's an effect i have on a lot of people<br />flick looks around for figurine; it's gone<br />joan: wait what is more evil than tantegorisch;<br />lupenna: it's gone by many names, its followers called it bogggsush;<br />paros 20, carlos 24<br />even aule is scared of this thing; it is THE aberration.&nbsp;<br />the grey tongue used to be a mountain; the mountain was severed and cast into the sea ; it's rumored that the bay itself used to be the residence of this thing, bogsush, it was a horrendous aberration; it appeared deep within the earth and then crawled through a rock tunnel that it carved out of the world, and resided in the bay; and then it was cast out by aule and some of the gods<br />joan: the other gods did more than aule did, or whatever<br />flick: this figurine was stopping tantegorisch from seeing me; it doesn't mean he's noticed me, but i'm no longer invisible to him.<br />if tantegorisch finds you, \"i don't know flick that well\"&nbsp;<br />carlos's vision, when struck unconscious -- primordial vision -- by the plant dogs, the black shape crawling its way through red rock;&nbsp;<br />this dark shape was this monster; there's some kind of similarity there; describing it gives you shivers remembering that moment.<br />other than a long rest, flick:&nbsp;<br />* i have confidence in all of us; in the meantime he's going to find us, but there's no need to go looking for him, but we need powerful allies. we should go back to the city and dig up what we can, and see if there's anyone that wants to fuck him up.<br />* carlos: a foe of aule's is a foe of mine</section>\n</section>\n<section class=\"secret\">* paros: i've always read so much history, but this is a chance to make some<br />* flick: can i take this as a flight extension on our contract, joan?<br />flick: \"we;ve only taken two long rests\" ???</section>"}
