{"_id":"6jqw928zacNmsxim","name":"047: The Order of Rust","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"nEIZOAbBi8YZmJDe","sort":800000,"flags":{},"content":"<section><strong>Session &sect;047: The Order of Rust</strong></section>\n<section><strong>Played November 21, 2020 (2020-11-21)</strong></section>\n<section><strong>Day: </strong>Early Morning Day 14</section>\n<section><strong>Level 8</strong></section>\n<section><hr />\n<h2>Recap</h2>\n<p>Flick emerges from her elven trance with worrisome gaps in her memory from the previous evening; suspecting foul play, she wakes Jean-Luc to check Nyuaka's bag for poisons and narcotics, but they come up empty-handed. Nyuaka's nightmares and their conspiratorial whispering wake Drav and, as yet unbeknownst to the crew, a goblin rune knight named Pjorg (the) Tallhearted down the hall, who had lost consciousness after consuming light exploded from archaic symbols he was studying. As Pjorg creeps towards the encampment, Vengeance is awoken by qi with the urge to swallow and steal as many of the azurite prisms as possible, only to become distracted by the curious pendants worn by the Ruhu family which Vengeance believes an emblem of The Order of Rust. With Eldar's help, Drav blends mystically into the rock floor as Pjorg bursts into the cave; Jean-Luc and Flick disappear into the shadows. Vengeance bagpipes nearly everyone awake, but Pjorg is so conspicuous in his clanging shiny plate armor that all attention focuses on him. After a bit of parlay, everyone decides he means no harm. Nevertheless, the main crew, suspicious of the possibly amnesiogenic azurite after hearing it called the \"Forgetting Stone,\" pick up their bedrolls and return to their landing above the Strigge River.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 id=\"toc_1\">Alternate Titles</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>I'm going to address the good god-fearing people in the crowd now</li>\n<li>'What the kids are listening to' is 'writing things down'</li>\n<li>What is this Cronenberg shit?</li>\n<li>The Order of Rust</li>\n<li>Ruhu excuse us all</li>\n<li>FNNH (Freshly nerfed new hotness)</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"toc_3\">Transcript</h1>\n<h2 id=\"toc_4\">Pj&ouml;rg</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Pjorg has been underground for the last few weeks, tracing out the pattern of some ancient runes whose location he's pieces together by collecting clues and gossip relinquished to him as he's traveled across the continent. He's come down to this area even though its potention was thought to have been exhausted. The rumors were that there was still something to find of the stone runes. He's generally steered clear of people, gathering rumors from itinerant travelers and loners. At first he thought that the prevailing opinion had it right, but he eventually discovered something interesting. Pjorg isn't accustomed to being underground for this long, and has lost track of the days and nights. He'd just detected something through the walls of the cave, and had brewed up a concoction. paean to artificer path not taken. graphite, acidic exuvia from cave animal, and phosphorescent fungi, smeared it across the walls. Shining out at him, where he'd painted it, were the hints of runes he was looking for. As he peered closer, they glowed exceptionally bright, (he'd left his darkvision turned up too high), so bright that they eclipsed his vision, and he passed out.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"toc_5\">day 14, 4:am, sleeping off the snake orgy</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Wisdom saving throw.&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>(At mightnight, Flick had found a corner with a good view of the main entrance, and gone into seiza (?) and gone into a trance.) She comes out of her trance, recollecting departing Sandford, coming north up the river, being transported across the river by Gerd, but can't quite recall where she is or what happened last night. She remembers entering a face and talking with people whose faces she can't recall, having a meal, and going to sleep. She recalls the salamander, and a lizardfolk, some humans, the earthen hand that grasped Jean-Luc.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick glances around her, and looks for her companions. She sees Drav, but has to take a split-second to recognize V and Jean-Luc. They have bedded down behind a low stone wall. She can hear snoring and light breathing around them in the cave. Flick steps around lightly to get a sense of who's there.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As she sees each of the sleeping figures, she can piece together who everyone is and what role they played, and recalls the events of the evening. She sees the giant salamander sitting next to a pile of purplish-blue crystal rods she doesn't remember seeing last night. She concludes that is none of her business, further turned off by the foul-smelling mucus coating them.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Constitution saving throw : 9</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>She still doesn't feel like dry-heaving, and with her sensitive stomach, it would have caused her to throw up, but she thinks she couldn't have had that much to drink last night. And remembers that the beer was fairly watery.</p>\n<p>She immediately investigates for apothecary kits or something used to adulterate the drinks.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>They'd told her they were miningn iridium for a while, and got an early start on beer making; the vat has quite a crust, to indicate they've been drinking it for a while; if anything it is really \"stanky\" beer. She takes a sniff for infiltration of a fungus or bacterium.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A very low perception roll</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>She doesn't detect a fungal presence. Because it's so close to Lhaska, her dry heat has probably prevented a lot of these harmful organisms forming in the first place. They may even have brought the beer vat with them to the cave.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\"Somebody is fucking with us, but I'm not sure what I can do about it.\"</p>\n<p>She does notice that everyone in the family is wearing a similar necklace; it looks like a gyroscope made of copper with a green patina.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>History 20</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>She's positive that has nothing to do with clan symbols or a familiy per se. She's pretty sure it has religious or magical significance.</p>\n<p>V is curled up like a little spoon in JL's arms, as the latter had too much to drink. \"You know what, Vengeance, I know we fight a lot, but you're ok.\" He had said.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Charmisma check?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>They two are fairly close to each other, but Flick can reach a hand in, separate out JL, and jostle him awake. \"Hey JL, what do you remember about last night?\" He looks over at Vengeance and groans, but his recollection is as bad as Flick's. \"Why does it matter?\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: That's all I got, too. You're no stranger to how it feels to be drunk.</p>\n<p>JL takes a moment to reflect and realize that he's feeling a hazy fog rather than the effects of a hangover. This isn't alcohol.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Insight^&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>JL feels like his inability to remember the name \"Kriobolis\". \"I don't have a headache -- I guess it wouldn't be the first time some nefarious group drugged me. I'm sort of against just killing them all in their sleep.\"</p>\n<p>Flick: \"Yeah that hadn't even occurred to me. I was thinking\" (she gestured to Nyuka and Lhaska) \"... I get the feeling that, if anything is doing this to us, it's to be found in their satchel, and I was wondering if you could take the wheel.\"</p>\n<p>JL: Yeah, this is what I was made for.</p>\n<p>Nyaka comes close to waking up, but he freezes in just the right way, giving her just the right touch to coax her back to sleep. She shouts \"Killer whales!\" and then falls into a deep slumber. Then he starts looking through the satchel.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>ADV to riffle through.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Ignoring the baubles and trinkets, JL looks for drugs or poison. There are a few vials in there; he's seen some of this stuff. it's the Ys version of ecstasy. He leaves it in the satchel. He goes back and tells Flick that they bogarted the ecstasy, which is a party foul, but they could easily have killed us.</p>\n<p>Flick gets incredibly mad. This reminds her something that happened when she was a teen, and a bunch of the village boys tried to get her plastered in ignorance of Elven metabolism, and it went badly for them; there were broken bones, and one got lost in the woods and was never found again. It precipitated a generational feud between her family and these McmMurtons, only 2 of 3 brothers got through the night. to this day they can't be in the same area of town or they'll come to blows. Made even more awkward by the fact that it's their grandchildren and flick is still in her (relative) early 20s.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Inspiration point!</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What Flick gets out of it, is that they spiked their drinks (the only frame of reference she has for this).&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Insight check.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>JL notices how angry Flick is. From JL's perspective \"this is just what you do at parties: why would anyone be angry?\"</p>\n<p>Flick closes her eyes and tries to run through some meditative exercises. Would you rehearse for me the arguments that we shouldn't kill them. JL: If their intent was malicious, we would be dead or robbed, and they just gave us stuff to help us have a good time. How many parties have you been to? Flick: Not too many.</p>\n<p>For one of the generations, when Flick was \"the same age,\" she was a normal part of the social scene, but after they aged out, she stopped getting invited to things, so it's been a while since she's been invited to a party, and it's kindof what drove her to \"find her own fun\" in the woods.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Perception checks all around.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Drav wakes up to the sound of JL and Flick whispering conspiratorily. Pjorg wakes up to hear far down the tunnell human voices; he had thought he was alone. They might be giants. Or demons. Given his unceremonious passing out, he's still wearing all of his shit. He rolls over onto his stomach, gets up, and tries to stealth down the corridor. He's still, despite the day/many years traveling in the armor, getting used to it, makes a fair amount of noise. \"I'm just not as loud as I could be\" he thinks.</p>\n<p>JL and Flick both hear the tinkle of metal coming down a fissure in the caves. \"Is this a fucking ambush\" flick says. JL: No. these guys have proven they're better than this. I'm not saying it shouldn't die.</p>\n<p>Drav wakes up (again). They are looking over towards the right hand side of the caves. She remains watchful, patting V on his head. He's yelling \"I'm wide awake!\" while asleep.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>DM allows V to spend 3 ki points to wake up.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Drav realizes that V's head is disturbingly active as V rouses himself. \"I've been awake and trying to swallow\" rocks which he thought were the purple-blue crystalline rocks.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>20 ft. per 6 seconds, doing an exorcist crawl.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Drav desperately tries to cover V's mouth, but he's too focused and slips through her ruddy dwarven fingers.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Contested grapple check. V's perception check.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>As he awake, he hears a deliciously gloppy sound. A fresh, crystalline blue turdlike object emerge from Lhaska's butthole as she burps.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Rolling initiative for everyone.&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Flick sees ...</p>\n<p>V: Let's not cause any commotion. I don't want to wake anyone up. I just thought we could take a few of these as a party favor or souvenir.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Lhaska turns about restlessly and settles back into sleep. Flick runs over and tries to grapple Vengeance. The memory of the boys trying to roofie Flick ... no! she gets Vengeance face-down in a wrestling hold.</p>\n<p>Flick: V, can I persuade you to abandon this course of action? V: Yeah, use me like a vacuum, and I'll suck up as many of these things as possible. Flick: What if I were to put you back over where we were sleeping. V: I don't think they'll suspect a thing; you should also try to swallow as many as you can. Flick: Vengeance I want you to try to remember what happened last night. V: I don't remember much.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Drav and V both got 18s, so remember everything from last night.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Flick: You don't remember anything because they poisoned us; these azurite bars, you don't want to swallow them. (But then Flick realizes that V is lying, but can't figure out why he would be. She gives his left wrist a twist) \"Could you please tell me the truth, I feel like this is important.\" V: The important thing is we get out of here with as many of these gems as we can. F: Why is this suddenly so important to you? V: They told us last night this is one of the most powerful substances that exists. Thank god we're the only people that know about it -- now's the time to act.</p>\n<p>Flick lets V go at this point. (It's possible they did say this and Flick can't remember.)</p>\n<p>Scunner is in a satiated thieves' sleep, believing everything to be safe.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav wants to make her way very slowly to Flick and Vengeance and ask what's going on. Eldar has provided her with protection in the past; Drav does something akin to prayer to Eldar</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>And fails an insight/religion check</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Drav reaches out to Eldar and feels like her spirit is more difficult to communicate with than it was in the past. It feels like she's been out over where Pjorg came came in from, and is distracted -- \"there's so many interesting symbols and hieroglyphs over here.\" and her attention is lost.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav makes a loud noise and sees \"Glunt\" wake up -- the sister. (Sister to Haigy, daughter of Jarisma, wakes up, and looks over at the group of you). She sees the wrestling and the group of them, drav in the distance.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jean-Luc starts humming a lullaby to try to get her to fall back asleep. Vengeance reaches towards his bagpipes ... to accompany . She is just about to fully awake. Drav recalls blindness/deafness in Riult's spellbook? She sees Flick mouthing \"Mage Hand!\" from across the dim room, and makes it appear behind Glunt's head, like \"this is your mother singing a lullaby\"&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>spell attack on riult's mage and then performance check</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>the gritty sounds of the lullaby combined with the soothing touch of invisible mage hand coaxes glunt back to sleep. JL injected a kriobolis-specific lullaby into things, maybe a GM sleeper cell sleeping song ?</p>\n<p>Flick: I think we should bed down for the rest of the night and take things when we're clearer in the head.</p>\n<p>Vengeance breaks off his bagpipe playing, emitting a \"record scratch\" upon seeing once of the amulets, whispering \"The Order of Rust!\" and whispers, \"Yes, just as I thought\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vengeance thinks aloud, back to his stepmother Dagonnara, and her son, the wicked Schlonzel, who wanted to join the Order of Rust, and practicing his Rust magic in a way that impressed V's father that caused V's father to favor Schlonzel even tho Schlonzel was not V's father's son.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>V Intelligence check. He believes his story. (I don't remember if this was a high or low roll)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Pjorg continues down the hallway as quietly as possible. bringing him about to 90 feet away.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>20 perception to hear what was going on in there 1d240; 225; 13 -- average. ? 120 feet away from the group when he hears this.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Breg did not wake up. Vengeance is still thinking about the order of rust and his father and the wicked schlonzel and how V's father always said he should be more like him, because everything he touched turned to rust.</p>\n<p>V has been told he's a half-elf, but supposedly his mother was the elf. Either way, he did have a step-mother, Daggonara, who has Schlonzel, she trained him from the time he was a little scamp in the order of rust, because that's what she wanted him to join, and by the time he grew up he was the worst person that V had ever met. Everyone loved him and thought he was amazing. (His mother, the elf, was never around). He could immediately change the properties of certain metals so they could do things like Rust slightly more quickly. (He was ionized?).&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Intelligence check.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yeah, everything he's saying totally checks out in terms of what he remembers. It's all coming together now.</p>\n<p>Vengeane goes flat against the ground and moves his hands as though crawling, drav pushing slightly against his forehead, both of them together preventing any forward movement.</p>\n<p>Vengeance sees a bluish-colored stone with a great deal of mucus coating it in front of him that would be great to slurp down. \"I'll slurp it.\"</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Constitution check.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Vengeance swallows a brick-sized stone somehow. In the gizzard he thinks works to digest his food he thinks it will be particularly efficacious.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL looks for a good place to hide to ambush Pjorg. JL moves to the opposite side of the room from where he's going to pop out.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Stealth 27, JL is hidden.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Flick hears the same thing, moving over to one of the low stone walls. Drav moves back. Then, without quite realizing it, Pjorg pops out into the open room. to his right are 4 sleeping humans, up and to the right a huge salamander with a pile of gems and another lizardfolk behind it sleeping; directly ahead of him (80 feet away; it's lit from the salamander) a monk face-down on the rocks who looks like he's trying to eat more rocks. and at the edge of his vision, a few more figures in the far distance. (Drav manages to hide! a historic day! Eldar swooped back to Drav to cover her up.)</p>\n<p>Pjorg, having stumbled into this room full of people, knows that something weird has happened. Are there rocks that HE can get behind. He thinks that his rhythms aren't synchronized with those of these people, whoever they are.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>a very bad stealth check?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Drav, as Eldar rushed back, she scintillated against a bunch of foreign armor, and the sparks of her spirit passage make clear that there's a goblinoid hiding behind the rocks.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL sees the entrance and attempt to hide of a goblin fully outfitted in gilded plate armor carrying a very large battle axe who ducks down behind some rocks quite obviously, and even V notices.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>JL insight as to his intentions. It's weird that he walked into the room and hid.&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>He's kind of baffled. (But Pjorg is also pretty baffled) \"He's hiding in ... the rocks...\"&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Raw intelligence&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Flick, Drav remember -- Flick can kind fo feel it, Drav remembers that Fundi was talking about establishing a hallowed ground , so it's consecreated ground; the specific effect is that everyone in the circle can communicate even if they can't speak the same language, which they were told was to talk to Ruhu, but it lets them talk to the lizardfolk and brittle.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>During the party, Brittle was all \"Get Smashed!\"</p>\n<p>JL is so confident that he blends totally into the shadows, gliding like a ghost next to Flick; Flick is actually surprised when he comes up next to her. Pjorg has no idea. JL's breath moves one of her stray curls. JL inwardly curses that it wasn't perfect. Flick feels for a moment the raw sexuality felt by Nyaka with JL earlier.</p>\n<p>Flick, \"are you watching that goblin too? he doesn't seem to mean any harm. should we ... see what he wants?\" JL: \"Also, who wanders into a mining cave ... by accident?\" Flick: \"Remember when you wandered into the death-knight's naked wrestling circle.\"&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Perception rolls</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Flick notices that the armor of the creature is slightly dulled by a patina of dust. Vengeance: \"dust, or ... RUST?!?!\" Flick: He is armed to the teeth, but he's not ready for burgling. he can't be here to take advantage of us. Vengeance: he kindof remeinds me of someone. Do you remember our friend Fez we left for dead at that snake hospital?</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We discuss whether or not Vengeance can even see Pjorg. he fails a stealth check so hard.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The guy on the floor pulls out his bagpipes and Frampton comes alive it.</p>\n<p>V: \"Do you remember Fez?\"</p>\n<p>Drav desperately regrets giving Vengeance a little breathing room.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL agrees with Flick that this goblin is probably not here for something nefarious. As V's bagpipes fill the air with cacophony, Flick concludes all the people are about to wake up. She uses Fleet of Foot&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Both Scunner and Lhaska wake up at this point. Lhaska, being a huge salamander, looks over to Nyaka and licks her. Scunner wakes up, and immediately sees Pjorg after being awoken by the bagpipe. and he nudges Breg: \"we've got a newcomer here. Looks to be alone.\"</p>\n<p>Drav stays hidden with her unprecedented 17 stealth. ready to cast a spell if needed.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Flick has a full rest, everyone else has the equivalent of 2 short rests.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav rolls for Eldar. She feels the spirit of Eldar infusing her; because she's sitting on the cave floor, she can see the rocks crawl up her and disguise her; once per long rest she can make a stealth check with advantage if she's still and touching rock or stone.&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Glunt rolls a nat 1, so she stays asleep, but the other three do wake up. she remains fully out of it. the other three are disoriented, but awoke from bagpipe music.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Haigy, the one who attended the same charter school that JL did.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>They were awoken by the bagpipe, but only see Pjorg, and respond to Scunner's shout. They, shout, \"Is this one of the Hat Baskets? They know that this Azurite is ours -- we only had a deal with them for the Iridium.\" and they start gathering up their weapons ...&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Brittle looks at what's going on and goes back to sleep. Pjorg, it's clear almost everyone has seen him glinting in the soft orange light from Lhaska.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg: Greetings, small ones, and appropriately sized lizars! My name is Pjorg Tallheart! Scunner: Is that it?</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Roll for Introduction. (Persuasion) -- 11</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I mean you no harm! (which is true) (he looks like a moderately sized piece of fools gold) \"I am embarrassingly slightly lost in this cave and was awoken by the sound of squabbling voices.</p>\n<p>The humans closest to him look at him scepticaly. FUndi , the elder is closest, and they are all kind of giggling behind him.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\"I do not mean to appear threatening. Is it the battle axe that I hold in my extremely large hands? or is it the greataxe strapped to my extremely large back\"</p>\n<p>Fundi: young boy, dn't you see the ribbon we've established . this is a itual circle, you can't just come in here. in fact, let me know about anyone you've had sex with who wasn't married to you. this is of paramount importance.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg: I am adept at reading multiple scripts and would ahve noticed signage to this effect in the hallway. and would ahve noticed such a warning.</p>\n<p>Fundi looks around himself, realizes he's telling the truth, reaches into a fanny pack and pulls out a ribbon and ties it to the stone just to his left and strings it across in front of you. Flick: that is&nbsp;very&nbsp;unfair ex post facto ordinancing! Fundi: As you can see there is a ribbon here and you may cross it by no means and you can't cross it unless you answer my questions to see if you'll corrupt this ritual space. Pjorg: that sounds totally reasonable except for your placing of the ribbon at this time. Fundi: To be honest, I hadn't known there was an entrance from this direction and otherwise I would ahve placed it here earlier. As you can see, I've placed one where accidental visitors might have entered and had to be allowed forwards after answering the questions. Ruhu excuse us all. Pjorg (to himself) \"not the true ... order of rust.\" \"I can answer your question in one simple statement of phrase.\" and he shows Fundi the rune on his shield. [The rune looks like a burning half of a cursive letter f] Flick shouts: It's the poon rune, am I right, up top! V: there better be some Poon-itive action.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Galen gets his only ever inspiration point.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Pjorg isn't invoking it, he's just showing it to him.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Intimidateion 8</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Pjorg: You see the shield symbolizes protection, what one must always use, but i have protection because of the celibacy oath that my order swears. Fundi takes a look. It appears to just make the shield weaker where it's been carved. but if you do subscribe to an oath of celibacy then you are welcome across the ribbon. Flick feels almost ontologically embarrassed by her attempt to make the pun. She flashed back to times at the Dacha where none of her humor was appreciated.</p>\n<p>Flick: Elven jokes are really long because they live for so long; they are like shaggy dog stories, and this 20 minute long joke that ends with ... a chief was going to have a baby, and the warriors had to get hippopotamus hide, and a pythagorus joke. JL is the only one who hears Flick whispering this to herself. Vengeance: Did you hear the one about the three elves wandering through the woods where the foo creature lives? JL is so annoyed that he sighs so loud he comes out of stealth. \"Flick for the love of Ruhu shut up with these stories.\" and then he realizes where he is . and the entire famiy turns to look at him.</p>\n<p>[2:02]</p>\n<p>Breg walks out into the center of things, rubbing literal grit from her eyes which accumulates as she sleeps. \"Everybody quiet down what the hell is going on here. Why isn't everyone asleep? This is perfect sleeping weather for a dwarf.\"</p>\n<p>Pjorg (in dwarven): is it perfect sleeping weather? I'm disoriented in this underground space. Breg: Oh, a member of the tribes. I see that Fundi has already allowed you into the hallowed circle. Please introduce yourself. Pjorg: I am, once again, Pjorg the Tallhearted, which is ... we usually leave out the \"the\". The tallhearted clan, i've not heard of them. Breg: is the tallhearted a dwarven clan? Pjorg: you can probably detect my accent . I've only learned the formal forms. Breg: you must have studied from a religious text with the older grammar and syntax. Come in, it's not even clear to me where you've come from.</p>\n<p>Lhaska starts 'barking' very loudly.</p>\n<p>Pjorg: Did I hear someone mention Azurite, the blood of the titan Azuroth? Breg: I've never heard it called under that name, but yes, Azurite, for sure. Pjorg: Oh, I've conflated it with a different Azurite. Breg: You may also know that it's called The Forgetting Stone. Pjorg: That may explain why I can't determine how long I've been underground. Breg: Yes, how close have you been to us? Pjorg: That, too, remains unclear to me. I was searching for ... something? But the journey led me. All these corridors kind of look the same. Breg: Well yes they've been carved out over thousands of years by the action of the water. I'm surprised you're still alive, as there's not much to eat down here. Pjorg: not luck as some but luckier than many. Breg: that's very vague. I like to be literally and figuratively concrete. (She still can't locate drav in the cave.) No matter, I'm sure she's asleep. Dwarves are very good sleepers.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick realizes that hostilities aren't going to commence, so she steps out into the open. V: Everyone relax, everything should be fine. (He cocks his self-killer and throws it at Jarisma to cut the necklace off her neck. He uses all of his hatred of Schlonzel to focus his attack.)&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>He rolls a 5.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>V pulls his selfkiller out and tosses it towards the Ruhu family. With the extra grease he's been crawling through it sorts of slides out of his hand along the floor towards them.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Insight for the Ruhu family.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Jarisma and Glunt, the daughter, who was asleep: \"This asshole is trying to attack us!\" Haigy looks sympathetic, \"Hold on, I think he's just hungover. This is just some kind of drinking game he's a part of.\" Glunt and Jarisma are making their way towards him to teach him a lesson.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav finally comes out of stealth, standing in front of rocks, and runs over to restrain Vengeance again. Drav just manages to smash Vengeance's head ungently into the cave floor while shouting out an apology. \"Sorry we're still working on him. Just ... \" she shrugs. They look sympathetic and cast an eye back towards Haigy. \"You sure you got him? We've had to deal with the same sort of thing with this guy. Hormones at their age, right?\" And then they exchange looks with each other because Vengeance is rapidly losing his hair. But they relax with Drav in control.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL, operating on the assumption they are not going to attack Vengeance, stays hidden.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Nyaka: Has everyone been woken up by this goblin? Flick: Yes. Pjorg: I'm&nbsp;notresponsible for the vast majority of the commotion. I was awoken by commotion of my own. Nyaka: Fundi, did you offer him opportunity to answer the question? Fundi: yes, he answered with flying colors, and I've pushed the ropes down for him, but he hasn't offered anything as far as libations or victuals are concerned. Nyaka: I'm not in the mood right now anyway, just make sure he stays quiet. (She looks at her satchel quizzically and settles back to sleep)</p>\n<p>Flick; What's happened here is a bit strange; hopefully we can stay friends after this; this tallhearted goblin means us no harm; let's finish the night's rest, and then tomorrow we can all head back. Breg: I'm fine with that ... arrangements.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The humans come towards Pjorg with thick twists of tobacco. Fundi: would you like to help us get back to sleep? and holds out a giant stogie. They are sitting sort of crosslegged in a makeshift circle but it's clear they're ready to pass out too. JL joins the circle. JL notices that he has to make up for the fact that Pjorg doesn't join. Jarisma: What's up with this goblin? Why isn't he smoking with us? JL: to each their own, let's just enjoy this fine ... slake. We're all just people living in a cave. Jarisma: well we do want to get out of here. JL: Man, you guys worry too much. They look at him a bit sceptically ; in return he takes a huge puff of the blunt. Jarisma slaps him on the back heartily, All right, yeah, you're a steady one, I'll fall in line with that. They start telling each other clan-related stories. Maybe a few tales about their lineage.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg refuses to join the circle and goes sitting off by himself.</p>\n<p>JL is too baked to avoid Vengeance.</p>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"7RMR2CZ9ihMHATLn","name":"Gaol Maidens","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"srmjxCv4QHqVw5AK","sort":3200001,"flags":{},"content":null}
{"_id":"7va2ucHabnWUeAry","name":"017. Stay wove, everyone","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"gNDm5xMcEMxCyTVb","sort":-99999,"flags":{},"content":"<div><strong>Day 7</strong><br /><strong>February 22, 2020</strong><br /><strong>Level 5</strong></div>\n<hr />\n<h1 id=\"recap\">Recap</h1>\n<p>Before bedding down for the night, Flick pressed Isabella and Lupenna on the true purpose of their plan to disguise Isabella as Lupenna while the latter skipped from plane to plane to catch Tantegorisch. They demurred slightly when considering the arrangement in retrospect, but Isabella remained convinced that she couldn't have tended the castle in her true form without causing terror amongst the townsfolk. Flick retired rather than adumbrate a detailed genealogy with her godmother and half-aunt, and the gang awoke the next morning to delicious stacked pancakes and an invitation to assist Isabella with research into Boggshosh, the elder god. Drav and Paros, delighted by the offer, perused old tomes with Carlos at the ready in case of overexertion. Drav, ever in command of her faculties, discovered texts on the ancient rituals of Boggshuosh cultists and a loose leaf from a memoir concerning <em>Sirmgalv</em>, a quasi-mythological world-tree. Paros, lost in contemplation, was Veenock'ed around and put in mind of a primeval rivalry between the evil spirit and the demon Nundocamar; he was further tasked with the recovery of an onyx ring with great psionic powers.</p>\n<p>Flick and Joan, meanwhile, took advantage of the crisp fall air and trekked to the North Tower, which they discovered to be more of a waystation for happenstansical travelers. Flick immediately ransacked the workshed and pilfered a pair of sealskin gloves and an unexpectedly strong rope woven out of fizzlecyst silk. Joan, convinced the tower housed eggs in need of protection, attempted to open the door from the downside up, and in so doing alerted the resident, Hale Clotwool, who introduced herself as a herder. Greeted also by the music inside (<em>Straight out the butte: never gonna' plateau</em>, by The Young Fustics^), the smells of a rich second breakfast, and the inquisitive head of a laid-up <em>turr</em> named Orbell Daedonbashur, Joan and Flick assisted in repairing the door and casing the joint. Flick's heightened conusance of portalian japery, however, shattered the placid free-for-all and brought her face to face with an avatar of Juniper Three School; together they inferred that the reddish-gold ingots were somehow altering the planar coherence around Egg Three School.</p>\n<p>By early afternoon everyone had reconvened at Castle Karn, just in time to witness an efflorescent belch of petals aflame exploding from Tobolux's <em>berninde</em>.^ It took Paros's increasingly worrisome familiarity with Veenock to make an assay at the truth: demonic BaphOMO^ got sloppy attempting to influence the current cosmological detente on Thuslubber^ and killed some 'weak and tasty' <em>bloemenwet</em>. Domonkos and Lupenna, unbothered by the general goings-on, began to draft up the details for an immortal castle timeshare, and the group headed towards <em>An Sr&aacute;idbhaile</em>. It quickly became necessary to implement 'ghost fog protocol,' involving, in part, mental exercises to prevent subconscious resentment of people considered mediocre; but, even perceptive Flick was taken unawares upon stumbling into Grenlich's immor.^ As Joan rushed forward to embrace the future of humanoid-manity, the other adventurers did what they could to injure the poor unfortunate gnoll, in pain, in need.</p>\n<p><strong>&mdash; H. F. Wylmott</strong></p>\n<h2 id=\"dbut\">D&eacute;but</h2>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<section>\n<div><strong>The Young Fustics</strong>:&nbsp;A traveling minstrel band of Tabaxi. Currently on Micelium Dank.</div>\n<div><strong>conusance</strong>:&nbsp;Awaredom.</div>\n<div><strong>berninde</strong>: &nbsp;A bottle-like home for a genii or ifreet.&nbsp;</div>\n<div><strong>BaphOMO</strong>: Baphomet's FOMO.</div>\n<div><strong>Thuslubber</strong>: The isthmus which encloses Snaff Bay west of Marshbout.</div>\n<div><strong>bloemenwet</strong>:&nbsp;Flowerfolk.</div>\n<div><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4169a396-7fff-8d76-61c6-85e04789584f\"></span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>An Sr&aacute;idbhaile</strong>: The gnoll village in east Thubudder.</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>immor</strong>: &nbsp;[A physical, spiritual, and cosmological inversion of the platonic gnoll village.]</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</div>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h2>Transcript</h2>\n<p>PUTTY voice</p>\n<p>underside of a portobello mushroom (gills / laminae)</p>\n<p>get an Aule voice</p>\n<p>write up carlos's switch initiative positions</p>\n<p>ian: aggressively secular; im a roman stoic</p>\n<p>real anti-science strain</p>\n<p>ian: doesn't get off the ground until 1920s until america</p>\n<p>shitauqua revivalism; science education in schools</p>\n<p>starting: just took a long rest soul rock was taking a bath the last they saw of him</p>\n<p>flick: they never revealed themselves to me; my foster parents never revealed themselves to me; they let me keep the wolf; snav did not mention isabelle; and maybe he thought that isabelle was lupenna who was locked away in the bear vase (snav sent us to castle karn in the first place)</p>\n<p>Remy Flitch</p>\n<p>Isabella as an Oni can change her size and form and appearance; acting as Lupenna while lupenna was out hunting down tantegorisch. Isabella knew what happened to Lupenna. isabella was surprised that something she was working for fell into her lap lupenna was plane-hopping. caught in a bear-plane. almost an accident that it manifested as a bear. the place itself is just like the material plane. ian: we didn't destroy the plane itself. no, you popped a whitehead on the plane's skin. figurine acted as a homing beacon. when VV tried to take over your mind and have you see lupenna, that did bring an authentic vision of her to you, and she was trying to communicate with isabella. flick: was it just a lucky coincidence? was the portal opened from the inside, by lupenna, or did isabella's touching it open it lupenna opened it, and the figuring allowed her to find an exit; she wasn't familiar with the plane, and it was directing hostility towards being breached.</p>\n<p>flick: why were you posing as lupenna? i don't mean to be self-centered, but what gives. people back in marshbout knew where to find someone that they thought was lupenna. were you laying breadcrumbs.</p>\n<p>change of administration? / continuity of administration</p>\n<p>oni: if i pretended to be Lupenna, there would be a continuity of administration; they expected her to be here as Raul's daughter. a boogieman monster living in the castle would have caused a stir</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>flick: domonkos thinks this is his castle. i haven't seen a deed but that seems accurate.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>isabella: my brother is a full oni, he's &hellip; related to the reappearance of buggshosh, - he's having some difficulty in resisting returning to his cannibalistic ways.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Uncle Rovine [I'm not sure why I have \"uncle\" here?]. BS is one of the elder gods. Carlos had a vision of. Rovi is my half-brother. he's full oni. do i have a child? i don't know. rovi's innate urge is to eat children. carlos: &hellip; lupenna a long time ago, lupenna removed the urges, and certain things changed recently, and he doesn't have the same protections up.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>carlos: the kids deserve it - isabella: are very tasty. oh, yes, hahaha.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>lupenna is flick's godmother.</p>\n<p>flick: the gnoll hunters took us in, and they needed help with something. carlos: we saved the princess flick: well they were also being bothered by the bog witch, --- or the gnolls could probably help us. flick: the grenlich is no doubt a lot stronger than the gnolls, but the gnolls are more well-meaning. but they still need our help</p>\n<p>kolmy is trying to change the entire moral system of gnolls brak shortpaw flick: mostly i want to see thaz again, because i have a thing for her.</p>\n<p>some gnolls were saved in the oven lum and cora were in the refrigerator.</p>\n<p>flick: tantegorisch is going to come for me, eventually. this is what i was given to understand by lupenna. the wolf figurine was some kind of radar blocker that rendered me invisible. when T starts looking, he'll be able to find us but flick goes to get some sleep</p>\n<p>was lupenna a werejackal all along? how did she fall in with all these spirit ogres? is it through VV connection? did they all use to work at Castle Karn Lupenna is like a hell-hound like her father (and part elf) --</p>\n<p>** jake: it's interesting he wants to resorb you, given that he doesn't know where you've been 'resorbing me is gonna be so good -- believe me, you want to resorb me'</p>\n<p>isabella comes up with pancakes to drav and carlos look like you have unfocused eyes paros: they are focused from 18-24 inches isabella: one at each? paros -- yes, reading 2 books isabella: ooh, you'll have to teach me that.</p>\n<p>boggshush. such a bogg. BS, you know. 'sometimes it's easier to abbreviate'</p>\n<p>riult's spellbook can't be damaged by fire or water, and won't deteriorate with age. flick: you can cast in the shower but it has a curse on it now.</p>\n<p>'Aquamuck'</p>\n<p>carlos (jake): maybe they can take me to whatever dimension they hang out in (naphula? and gluder?)</p>\n<p>Drav: transcription of the Xanthu tablets. covered in black leather; printed on a printing press. at least 200 years ago. describing the ways in which the followers of BS would prostrate themselves, the language the cultists would use, how they would worship, some of the rituals they would use to invoke BS. also: historical text: the present state of the islands in Snaff Bay. touches on how the myths regarding islands greated when top of grey tongue severed; but how before that, the depression made by one of the forms of boggshush and how it was kicked out by the gods working together. but it's always retained that imprint.</p>\n<p>i have paros roll for his new sanity stat [10] . attribute. jake: it's like the carebears movie flick: i'm still tripping balls on all those goodberries i ate Revelations of Nundocamar. (almost sounds like a jedi but not quite) jedi terrorist. terrorist group ? three folios that have been bound into one volume.</p>\n<p>paros retreats into own mind while reading the text; suddenly it feels [19] roll for feel. felt this before. because he's done training to read people's minds and telepathize with people. usually it's a johnny mnemonic space; but this time he feels paralyzed; drav notices. johnnny NO-monic. drav: 15 &hellip; perception. paros's breathing becomes very shallow and his eyes close. he has a heartbeat. drav has seen this before as a wizard; if you'd casts a paralyze spell.</p>\n<p>carlos: is that a problem? did the book cast its own spell on paros?</p>\n<p>paros hears veenock. 'wonderful to be reacquainted with you.' paros derived his power from a demon that he made a magical pact with. ? (sorcerers - special lineage, or sell souls -- that's actually warlock) convort paros from sorcerer to warlock veenock and nundocamar competed a long time ago to take over this high elven cleric Valeryl; like beryl, but val. carlos: why do these demons waste themselves on paros? paros: it's mutual veenock: i'm trapped in here paros: maybe my mind is some kind of candy they can't ignore.</p>\n<p>drav wants to get him to wake up. you can see his hands starting to twitch writing 'valeryl' in clumsy elementary school letters. drav runs and gets carlos flick has cast 'PFGE' on paros before.</p>\n<p>veenock: nundocamar got the elves body to apply some talisman to shield his body from me. the defeat bothered me and still does. veenock: 'i want you to get me that ring' 'one of my metaphysical ears is stuffed up'</p>\n<p>drav comes across the loose manuscript flick: 'we got fucking props. this campaign fucking slaps'</p>\n<p>the watermark from Eaton ** paper store: ahh, just a papyrus outlet! matt: either well to do, or lived in that area</p>\n<p>carlos: has veenock's advice paid off? paros: veenock told me to grab the ashes from defeating naphula and gluder</p>\n<p>flick: can joan and i spend the day to check out the north tower. she hasn't had as much time for me with her egg to take care of</p>\n<p>** remy flitch might come up to us and ask for back-pay; we fought a demon fish that let us breath underwater. you think you're shit, you low-level rogue.</p>\n<p>drav look through Xanthu tablets to see if there's anything practical find the text of the rituals to invoke a henchman or apparition of boggshush, and by studying the ritual, you could figure out how to stop it; nat 1: so drav thinks she knows how to stop it.</p>\n<p>north tower is tidy; quaint. smoke coming out of the chimney. flick: i knock an arrow and proceed through the portcullis. tools for landscaping and masonry; workman shed; hay</p>\n<p>flick: 'doing joan: 'what is this, a tower for eggs?!' '</p>\n<p>paros: what if someone's casting create smoke? people: looks like things have been recently moved around; pieces of fresh earth; not crusty earth flick searches shelves and tools thoroughly. (masterwork weapons and amulets) 17 investigation find a rope of climbing what attracts my attention? made of silk. fizzlecyst silk. not poisoned. coarse silk. hoist it. 3 pounds. tke it out into light; can i tell anything about its tensile strength. not made of twine. constructed very well, it doesn't fray. test its strength, it holds surprisingly strongly. it's not elastic. (fizzlecyst silk is elastic, tho, says flick) domonkos and S&amp;M stuff. weird shit? Straight out the Butt. album title. part of textile process. stay wuv, everyone. 'i'll have snav take a look at it later'</p>\n<p>joan: while he's burgling them. joan smashes bottom of the door up</p>\n<p>shoplifting. simpsons. pick up stands to pick up sweet sweet olives.</p>\n<p>'you can take whatever's not nailed down' 'you can talk to anyone with a name above their heads'</p>\n<p>pair of gloves that aren't used for landscaping. made out of marine animal's skin. sealskin? patterns over them, where barnacles had attached, and been ripped off, makes white sigils.</p>\n<p>joan then knocks on the door they open door, joan stays on feet and don't kick the person 'why are you trying to break my door down' flick: 'i suddenly realize we have no good reason to be here' jake: 'why are you casting create smoke?' somebody wearing a hair net, and clothes in fine and soft plaid pajamas making breakfast</p>\n<p>flick: can i ask you questions hale: can you help me fix the door? has a huge goiter on the neck orbell head pokes way around her joan: 'will the bison hold my egg?' hale: 'you want to know if orbell will hold your egg' has heard of lupenna i'm just passing through hale: i'm an itinerant herder; not a tramp, a herder ian: [14] insight, yeah she's telling the truth joan fills hole with dirt; it's not fixed but i can see where you're going with this joan pets orbell</p>\n<p>flick: we're trying to get a feel for the environs smells very earth; cooking up a breakfast; like a delicious savory breakfast, greens being tossed around too. 'the name's hale -- would you like breakfast? more like my mid-morning meal' 'i've been up for 6 hours' flick: see tracks?</p>\n<p>jake: how come orbell gets preferential treatment? joan: is hale exaggerating her herder status orbell has a festering wound joan finds some pr'lll [20] investigation. in earthenware jars flick: i can communicate with it 'to an unschooled person would sound like friendly noises -- communicating that i'm a friend of the land' joan stripping the copper wiring</p>\n<p>hale: things left over from previous resident. flick: anything strange or offputting. i can defend myself against wolves or coyotes attacking the herd flick describes mushroom dog fetuses and the leaf dog</p>\n<p>fick: 'i don't want to alarm you, but i wouldn't go too much further west' hale: 'you're describing the deciduous forests. i try to stay out of the forest. ' a lot of spirits and evil creatures flick: i would have put that down to provincial nonsense flick offers goodberry to orbell gives hale 2 pounds of fizzlecyst meat. ** 'time doesn't pass in the bag of holding' -- definitely not true instructions on how to cook it so --- is fiszzlecyst meat bad?</p>\n<p>A spell called rope trick</p>\n<p>joan found some reddish-gold metal ingots orbell tells them about two triangles, spiralling around it felt like it wanted my heart flew above you why are you limping: orbell: congenital defect amongst some of the rubbing, on the ankle typically they callous over and then it's not a problem</p>\n<p>Baron Won Ween -- legally distinct 'orbell's a good egg' flick feeds Orbell 2 goodberries image of snav that pops into his head; seems like he's superimposed on the trees -- sideways trees that were around thuridan because of the way his bubble interacted with material plane. snav isn't alarmed or in danger. goodberries materialize as per usual. orbell: quite a lot of sugar flick: 'i think you're gonna like the stuff' paros: you know that grass turns into sugar&hellip; that's like the whole point</p>\n<p>orbell deadenbacher joan officially has a tail</p>\n<p>downstairs walls 12 feet thick; alcoves come to point for arrows upstairs walls thinner; central place, and doorso leading out into exterior central room is dining room; old table; chairs; flick is taken aback that the structure is so mundane. thrown off by snav vision. put off by how mundane structure is. so she detects portal to make something interesting happen</p>\n<p>** in-world seltzer kegs flick: is it really just a shepherd waystation</p>\n<p>** maybe restrict ian's detect portal to &frac14; mile, because i just can't joan is drawing on the egg with hale and &hellip;</p>\n<p>the note was tucked between two other volumes; someone probably took the rest of it and left that page there describing where nicklefurrow is paros: Commentary on the diaskisdein i have to get some of zorbwood. fascinating stuff.</p>\n<p>hale has drawn a picture of dravita. that leaked horribly. you burned it. joan hears faintly the sound of grass burning, or an animal screaming. and flick detects a very tiny portal below you, right on this egg. flick: i rush downstairs and take a close look. egg starting to ooze a fowl greyish liquid. starting to ooze feather liquid. it's starting to hatch. flick tells joan to put the egg down for a second. but joan did want to have experienced people flick backs up as far as she can get joan just sees the drawing what happens to the feathers? they're being sucked into joan's bag, into a heavy part of the bag flick: i ask if i can see, and approach cautiously feathers are passing through the bagg, and passing into the ingots, and then coating them, like they are wrapping the ingots. flick goes to pick up ingot. Wisdom check 13. everything in front of her appear back, then pointilistic spots of light appear; no proprioception. going to focus on points of light and see if they cohere into anything mimetic. flick in real life hunches over the egg protecting it flick in vision sees juniper in negative 'it is not time for me to to be born yet. why are you trying to open this egg with your portals' juniper three school was the original sausage person in the candy lab with the spirited away mask. three school an ancient constellation of creatures. and there are other three schools with their own curriculum. and juniper studies life and death. flick: 'i wasn't aware i could open anything. has it had the effect every time?' juniper: i think there's something in the vicinity. jake: it was causing problems for solrak too, wasn't it? flick: you need to let me go. juniper: i'm not the one that's holding you here. angela: hale was drawing on the egg? juniper: you were the one that made contact with me.</p>\n<p>joan grabs the ingot out of flick's hand. wrapped around egg, drooling on it. feels a residual need to stay hunched around it. joan: 'hale thinks we're crazy now, thanks to you' hale: i just sort of zoned out and started drawing these on the egg; hobo signs oh, the people here will attack you, or they are very nice jake: what did she draw? dravita. having never met it before? flick: she claimed not to have seen any of the mushroom dogs flick turns to orbell; try to convey to him 'who is hale --- have you seen her take off her mask' 'who is she right before she goes to sleep' i can talk with it because i'm a ranger, not because it's a magical beast joan: what does this symbol mean to the tramps? this means that, uh, you can usually find some pretty cool tools and stuff in the shed outside the tower i'm doing it on an egg, it's not on the wall jake: have you drawn that one before? it's one of the lesser used ones, but sure flick does a somersault out the door back to the library -- midday joan: it smells like asparagus popcurn in here? drav tries to figure out &hellip; the text jokes on text of jabberwocky 'ya best start believing in grey tongues, lassy' _ simpsons reference by ian? leuqline is like a ley line 'where a bunch of people each give you a flower wreath, one after the other' jukas: like a star wars swear carlos in particular would know what it is: when you dispel undead, you can see the signs of their passage. jukas is the name for that image; like undead &hellip; spoor. the signs that ghosts leave. aule is interested in extirpating them. and sirmgalv? - drav: you may not have known this before; almost like a world tree, but also known as the EarthRoot. a very powerful grounding force for the planet in the plane. things that have been splintered off of it have powerful magic baked into it. like the fountain of youth in that people look for it. carlos: maybe we will find magical weapons and undead stuff in nicklefurrow</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>tobolux bottle exploding</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>cork pops out and stream of flower petals pushes itself out of bottle.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>voluminous clouds of petals fill the air to the point that you are choking.</li>\n<li>it's fragrant but it smells like burnt vegetation.</li>\n<li>tobolux doesn't come out.</li>\n<li>carlos: is this what happens to ifrits when they die?</li>\n<li>carlos: maybe she cried to death? but we didn't think we killed her. (yes, aule said she was healed)</li>\n<li>form this cloud that settles on the ground, that starts disintegrating; a mist that remains inside the bottle that isn't coming out.</li>\n<li>doesn't seem like it would be in aule's domain.</li>\n<li>[6] arcana check. the mist mystifies you. you can tell that something has happened to tobolux.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>demon FOMO . fiend FOMO.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>BAPHOMO. (baphomet fear of being left out)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>veenock says that he's making a play for the area</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>he's trying to get a hold on the peninsula through the taste flower folk</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>i'd be careful; if you want to find where the flower folk hold sway, go to the slubber</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>jenny is going to be sad that tobolux is dead.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>veenock: they must have thought they would be invulnerable here; and indeed, who would have wanted to come here</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>paros: what changed</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>veenock: that's the question, isn't it.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>paros: i'm carrying around creepy ashes for him</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>veenock: hey man if you find a party you don't ask where the beer's coming from. you just start drinkin.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>the ring. yes.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>black (onyx gold) gold. texas tea. bubblin ground. veenock is a texas oil prospector.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>exon backwards is NOXE. SEXAT is texas backwards. clear as oil. unique new york.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>the flower folk all the demons do is compete to see who's going to be king of the hill. when you're immortal, that's one of the places you end up. veenock: what are veenock's hopes and dreams. veenock is different. this is a new scene, baby. veenock's gonna live large.</p>\n<p>hasn't written popcorn back. drav slaps paros for 4 damage. with a gauntleted fist.</p>\n<p>nonfatal damage is sibling damage put a boxing glove on the arrow arrow-dynamic</p>\n<p>paros comes to: there are a lot of petals; seems like it could be related to flower folk. demon called baphomet that might have eaten tobolux. seems like they are generally vulnerable. carlos: is that also where the ring is?</p>\n<p>flick is worried about the gnolls, hearing about the things from orbell carlos: maybe the weird dogs are coming through portals? carlos: and then we'll go to the slubber to help the geniis in need.</p>\n<p>domonkos and lupenna will work it out between them. we're both essentially immortal, so perhaps a time share. joint custody of the castle. drav: draw a line down the center lupenna empties out a bag of rice: domonko counts</p>\n<p>flick learns what her gloves can do rope of climbing can hold up to 3000 pounds, and would have to study rope a typical flick rest, saying 'flick' and spidermanning across the castle flick is wearing them short rest and make way to gnolls</p>\n<p>flick can't get lost by magical means. paros: what about magical nice-ness.</p>\n<p>towards gnoll village: fog gets thicker towards gnoll encampment. paros [17] does this fog seem magical? magicky the fog is natural. it seems unusual.</p>\n<p>now we're in the ghost fog ghost protocol 'subconscious resentment of people he considers mediocre'</p>\n<p>fog is so dense that it's about 30 feet away oh yeah, i should have said picture the caterpillar from alice in wonderland can we see texture / color</p>\n<p>flick tries to move around stealthily 'have you come to pledge yourself to me' flick ignores and tries to move around</p>\n<p>paros: as it's accordioning, what kind of music do we hear flick: intelligence check to recall information about the creature some kind of demonic form that has taken her on flick moves until lightly obscured and then try to hide again</p>\n<p>joan says 'yes' to kolmy 'well then, come closer to me' flick: 'dont!' joan stopped when flick told her to you do whatever your friends tell you to? well, can i be yourfriend ? joan: yes. then proceed.</p>\n<p>natural explorer gives advantage on initiative and on first turn against attack rolls against creatures that have not acted that turn</p>\n<p>grenlich: come closer, let me see you joan strolls forward : ground around you bubbles with mold. as you lift your foot up, the mold blossoms in your footprints. the only place that's not covered in this is exactly where you're standing. flick: i bet the spores possess people paros: i'm casting haste for fun</p>\n<p>flick got back of familiar and dragon-hopped out of window and taken on magical tour of plateau</p>\n<p>joan is disgusted and is going to attack paros: i think with my grapes joan: goes into a rage because she feels like she's been tricked. grenlich: 'i've evolved well past gills' 'you've done such a wonderful job hurting me' ethel is out of the way</p>\n<p>carlos religion check [14] see in hammer spiritual hammer [9 damage] flick casts hunter's mark flick advantage against being charmed, and magic can't put her to sleep 28 piercing damage [took joan's full damage] drav casts fireball paros: is there mycelium 'dank with mycelium' 'mycelium dank' is the label</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>grenlich goes after joan with two of its fungus arms wisdom saving throw, DC 16 -- joan is charmed and doesn't feel the urge to attack her anymore</p>\n</section>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"8BNOPdjrju4VlYFd","name":"Marshbout fish thing","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"IahJpr0JiteucCD5","sort":300000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>but so many people walking around in \"hat suspenders\" that V could easily pass for a weird judge.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The judges are all past their prime. The fans are dressing as their favorite judges, especially \"Sturgeon\" Pete. Some fans are dressed up as fish. There are fights between people jumping in to question a ruling; and other fights between people and judges where they accuse the judge of just being a fan dressed up as the judge.&nbsp;</p>"}
