 next juniper; but juniper is a consistent being;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;juniper won't kill you to get the mask; you're being used as a host to create her. the mask will fall off<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;can we have a pamphlet? and a course catalog?<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;and karnish!<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;KARNOSH = paros + karnish or carlos + karnish {+ gnoshing}<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;karnish is protector / guardian spirit of the grey tongue<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;genius loci or tutelary spirit<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;karnish is all that's left of the great mountain deity when it was a mountain; before the top was severed during a fight amongst the gods; karnish is the spirit, and castle karn is named after<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;juniper is independent of karnish. 3schols are usually scholars or explorers, and find their way around through investigation or curiosity.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros: i'm a scholar/explorer<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;ermann: my specialty isn't on 3schools. the pattern that keeps them intact preceeds the birth of the first humanoid species. this is an arrangement that came to us from the gods.<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos: what's their interest in the grey tongue specifically<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;juniper and hers are interested in looking at life and death; recently the grey tongue has been the locus of a lot of that activity<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;drav: but that's specific to juniper;&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;they all have different raison d'etre<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos: what's the origin of bad stuff<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;ermann: it's got worse recently, but started since karnish temporary banished by tangegorish (\"quarter of a century ago\"&nbsp; years ago)<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;we'd like to see karnish reinstated; even under domonkos, karnish was able to thrive. things were terrible under tantegorisch.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos: we have a theory about the ghost-fish (gauche-fist)<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos: one of tantegorisch's clients, von veen, is inside the fish<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;might be specialty of someone concerning themselves with spirits. i don't have much in the way of magic<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros: what is history medicine like then ?<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"dr\" of history. ermann: hands you secular ministrations, penned by doodril frogwarts, burghar and sublunar cognoscente. best seller. i think this should interest you quite a lot.<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros: medicine used to fix history?<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;what is karnish supposed to look like?<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;show them the spirit troll<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;spirit form, and elemental locus form, when she takes on the power and appearance of earth itself, and looks like an avalanche or a landslide of rocks in perpetual motion. she's only appeared in spirit form since she was banished.<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"throwing behaviors\"&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos: can you refer us to another professor?&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;point to Ymenestra -- a visiting lecturer. she's a fate-runner . they effect exorcisms by becoming one with the host and drawing out the evil forces possessing them. even if it's a giant fish. her knowledge may be more practical than academic, but she is lecturing here.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;ermann gives joan a sweet high-five<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;does ermann toke<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros telepathizes<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;plus paros is kind of a paranoid stoner -- is it wired in here?&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;black footed ferrets steal gold.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;phrase: \"i'll give it the old nickel try\" -- if doing it is worth less than the effort it would take to say \"no\". it's a gnomish expression.<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;to pot<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"you should really try this\" -- pulls out a jug of white liquid. it's trolls milk.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros telepathizes with her again. d20 please.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;she gives them a jug of milk&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;tastes like very good milk. and you're not sure if its this, or something else recent, but you feel like you're super-tough now, like nothing could hurt you.<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos: it's b/c karnish knows were trying to do her will.<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos: \"we all had more than you did!\"<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;homeopathic dosing.<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"body by trollmilk\"<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;as you're about to leave, and ermann spots the bracer. paros notices you address her directly.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"this is how you've been telepathizing with me\"<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"hi, i'm paros\" -- \"you make such a good student on the first day, introducing yourself\"<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;it will be an overwhelming source of difficulty if you continue<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;the bracers are meant to be used only by those who are devotees of dalariel, or those who are skilled in the ways of the mystics.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;a mystic we have here, her name is phoenix molvraki, she's from very far away,&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;gives a bracelet -- not only will this make you feel like your arthritis has been cured, but it will suppress the abilities and side effects from the bracer. i'd suggest talking to phoenix. their life has been spent learning about this kind of energy and communication. and i think they can help if you want to persist on this path.<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;for religious followers, the abilities are granted by who they pray to<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros can just take bracer off; the bracelet is also phoenix's calling card, since she moves around a lot<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;i wouldn't recommend direct communication yet; it might do permanent damage to you<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros: i had a vision of a friend electrocuting other two.<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;i'm going to cover my braces here<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;have you had other signs of psychological intrusion<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;it could have been any of those things.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;... erodes the distinction between different elements, which can emerge through the bracer that will manifest in real life in time. the visions are harbingers of what's to come. it's hinting at the possibilities.<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;rolling charisma check<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;when ermann showed the karnish spirit, you have image of a great war&nbsp; , on one side there are thousands of dragons; on the other side, thousands of giants, some are great wizards, some are mercenaries, and coming to clash in the middle. you feel deep within yourself an ancient hatred for the giants.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;not sure if karnish was giant or part-giant.&nbsp;<br />-&nbsp; &nbsp;not specific hatred towards karnish, it just called this into her mind.<span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Georgia; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"8zkrPUJ0M6fS2jV3","name":"Stato's Den","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"sFfN93bzEwcqcSqV","sort":1000001,"flags":{},"content":"<h2>Food</h2>\n<div>- Unicorn marshmallows ?</div>\n<div>-&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<h2>Creatures</h2>\n<div>- Theen [a Likho] to annoy Vengeance when he's in the back room.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>### Clurichaun (by a different name)&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp; - perhaps in a ground-level wine or beer cellar</div>\n<div>&nbsp; - \"tormenting their hapless hosts with cruel pranks\" unless well-supplied with alcohol, in which case they guard the cellars</div>\n<div>&nbsp; - __attrition__: can make adventurers feel hung-over next day</div>\n<div>- serve __dipsaviar__ from the lake</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>### Garroter Crabs</div>\n<div>- maybe some __Garroter Crabs__ (\"aggressive, blue-black freshwater crabs\"), which are alternately seen as divine and respected and sacred (and used for augury), or tasty and eaten</div>\n<div><span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>- __trade goods__: serve Garroter Crabs in dipsa milt (\"dipsoft\")</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>### Bone Crab</div>\n<div>- __trade__: bone crab legs (\"incredibly powerful\"), good eating</div>\n<div>- __clues__: the bone-home in which they live is the skull of a missing person? a kind of monster no one thought was alive anymore?&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>- Some crabs retain fragments of memory from those they devour, and these crabs recognize friends or attack the foes of those whose skulls they wear.</div>\n<div>- this is definitely not true as a cause, since all crabs are scavengers (White Ghost Shivers), but there's probably something else going on misattributed to the crab's flesh: \"Because they eat carrion, bone crabs carry a dangerous disease&mdash;white ghost shivers, which wrack victims with fever and delirium. Sailors and others who eat a bone crab's unwholesome, diseased flesh rarely survive it.\" - it actually sounds like a drug trip. hallucinations. (probably just crabs around a certain type of food source)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>### Living Wicks</div>\n<div>- unlit __Living Wicks__ are under the drop cloths in the backroom of Stato's</div>\n<div><span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>- __combat__: Vengeance or anyone else could command them (and then a fight to extinguish them) \"Living wicks are active only when their wicks are lit, and only respond to the telepathic commands of whoever lit them. This makes it easy to transfer living wicks between owners, even those not well-versed in the use of magic.\"</div>\n<div><span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>- __combat__: also a self-destruct mechanism: If their controller demands it, all living wicks can release the magic contained within their form all at once, engulfing themselves and anyone nearby in flames.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>### Bucca</div>\n<div>- love to steal from miners: Hidden in Crevices. Buccas are tiny, underground faeries who are also known as \"snatchers,\" because they love to steal from miners and hoard precious minerals and gems in tiny, trap.filled crevices. Their small size makes them easy to overlook.</div>\n<div>- __character__: Drav might know about them: Buccas are often enslaved by derro as treasure seekers and can be summoned by some derro shamans. Buccas are the bane of the dwarves of many mountains and hilly cantons, serving as spies and scouts for evil humanoids.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>### Empty Cloak</div>\n<div>- perhaps upon a Living Wick or actual mannequin&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>### Lantern drake</div>\n<div>- that feeds on the Living Wicks, -- hence the Empty Cloak? Unless Palchin considers it good luck</div>\n<div>- __clues__ __character__ loves discussing magic and history (telepathically of course)&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- __suspense__ if caught in magical darkness it can't fly or glow and takes radiant damage.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>### Boloti</div>\n<div>- __combat__ (for the lake)</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>"}
{"_id":"98TdftZbJ3mcb2tH","name":"past prep notes","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"NdtTfwZe9YTsCoFv","sort":900000,"flags":{},"content":"<h1>floating</h1>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4df32846-7fff-5210-cb02-f3aa1787ea27\">In Jean-Luc's sword the lithography for lucy can conjure a demon who is the opposite of jean-luc so not confident , but ugly and very capable ?</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d6bb3f54-7fff-350f-67f8-19197d34917b\"></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">think ahead of time what the major NPCs will know about other NPCs and PCS</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">voice impression&nbsp;</li>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">bad rod serling impression</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">thurston howell III</li>\n</ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\"one of the three curses he had received from Poseidon. \" (to distribute at others)</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Phaidra: loveless marriage, and unrequited love that gets the recipient killed</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">melted stone house</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">interesting / mysterious landmarks instead of \"fantastic locations\"</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>047 order of rust</h1>\n<h2>Preparation</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>more voodoo-adjacent things, like the weird conical pyramid diaper i saw under the bridge.</li>\n<li>Drav sees some hieroglyphic type things in those cool rounded corner rectangles and they are making reference to tan-axe gore sledge (and did someone try to scratch them out, but she can kind of see dwarven glowing text below the scratches) ? aka tantegorisch</li>\n<li>Jean-Luc begins to feel more acutely his non-magicality, and may need to continue to calibrate or specificate his position w/r/t that.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Post-paration</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>really have to establish timeline for the miners down here.</li>\n<li>give Drav some stealth help</li>\n<li>what does happen to V when he swallows the azurite.</li>\n<li>(why are there stone walls down here?) was it a palace or something? why the azurite?</li>\n<li>Pjorg's abilit to kind of see the future with Jaap's augury stuff</li>\n<li>blood of the earth</li>\n<li>creates a sort of event horizon so it looks like creatures aren't changing (werewolves)</li>\n<li>creates a wormhole by sinking through planes</li>\n<li>sinks through rock it's so dense</li>\n<li>Betrayor thought the rune magic was bringing back / harnessing this potential?&nbsp;</li>\n<li>so-and-so Fussbudget</li>\n<li>Giselbert: a Norman personal name composed of the Germanic elements gīsil 'pledge', 'hostage', 'noble youth' (see Giesel) + berht 'bright', 'famous'.</li>\n<li>place: Ardglass</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>046 all men had their fill</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>how do i make dwarven architecture and rock carving techniques interesting?</li>\n<li>\n<section>study of ancient things revealing secrets</section>\n</li>\n<li>\n<section>\"fakes\" like fake sculptures</section>\n</li>\n<li>\n<section>tombs</section>\n</li>\n<li>\n<section>can't just be \"what dwarves are like\" : there has to be a thing to do, a mystery, a conflict or challenge</section>\n</li>\n</ul>"}
{"_id":"9Wmop6Rdmyw3hMb1","name":"028. [Untitled]","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"3raMqXjxKE8cvKwn","sort":431250,"flags":{},"content":"<p>Saturday, May 16, 2020</p>\n<p>level: 6</p>\n<p>game day:</p>\n<h1 id=\"recap\">Recap</h1>\n<p>[I don't think I made one]</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h1 id=\"transcript\">Transcript</h1>\n<p>rovine: this sounds like a bit of a new development to me. perhaps the columns have responded to H&rsquo;s attempts to drench them in blood.</p>\n<p>hieronymus: that&rsquo;s the power of hope name for their radiant fizzing more things to hide behind; or levels, because of jean-luc and flick how does murphy transition from character voice to narration voice</p>\n<p>to &ldquo;have a klank-off&rdquo;</p>\n<p>slugg is female with shortbow</p>\n<p>look up where people with armor usually got hit allow to make insight on angel when i prep, assume they are going to be rolling insight on everyone or reading their minds and things like &ldquo;what do i see out here&rdquo; types of cover things to say while i&rsquo;m clicking around</p>\n<p>downdraft? should have had angel edge flick () more for jenny &mdash; i&rsquo; not sure what draws her in let the kobolds bravery actions speak for itself should have had physical description of scepter. (i was going to tie its various functions into their improvement) ways that Rovine would actually talk about their adventuring party, and why isabella told flick about tantegorisch?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Carlos follows drav down the passageway and readies an action to cast Calm Emotions if anyone notices Carlos and approaches.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Hier is around the throne, which has started pulsating, and giving off a faint heat. He holds a cube of bouillon (a mixture of entrails and offal) over the throne at the end of his thorny quarterstaff like a marshmallow over a fire to try to heat the meat mass and lure the angel towards the sacrificial viscera with the smell.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick watches a bead of blood dripping out of the cube; it makes contact with the throne&rsquo;s seat,</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Magnificent spectacle; beautiful queen with gold crown and jewelry, has a scepter and a greataxe</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Queen: Who dares to intrude on the temples? Out with you all, or you will be killed! and makes to slash at Hier with the greataxe.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Hier: You mean everyone &hellip; but me, right? [Persuasion 9]</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Queen: I could grant you immunity, as you {{brought me into existence}}, but no you are an intruder, and have merely taken the sacred entrails and brought them here, where they can revive {us}.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Hier [WIS 17]: Taken by a vision of the Queen as the full summer sun at the sky&rsquo;s zenith, heat waves pushing you further and further into the ground with each effulgent pulse, and the approaching eclipse that would have blocked off all sunlight forever. He backs up a step or two as he regains his composure.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Jean-luc examines the scepter. [HISTORY 11]. The Queen resembles certain harvest deities; the scepter allows her to choose between the specific role she is adopting, or which aspect or facet of her being she&rsquo;s prioritizing. He nocks an arrow and waits for a target.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick arrests the progress of Rovine as the latter inches his way along the wall, presumably making for the open exit. Before getting a word in edgewise Rovine evinced surprise at the appearance of the hitherto unrevealed elf and the strenght of her bosky mephitis. - Do you know Isabella? to which the oni asked in turn for any more insight on the intentions of his sister, and</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What connection do you have to this temple? to which: I am here by happenstance after the kobolds recently came upon it as an attractive site for their sacrificial rites.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: If i let you escape without revealing your position to the Queen, could we meet up later and chat about Tantegorisch and defending myself against him?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Rovine: You certainly wouldn&rsquo;t be &ldquo;letting&rdquo; me. I&rsquo;d be leaving &hellip; strategically &hellip; on my own.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: So you wouldn&rsquo;t mind if I try to get her attention? (and makes to call over to her) {{Should have allowed an INTIMIDATION check here}}</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Rovine, calling the bluff, declares them both at risk should her attention be redirection from Hieronymus.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The two continue bickering over whose departure from the Temple is more urgent, until Rovine offered to discuss anything Flick wanted to on the Temple ground.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: Well, in the meantime, Isabella sends her regards, and my name is Flick. Does that name sound familiar to you?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Rovine: Yes, it does. Isabelle has talked about you I believe. I don&rsquo;t know if she&rsquo;s gone into that much detail. From what i remember, your name wasn&rsquo;t to be brought up. I think she was deep in her cups and that&rsquo;s how mention of you came about. You were supposed to be something of a secret. I would gladly speak with you afterwards and you are welcome for the display of sophisticated strategery which I am about to display.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Slugg exhorts her vanguard to attack the enthroned Queen.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick [INSIGHT ] realizes that Rovine was covering for his cowardice with the strategy bit.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The kobolds, led by Slugg, stab into the Queen as a group.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick and Jean-luc, exchanging aporiac looks, tacitly decide that the Queen&rsquo;s attacks on Hieronymus don&rsquo;t decide the ally-enemy issue sufficiently for either to cast their weight on either side.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The attack on Hieronymus coincided with a loud scream by Roxffallana at the other temple. At the same time, Hiero screamed to fellows: We cannot let this slight against me go unavenged. To arms!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The first celestial to appear, the Green Spring, now in full command of her weapon, swungs out with her longsword, releasing a coruscating arc of radiant fireworks which passes through the kobold mob, leaving each one burnt and lifeless.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick [HIST 15] recalls that the Queen of the Sun has a coterie of bodyguards that protect her temples, and are related to either agricultural or natural cycles.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Kobold blood begins to drench the nearby column, and another celestial form appears; the two guardians move to protect the Queen and release the other guards.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Drav casts her eye to the entrance of the other temple, where Roxffalanah and Fez, now two small figures in the distance, appear unmolested.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>JOHN CULT-TRAIN</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>they have salafist tendencies?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Drav [HIST 16]: xanthuc temple was center of galactic polity - DM: the center got so nasty that everyone moved as far away as they could</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Drav: I don&rsquo;t feel too bad throwing a pot-shot at them then</li>\n<li>Drav: is there anything elemental that they are resistant to ?</li>\n<li>[Drav: nat 1 on INSIGHT: they are vulnerable to necrotic damage?]</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Angel takes a hit from melf&rsquo;s acid arrow, and will take more damage next turn</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Rovine chicken-flies over the kobolds between him and the window, and tumbles through the window.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Rovine: athletic prowess and something &hellip; allows you to do &hellip; on the battlefield</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>H: I love you so much!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Drav saw Rovine go directly over her: maybe a beard chap is what i need</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Carlos casts healing word on Hieronymus (&ldquo;do i need a word for this?&rdquo;) - H feels like most of the &ldquo;word&rdquo; went to the bagpipe somehow. H pumps fist and freeze-frames in the middle of the air, and tosses a party-favor bag of poison to Carlos: &ldquo;Thank you!&rdquo;</p>\n<!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>H tries to his Queen , but misses, and can still spend a ki point to flurry of blows - hits once; slid so close to the throne that gives a one-inch punch</p>\n<!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>H: i think she&rsquo;s almost dead!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Kobold?: the intruder fights back!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>wut &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>the Queen misses hieronymus because he&rsquo;s so close</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>H: you really beefed that one! and throws the meat into her face. the Queen knocks the meat into the nearest column.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Orange Mist arises at the queen&rsquo;s beckoning. - Sailor Moon, arise (no response from the other column)</p>\n<!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Queen: we&rsquo;re more of an agricultural society; we stay away from the mountains. we&rsquo;ve brought the mountains to us with the earthen mounds !</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>DK readies an action</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: Great queen, and creature of divinity: may we appeal to the great generosity you show as the giver of all bounty. \\</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Queen: and what tokens do you bring to trumpet? signal? your goodwill</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick : we awoke you</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Queen: do you think i like being awoken to deal with the transgressions of mortals</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: our transgressiosn were unwilling and i beseech you if i may withdraw this wellmeaning fool from your circle; we would depart your domain forever</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Q: this idiot has been marked by my scepter. and he shall not escape, except, if he gets out of here. he will serve as an example for all your kind. without having the proper tokens or lineage.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick BA &mdash; 18 force damage; then sharpshoots &mdash; misses after a reaction protection cast on queen.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Queen of the Sun: we&rsquo;re protecting you from an even more dangerous force. - it&rsquo;s Xanthu! who else would you think? Xanthu lends her name to these temples. Xanthuc is the locative ending.</p>\n<!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: what a rich tongue.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Queen: just like our kingdom used to be.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: if we can get H out of here, we&rsquo;ll be on our way. Or I can &hellip; force &hellip; the issue.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Queen: diplomatically ? sadly my ire has been raised and he must go!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Suffers kobold attack.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>DK attacks first kobold to make a move as a sign of good faith to the queen.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>H shouts out &ldquo;noooooo they are our friends!!&rdquo;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>DK hits slug right in the chest: &ldquo;Ughhhhhh&rdquo; with a sneak attack damage arrow</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>&ldquo;miscellany of rusty daggers try to cut into the queen, like someone getting shivved in prison&rdquo;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Slugg: On, Bulgarius! bulgarius bites the queen with black liquid dripping from its mouth; the Queen screams, and Slugg slices her head right off; she disappears and the scepter clatters to the floor.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>Angels: Queen! we will avenge your death, temporary as it may be! Until the next rulers can step up and revitalize you.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>FLick: da fuq?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Angels: this was once the center of a great kingdom!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: A real Cressidan standoff (when everyone is pointing hand crossbows at each other)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The Silver Wheat will let none go! pulls out a longsword and</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Uncanny dodge used to halve damage.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Orange Mist? casts light on the stone tile, and Bulgarius disappears</p>\n<ul>\n<li>should have let anyone roll arcana ?</li>\n<li>it&rsquo;s been banished to another plane.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Silver ?? comes down on Slugg and her longsword plunges through her body. maybe the armor &hellip; cushioned it ? &ldquo;i&rsquo;m in a bad way. get this flying duck off me&rdquo; (redundant).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Samuel &hellip; who the fuck &hellip; ?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>H, the original angel perks up and supermans over to you; she&rsquo;s flying with her longsword straight out (</p>\n<ul>\n<li>H is flatfooted ? does 23 points of damage.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Drav:</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Rovine: &ldquo;do you need help getting your little dwarf feet up into the window. let me help you, teddy bear&rdquo; &mdash; tell that elf this is part of my strategy to help the little ones get inside.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Drav: 8d6 lightning damage, dex saving throw.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>green spring, orange mist, silver wheat</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>ocean spray; sierra mist</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>same logical status d20 roll (etc) equals or exceeds number , then success; attack : equals or exceeds armor class saving throw: equals or exceeds DC</p>\n<p>orange mists&rsquo;s natural 1 &mdash; fried her wings; and she can&rsquo;t fly anymore</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>drav moves rest of movement over</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Rovine: these damn angels. what&rsquo;s slug going to do without his beast? - dark cloud emerges from hands and settles onto the ground</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Rovine: i can&rsquo;t let a single kobold die. a single one would be unforgivable.</li>\n<li>those guys have just hidden! or &hellip; fallen asleep ?</li>\n<li>they tend to bleed easily. with the dry air &mdash; they&rsquo;re used to a more aquatic environment. also i think bulgarius is back.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>Carlos requests a boost from Rovine: &ldquo;i need to go after my squishy friend&rdquo;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Rovine: please don&rsquo;t attempt to remove my battle chaps. do you need a boost? i can see i&rsquo;m an essential contributor to this battle.</li>\n<li>the kobolds aren&rsquo;t interested in attacking Carlos &mdash; covered in hair. they are trying to protect themselves from the angels. (should i have required an insight check?)</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>Jean-luc has &ldquo;mad&rdquo; hitpoints &mdash; using a qualitative HP system. Carlos moves himself in front of drav Drav hugs carlos. Carlos heals Hiero. Can drav lend her power to Carlos &mdash; she&rsquo;s just so touched. but is unable to. Carlos casts the protective version of &ldquo;these rocks look great&rdquo;</p>\n<p>Heiro can see Rovine through the window. &ldquo;we could really use your help about now!&rdquo;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>R: i think they just want us outside? [persuasion 8] &ldquo;yeah outside seems pretty safe to me&rdquo;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>H: maybe i&rsquo;ll join you out there! runs towards him.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>OA from the green spring. H goes to run and GS slashes his back wide open, and he goes splashing across the floor.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Hiero has a dying vision of Roxfallanah jumping through the window, galloping over to hiero, throwing her hooves in the air, and screaming &ldquo;no no why?!&rdquo; and then H&rsquo;s ghost rises up from his corpse and flies into the mouth of the mule, and the mule bucks around a bit like a possessed/and/or/castrated pig. H speaks from the mule: &ldquo;it&rsquo;s ok everyone, don&rsquo;t worry&rdquo; &mdash;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>the rest of you see the kobolds and rovine stars smelling the air: kobols shout : not haired?? and start snuffling around the open body</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>jean-luc tells angel that he is not its enemy.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>angel: of course you are, you&rsquo;re in our temple!</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: run towards me!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>silver wheat slashes at JL ineffectually as he disengages and runs towards flick</li>\n<li>JL: i&rsquo;m going to respectfully decline</li>\n<li>Angel: impossible! a declination is inherently disrespectful.</li>\n<li>then JL turns back and fires. &mdash; critically fails.</li>\n<li>SW deflects arrow back into stairs; the entrance to stairs crumbles and is blocked.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: bonus action Zephyr&rsquo;s strike. &mdash; looks over to chaos on right, and JL &ldquo;who&rsquo;s a pretty cool guy&rdquo; and i dash to go to his aid. i think my buddies have throne chaos pretty well in hand.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick gives one last chance to &hellip; surrender</p>\n<ul>\n<li>21 piercing.</li>\n<li>Angel: can your arrows bring down a magnificent bird such as myself?!</li>\n<li>22 piercing. I say &hellip;&hellip;&hellip; xhhhhhah. she disappears in a flash of radiant light.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>F checks in with JL. didn&rsquo;t i tell you about that time i was in a horse-house in whatever city that was</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>F takes cover behind column. JL feels cool wind rush up and carry her off.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Slugg calls out into the darkness for Balgarius and goes to attack Green Spring.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>force of Slugg&rsquo;s loyalty to steed gives her power to cut through this Angel; she disappears in a blast of energy.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>title: ? - &ldquo;the object of their swordly attentions&rdquo;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>orange mist: my green sister, do not leave me here landbound!&rdquo;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>&ldquo;out of the darkness and into the fray!&rdquo; &mdash; balgarius lunges out and latches onto Orange Mist&rsquo;s leg.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>get your ugly beast off me! I&rsquo;m an angel &hellip; of the mist !!</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>all the other kobolds start sniffing and moving closer to hieronymus, and pawing at his open wounds.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>H takes 5 points of eating damage and fails a death saving throw.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Orange Mist tells kobolds to go back where they came from. she is hurt too much; can&rsquo;t get longsword into play; she can&rsquo;t fly away either; she&rsquo;s unavle to do anything except the dodge action.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>give angels self-healing from now on.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>drav casts fire bolt.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>hears in the wall &ldquo;help me first. my situation is dire here&rdquo;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>can see the vague three-dimensional outline of a face pushing its way through the wall. &ldquo;just another moment and i&rsquo;ll be dead&rdquo; [drav 8 insight] &mdash; you are not unconvinced by its plea.</li>\n<li>carlos [25 insight] &mdash; it&rsquo;s definitely lying. it&rsquo;s not in a dire situation. &mdash; Carlos: ignore the wall, drav!</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>(wall): ignore me at your peril. this involves all of us.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Carlos taps on its face. these rock-like claws come and swipe at you; it looks like they are trying to pull you in with it. Skip nimbly out of the way.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Drav shouts: &ldquo;get away from our friend!&rdquo; **should have allowed strength (intimidation)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the kobolds are too busy engaged in eating.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Drav tries to &ldquo;killing dissuade them&rdquo;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>shatter with sculpt spell.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>under the floor of temple; circle opens up in the floor; crushes all the kobolds. hiero&rsquo;s body left on a perfect pillar holding him up. underneath, you&rsquo;ve exposed some sort of hidden chamber.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>ROvine: looks like you all have this handled (backs up slowly)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Carlos casts healing word at 1st level again on .. .H?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>He&rsquo;s alive!!!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Hiero &mdash; multitude of kobold body parts strewn across rugged collapsed sunken chamber. hole.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>H bows to those around him; thank you! i was rather enjoying being torn apart but i understand that ultimately it wouldn&rsquo;t have been great for me. you each get a poison (oprah style)</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Carlos pats XANTHU on the head some more</p>\n<ul>\n<li>&ldquo;this is a matter of some urgency! i will bring you in here with he, and then you&rsquo;ll be forced to help solve it&rdquo;</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>SIerra Chunks is my other sister.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Heiro casts Faerie Fire. affects Slug and Bulgarius.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>even with dog attached to her leg, and slugg pressed in close, she manages to dodge out of the way. &mdash; they both start shedding light in a 10-foot radius. (almost like she can turn light on and off)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>JL moves to get better angle on Orange Mist to fire an arrow.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>DK [9] to attack.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick : amazing how much aplobm she has</p>\n<ul>\n<li>a new family will emerge and we will again defend the temple for ritual purposes.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick moves 35 feet &mdash; addresses orange mist in elvish: &ldquo;creature of light and air, answer me true as your nature demands: if we slay you , will that release the creature that your queen mentioned?&rdquo;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>OM: it will not, but it will mean we&rsquo;ve failed in ejecting you from the temple.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>flick&rsquo;s in love. and then fires at her. after she commits to getting them out. flick misses.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>OM: the power of xanthu still allows me to reject your claim to this place.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>she now demonstrates a renewed vitality; as slugg slashes at OM, she dodges both of them with alacrity. &mdash; I will be able to hold you off in the end!</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>OM brings sword down on Slugg , and up to the hilt, but Slugg is standing there, one hand on bulgarius, looking menacingly. &mdash; this is our space now! whatever you do, we&rsquo;re going to claim it, and your stupid old family will never get it back!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Slugg: i would give my life first before i let balgarius die (not BULGarious) ; it&rsquo;s more like a schaw.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Drav magic missle: 12 force damage. to kill the orange mist. 3 glowing darts appear, and strike her in the heart.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>OM: you should know that you will not be served well in this place. there are other forces that will seek to expell you!! and exterminate you !!! the stone man is xanthuuuuuuuuuuuuuuu&mdash;</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Slugg: nice work. nice missile trick. it reminds me: i knew a kobold named Myssultriq. a real upstanding citizen. i think he was mayor of kobold town for a while. i never visited.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: i want to head down into the chamber.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>casts goodberry and gives 6 to jeal-luc.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- -->\n<ul>\n<li>JL eats one of them now.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>stone man not emerging further from the wall.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>drav: we&rsquo;re standing just out of range taunting him.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick: goodberries falling about 6 feet above. then a tail is hanging out. part of balgarius&rsquo;s tale is cut off in mid air.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>sheared clean from where it&rsquo;s hanging. flick pulls tail towards herself. picks up slack in tail; looks like Flick is pulling B&rsquo;s tail.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Flick feeds tail back in through hole. palpable hole / rim to portal. as last of tail goes in, flick pinches the boundary closed (or is that what did it?) &mdash; but slowly.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>XANTHU: help me get out of here. now that the angels are gone, it&rsquo;s even more urgent.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Drav [arcana nat 1]:</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>carlos [13] &mdash; not quite sure what this is. it feels vaguely evil.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>hasn&rsquo;t been 10 minutes since cast THese rocks look great.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Carlos wants to see what happens when spell wears out</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>Drav peaks over edge of hole</p>\n<ul>\n<li>see the rubble and kobold bodies. faint sound of blood dripping out of them. hiero is still stuck on the pillar.</li>\n<li>room extends in either direction, at least to each side fo the temple. trouble seeing to the right, but can see to the left, and looks like there might be holes in the ground but too dark to tell.</li>\n<li>drav looks around first floor for hidden staircase.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n<li>\n<p>FLick; you don&rsquo;t see Rovine anymore. you do see a 15 foot tall purple gnomelike creature. dressed like a bespoke vampire. white ascot, and form-fitting tailored 3-piece suit. shiny winklepickers.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>flick: greetings, dapper fellow. did you happen to see a large, strategically gifted ogre mage around here.</li>\n<li>rovine: it&rsquo;s me, you idiot. i can&rsquo;t believe i just had to confirm that for you.</li>\n<li>flick: we dealt with the angels</li>\n<li>rovine/raxivort: all part of the plan!</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --> <!-- --></li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --><!-- --><!-- --><!-- -->\n<p>Drav discovers another secret stairway in the other corner (lower right?)</p>\n<p>ROvine walks further into the room, : my unamed minion, look at you! you&rsquo;ve proven yourself as Slugg, the chieftain, i bestow upon you my boon! (improvised little ceremony; licks his hand and brushes down balgarius&rsquo;s fur) &mdash; Keep up the good work!! then Rovine takes a practical magic smoke bomb and back out the room. &mdash; Slugg: ahhhhh my lord raxivort!!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Rovine winks at Drav on the way out.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</section>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->"}
{"_id":"9WzGJF1gLpOXhrDn","name":".timeline","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"IahJpr0JiteucCD5","sort":100000,"flags":{},"content":"<div dir=\"ltr\">6 months ago (beginning at semester)&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">ymenestra checked out castle Karn</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>11 months ago</p>\n<ul>\n<li>peryton begins acting weird</li>\n<li>fish start dying near Red Fox University</li>\n<li>Von Veen kicks up his activity</li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>1 year ago</p>\n<ul>\n<li>meteorite landed and created plahnage lake</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">23 years ago:&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">isabella comes back ?</p>\n</li>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">make isabella same as Lacrey</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">lupenna briefly returns to do ? after boggsush shows up</p>\n</li>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">maybe this is when Ymenestra last saw her and helped her plane travel</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">installs &ldquo;Belzee&rdquo; (Lacrey Errorooth) in her place</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Where is Isabella?</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">24? years ago</div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">calliope's powers extracted from her in form of Aurelia</p>\n</li>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">which means Aurelia can't be Flick's mom</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">calliope draining cultists now</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Boggsush arrives</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">26 years ago</div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">tantegorisch banished</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">41 years ago</div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Lupenna and Isabella leave to hunt down Tantegorisch</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">tantegorisch kills Aurelia \"and baby Flick\"</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Calliope moves into north tower on faded mesa</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Baron moves into castle karn</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">domonkos imprisoned</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">flick born</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Baron and Meliona (later Talma) have a child</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>1000 years ago [&sect;044]</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bogshush crashes into what is now Snaff Bay, causing earthquakes and tsunamis which radically alter the coast and the original circle of mountains forming Moraddin's Crown</li>\n</ul>\n<p>1000+ years ago</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bloodsledge Ten-Axe held off the incursions of the Great Continental Desert within the circle of mountains known as Moraddin's Crown, the only remains of which are the Nephil Mountains on the West, the Braided Mountains on the East, and the three Goblin Peaks (Goblinsmith the tallest)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>2000+ years ago</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The Continental Desert extended inside what would be made into Moraddin's Crown, and at the Southeaster edge of that region the Manush maintained religious sites, including what is now the top of the Temple of Kashtari in Sandford.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/8Maa5qYoNkbhDkXotNfVvC1cJAJvprnk87ct3WVSXE8HDhLQiBtSzeQgwKiRyNodJCSVvi44k8ZjP1GPfgUPWC7unP5rc4DF0Yixchp5ZwUgobmVmRuSnEwYuG1DGMjjUb2xyDSy\" width=\"964\" height=\"350\" /></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</section>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-6476343c-7fff-d60f-9b37-3df7604976d2\"></span></p>"}
{"_id":"9qoWHUXwK5vvENvb","name":"Dothlarshian Po'otay","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"1rJeQMjAwEFFzp63","sort":300000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>A hallucinogenic and disocciative drug extracted from the jelsinka succulent, a species native to the Doshlarshi desert.</p>"}
{"_id":"BJ7ThdVDRoy1Ri51","name":"049: [untitled]","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"nEIZOAbBi8YZmJDe","sort":1000000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>2020-12-05</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>spirit shroud for JL with lydia sword</li>\n<li>do interesting things with toolkits/proficiencies</li>\n<li>tishara vernix trying to collapse distinction between material and ethereal planes -- repercussions for everyone, but especially flick.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section>\n<h2>prep</h2>\n<p>Yeah I suppose on some level, or for each thing, make sure it relates to (a) the major plots (b) the character interests.</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Hat Baskets</strong></span></p>\n<p><em>Flirting with becoming an operating arm or cell of the Thistlemilk Kids (TMK), S&amp;B ?&nbsp;</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Oriax</strong>: a banderhobb passing itself off as a genasi\n<ul>\n<li>First seen \"working\" at <strong>The Fountain of Elegance&nbsp;</strong>\"bookshop\"</li>\n<li>Oriax is having the screws put to her by the Hat Baskets</li>\n<li>Not actually a bad sort; might be helping out Oksana with a debt</li>\n<li>Why would Oriax have any idea what Flick meant about the Log Book (especially called a \"ledger\")? Did she think it was something else? Seems like she was just buying time. Which means she's gone back and described the encounter to whomever.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Rosindra</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>did she rope in JL because she just happened to see him and decided to rope in a dupe for a project? she must also be in hock to somebody. -- that's why i can't remember/find JL's insight check on this: the recording stopped early .</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Tishara Vernix</strong><br />\n<ul>\n<li>why is she so ruthless?</li>\n<li>is she herself being made to do something by TMK?</li>\n<li>where does her money come from again?</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Gaol Maidens</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Scunner</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>why did scunner recognize JL, and, if so, not say anything</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Yolindar</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>probably working withTepplin and Ipso Fatso\n<ul>\n<li>offered GM help: getting Azurite</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<section><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Barazar Sod</strong></span></section>\n<ul>\n<li>Probably makes more sense that he's illegally trading medical supplies than arms (but could be both)</li>\n<li>Tasha/HB are blackmailing Barazar with what information? to get him to do that</li>\n<li>Maybe they were all part of a cabal of people that invoked SB to get rid of TG, or vice versa. I feel like this doesn't work, or else they would all be equally culpable.</li>\n<li>Still, why does TG care about Flick?\n<ul>\n<li>EP now both Flick and Jaap</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Barazar and Jantien have a shared interest in another gnome diety that's made itself gnown to them, Dandegoss. And so ... is she also helping him? Or maybe she's a cleric now for a spin-off deity cult. Or she'd always communicatd with Barazar and he told her about this new \"church\". Does he know a bunch of other gnomes too?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>The Countenance of Selfless Mercy&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n<p><em>Good thing for Drav to continue to/be able to research. Link Drav research with Jean-Luc practical and tactical knowledge.&nbsp;</em></p>\n<p><em>How to work in:</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Jaap and Garl Glittergold&nbsp;</em>\n<ul>\n<li><em>maybe has to do with why GG saying nothing about his sister</em></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>The group of people who did the TG/BS thing\n<ul>\n<li>Barazar Sod</li>\n<li>Venix family</li>\n<li>Yolindar?</li>\n<li>Ipso Fatso?</li>\n<li>The Order of Rust</li>\n<li>Raul knew? Or kept it hidden? Raul was even part of it?</li>\n<li>Maybe a Gormflaith druid too or something?&nbsp;&nbsp;\n<ul>\n<li>Why would Lupenna and Isabella never have mentioned this? Or Rovine's sister (did I ever include her?)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>I think I need to twist TG so he's not all evil, which means they did something like make a pact with him to banish SB and then found some way to banish him too. Which must have involved some other wizard-anti-wizard type cabal (The Erudite)</li>\n<li>So Kriobolis isn't really part of it yet but that's going to be going on behind the scenes. they might need TG or something to deal with Ipso Fasto and Pelaria.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"CEZgIb7LgUhQVYet","name":"004. Small potatoes","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"GF8k0MkmV1DIfHvo","sort":200001,"flags":{},"content":"<div><strong>Session</strong>: &sect;004 Small potatoes</div>\n<div><strong>Played</strong>: October 26, 2019 (2019-10-26)</div>\n<div><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-06a38130-7fff-8393-b15d-1db4633e4b91\"></span></div>\n<div><strong>Day 1 (cont.) &bull; Day 2</strong></div>\n<div><strong>Level 1</strong></div>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<h1 id=\"recap\">Recap</h1>\n<p>After puddlizing^ the immor, Flick, skifting [flitting] from tree to tree towards the gnoll village, was anticipated in the approach by Joan, who hailed a half dozen of the canine creatures. This latter approach proved its merit, when Thaz, a stealthy outposted guard, got the drop on Flick's hedge-creeping. The magician Mezlar brokered systatic [commendatory] introductions of not only the gnolls but a greedy pig named Gribble which Carlos believed to be out of Paros's romantic league. After Thaz impressed them with hearty calisthenics, Mezlar offered as bivouac the empty home of a recently deceased community member. Flick, ever the detective, described the \"fetus mushrooms\" seen earlier that day to Mezlar, who instantly recognized the object detailed. One of the gnolls, Kolmy Shortpaw, had, a few months ago, moved north of the village near an expanse of desecrated ruins, and renamed herself Grenlich. The gnolls had been rooting out and burning the hodmandods, but a report of them so far from the village was worrisome; such expansion indicated that Grenlich, once trained by Mezlar's father in techniques now forsworn by the village, could become a sore threat soon.</p>\n<p>Mining Mezlar further for renseignements, the group learned that Joan's black orb could instantly impart a year's worth of solid core training to one employing its power, and that the material substance of Flick's figuring bore similarities to an onyx-like stone quondam [formerly] mined nearby. At this point, Joan ceremoniously burned Dravita in the town bonfire, and everyone, exhausted by recent travails, betook themself of a nocturnal rest.</p>\n<p>The next morning, Flick abraided [awoke] to the cool 'magical cleansing' tongue of 'Jasper and the Lady Violet' (<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-157e22db-7fff-584b-df9d-5a77955c35fc\">An intelligent horse who lives with gnolls; a practiced surveyor and mathematician</span>) and its porcine friend. Trivialities were soon shoved aside, though, as a gnoll trapper was carried into town having had his heart torn out and a bevy of winged hodmandods flew into the village, petrified most of the congregated with horrendous shriek, and made to extract the life-force from the dead trapper. A misplaced lightning bolt from Joan allowed one of the creatures to bud a landbound form, and in the fight at least one gnoll was splashed with a sticky ichor before the monsters could take flight. Hoping to provide aid, the adventurers met with Brak Shortpaw, sister to Komy and resident Lorekeeper, who revealed that the trapper's heart had been removed by a not unfamiliar harpy-like creature, and that the appearance of the hodmandods likely an unfortunate coincidence. Apprised of these new developments, the gang took a moment to regroup and steel themselves for their next step.</p>\n<p><strong><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-cda8b283-7fff-ce14-5826-a45e6080090d\">&mdash; Hingleburt Tauncelledonque, esq.</span></strong></p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>puddlizing</strong>:&nbsp; (perh?) reducing to a puddle</p>\n<h1 id=\"transcript\">Transcript</h1>\n<p>[n/a]</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>joan burns dravita</p>\n<p>how many of the small potatoes die ?</p>\n<p>so there&rsquo;s the heartless gnoll (metaphor), and the spit-on nurse gnoll</p>\n<p>will burnt dravita come back in a dream ? or otherwise ?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>====</p>\n<p>[0:0]</p>\n<p>group of 6 gnolls approaching</p>\n<p>party has come into the gnoll village</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>joan wants to be able to just go up and say hi to people, not make checks</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[0:3]</p>\n<p>gribble and pigs trot over</p>\n<p>knives described</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>paros wants to find the pig thing that he saw earlier</p>\n<p>jake &ldquo;have mezlar tell him that pig&rsquo;s out of his league&rsquo;</p>\n<p>flick convinced by joan&rsquo;s friendliness (amicable, neighborly, sociable, genial)</p>\n<p>matt: &ldquo;a pig&rsquo;s going to swipe right on you&rdquo;</p>\n<p>[x] &ldquo;swine&hellip; right?&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[0:4]</p>\n<p>one of gnolls gets drop on Flick, wearing leather armor</p>\n<p>THAZ - sort of like british &ldquo;eh, chap&rdquo; type</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>gribble says &ldquo;hi&rdquo; really loudly</p>\n<p>looking for food. knows people lie when they say they don&rsquo;t have food.</p>\n<p>pigs are knee-height; flick gives berries; pigs come over; flick casts the berries&nbsp;</p>\n<p>gribble (female) is greediest</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[0:9]</p>\n<p>(ian recounts finding the fetus mushroom)</p>\n<p>Thaz does some calisthenics</p>\n<p>&nbsp;when the gnolls walk back to their houses</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Mezlar does talk to Joan</p>\n<p>Mezlar asks Joan if they still need place to stay</p>\n<p>one of the gnolls living at a home died recently, offers them the center of the village , not the central lodge</p>\n<p>[0:11]</p>\n<p>reactions to the mushroom fetus : &ldquo;oh god, where did you find this?&rdquo; &ldquo;a few hours? her range must be expanding&rdquo;.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;one of us who is up to really dangerous experimentation, and we&rsquo;ve seen these things cropping up. we eradicate as soon as we see them. they are designed to be evil&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;no longer considers herself one of us.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;her name used to be KOLMY - a few months ago she decided she didn&rsquo;t want to live amongst us any more. She took a hag name, the GRENLICH, in the ruins to the north. the camp seems to disappear when we approach&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>joan: &ldquo;is there harm in me carrying dravida&rdquo;</p>\n<p>mezlar: &ldquo;no? but we burn them&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;the pigs turn their noses up at a slightly rotten berry&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>joan: &ldquo;if we go up to GRENLICH&rsquo;s cottage, and play nice, will she be taken in?&rdquo;</p>\n<p>mezlar: &ldquo;sheh might be living in the ground, or a pocket dimension -- she knows when we are coming and can disappear&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[0:15]</p>\n<p>joan offers the orb</p>\n<p>mezlar: &ldquo;do you have a rag &hellip; to hold it with?&rdquo;</p>\n<p>carlos: &ldquo;how much of a threat is kolmy?&rdquo;</p>\n<p>mezlar: &ldquo;she&rsquo;s a great threat. she learned her magic from my deceased father. he taught her things that we&rsquo;ve since &hellip; shied away from [abjured; renounced; rejected&rsquo; forsworn; disavowed? ; repudiated; abnegated; ]. and she turned towards some of those darker arts.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>joan: &ldquo;is he dead because he killed himself because he was so embarrassed about that?&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>mezlar: swallows the orb. &ldquo;come at me&rdquo;</p>\n<p>joan: &ldquo;no, we&rsquo;re alright.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>[0:18:30]</p>\n<p>talking to mezlar about the figurine, how it&rsquo;s mined from a stone nearby (possibly)</p>\n<p>how dwarves / deep gnomes trying to dig under castle karn?</p>\n<p>how lupenna was born more than a generation ago, and used to live in castle karn</p>\n<p>[42]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[0:59] - in the midst of our break / ian talking about&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[...]</p>\n<p>[1:10]</p>\n<p>Ian and Matt talking about sorcery points and metamagic</p>\n<p>sorcerous origin</p>\n<p>sorcerer&rsquo;s path is how they can use their metamagic ?</p>\n<p>[1:15] &ldquo;silent butt tickle&rdquo; spell prepared</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>next morning :&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[1:16] - Flick awakened by a horse licking her hair</p>\n<p>horse voice &ldquo;this is magical saliva, this will keep you clean&rdquo;</p>\n<p>pig climbs up on the horse (JASPER (male))</p>\n<p>[1:18] gnoll who was setting a game trap had heart ripped out</p>\n<p>thaz : &ldquo;i don&rsquo;t think that&rsquo;s all we have to be worried about&rdquo;</p>\n<p>[flying into down: but flying towards you</p>\n<p>Dravita was burned the previous night.</p>\n<p>creature shriek</p>\n<p>[1:24]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;gnolls also unable to move.</p>\n<p>(40 total)</p>\n<p>gnolls have bows</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[1:38]</p>\n<p>still fighting, Joan trying to figure out how to attack</p>\n<p>scales around joan&rsquo;s face falls away --&nbsp;</p>\n<p>crit fail: joan spawns another one</p>\n<p>flick rolls 23 to be able to follow the flight path of&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[1:44]</p>\n<p>vargouilles?: oblong collection of sinews and tendons - on the ones flying away (two got away)</p>\n<p>- jake trying to figure out how to cast \"eternal flame\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp; - send down bolt of radiant energy; lets down a mini-shriek</p>\n<p>- 80 ft. away now</p>\n<p>- paros tries ray of frost; resistant to cold damage</p>\n<p>- two dead vargouilles on the ground; a dead gnoll too.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- paros: is that the gnoll that was taken?</p>\n<p>- thaz?: no, i think that's someone else.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- mezlar grabs other gnolls: \"get her to the altar!\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp; - no one died during the battle</p>\n<p>- Thaz: we should see who that is and what those creatures are.</p>\n<p>- you see: one of the gnolls, wearing dark blue tunic, little books on it;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; - they don't write anything down (i said?) but they make images of books</p>\n<p>- thaz: hands it off to Brak. she's got pretentious about learning ... but she's generally the lore keeper, insofar as it's dedicated to one gnoll.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- no one is touching the dead vargouilles</p>\n<p>- joan: does brak every look deep in thought?</p>\n<p>- flick introduces self. very happy to have aided in your defense in any small way. do you have to deal with the heart-getting-ripped-out thing often?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>## 1:52:34</p>\n<p>brak: yes, we've had that before but never in concert with these vargouliles. they look like a form of the mushroom aberrations. we've never seen the flying ones. that plop-thing was totally new. i'm going to blame that on Joan.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; - i should cleric-fy. i never made it into cleric school. i had to apply the abstract arts. i've kept in touch with some of our history. the one who brought her in didn't know. there are creatures that live in the mountains and take the hearts of living creatures. i think they feed them to their children. they go after everyone INCLUDING THE DRUIDS UP NORTH; who you think would be able to take care of themselves.</p>\n<p>- there are multiple, and they look like large vultures; stealthy; intelligent; they take the hearts out.</p>\n<p>- flick \"mushroom bats\"</p>\n<p>- carlos: they are probably ... smell the dead.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- flick, yes, they appear to reproduce asexually after eating dead flesh.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- brak: are you a scientist?</p>\n<p>- flick: no, probably the opposite. brak: what does that mean?&nbsp; I'M THE ONLY PERSON WHO HIT ONE OF THESE THINGS WELL</p>\n<p>&nbsp; - flick: i understand less about these things with everything i hear.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>## 1:57:00</p>\n<p>- carlos / paros: can we talk to the mushrooms?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[2:01] contamignoll</p>\n<p>[2:02]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>end of session</p>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"Cjp3YCQAnyI7gN2Y","name":"Star of Tepplin","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"1rJeQMjAwEFFzp63","sort":100000,"flags":{},"content":"<div>Eight-pointed silver star</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>One of the symbols of Tepplin Baronian; in particular, that of his distilleries in Albland. When he fortified the compound after raids who were after a secret ingredient, it was suggested that he use the eight-point shape. It's suspected that the color of the star has something to do with the secret ingredient they were after, as a kind of \"fuck you.\"</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Entirely by accident, Jean-luc claimed to the Seomra \"Elphs\" that he was a constable or retriever for Baronian's estate and that Flick and Aphelia had stolen a secret recipe used to make one of the draughts.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>"}
{"_id":"CrXP9wyR6JWvLRl9","name":"Lydia","permission":{"default":0,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3},"folder":"wf40lADkdvhEIKuG","sort":1200000,"flags":{},"content":"<ul>\n<li>daughter of a shopkeeper</li>\n</ul>\n<p>from JL perspective</p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-0b0dd1ff-7fff-4a65-6669-b5e2dc1916fa\"></span></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">why </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">did </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">they break up</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">He carries around a sword he calls \"Lydia\" after the woman who stabbed him in the heart, (she's also a perfectly nice person and the break-up was amicable).</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">his sword, which stabs, is named after a woman that stabbed (but didn't) -- so really his sword won't, either ??</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}
