{"_id":"EmGy2PDabdrVnxyL","name":"043: I'm uhhhhhh pretty good at not getting in the way","permission":{"default":2,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3},"folder":"nEIZOAbBi8YZmJDe","sort":200000,"flags":{},"content":"<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Session</strong>: &sect;043</div>\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Played</strong>: October 10, 2020 (2020-10-10)</div>\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Day</strong>: Day 12</div>\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Level</strong>: 8</div>\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" /></div>\n<h1 id=\"sister-light-sister-dark\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-line=\"20\">Recap</h1>\n<div><span style=\"color: #191813;\">[not written yet]</span></div>\n<h1><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Transcript</span></h1>\n<div>dragon-mouse (galen's report)</div>\n<div>they've gotten a night's rest, or</div>\n<div>Vengeance has been holding Flick's eyes open while she tries to trance. \"If you really want to be a monk, you're going to have to sack up and embrace the lifestyle.\" Vengeance has started the training, and Flick has no inkling.</div>\n<div>Vengeance as a half-elf has to sleep with one eye but he can trance with the other eye.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<h2>Waking up at the&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #191813;\">Monarch's Pelt</span></h2>\n<div>Jean-Luc wakes up in the morning to a dagger pinning a piece of paper to the door of his room. He recognizes this as standard thieves communication, albeit slightly more sinister than necessary. Checking the room to confirm that nothing else has been disturbed, he walks over and investigates the dagger. It looks like an arsenical-bronze blade, and individual strips of rawhide dyed blue, green, and white are tied around the hilt to form a grip. On the obverse is a drawing of the city with a particular house marked with an X. The reverse contains a note in bold calligraphy:&nbsp; \"Twilight. Bring the dagger.\" Jean-Luc surmises this note is an instruction from the Hat Baskets (aka the Priest Ground Bag) regarding where and when to meet. Seeing he's in no rush, he lazily enjoys smells of roasting meats, fresh bread, and tangy ale wafting up from the kitchen, set to further delight by comparison with the clean bay breeze and the distant mewing of gulls.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Vengeance, chary of the company such environs have no doubt attracted, says to himself, \"I hope they don't expect us to make chitchat with the others villagers here.\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Flick in frustration examines Shoemaker's goodberries, beginning to wrinkle and shrink from waterloss. She believes she could preserve their healing qualities and clues as to their ultimate provenance (she wants to see why it's behaving so strangely -- if she's able to show the essence to an arcanist) by preserving them in a jam or a jelly, which would extend their useful lives by a few months.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>A discussion ensues regarding preservation of foods in a bag of holding. It may preserve them more than if they were in the open.</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Walking into the kitchen, Flick asks for two cups of sugar, a canning jar, and some boiling water. One of the chefs, a tall willowy woman with short-cropped brown hair, cautions, \"You know you can't make fires in your room.\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Flick: \"All I want to do is cook these berries on your stove for an hour or two and seal them in a jar in some boiling water.\" The chef looks at Flick like she needs to get over herself. \"i have to prepare for the guests all day long. i guess -- there's a little room on the hearth -- if you wanna grab a cast iron pot, you can take one, but don't get in the way of anyone.\"</div>\n<div>Flick: \"i'm uhhhhhh pretty good at not getting in the way.\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Flick ends up with a jam ...</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>20 hit points worth</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>... though she's not planning on spreading it on toast. Nevertheless,&nbsp;Vengeance tries to procure a toasted baguette to spread it on (after Flick gives him a little bit). \"Oh nice! continental breads!\" and he stuffs his pockets full of them. There are no baguettes, though. Mostly pumpernickles and dense black and brown breads. the seeds are pretty well crushed. there are finer loaves. His desire for a smooth bread experience is matched pretty closely. He usually dips his bread in water, which is why dipping nuts in them is even worse. He also has a 'bread cup' to pour water into, which mostly drains out the sides and then he eats the soggy bread. \"Everything I own is actually made out of bread,\" he mourns.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>A little kid decked out in a beanie and a onesie emerges from the kitchen.&nbsp; \"Hey can i get you some bread?\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: \"ooh, i don't know if i like this. I think I found what i was looking for.\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>kid: you seem to really be picking through them. people around here dno't have great hygiene. i have to wash my hands before each meal.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>The DM thinks that \"maybe\" this is for religious rather than germ-theory reasons, which would make sense. Luckily, no one calls him on it.</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: \"you mean other people have access to this bread? i thought it was just for me,\" he declares, standing in the middle of a very crowded small room with two long wooden tables, six people waiting behind him to get at the bread.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: oh, i assumed they were here for other stuff. geez. josh. sorry. i'll just ve another ten minutes or so.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>YOU BETTER GET OUT OF THE WAY, WE WANT SOME BREAD HERE. WE WANT BREAD, WE WANT BREAD. as the other guests begin to pound the tables demandingly.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: if you can even call this bread, i'm not sure. i think i'm going to take my business elsewhere.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>The kid bristles. \"People around here love my mother's bread. i'm always been told you should be as nice as you can if it's a stranger you might be impugning.\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: it shouldn't be so hard on me! (he takes a bit of a ceramic bowl and cracks his front tooth). \"not again!\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>the kid digs under the pile for the lightest, creamiest loaf to give to him. it's still loaf shaped. \"what's a breadstick?\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: you know what a stick is, right?</div>\n<div>kid: is it like that?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>a guy behind vengeance is holding a stick ready to smack some sense into you.</div>\n<div>vengeance: a perfect example! (and he tries to take a bite of the stick)</div>\n<div>[performance ] it's not quite clear to the ruffian what vengeance is going.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\"hey, get off my stick! that's my favorite whopping stick don't try to chew on it. get out of the line!\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: sorry, sometimes everything looks like bread to me. i guess i'm just hungry.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>ruffian: there's a baker in town if you want to have a go at being an apprentice.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>flick, meanwhile, has a taste for coffee which she acquired in marshbout. she had to hang around in coffeeklatches. she's in the corner, suddenly abraided from her caffeinated reverie by whatever's happening at the bread table.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Flick intuits the presence of vengeance behind a very large threatening man holding a stick. the child interposes himself between vengeance and the other customer. \"ok, ok, you wouldn't want to hit a kid, would you? everybody just back up.\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance tries to overturn the table with all the bread on it. \"i don't know why everyone is making a big deal out of this. all I wanted was one piece of bread so my friend could have some toast with jam. it's not my fault, ok, it's hers\" and he points to flick.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>after vengeance knocks the table over, the kid gets out of the way, \"ok you guys can go at him, get him out of here.\" six people approach vengeance and go to throw him out of the inn.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\"you're listening to that beanie boy?\" Flick makes some comment a about b-boys</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>Breakdancers?</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>ruffian: \"that's the missus's kid. everybody respects this little tyke\". they all give his beanie a nuggie. vengeance kicks and flails ineffectually, cautioning, \"\"better check under that beanie and see what he's hiding, I have a bad feeling about this kid.\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>luckily flick's name is also a word, so no one associated it with a person.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance can see that there is an addlepated old woman who latches onto his accusations of the beanie child and eyes his hat suspiciously. everyone else is deaf to his pleas and picks him up and throws him out onto the street.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\"See, that addlepated woman knows what i'm talking about! listen to her!\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>through the doorway, she points at vengeance: \"cursed you are: cursed!\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: oh no.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>The DM requests a luck check to determine how recently it rained.</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>it rained pretty recently: not last night but the night before. it's so muddy that he doesn't get hurt, but he's now covered in a sandy mud.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>flick turns demitasse upside-down, throws some copper jots onto the table...</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>The DM quotes from <em>Kingkiller</em> #1: The innkeeper's mouth pressed itself into a straight line that was not quite a frown. \"Of course,\" he said as he emptied his purse onto the table then fingered through the jumbled coins: heavy silver talents and thin silver bits, copper jots, broken ha'pennies, and iron drabs. \"Does anyone have a shim?\"&nbsp;</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>... and follows the crowd out the door, stopping on the way to grab some floor bread.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>To the townsfolk this would be known as <em>flierb&ocirc;le&nbsp;</em>(from the Frisian, of course).</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>most of the customers are helping the kid get the table upright and put the food back on.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: thanks friend. can you believe the nerve of those people ? they didn't even heave-ho three times.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>flick: yeah, i noticed that. maybe they do things differently around here, but it didn't seem respectful. (flick gives Vengeance a piece of bread and offers him the jar of goodberry jam)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>addlepated woman: each number not in a \"heave-ho\" is left as a curse through which for you to go. my prosody's not what it once was.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: so ... i'm double-cursed now?</div>\n<div>flick: sounds like.</div>\n<div>DM: sounds like you're only singly-cursed, since they didn't count up their heave-hos.</div>\n<div>vengeance: so it takes away the curse?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>The DM clarifies that, in fact, each heave-ho is another curse.</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: so if i'd gotten two curses it would have canceled out? uhhhhhh.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL is still in his room, enjoying the fact he got to wake up in a bed. a nice change of pace. he hears a bit of commotion downstairs. \"i don't care what this is, it's not my problem. nothing's on fire and i don't hear bloodcurdling screams.\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>Galen 'reminds' DK that Jean-Luc's toenails look freshly cut, since Vengeance trimmed them last night to make a necklace to ward off curses.</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL didn't notice -- V has done this enough to be able to do it in people's sleep --&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>DK requests to determine whether or not the necklace would have any effect on Jean-Luc. Vengeance's arcana check is a 12.</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>it's unlikely, but it's possible that it would could ward off a curse, but probably not at the expense of JL. thsi old lady's curse. but as far as you could tell she didn't have any body parts of yours, and wasn't personally afflicted by what you'd done. the curse has a tenuous hold on you anyway, even if she were powerful.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>ian: is there a kind of magic that has to do with sympathetic attraction? where you require pieces of a thing to exert control. me: absolutely. it doesn't always have a negative connotation. there are cultures where it's part of their world, and for others it's necromancy. sometimes it might be real, and sometimes it might be believed.</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL heads downstairs, grabs some breakfast tea, some bread and cheese.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Vengeance was hoping not so much to absorb the curse into JL, like a voodoo doll shield of JL. Vengeance is trying to Munchausen-by-proxy Jean-Luc so that he comes to depend on Vengeance. (actually curse him and make him sick).</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Externally, Flick sees Vengeance pull out a necklace of toenails string together with devilfloss. He realizes Vengeance is more occupied with this bit of charm and puts away the jam and stares awkwardly down the street.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL comes over Vengeance muttering over some toenails that might be familiar</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>(with a 20 passive investigation, he probably does know.)</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>After seeing the dagger this morning he'd probably checked over himself for tattoos, and noticed his nails had been cut -- that he knows exactly what Vengeance has done. (\"There may be a time when Vengeance has to die\")</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL doesn't believe in folk-magic of this sort, or only of the fringe centers, the way real DK thinks about astrology. (\"i think it's cool, but i don't believe in it\")</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL looks around to make sure no one's listening, now that they'lre out in public. it's pretty loud, even in the morning. there's the beach market at which also some celebration seems to be happening making a lot of noise.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL : it seems like we should wait for our friends at the Temple to take care of Fez. How do you feel in the meantime about getting involved in the local thieves' guild?</div>\n<div>Flick: YesSssssss!</div>\n<div>JL: i should warn you, -- the reason I fled Kriobolis is that the local thieves' guild put a price on my head, and these people also have a gripe with the Gaol Maidens. we might have a mutual interest then, but it's possible that they might try to kill us. i'm pretty sure they won't, but it's not out of the question.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote>\n<div>The Demerast Saga is mentioned for the first time.</div>\n</blockquote>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: purely out of curiosity, what was the price?</div>\n<div>JL: i'm not sure, but you're welcome to try to collect</div>\n<div>[JL is intimidating Vengeance out of being serious. Vengeance doesn't even notice that JL is trying to intimidate you. ]</div>\n<div>Vengeance: Yeah, maybe I will. Um, how are you feeling today, JL. are you feeling ... cursed at all?</div>\n<div>JL glances at the necklace and shrugs. well i slept in a bed, I had breakfast to eat, I'm in a city , and nothing is trying to kill me, so i'm better than i've been in a few days.</div>\n<div>vengeance: definitely nothing is trying to turn me into a bag of bones</div>\n<div>JL: but i should warn you that the GMs are quite capable of collecting the bounty and we shouldn't take them lightly.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL notices that as Vengeance fingers his necklace, two of the toenails fall off, being insecurely tied to the string. JL calculates that over time the necklace will disintegrate of its own accord.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>where the necklace falls in the sandy dirt of the street he sees a metallic glint. JL picks it up. it's a very simple circle and pin brooch that bears a distinctive design. creatures carved into it; something that looks like a lion, and a goat, carved delicately around the circle.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL: [history]</div>\n<div>flick: is this a clue?!</div>\n<div>JL: there's a kingdom -- lowest ithsmus on the right; a kingdom that when he was learning old thieves' legends, was rumored to have been started by a group of seafaring pirates who settled down and formed coastal communities to raid the surrounding areas. over time it became an empire, which would take advantage of the agricultural people in the hinterlands. these two animals were on their crest. the empire itself is even considered to be historical by this point. he can't be sure what modern use the symbols are being put to. just by looking at the item, it looks like it was made recently to evoke that imagery of that empire (exploitative piracy).</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>it looks like it's made out of sandford brass. JL puts it in his pockets.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL wants to take a day to enjoy things not trying to kill him.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>they head towards the southern harbor district. Flick follows JL, but thinks they shoould look in on Fez too. he's about 3/4 of a mile away in the direction of the harbor.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>[1:22]</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>On the outside it looks like Alphonse Alpothecary. they were told to go in and ask for a lotion that matches your dagger.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: wait, before you go in there, did you see the sign? (he can barely walk because he's laughing too hard, dropping ever more toenails ffrom the necklace like breadcrumbs. ) DK: you have at MOST ten toenails. IAN: you could break them smaller. DM: you might be leaving an actual trail of breadcrumbs.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL walks in, produces the dagger, and asks for a matching set. I think just a few have come in and they're going to be in the back room. he walks to the front, locks the door, and draws the blinds shut. behind the counter is a trap door with stairs leading down into a basement space.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL to himself: standard back-roo criminal fence stuff. no guy obviously standing in the shadows ?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Vengeance runs inside and says, \"I'm privileged too.</div>\n<div>JL: the archer's with me. the monk i take no responsibility for.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Alphonse: old monk, are you lost here? have you mistaken this for a place off sanctuary?</div>\n<div>vengeance: i'm hoping it will be, but i did have a question. do you happen to do custom weapons here.</div>\n<div>alphonse: we don't --- as you can see this is entirely an apothecary, we havae potions and lotions and medicaments and ointments and jointments. do you desire any of these things?</div>\n<div>vengeance: oh yes. uh. (and tries to wink) i would like one of your \"sharpest\" ointments. something that really \"cuts the air\". something \"pungent\". im not great at this double-talk. i need a real weapon.</div>\n<div>JL: the monk is with me, begrudgingly.</div>\n<div>Al: ok, follow behind us.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>downstairs doubles as al's recreation center. a few intellectual board games. plush chairs. the floor is covered in very nice rugs. it looks pretty cozy. it reminds you of rovine's study under the xanthuc temples. fewer books, though. al is not an intellectual. there's an array of pipes and tobacco, pipes made from bones and animal parts. this might be akin to a bachelor bad.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>al: if we had to get rid of your friend here, i was going to say that we were just going to fuck, and that would i imagine have gotten rid of him.</div>\n<div>JL: it wouldn't have; i shudder to think how he would have responded.</div>\n<div>al: a companion after my own nature, then. well met, old monk.</div>\n<div>vengeance: i mighth have been put off by it, but a man of your sense of humor, i have to forgive you anything.</div>\n<div>al: you sure are good for the heart. they do teach monks the arts of courtesy these days. i must say you're a shining example.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL: i was hoping to find a set of daggers for close-quarters combat (stabbing rather than slicing)</div>\n<div>al: why didn't you visit the more traditional armorers in town?</div>\n<div>JL: the standard daggers are someone clumsy. i need something more refined</div>\n<div>al: we do indeed deal in</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>[1:31]</div>\n<div>Al goes over to nice benches that line the walls, carved in geometric patterns; they don't look like they can be opened, but he places his hand on the top and runs it along the edge, and suddenly the tops become hinged and they open. he motions them over.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\"yes these are my daggers here. there are some masterworks -- small throwing daggers, stilettos, singel-edge, dual edge. they all look well-crafted; they are of some kind of pleated, folded metal (like damascus steel). these are all laid out on a plush surface. on the right are a few in boxes.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\"these over here require a special touch; they are extraordinarily expensive; i must maintain my intimate quarters down here, but it seems that the ones visible are probably to your taste and ability to purchase.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>flick: are you calling us poor?</div>\n<div>al: not poor, certainly.</div>\n<div>JL: shut up!</div>\n<div>al: i can see that Berchazius has had his hands on you recently (the shrimp merchant). you're just not the tippy top of the elite. i don't see any of you having a trust fund.</div>\n<div>JL: if only we were in krobopolis, or krebolis, or whatever . crapple-toppolis?</div>\n<div>JL reaches towards the stiletto points.</div>\n<div>al: monk, what is your name</div>\n<div>vengeance: you know, i change it so often. you can call me (french) vengeance</div>\n<div>al: speaking of touching, if you'll allow me</div>\n<div>al reaches out and touches vengeances, and vengeance turns into a straw mannequin of himself. \"your friend here will provide an excellent mannequin for target practice. he should experience no pain and retains at least the better part of a quarter of his awareness while the spell lasts. it's only five or ten minutes or so. it looks like straw, but it provides the give of flesh.\"</div>\n<div>flick: what in the fucking world</div>\n<div>JL: i pick up the stiletto and [investigation check] (+2 attack, +1 damage masterwork . if he's looking for something rarer, it's probably in the little boxes.)</div>\n<div>JL resists the temptation to stab Vengeane. \"these feel quite nice, how much\"</div>\n<div>al: let me see here, what are we working with: -- for this one here, i think it would be about 250 of the king's coin. i don't necessarily need gold tho. i accept gems too: quite easy to fence as long as you're not crystals of catarryth, are you?</div>\n<div>JL holds open the bag of gems from the burrowlings.</div>\n<div>al: oh my whever did you get this? it looks like a hoard of one of our rodentia friends.</div>\n<div>JL: good eye. they didn't need them anymore.</div>\n<div>al: i'll bet. it's a question whether or not they need them to begin with. it appears they are quite susceptible to this kind of mineral madness. (latvian: dārgakmens trakums)</div>\n<div>yes, let me see -- he pulls out a loupe and looks through the bag, picking out a few (pearl, some gemstones). this should make it even. i hate to deprive you of some of the most valuable, if this is your whole store.</div>\n<div>JL: then we have a deal.</div>\n<div>AL: was it tashara who sent you here, or malenka? reminda? i know she's been getting on the scene.</div>\n<div>JL: i think a man of your profession appreciates a little discretion.</div>\n<div>AL: they will miss out on the commission. they didn't provide a calling card?</div>\n<div>JL intuits nothing nefarious on the surface, but he's not positive it's just to commission them</div>\n<div>JL: nope, i jus wandered in by chance.</div>\n<div>al: seems very unlikely , esp with that dagger, and does seem like discretion is the better part of good relations. (echoed by JL, vengeance). you three, i tell you, we could have been real friends</div>\n<div>Flick: could you turn our friend into a real boy, now.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Al pulls a long saber out from behind his robe, and slices off the head -- the straw superstructure collapses and vengeance is standing there underneath.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL: that's a nice trick there.</div>\n<div>Al: I'm glad you like it. it took me many years to master. You wouldn't like to know what happened in the intervening years, I daresay.</div>\n<div>Vengeance: i have quite a headache now. quite a my-grain.</div>\n<div>alphonse: yes well being an apothecary i can fix you right up with that.</div>\n<div>vengeance: good, because it's looking to become a haymaker.</div>\n<div>al: aha, yes, very good, i knew you were funny</div>\n<div>vengeance: i knew you were a man who would appreciate it</div>\n<div>al: i certainly am. anytime you want to come back here without your fellows is fine by me too.</div>\n<div>vengeance: hm, well, i actually had a question as to whether you could make a hawk hatchet for me.</div>\n<div>al: what is that?</div>\n<div>vengeance: it's sort of like a boomerang, but it has blades on it; it's very difficult to use so only real experts should try. fortunately I am one; i just haven't been able to find it anywhere</div>\n<div>al: i'm not actually a metal forger, i'm just a middleman. even with your description it's hard for me to picture what you want. i must say, tho, as a custom product it would be even more expensive than the one that your friend here just purchased.</div>\n<div>vengeance: it shouldn't be too hard to make.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>he takes a dagger and carves into the wall a stick with two scythe blades on either side. a short, double-sided scythe. nothing like a boomerang.</div>\n<div>al: so you just need scythe heds affixed to a staff? a peasant weapon?</div>\n<div>vengeance: well it doesn't look like a boomerang but it behaves like one</div>\n<div>al: yes, even the name of a maker i don't have for a weapon like that. it sounds like you're looking for a specific artefact or legendary item. is one of its nature told of at the monasteries? it sounds like one of a kind.</div>\n<div>vengeance: yes, i mean, it's a classic monk weapon, only i was never allowed to use a real one, i had to use the rubber version, which is basically a toy, but I got really good at it, and i'm ready to prove my skills. i thought you were a weapons man!</div>\n<div>al: as i've said, i'm a middle man, i sell expensive weapons to clientelle who can affor it. i don't make weapons from scratch or traffic in these childlike notions of what constitutes weaponry that may appear to a solitary half-elf in his wanderings through the woods.</div>\n<div>vengeance; you sure talked a big game about those daggers. and your voice is really cool. still, i'm disappointed that you don't know this.</div>\n<div>al: well i do a different voice for the apothecary and weapons clients, and it takes a bit of time to transition. i can't help you with the weapon.</div>\n<div>vengeance; what's the name of that blacksmith again?</div>\n<div>al: the one who definitely can't do that one?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Melford Bloodsledge, she owns a forge neer the Zinc Hills, just once you're north of the city ask for her. it's known that she does pieces for a price, and can be quite discrete when the need arises.</div>\n<div>vengeance: i just need someone to make it for me, and maybe you can enchant it.</div>\n<div>al: i can only do parlor tricks, nothing like enchanting a weapon</div>\n<div>vengeance: dammit, i thought you were a magic man.</div>\n<div>al: no, that's my cousin Dimitrio. he's the magic man.</div>\n<div>vengeance: i wish you would have told us you were a middle man at the beginning.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>al eyes the other two men.</div>\n<div>flick and JL shrug helplessly.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL: i thnk you for your service, we must be going, i hope our paths cross again.</div>\n<div>al: let me get you that headache medication. up, up!</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>al goes to the bathroom.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: fancy a trip to this blacksmith?</div>\n<div>JL: i'm a bit low on coin</div>\n<div>vengeane: you did lose much of your savings just now. where's the rest of your money?</div>\n<div>JL: in a bank in kribopolis / krebulis</div>\n<div>vengeance: do you want to give me the account number in case you forget it?</div>\