inting in each opposite ?</div>\n<div>melford: monk, you have any interest in this? we can't get it to fly.</div>\n<div>vengeance: uh, i dunno</div>\n<div>melford: gelston, throw that in the lake, we're donen with that</div>\n<div>gelston: ok!</div>\n<div>vengeance: well, hold on, --- are those blades serrated?</div>\n<div>melford: nah, they're silky smooth</div>\n<div>vengeance: can you ... make them?</div>\n<div>melford: yeah just cut notches in there</div>\n<div>vengeance: it's more aerodynamic that way</div>\n<div>melford: sure, you'll always know it wasn't forged that way</div>\n<div>vengeance: i'll just get someone to cast a forgetting spell on me</div>\n<div>melford: that seems like a lot of trouble to go through</div>\n<div>vengeance: no, no, never too much trouble for a real hawk hatchet</div>\n<div>melford: is that what you call it?</div>\n<div>vengeance: yeah i guess it sort of looks like hawk wings</div>\n<div>Gelston: we call it a self-murderer becasue no one's ever used it without killing themselves. i hoped it would ahve some kind of mechanical use. there were people comin through with constructs, talking about simple machines.</div>\n<div>flick: what did you say?</div>\n<div>Gelston: yeah, we got gnome folk up from some university looking for constructs, robots, they showed us these real simple boxes. i was like look they got a lever, they got a screw, we got this self-killer here , that's gotta be something, but they didn't take to it.</div>\n<div>flick: were they wearing headgear or circlets?</div>\n<div>gelston: they looked studious. red fox university, that's what it was called.</div>\n<div>flick: they didn't have an ogre?</div>\n<div>gelston: no, it was just gnomes, academics</div>\n<div>flick: and they wanted you to make a robot?</div>\n<div>gelston: it was like an ambassadorship, looking for people making analog machines, robots, constructs. they'd heard a lot about melford here, and i was happy to be able to offer them the self-killer. i think melford maybe made some custom pieces.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: maybe you ment to say it was a Melf-killer?</div>\n<div>gelston: oh, of the acid arrow fame? i don't think melford gets her name from there hold on MELFORD WHERE YOU GET YOUR NAME FROM yeah it doesn't sound like it sounds like she gets her name --- her father's name was melford and his mother before him, so i think it's a family name.</div>\n<div>vengeance: ok well that makes sense.</div>\n<div>flick: do you want this thing or not?</div>\n<div>vengeance: yeah, i'd like it. do you mind paying for it?</div>\n<div>flick: how much for the self-killer?</div>\n<div>gelston: you want this? i mean, this took a ton of work, maybe 20 gold pieces.</div>\n<div>[insight check flick natural 20 -- she thinks she could get it for less than a gold piece]</div>\n<div>flick: melford, can i examine this thing? be careful</div>\n<div>she spins it in a dsultory manner. now --- this edge is all wrong. isn't this tine completely counter to the way it's supposed to be?</div>\n<div>vengeance: no it's perf --- yeah, you're right, it's totally</div>\n<div>melford: what's that? lemme see that?</div>\n<div>flick: you're willing to have your name out in the street with a tine</div>\n<div>gelston: look i'm just an apprentice so if'n i can get my name out there at all that's worth its weight in gold to me and i'm ignoring the fact that words don't weigh nothin.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>flick: the gold is going to be flying out of this shop after everyone's takin' in by this bill of goods. and everyone comes and claims refunds for this shoddy work aand your mistress has to pay out.</div>\n<div>gelston: hey we have a no-refund policy here</div>\n<div>flick: if anything you should be paying me for keeping it here</div>\n<div>gelston: look, maybe we can come to an arrangement wehere you bruit my name about and i lower the price, but this is a fine product,</div>\n<div>flick examines it again. [12 persuasion]</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Gelston (male) ...</div>\n<div>Tordo (female) steps in, confidently, with a 4 on her wisdom check</div>\n<div>flick: this is 4 degrees off true.</div>\n<div>tordo: i mean, you are an elf, i can't see that 4 degrees.</div>\n<div>flick sets it on the rack. i will pay certain people to waste my time in certain ways, but not this</div>\n<div>tordo: ok, ok, let's say 10 gp, those scythe heads are 3gp each, and that's a nice black teak quarterstaff.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: look, where are you supposed to hold this?</div>\n<div>tordo: i know you're jokin when you say that. you must know how to hold a quarterstaff. i see that weird shrimp merchant's been holdin your \"quarterstaff\" lately. you've got his signs all over you. why don't you clean yourself up by the way. you gonna show yourself with that shrimp man's disgusting oils all over you</div>\n<div>vengeance: a lot of people prefer the smell of shr*coughing fit*</div>\n<div>tordo: you can't even say \"shrimp\" without coughing.</div>\n<div>flick: tordo, for 20 silver, we'll take it, everyone gets a recommendation for your shop, and we'll make it clear it was a cast-off that you challeneged yourself to fix if we're challenged.</div>\n<div>tordo: yeah, you'lve got a deal there. flick gives her a half-noble.</div>\n<div>vengeance: guys this is perfect, i'm so excited to try it out!</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>the sickle heads definitely stay on.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: this is like a combo between a short sword and a quarterstaff.</div>\n<div>[can vengeance attack with the other blade as a bonus action?]</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>it's probably around 12 or 1 pm.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>they head back to the temple of kashtari to check on Fez.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>on the way there they divert slightly to scope out the place they're supposed to meet. it looks like one in a series of row houses. nondescript. from his thieves' knowledge he's probably going to have to show the dagger, and whatever happens is going to be in the basement. like a marxist-leninist group meeting in the basement of a residential house. JL doesn't see anything overtly sinister about it. there is a kind fo back alley for horse or cart traffic that connects to the roads on either sides, and a small fenced-in area in the back. to spy on it, he'd have to get up top, or view the back rooms through the houses on the other side of the back alley.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL: it seems like it would be a poor guest to spy now, and instead check in on Fez.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>They avoid the guardds at the front and head directly for the infirmary. the pavillion top has expanded, and more shade is being provided to those inside. there don't appear to be more patients than there were before.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>They see Odeshka but not Vaka. Fez has been moved to the other side; they're keeping open beds closer to the entrance. he's on a cot with an umbrella, a washcloth across his forehead, loose blankets and just in his underclothes.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Flick and vengeance [nat 1 perception] thinks his cheeks are raging with fire. Even the little vengeance knows about monastic healing tells him that Fez is probably fine.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Flick: omg, has anyone looked in on him at all?</div>\n<div>Odeshka: our generosu donors, how are you doing today. have you come to check on yoru friend?</div>\n<div>Flick WHAT DID WE GIVE YOU</div>\n<div>JL: i gave them five gold</div>\n<div>Flick: Fez looks like he's barely going to live through the night, what's going on with him.</div>\n<div>Odeshka: no, he's been recovering miraculously. Vaka said it wasn't the marsh sickness. he's been resting and barely talking in his sleep. follow me.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>close up flick can see that he's not sweating, there's no pallor, and he's not exuding a fisih aura. every other person has dried herbs hung up around him, but they haven't had to around Fez</div>\n<div>Odeshka: he's here as an unusual patient. we give him the same level of care, but he'll recover much quicker. we don't have to fight against continual decomp. Vaka told me that the departure of his patron deity is doing the most ot hurt him. almost like his life's purpose has gone out of him, but the body is healthy.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>this is the first time Flick has heard of Fez being involved with the divine.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Odeshka: i assume you'll have to take him back to the Newemp Shire, which may be what he needs to fully recover. or a temple of his patron deity as when he was still in the colors of a paladin.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL notices that Odeshka's canines are noticeably longer than a humanoid. [nat 1 survival] JL identifies her as a sun vampire. (DM clarification: not all vampires are evil, it's a legit species). It's certainly the tannest vampire , and also has that victorian clothing look with the skirt.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL remembers seeing that child's face in the window of the temple yesterday. Another glance today bears no fruit.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Vengeance reads from his mind palace ... \"my mental files are unorganized right now, even though the monks spent so much time teaching me mnemonic tricks\". fellows, perhaps you've heard of the Manoosh? the manoosh? they are a group of Naga, and i know you probably don't know what that is, it's a human-snake race. the primary concentration center for them is the Dayama desert, in the middle of the continent. you may recall meeting them here, in this temple. \"LEXICON: \" vengeance goes into a trance and starts reciting everything he knows.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>JL: why bring this up, vengeance?</div>\n<div>vengeance: hm, good question. it might just be helpful, in case, .... oh right, Vaka, is he here?</div>\n<div>Odeshka: I can see if I can find him inside, and appears with Vaka after a few moments.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Vaka: my friends, how do you do this day? i take it you've seen the condition of Fez, recovered so quckly.</div>\n<div>Flick: our hearts are heavy that there are things your healings skills won't be able to touch, but we're grateful for all you have been able to do.</div>\n<div>Vaka: it's quite sad; a adventurers, if you could bring you any information from distant realms, i think any of it might be helpful here.</div>\n<div>Flick: well we met the creature responsible, in a radiant pool under the Xanthuc Temple near the Alldrink.</div>\n<div>Vaka: yes, we did learn about them in some of our religion classes.</div>\n<div>Flick: we were the victim of the first of many thirst traps. this Thing insinuated itself into our group; i'm a little ashamed for not doing something sooner.</div>\n<div>Vaka: Flesiksa, someone over here is talking about thirst traps, isn't tha twhat your doctorate on?</div>\n<div>Flesika: Someone talking about thirst traps?</div>\n<div>Flick: thirst traps are when various strange creatures pose as a woman from someone's past in an attempt to entice them into acting against their interests. is that what you specialize in.</div>\n<div>Flesika: oh, no, I suppose the common term is Oasis, but it goes by many different names. you see, we're from the desert and oases are a subject of much contention.</div>\n<div>flick: so when you find above-ground pools in the desert, you call them thirst traps?</div>\n<div>flesiksa: that's right because they catch you because you are thirsty.</div>\n<div>vengeance: isn't that how the giant sandworms catch their prey?</div>\n<div>flesiksa: you've seen the sandworms?</div>\n<div>vengeance: yes, i know all about the dayama desert in the middle of the continent, i might add.</div>\n<div>flesiksa: you sound like you're reciting from some sort of tome. are you sure this is a natural area of knowledge for you?</div>\n<div>vengeance: yeah, it is , but i could always stand to learn more about it.</div>\n<div>flesiksa: you know, whatever humans do in the desert. a lot of lizard export. it's a pretty low economy sort of area. geographiacl exploration, and psychological exploration of time beyond geography that lends meaning to the land itself. is that what you mean?</div>\n<div>vengeance: saying \"you do what humans do\" is an odd way to phrase it.</div>\n<div>flesiksa: you're one to talk!</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>desert exports: dankana -- old sanskrit word for borax(borax)</div>\n<div>- a flux for soldering and in the refining of metals and assaying of ores.</div>\n<div>- in pottery glazes</div>\n<div>- heat-resistant base</div>\n<div>- preservative?</div>\n<div>- mild base, so combat acidity</div>\n<div>salt, salts,</div>\n<div>certain animal pelts</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>vengeance: that's just the way i speak.</div>\n<div>flesiksa: your companions are humans, and they speak much more normally</div>\n<div>vengeance: i wondered if you knew anything about creatures called the Naga</div>\n<div>flick: these naga, do they have to eat people, vengeance?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>on \"naga\", the three naga all react as though they weren't expecting that to be said.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Flesiksa: the naga, yes, they are a mythological race, like centraurs, quite handsome, i'm told, they were in the myths, and thirst traps themselves, if i were to use your meaning of the phrase.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>flick now notices that the skirt extends in a kind of short train. under the pretext of taking another look at fez, she walks right behind flesiksa and steps on her tail. she feels that she makes contact with the tip of her tail. as she does so, she hears flesiksa hiss. the tail must be curled up under them compactly, at least while people are here. they are making an effort.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>hhhhhhhh ... you gotta watch that ... are you trying to flat-tire me? please be more careful, these tdresses take quite a while to weave.</div>\n<div>vengeance: we're not trying to step on any toes here. just hypothetically, if this were a ... Naga temple, would it be a temple to the god of Arogya, or Kastari, the god of the forge and the kiln.</div>\n<div>flesiksa: well it's called the temple of kashtara, so ...</div>\n<div>vengeance: i guess it was the \"h\"</div>\n<div>flesiksa: some of those here have trouble with their \"s\"s</div>\n<div>vengeance: which one?</div>\n<div>flesiksa: well how versed are you in religious iconography?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>...</div>\n<div>like Vaka told you, we're making renovations inside. this is just a temple we found. quite sturdy, too.</div>\n<div>we weren't the ones who carved the double-helix. but if that's on there, the temple is to that god.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>flick: do you find it hard to hide the fact that you're snake-people in the midst of a human town?</div>\n<div>f: do i find it hard to hide that there _are_ snake people?</div>\n<div>flick: it's none of our business at the end of the day, but we would appreciate honesty, with our friend in your care , and what your _game_ is.</div>\n<div>[intimidation nat 20]</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>flesiksa looks a bit cowed. yes, our illusion here is not meant to be closely scrutinized. we primarmily receive those who can barely perceive the world around them. please, don't reveal our secreet. for some reason, the story that this is an old temple we found seems to carry water.</div>\n<div>flick: we don't want to make trouble. all we want to know is if we should be trusting you, and what you ahve to gain from taking in the sick folk.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Vaka, in hearing range, comes over and puts a hand on flesiksa's side, \"it's ok, i've already told the unseemly monk what we are. his ventures into the city haven't resulted in any adverse press, so this is fully within what i've allowed</div>\n<div>Flesiksa: we want nothing more than to rehabilitate these creatures. it's just that ... this marsh sickness is unusual for us, coming from the desert, but what led us to take it on is that somehow the process they are going through mirrors that of the mummification rituals which the dead go through in our culture.</div>\n<div>flick: what brought you to this ... and please don't take this the wrong way ... so you're a bunch of sand-dwelling snake people</div>\n<div>vengeance: the manush.</div>\n<div>fles: yes, the manush. there are many naga, and we're just one self-identifying group</div>\n<div>flick: you're teh manush, who live in the desert, and ahve come to a place literally named after soggy grassland, and are posing as purveyors of medicine for a disease whose symptoms you recognize as a kind of mummification</div>\n<div>fles: well, this town is \"Sandford\" -- originally this was a Manush stronghold, it was one of the outposts of the empire when the desert extended here. the sandstone still exists, and you can see that the temple still stands.</div>\n<div>flick: this whole area used to be desert?</div>\n<div>fles: yes, it did.</div>\n<div>flick looks at the wall segments.</div>\n<div>fles: those walls are from after the desert reverted to decisuous land. no, those are build of fired brick and limestones or granite? this temple here extends at least its length again into the ground.</div>\n<div>flick: are you here to take your country back</div>\n<div>fles: that is impossible, for econolgical and religious reasons. but this is still a center of much power for us, so we maintain it that way, and when we can help the locals, we do so.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>[flick calc 21] - she's telling the truth about what she said.</div>\n<div>fles: the temple is considered a bit of a curiosity ehre, and we encourage that interpretation.</div>\n<div>flick: we're glad our friend is doing well, and we have an appointment to keep. we'll bid you a fond farewell.</div>\n<div>vengeance: one last thing. i wonder if our friend could use a quick prayer to arogya.</div>\n<div>vaka: are you suggested his new patron should be arogya?</div>\n<div>vengeance: uhhhhhhhhhhhhhh. yes.</div>\n<div>vaka: i've never heard of such a thing.</div>\n<div>vengeance: he told me if i was ever incapacitated i could make decisions for him.</div>\n<div>flick: no he didn't.</div>\n<div>vaka: i assume you can discuss that amongst you. it wouldn't be too late to just ask him when he recovers fully. but i don't know that it's been done before. a halfling -- who isn't more trustworthy than a little halfling to be an ambassador. there's i would hope no need to say this, but you won't speak poorly of us to the town, and we will make sure your friend recovers fully.</div>\n<div>vengeance: normally i trust all snakes and serpents.</div>\n<div>vaka: please don't call us snakes</div>\n<div>vengeance: there's something about this whole situation that doesn't seem right</div>\n<div>vaka: and from what i've heard from the nurses, noone thinks you seem right, so a sort of equilibrium has been attained</div>\n<div>vengeance: it takes one to know one</div>\n<div>vaka: that's pretty redundant to what i said</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>flick: we're not here to break him out of prison</div>\n<div>vengeance: i was hoping to use my hawk-hatchet</div>\n<div>[for a moment, the conjunction of the idea of kashtari, teh god of the forge, and that with the idea of forging individualized magic weapons, occurs to you, but then disappears]</div>\n<div>vengeance: darn. you know ... when ...</div>\n<div>flick: it'll come back to you.</div>\n<div>vengeance: fine, if you just want to sleep and die!</div>\n<div>vengeance sinks down next to fez's cot and clasps his hands in his. dont worry little bud, we're going to get you out of here.</div>\n<div>[religion check] as vengeance is grasping fez's hands, suddenly a brilliant voice and apiercing white light appears. I am Sustha. do you wish your friend's recovery. (Sustha is another patron saint of the recovering or the convalescent, she's reaching out to you, here. ) Sustha, where's Arogya? you're sending your lieutenants? i want to talk to the real deal!</div>\n<div>Sustha: Arogya has larger things to attend to. in case you haven't seen, there are dozens suffering from the sickness, here. your friend presents a special case: he is a halfling, and you wish him to recover, and he's lost his benefactor. if you tell him when he recovers that there is one waiting amongst the Manush, then that is all that I ask, and it's clear that you're willing to be a vessel of this kind, by how great your concern for the halfling is.</div>\n<div>vengeance: so ... what do i get?</div>\n<div>Sustha: a real mercenary perspective, I see. what is there to offer you? i can see in you a great well of healing potential. i can promise to increase that above its typical manifestation for you.</div>\n<div>vengeance: hmmm, nah. let's just let him die.</div>\n<div>Sustha: your friend will not be allowed to die, but the manner of his procession through life will still be up for claim. goodbye, vengeance, and look towards the brighter side of yourself, rather than the darker.</div>\n<div>vengeance: i'm still waiting to talk to Arogya. i'll get through one of these days.</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
