{"_id":"LHhsg9IkujaXrs81","name":"035: Zombie Dinosaur","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"P1XiX3k7BG1TWAxw","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"<p>2020-07-04 (July 4, 2020)</p>\n<p>Level 7</p>\n<p>Day 10 (mid afternoon)</p>\n<hr />\n<h1 id=\"recap\">Recap</h1>\n<p>Flick, Drav, and Paros are whisked to the Forest of Horth where Joan has just teleported on an archaeological expedition for some dragon/dinosaur bones to find out about the ancient enmity between giants and dragons. They kill a necromancer, Feniendum, and her newly animate pet Nugget, while discovering that Graal is under the sway of Feniendum and is succumbing to a necrotic zombification disease. They bring Graal back with them to the skirt of Seomra Crann after promising to heal her.</p>"}
{"_id":"MLYLEbOkNvKCq0aB","name":"Flick","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"HnsRctNEFA19GYLE","sort":200001,"flags":{},"content":"<ul>\n<li>Suspicious of things that come from underground, just because they are not from the woods? (such as Cyrowan). Being naturally creepy doesn't help Cyrowan's case, either.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Looking for teleportation sigils: maybe in Nerch's journals ?</li>\n<li>Flick's relationship with spirituality / religion. Her foster parents were the equivalent of Xmas and Eastern presbyterians. her schooling was not parochial. She didn't get the sense that there was a \"there there\" when it came to religion. Her sense of the divine is more druidic, like from Gonfalon, Shoemaker Byte, and others. But her parents didn't -- she doesn't worship Silvanus. Her sense of a higher power is going to bottom out in some kind of animation of natural forces rather than a deity with temples. The gods clearly exist, but she doesn't worship them. (Silvanus is a deity in the Forgotten realms, \"Summer Oak Tree\", ) The equivalent of knowing about as much as someone who went to Catholic school but wasn't a catholic at home. Gonfalon would have made knowing about the rituals and what he observed, but it's not in her heart, and she doesn't know a ton. She's not religiously educated. She doesn't have a sense of what the other gods are. (&sect;045)</li>\n<li>Believes that you notch a belt first, as much as you can,&nbsp;<em>then</em> get enemies to assign to each of the notches. (Notches Libre)</li>\n<li>When she was a teen, and a bunch of the village boys tried to get her plastered in ignorance of Elven metabolism, and it went badly for them; there were broken bones, and <strong>one got lost in the woods and was never found again</strong>. It precipitated a generational feud between her family and these McmMurtons, only 2 of 3 brothers got through the night. to this day they can't be in the same area of town or they'll come to blows. Made even more awkward by the fact that it's their grandchildren and flick is still in her (relative) early 20s. (&sect;047)</li>\n<li>\n<div>The only city Flick has experience with is Cressida. and the brief stay in marshbout, so she doesn't have a good comparative grasp of levels of civilization. Sandford strikes her fairly provincial understanding . Cressida is like \"athens in its heyday in terms of the qquality of its buildings\". it lounges along the shores of the lake for 11 miles. \"A lot of people say they're from cressida when they're actually from north breszleton.\"</div>\n<div>__north breszleton__ / north breziltin</div>\n</li>\n<li>Scared of lightning.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --><!-- --><!-- --><!-- -->"}
{"_id":"MjkIqF9SuEP6VnJC","name":"037: Four-hundredths of a unit faster","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"Ho4c14ccdD0ZFAmy","sort":200000,"flags":{},"content":"<h1 id=\"037fourhundredthsofaunitfaster\">037. Four-hundredths of a unit faster</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>2020-08-01 (August 1st, 2020)</li>\n<li>Day 11 (mid-morning) to about 12 seconds later, give or take a few movie-time conversations.</li>\n<li>Level 7</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->\n<h2 id=\"recap\">Recap</h2>\n<h2 id=\"transcript\">Transcript</h2>\n<p>Jean-Luc: Doesn't know either way if Nerch is controlling the other hobgoblins wearing gold circlets.</p>\n<p>Gluggranok and Nerch are sitting on the back of the cart eating lunch, and Udrek sits next to them. Jean-Luc contemplates his Tepplin distillery bottle of hard spirits. [Intelligence not great]. JL is pretty confident Udrek is going to be into an offer to share drink. Joan sits cross-legged, reading out of certification tomes.</p>\n<p>Startrella: Oh, so <em>now</em> you're sharing this stuff?!</p>\n<p>Jean-Luc [History not bad] knows there are some words not to call hobgoblins; (Jean-Luc is proficient in multiple slurs and curses as part of his thieves' cant). The worst one:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>blidge (the b word)</li>\n<li>'hobgolem' is not offensive nor inoffensive; it's a neologist (\"A Brianniel original\")</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->\n<p>Jean-Luc goes to share a drink with his \"friend\" (waffleface - very familiar (tu); frinkle - (usted)): Share a drink with me waffleface.<br></p>\n<p>Udrek: Just. Spoke. About. Drink. Udrek Teetotals. Drink. Depressant.<br></p>\n<p>Jean-Luc: You're just drinking with the wrong people.<br></p>\n<p>Udrek: What makes. Wrong? Jean-Luc: If you're getting depressed when you're drinking alcohol, I think you're doing it wrong. (He takes a big gulf and offers it to Udrek.)<br></p>\n<p>Udrek: Haven't. Made. Appropriate. Friendship. Gestures.<br></p>\n<p>Jean-Luc: In my culture, the first appropriate gesture is to share a drink with someone.<br></p>\n<p>Udrek: Understandable. But. Personal. Preference. For Stimulants. … You. Have. Any?</p>\n<p>Flick thinks about her <em>goodberries-on-the-vine.</em> (Do they negate the need for food like cocaine? Experimentation is required.) Jean-Luc maay have U.S.S. (urban-style stimulants). Paros has <em>Haste</em>? Jean-Luc has a soggy vial of fizzlecoke; Cyrowan probably dripped into it at one point.</p>\n<p>Jean-Luc: It got a little wet, but if you want I've had worse stimulants than this fizzlecoke here.<br></p>\n<p>Startrella: You got some wet fizzlecoke? I know just the trick. I know how to dry that stuff out.<br></p>\n<p>Jean-Luc: Oof. .. Yeah, what's the trick.<br></p>\n<p>Startrella: I guess you just heat it up for a while. You have to make sure you don't burn the coke. You use a dry double-boiler situation.<br></p>\n<p>Flick: So the trick is evaporation.<br></p>\n<p>Startrella: Yeah! That's it! Travelling amongst the stars you learn so much physics it can be really helpful. And it expands your minds for those times your mind is primed to expand. (She wanders over).<br></p>\n<p>Flick: Hey, Startrella, our friend Udrek doesn't want anything to bring him down this early in the morning. Would you happen to have any powders or stimulants or \"caffeinated\" substances we can give him?<br></p>\n<p>Startrella: Like i was saying, if one of you does something real nice for me, I can take one of these starmotes and pretty much turn it into anything.<br></p>\n<p>Flick: Real nice? Like what?<br></p>\n<p>Startrella: I dunno -- nothing's coming to me off the top of the dome.<br></p>\n<p>Flick: Like, if we helped you across the strees, or carried your grocery bags while you were trying to open a door? That kind of thing, or were you speaking in code?<br></p>\n<p>Startrella: Yeah like if you dig a hole and fill it with water and place your cloak over it that might do the trick.<br></p>\n<p>Flick: [Insight 13: if flick can create a meditative environment or pull her into the ethereal place; something to provide a sensory deprivation environment]. (Flick walks over; )</p>\n<p>[…]</p>\n<p>Vengeance: It's not me, it's my sentient staff that likes to pet … not ogres, but … your wonderful pet. I apologize for my staff's behavior. (His feet begin scrapingi a hole in the ground.)<br></p>\n<p>Glug: Udrek isn't my pet. We grew up in the same town! This is all looking a bit fishy. (He comes over and interposes himself between Udrek and the others.) I'm not nsure what you're trying to do here. Udrek can make his own decisions. All this fudging around with his head while we're eating -- I think you should just make your way on.</p>\n<p>Jean-Luc pretends to trip in order to attempt to knock the circlet off. [two nat 20s to touch and deceive] He does it so delicately that, as he tries to pull it off, he can feel that it's embedded in Gluggranok's head, under the skin and adherent to the skull. [Strength] The circlet comes loose from his skull under one adhesion point and Jean-Luc gets as finger under it and pulls up (and out). Glugg screams as a clump of scalp tears off and he goes completely catatonic.</p>\n<p>Jean-Luc: I'm sorry, I tripped on this tree here. -- No, I'm not sorry, this is how I do things.<br></p>\n<p>Cyrowan: Master Luc, this isn't how you get the ladies. Not by being a drunk and a stumbler.<br></p>\n<p>Flick: Shut up, squire, nobody asked you.<br></p>\n<p>Cyrowan: I'm Fez's squire, how dare you talk to me that way. Lord Fez, tell him!</p>\n<p>[Initiative]</p>\n<p>Udrek reaches behind his back, produces a massive chipped claymore, and swings at Jean-Luc with his non-coke-fingernailed hand. Jean-Luc is hurt. Paros, pulling out some sweet aromatic oils and a fizzlecyst tongue, casts Suggestion and imposes disadvantage, \"I [Udrek] don't remember putting that fire out yesterday… \" Udrek fails. \"Oh. Trees. At. Risk. Of Fire?\" Jean-Luc feels the kettlehelmet trembling, and Flick has a distant memory of being compelled to put out the bar fires. \"The fire is no joke!\" Yells Flick.<br></p>\n<p>Nerch climbs up onto the cart and attempts to push the boxes off the cart. \"Hee. Hooo. Heeww.\" The cart rises up into the air as if on hydraulic suspension. Three boxes fall off the back of the cart, and one cracks open. It looks like the cat bus from My Neighbor Totoro, but without a cat face. Or eyes. But it can somehow see where you are. The Cart (Carty B) reverses and attempts to slam into Flick, who jumps nimbly out of the way.<br></p>\n<p>Jean-Luc and Drav intuit that Nerch was an urchin, and was called Nurchin as a kid to make fun of her. It's probably why she gets along with Udrek, who's being raised as an Organiborg Hobgolem.<br></p>\n<p>The rear door of the cart's bed flips up to provide cover for Nerch.<br></p>\n<p>Cyrowan: I'm here to support you, Ms Drav, as Fez is indisposed with raging fish diarrhea.<br></p>\n<p>Joan: I can't concentrate with all this gosh dang noise! (and rushes 80 ft closer to the fray and goes into a rage for various reasons -- \"I need to know about this protocol!\")<br></p>\n<p>Jean-Luc gives Udrek a wide berth, comes up to Gluggranok, and rips the metal circlet off his head with a sickening tearing sound. The circlet comes off the head with chunks of hair and skin attached, almost his entire scalp, and even laminae of his skull. Udrek bellows in a rage, altho the possible fire looms larger in his mind. \"Forest. Important. Friend. In Pain. Conundrum. Using algorithm. To Decide.\" Jean-Luc dashes for the treeline. Gluggranok remains passed out on the ground.<br></p>\n<p>Flick runs up a nearby tree; \"A mere wagon skin is no barrier to the power of the planes\" as she marks Nerch and sharpshoots at her, wounding her significantly with the shots. Startrella: What are those cool ripples you're making over there?<br></p>\n<p>Nerch: I tried to get them to spring for a top to this thing. Maybe I should have tried a bit harder.<br></p>\n<p>Flick: That five gold you saved isn't looking so great now, is it?<br></p>\n<p>Nerch: No, just Udrek's learning board would have covered this. He has an invisible one, but the other one's made of wood, and that would have been great. -- and she loses concentration, at which point the cart reverts to inanimation. -- Carty, no! Carty B!! I lost Carty A a while ago. Carty A's the one with the top on it. You should see Carty C, it doesn't even have wheels, it's just on runners.<br></p>\n<p>Flick envisions the headlines after a fireball: Carty B model recalled due to flammability.<br></p>\n<p>Drav expertly places a fireball over Nerch's head; Flick sees that the entire wagon catches on fire, and Nerch is engulfed in flame and dies.<br></p>\n<p>Flick: Poor Nerch, we hardly knew ye.<br></p>\n<p>Jean-Luc: I'm not entirely sure we're not the bad guys here. But … I'm o.k. with it.<br></p>\n<p>Flick immediately hears the sound of arrows thudding into the trees around her. Targetted by an expert archer herself this time, she is pierced by arrows.<br></p>\n<p>Rovlar: For Nerch! Nerch won't die unrevenged!<br></p>\n<p>Flick: It's AVENGED!<br></p>\n<p>Rovlar: \"Revenged\" -- it's … hobgoblin slang!?<br></p>\n<p>Carlos jumps onto Mule, who carries the dashing, sturdy cleric closer to the battle. Startrella, still in the trance, remains … in the trance.<br></p>\n<p>Vengeance: Hey, Jean-Luc, do you mind if I give that device that you're holding a whirl. I just want to see what happens if I plug in. -- Jean-Luc tosses Vengeance the circlet, and the monk takes the prongs and jams them into his \"brain\" .. or however it was placed in Gluggranok's head.<br></p>\n<p>Flick: Oh, god damnit!<br></p>\n<p>Vek: I'm not sure they know what they're doing here, but that could be very powerful domination magic in those things. -- Drav tends to agree with Vek here.<br></p>\n<p>Cyrowan: You guys really like playing around with cerebral restylings, don't you. I mean, Lord Paros has enough going on to cover for everyone. If I were under the effects of an ancient higher power, I bet you all would know about it right away, you're so clever and attuned to things.<br></p>\n<p>[Galen's computer freezes, so I throw to Carlos for healing.]<br></p>\n<p>For a minute Vengeance feels his brain get cloudy and finds thinking difficult. He briefly feels bound to protect the contents of the boxes and take them somewhere. He feels comradely feelings towards Udrek and Gluggranok and Rovlar, and a generalized compliance with a nebulous force of masters. But then it looks like it didn't adhere to his body properly; some of the metal wiring snapped, and it doesn't seem like it would work anymore. (Maybe if he'd used a fizzlecyst fixative…) \"Everyone, I think I know what's going on here: mind control. I believe I've solved the case.\"<br></p>\n<p>Carlos casts Healing Word on Jean-Luc.<br></p>\n<p>Vengeance: Take it from me, and --<br></p>\n<p>Rovlar (aka Vengeance): I adopt vengeance as my name! -- What were you saying?<br></p>\n<p>Vengeance: If I could just say to you, it's not all it's cracked up to be. It's a difficult life, and I don't recommend it. If I were you I would pack it in now. -- And he casts Confusion (Qi-xotic confusion) on Rovlar. Fez continues eating some wet grass.<br></p>\n<p>Vek: Fez doesn't really look like he knows what he's doing anymore. You should take care of him.<br></p>\n<p>Cyrowan: Yes - what should I do?<br></p>\n<p>Vek: SHould go back and check on him I think.<br></p>\n<p>Udrek: Poor. Nerch. Will extinguish. This fire. Later. Other fire. Now.<br></p>\n<p>Paros fires a fire bolt at the branch on which Rovlar is standing, but it falls short, adding more flames to Nerch's pyre.<br></p>\n<p>Udrek: Nother. Fire. NOoooooo.<br></p>\n<p>Joan sits down next to a tree in order to be able to punch it and maintain her rage. Jean-Luc dashes into another bunch of trees.<br></p>\n<p>Rovlar: Vengeance will visit you too! I see you making your way across the open ground.<br></p>\n<p>Jean-Luc: You know you could surrender.<br></p>\n<p>Rovlar: Why surrender when I have the tactical advantage of being higher off the ground than you?<br></p>\n<p>Jean-Luc: You're outnumbered.<br></p>\n<p>Vengeance: Jean-Luc, take a break here, I'm going to handle things.<br></p>\n<p>Gluggranok remains unconscious and continues to lose blood.<br></p>\n<p>Flick sharpshoots Rovlar, hitting once, and -- YOu'll never get another arrow that high! (Rovlar) -- missing -- I told you! -- at which Flick disappears into the Etherial plane, the Magician Archer and sky-walks out his movement speed to between two trees. [Perception 17]. Though never having done this before, Flick acclimates rapidly, and sees the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>In the distance where Aphelia and Cyrowan are, Flick sees the merging of a dark black and bright white smoke</li>\n<li>Where Drav is, Flick sees very faintly and rippling, the figure of Eldar suspended inside a massive suit of crystalline-light plate armor</li>\n<li>Startrella, sitting there, in her papasan, is trying a couple different ways of trying out the fizzlecoke in the ethereal plane</li>\n<li>Paros looks like a buffet; heaping, steaming trays of spirit food</li>\n<li>Behind Flick, reddish-gold tendrils, like smokey vines, hundreds of them emerging from the boxes on the ground, and going straight up into the sky, disappearing a hundred feet up due in part to the limited visibility of the ethereal plane. A single tendril emerges each from Udrek and Rovlar.</li>\n</ol>\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->\n<div>Drav dashes closer to Gluggranok intending to stabilizer her next turn. Mule, bored, makes her way down to a freestanding cabin a few hundred feet south.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: Where did that elf go? It's probably because I'm so high up and she's so far down, she gave up her tactical advantage. I'm trained in the arts of battle and strategy!</div>\n<div>Vengeance: Listen, Vengeance, I feel a great deal of sympathy for you, and I understand where you're coming from.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: A true warrior doesn't need sympathy.</div>\n<div>Vengeance: Of course not. I only offer you understanding. And solidarity. WHen I was a child, I had a very controlling father. Perhaps you know what it's like being under control yourself by a tyrannical device or whatever it is that's controlling you. I want you to know that it's okay. When I failed my fishermans exams, my father beat me near to death, and that changed the course of my life, and I realized I didn't have to be under his control anymore. So why don't you just come down from there and we'll unhook you from that thing, and you can live your life as a free hobgoblin.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: I too used to be subject to the whip. I would go out in the evenings looking for midges, those delicious little bugs, and a few times I was caught by monsters, and my parents would beat me, but I always took it as a sign that they loved me!</div>\n<div>Vengeance: Oh, you love midges too?</div>\n<div>Rovlar: One of my favorite delicacies.</div>\n<div>Vengeance: What's your favorite kind?</div>\n<div>Rovlar: I like the slarm … ones. Buttermidges. Blue-green midge, i like it for the taste, even tho people think it's a panacea.</div>\n<div>Vengeance: You know if you pour some fizzlecoke onto a midge and pop it in your mouth it'll explode. And my goodness, the sensation is wonderful.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: Like a pop midge? Vengeance: Midge pop.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: nouns!</div>\n<div>Vengeance: Well you are a very knowledgeable lady. I wish you would come down from there. I don't want to have to hurt you. You're probably an innocent person. I want to get that thing off of you, so come down.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: You want to get what off of me?</div>\n<div>Vengeanec: The mind-control device.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: You mean the way that the desire for midges controls my mind?</div>\n<div>Vengeance: It is a very powerful desire. but I'm talking about this (holds up circlet)</div>\n<div>Rovlar: WHy are you holding that?</div>\n<div>Vengeance: I just found it. … This is what you're wearing right now. We have some really great surgeons here. Jean-Luc has taken some classes, and he can take that out for you painlessly. VERY painlessly.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: No, no. I was with you talking about the midges. I was willing to make a full spread with you. But the cap -- absolutely not!</div>\n<div>Vengeance: I promise, once you come down, we'll go on a full midge hunt, fry them up, it'll be delicious.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: WHy can't we do that with the cap on. In fact, you all look like you would wear these caps well. In fact, I can extoll their virtues to you at length.</div>\n<div>Vengeance: Just come down and we can talk aboutthat.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: Is that blood on that cap you're holding.</div>\n<div>Vengeance: No, I just had it in my bag with some loose newt jelly.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: Oh, a platter of Bertram's midges with newt jelly (and he begins drooling out of his nose as hobgoblins do).</div>\n<div>Vengeance: quick, somebody cast a freezing smell and then we can pull him down by his saliva.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: Oh, i thought you were going to eat my drool as icicle treats. I've heard those are pretty taste.</div>\n<div>[Deception check for newt jelly. ] In the Ethereal Plane, Flick sees people as kind of ghostly shapes without sharp details.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: Ok, so it's not blood, but I don't want to let you near my cap: this is important to me.</div>\n<div>Flick and Vengeance have an ominous feeling, perhaps that they are being watched. Flick can see blue, gem-like or gravelly twinklings on the ground below her. like stones spread out through the grass. She decides to attack Rovlar from within the Ethereal Plane into the Material Plane using force damage.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: I'll avenge Glug too! Even though he's pitiable and still alive.</div>\n<div>Carlos heals Gluggranok, The wound in his heal closes up with just a bit of residual bruising and looks like he's sleeping.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: What's going on over there, did you help him? I thought i was going to have to avenge him.</div>\n<div>Jean-Luc: We don't have a quarrel with you.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: Then why did you kill Nerch!?</div>\n<div>Jean-Luc: Well, we <em>had</em> a quarrel with Nerch.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: I'm notn sure why you think a quarrel with her is different from one with me. Although, I suppose, if it was about midges -- she does really despise midges, and I could see how that could escalate into immolation.</div>\n<div>Vengeance: Yeah, that was the reason, you're right.</div>\n<div>Jean-Luc: We're happy to end this without further bloodshed.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: So you'll just make your way south. Can you dispell whatever you did to Udrek?</div>\n<div>Jean-Luc: It'll wear off. He's basically going to sprint for a minute.</div>\n<div>Drav: I think it's for 8 hours-- Jean-Luc: Either way it'll wear off.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: WIthout Carty-B or Udrek I'm kindof defenceless here. I mean, tactically, I have an advantage, but defensively, I'm at a disadvantage.</div>\n<div>Jean-Luc: Like I said we're not looking to hurt you.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: Ok, then … go away.</div>\n<div>Jean-Luc. Can't do that. [Persuasion ?]</div>\n<div>Rovlar: I'll come halfway down the tree …</div>\n<div>Jean-Luc: Good first step.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: In exchange, will you get Udrek to come back? Or, you know what? I'd really like to see Gluggranok conscious.</div>\n<div>Jean-Luc glances over at Carlos.</div>\n<div>Vengeance: What is in those boxes, anyway?</div>\n<div>Rovlar: that's a great question, Vengeanec. They are supplies that we need to get to the coast. It's probably best if you leave them alone. I think that handling them will give you a tactical disadvantage. It's wise to proceed south. You know what, don't even worry about Udrek or Glugg. Why don't you head south, I'll take care of this.</div>\n<div>Vengeance: If there's anything I hate it's a tactical disadvantage. I think I'll just take a quick peak to see what's inside.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: I'd really suggest you not do that.</div>\n<div>Carlos slaps Glugg awake, but his eyes don't focus and it looks like he's awake but he's dissociated from what's going on around him.</div>\n<div>Paros (has he read something on the trauma involved in separating from the hive-mind?) walks over to examine Gluggranok.</div>\n<div>Cyrowan: (in the distance) the way you're taking care of yourself, master, is really going to pot. I love grass as much as the next person but you should really give it a rest.</div>\n<div>Jean-Luc is remaining aware. Gluggranok's eyes refocus, and he sees that Vengeance is holding the metal cap, and he goes to grab it out of your hands.</div>\n<div>Vengeance: Woh, Gluggs, this is mine now. -- and he skips out of the way. Glugg starts moaning inarticulately. -- Oh, man, this guy is going through some serious withdrawal. Startrella, do you know of anything we can do to help him? any clinics we can send him to?</div>\n<div>Startrella: This looks like … maybe he's been on too many drugs at once. Usually I say put in him a drunk tank. Wait, what's he doing now?</div>\n<div>Gluggranok has started making his way back towards the boxes. He arrives at the closest box and feverishly starts pulling out all the packing material.</div>\n<div>Flick latches onto Rovlar's shimmery ghostly form and fires onto her. [As an Unseen Attacker, Flick gets advantage on the attack.] By Rovlar's lights, he's blasted back like a fat man getting hit in the stomach by an invisible cannon ball. Flick hears his groans of pain through the Charlie Brown Adult wah-wah filter. Flick comes out of the EP and hits her with another arrow; Rovlar's dark purple blood begin to stain the tree.</div>\n<div>Rovlar: My sweet midge blood!</div>\n<div>Flick: Is this not what we're doing?</div>\n<div>Vengeance: It is unfortunate that you did that. On the other hand. .. (and he eyes getting over and drinking some blood)</div>\n<div>Rovlar: Vengeance, my midge-infused blood makes a delicious (syrup) / rock-candy!</div>\n<div>[end of session]</div>"}
{"_id":"Mmq66ywCRNHspg4Z","name":"fifth edition options","permission":{"default":0,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3},"folder":"NdtTfwZe9YTsCoFv","sort":50000,"flags":{},"content":"<h1 id=\"fiftheditionoptions\">fifth edition options</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>character flaws</li>\n<li>character wealth at higher levels</li>\n<li>700 gp per character</li>\n<li>\"better saving throws\" in certain circumstances, as boons/awards, items, etc. </li>\n<li>variant skill list</li>\n<li>skills further defined (helps DM lay out options for players)</li>\n<li>Complex skill checks (a different way of creating suspense)</li>\n<li>Poison Handling (45/46)</li>\n<li>Conditions <ul>\n<li>see </li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/posts/203-fighting-dirty-cinematic-combat-stunts\">Combat Stunts</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>something or other somebodies of Hieronymous</p>\n<h1 id=\"todo\">TODO</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>get comfortable talking herbs</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"punsinformingeverything\">puns informing everything</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>something doesn't smell right about this (in both senses)</li>\n<li>Fez will have to \"eat crow\" since Flick and Jean-Luc were right about Cyrowan.</li>\n<li>it doesn't bear repeating</li>\n</ul>"}
{"_id":"N2S9yof2MnRioM1s","name":"048: This is not for this","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"nEIZOAbBi8YZmJDe","sort":900000,"flags":{},"content":"<section><strong>Session &sect;048&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;This is not for this</section>\n<section><strong>Played November 28, 2020 (2020-11-28)</strong></section>\n<section><strong>Day:&nbsp;</strong>Day 14 wee hours through mid-morning&nbsp;</section>\n<section><strong>Level 8</strong></section>\n<hr />\n<h1>Recap</h1>\n<p><em>Pjorg translates some runes &bull; Waking up in the caves &bull; Jaap Jansen drops in on the adventurers &bull; Up and across the river&nbsp; (Gerd redux) &bull; The Fountain of Eloquence &bull; Jean-Luc indulges his alcoholism &bull; Pjorg sets Vengeance off on a wild rust chase &bull; Jaap sees some Gormflaith &bull; Oriax promises a meet-up</em></p>\n<h1>Transcript</h1>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h2>prep</h2>\n<div>- sister taken, thought that it's the taellacht gormflaith, but their MO is definitely _not_ secretly taking people, it's concerted raids.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- but they go to the teallacht to see if she is now a slave? or they hunt around to see if they did it? might be a nice spy/investigation&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- also what might the church want him to do?</div>\n<div>&nbsp; - well there was the thing with the kobolds and the temples of xanthuc</div>\n<div>- a way to allow him to desing speaking stones -- which means I have to build out his parents and what's going on at home.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>so both of his parents are clerics ? for the same glittergold ? GGG ? do i have any other G names&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>deep gnomes stealing zorbon for tinkering, so they don't realize it's terrible ? glittergold wants michael to play a prank on gnomes to free the zorbon and teach gnomes a lesson</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Onfalon returns as a corrupted circle of spores druid</div>\n<div>maybe he needs to be saved, or something;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- is he the one that can tell flick about horizon walker ness (and boggle pompholux)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Some group is being trafficked/tracked by Ituktilik Meffatar&nbsp; Ituktilik Meffatar (sort of ratface mcgillicutty backwards)</div>\n<div>- does flick or joan own remy something?</div>\n<div>- teams up with reginald and briffa ? or conflict between then even tho they're on similar mysteries (but not the same mystery, just they overlap)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>One of the gnolls has a prison-gem heart, and eating that heart does something to Calliope. -- or, they find it in her nest (Actually they could find a bunch of stuff in her nest</div>\n<div>maybe barazar is helping the hat baskets trade to gormflaith, because he's connected with a society person who ... what's her face ... knows. the hat baskets principal</div>\n<div>red herrings to make them think sister taken by unicorn (haengest / the other one)</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Jaan traveled south from such-and-such town in Selb Forest, maybe through cressida on the west side of the braided mountains. actually maybe he grew up in the same forest as Flick (but flick is east, jaan is west). did he know gonfalon, the (now maybe converted) circle of spores druid or something.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>what ... is selb ... forest like ?? i guess there is a group of forest gnomes there. and some kobolds that attack from the hellor mountains, on the foothills of which grow the westernmost reaches of the selb.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>and uh ... the so-and-so of marshbout or the greater area combined to get rid of BS influence, but had to team up with TG (tantegorische)&nbsp; -- or someone hatched a plan to get rid of him at the same time ? -- or they faked the existence of BS to get TG to cooperate (or actually mini-invoked BS to get TG into play, or the whole thing vice versa)</li>\n<li>he came across the Moving Toyshop on his way down there. maybe give him some kind of deck... ? for divining? or a tarot reader he's traveling with?&nbsp;</li>\n<li>it's his cousin driving the shop, which he didn't tell him until the last minute. -- and then disappeared. gives him the deck of illusions.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>why wouldn't his uncle help him out? cause he's a damn gnome</li>\n<li>\n<div>maybe reginald and briffa, told him about the unicorn clue</div>\n<ul>\n<li>if R&amp;B, then why wouldn't they be pursuing the adventurers? (if they are indeed investigating?) maybe they're investigating something parallel but not equal.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>the mirror idea</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>the \"making bad choices\" clue</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>the taken by raiders / gormfaith</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Jantien wanted to become a cleric but couldn't actually get investitured or whatever it's called</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Exuviae / Hengest</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>brings some turnip schnapps ?&nbsp;</div>\n</li>\n<li>the dream I had, where you can attach to someone's brain visuals in the past to learn about them, but that connection opens up their current body for being taken over, and then they can't be connected to anymore in that way.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</section>\n<p>Though Jean-Luc is discombobulated by slake, and the rest of the party still somewhat groggy, Flick, in mind of Nyauka's epithet for the azurite (\"Forgetting Stones\"), suggests they spend the balance of the evening as far away from the blue ore as possible.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick (to Pjorg): You're quite a bit taller when I come up next to you. You come up to, what, my waist?</p>\n<p>Pjorg: Thank you, small one, for the compliment, but I assure you that I'm much taller than I seem.</p>\n<p>Flick: I'm going to level with you, Pjorg, being around our group but not a part of our group tends to go badly for people. Are you lost?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg: I'm currently trying to decide if that was a threat or not.</p>\n<p>Flick: Just a statistically valid generalization.</p>\n<p>Jean-Luc: It's an empirical fact. Turns out the p-value of people who die vs. people who live</p>\n<p>Haigy: Well within a single standard deviation!</p>\n<p>Jean-Luc procedes to tell him about Cyrowan, who meant well, but who ... died. He had to ... go. That's just what happens when you're on the periphery.</p>\n<p>Flick: If by \"meant well\" you mean served as the anchor for some kind of hideous eldritch kraken.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Pjorg insight check. 13.</p>\n<p>Jean-Luc isn't telling the whole truth, and may have been more culpable than he is admitting. Pjorg is looking for someone to watch his back and wander with as he searches for things. \"Small one, I will allow you and your friends to join me.\" Flick, used to endorsing eccentricities, rolls her eyes. \"It would be a real priviledge. We're in a mission to rescue a creature from those who would exploit it ,and you're welcome along.\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: let's pick up our bedrools and head toweards the opening. I think these stones are messing with us.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Gerd's gender depends on its favored terrain. (Earth, sea, sky).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Jean-Luc CON check. Slake is pot + laudanum. 1d4. He has 2 levels of exhaustion for 2 hours.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL, too tired to argue one way or the other, lets Flick carry his stuff. They camp by the entrance. Pjorg sees Flick go to pick up JL's stuff, \"Small one, allow me to bear that burden.\" Flick, \"Oh, well if you insist\" Flick says theatrically. Pjorg: \"WHy has your voice changed so?!\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vengeance is hanging back with an eye to getting some of the Azurite. Drav picks up him and hoists him on her back. However, she feels a strange pull from Eldar back in the direction that Pjorg came from. \"Are you sure you don't want to explore the wall symbols that I saw?\" Drav, \"Oh yeah, we never talked about that. What Symbols are these, where are they coming from?\" Eldar: \"THey were inscribed on the walls, and they looked similar to some of those on the Ten-Axe archives, but it was clear that some exotic power was coming to them from behind the wall; from another source.\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick does not notice that Drav stops momentarily. She's not compelled magically, but is able to feel the pull of Eldar, who does not technically reside within her, but flits about vaguely.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Pjorg's understanding of Eldar is that she's sort of an imaginary friend. Drav hasn't revealed her existence to the rest of the party. The DM clarifies: An imaginary friend with very real effects. The ffects were detected in one circumstance, in a special area where people's subconscious could come to life (under the Xanthuc temples).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap knows the Xanthuc temples as the southernmost location on the map given him by someone at his village; the kobolds have made their way there from further to the west of the hellor mountains.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav hews close to the rest of the group and runs to catch up. As she does so, she can hear the quiet rush of the river flowing below.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Long Rest finishes (about 150 feet away from Lhaska</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick attemps to recall the names of the cousins of the familiy who has a generational grudge against her (the McMurtons) .</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; WIS save KH. Flick CHA (11). Drav 23, JL 14, P 6 (did just wake up; not going to sleep).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav, JL, and Vengeance pass out. Flick isn't trancing any more. Pjorg's just awoken, essentially. As Flick is trying to recall the names of the McMurtons, she thinks back to the one boy lost in the woods, never found again, ... his name started with an \"S\". She can see his shape in her mind's eye, a totally black figure, surrounded by fog.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; INT save KH. 15.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The particular sheen of the darkness reminds her of the wolf figurine -- she's reminded of the way she sees the MP when she's in the EP. (Washed out and greyscale, out of focus. ) As this figure walks towards her, a dark green swampy woods materializes behind him, and instead of a three-dimensional rocky exterior, he begins to look like a hole through space. What she thought was a forest begins to look like creeping greyish green tentacles pushing through a hole in space. Flick fixates on his silhouette, and attempts to detect (the closest) planar portal (Detect Portal).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>At first, though \"all signs point to portal,\" she's reluctant to assign it that; there's nowhere the portal goes, and then she recognizes that it has all the materials trappings of a portal, but seems almost like ... someone sent something to see if a portal could be made. Whatever the silhouette is made of. She can't tell the relationship between the tentacles and the \"portal\" assay. She then snaps out of the vision to see Pjorg polishing all the dust off his armor.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As he's cleaning his armor, he notices that some of the runes he was looking at blasted away the dust in the mirror image of teh runes on his chest. Pjorg transcribes them and their proper orientation. He gets a section that, with attention from a specialist, he could puzzle it out. He spends the rest of the LR trying to figure it out.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; DC = 16? In the past, Pjorg is a memory-by-repetition, strength of mind, or stubbornness (will become constitution). Because he has 4 hours to examine 5 letters, he manages to determine the letters \"g-o-r-e-s\" (the spaces between the letters aren't in this runic alphabet)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg starts thinking of Bulls and the people gored by them.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick keeps the watch since she's up. The all wake up at an appropriate time in the morning. JL has a bit of a hangover, but he's dealt with things like this before. \"Won't be the first time.\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>They examine the river gorge as we ...</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Cut to the surface and a wagon ...</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>being pulled by three stout ponies. It has embroidered on the outside &lt;&lt; insert my description here &gt;&gt;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>On the driver and shotgun position there are two gnomes: Nissi, wearing a deal of fussery, a five-piece suit made out of bright blue velvet with gold embroidery and a top hat. his horse strop is made from a strange purple leather with feather tassels on the end. Next to him sits another figure, Jaap. A small forest gnome, dressed practically, with greens and browns, with a big shield with the image of another weird gnome (Gaarl) on top of it; no hat. His hair is crazy, like most gnomes, as though he's just touched a tesla coil -- there's probably one around somewhere. He also has a beard. black hair and black beard. No silver hairs yet, because he's young for a gnome. his beard he quickly combed after touching the coil.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap had been forbidden from entering the mobile toyshop, but the curtain separating the driver and the cab , which is usually black behind, this morning oddly enough betrayed a tesla coil, which Jaap had reached back to touch. Nissi slaps his hand, \"Hey, I said no going back there!\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap: I had to have a look...</p>\n<p>Nissi: Looks like you've had a touch</p>\n<p>Jaap: how could you tell?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Nissi: I'm wise where it counts</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap is very tempting by what's in the wagon. Nissi points out various landmarks. \"Or maybe I'll drop you off a little earlier\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; DEX KL.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Nissi's been driving worrisomely close to the edge of the river gorge. He then takes a sharp right turn with the wagon, as if to jump it over the stream, much like Garl Glittergold in his \"Santaclause\" aspect. However, the wagon just begins falling and plummets down towards the river.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick and Pjorg, still up, hear the sounds of high-pitched screaming and look up to see a caravan catapulting over the edge of the river.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Roll initiative</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vengeance, distracted, tries casting slow fall, realizing too late that it's something that only affects him. \"If you just forget to fall ... ?\" Pjorg recalls one of the blasted dwarves named Digging Less Addams; they weren't liked by dwarves because they advocated for their first name.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The river is about 200 feet below.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Jaap perception roll, 22</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Just as he tips over the edge, he can see a few people clustered in a cave opening about 60 feet below. There are isolated entrances that pockmark the cliff face, but two of the people have noticed him. He takes stock of things and Dimension Doors and pops onto the ledge.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap reaches out to grab Nissi, and grabs one of his many frock coats; instead he's holding a full bottle and a deck of playing cards. \"I hope you enjoy your new friends!\" and plunged down with the wagon. Jaap sees the sly wink of his uncle, Jan, emerge from behind the face; he recognizes a classic gnomic prank.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap: Classic, Jan. Thanks!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As he plunges into the water, it looks like a bubble of air surrounds him and he begins floating back up north.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\"Aw, sweet, I got some turnip schnapps?! That's totally my uncle.\" He recalls that Jan is very proud of his turnip farm and makes disgusting schnapps and other products from them. They have a very high alcohol content, and may have other properties; but in either case they are hand produced from his distillery. (Jansen Distilleries in Atkhatla) and you can smell it through the bottle (year-old swampy boots) \"Ah, now I'm getting homesick\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Cards are Deck of Illusions</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Everyone sees a tiny gnome materialize while behind him drops a shop-sized wagon with ponies. Flick rushes over to see what happened.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Arcana.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick sees the wagon explode on impact. But he doesn't see any dead animals or gnome. She turns back to Jaap. \"Hey, how is everyone? I'm doing great!\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg: Hello, verrrrrry small one.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap runs over and hides behind the dwarf. Whispering: Do you know there's a goblin here?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; retroactive Stealth check on dimension door appearance. very bad.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>When he jumped in, he somehow managed to drop every item on his person; amulets and vials and weapons. He's there picking them up, heaping them onto his cloak and dragging them up behind Drav.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav: What's ... going on here? (She notices immediately some generic clerical signs on Jaap). \"Hellowww... We just met this goblin a few hours ago. We don't know each other yet.\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: Yes thanks we know there's a goblin did you come down here just to tell us that?</p>\n<p>Jaap: I was worried about you guys; these goblins can be pretty mean, you know.</p>\n<p>Pjorg: A goblin, where?! Hahahahahah.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg seems amiable, if deluded. If it helps him fight, he can feel as big as he wants.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap's history with goblins is no personal history, but just general distrust. But gnomes do like dwarves as allies because neither likes goblins. (The Biterbig gnomes live close to dwarves, as do the Flundarst gnomes, who are up in the top layer, and dwarves are lower.)&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap: Oh, ok, this seems not to be a problem, then.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; History checks all around. JL is barely awake.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL has been dreaming of his family and past girlfriends as goblins for the past three hours. Not surprisingly, Pjorg doesn't know too much about them. Drav knows a great deal about goblins.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg thinks to himself (goblins are actually the most honest, upright folk the world has ever seen; all of them are chaotic good, fighting for the good of the land)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav knows that they have been conspicuously absent from this area of the continent; really anywhere east of the Ocean of Rel. There are legends as to why; some say there was a genocide, some that it was an exodus to head for a Cockayne/cocaine paradise. Flick knows there aren't very many around.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; bathroom break</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Jaap INT check.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Now that Jaap knows that Nissi was Jan, he thinks back to stories he was telling about the fantasy land he supposedly grew up in. The land of Milk and Honey, and he realizes that some of these things could have been hints to him about leads to pursue on his quest. Jaan did wonder why Garl hadn't been all that evident in helping him.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- rumor about evil unicorns who would seek out virgins to consume their blood (hearts?) and sustain their immortality</p>\n<p>- legends of Kalarduan, who stole the heart of Ogremoch, and the theft caused the latter god to turn evil, but gave Kalarduan the power to control earth elementals. Jantien was never able to receive the welcome from the gods into the clerical faith; it's possible she might have pursued something similar</p>\n<p>- creatures that would steal the hearts of people in order to gain certain powers&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap reflects on how inventive his sister was. Flick's eyes flit between the wagon flotsam and Jaap. \"I think he's alright; he got away fine.\" It doesn't take a lot to convince Flick of things anymore. Drav is sleepy and doesn't understand anything that's going on.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: We do need a way out of these caves.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL: Oh yeah, we were not thinking ahead. (He's still processing returning).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: The snake cult must have gotten in somehow; can we go back out the way Pjorg got in?</p>\n<p>Drav: Oh yeah, I didn't mention, that eldar mentioned some runes in that direction.</p>\n<p>Pjorg: I ... oh, RUUUUUUUNES. I saw some runes. Upon a wall. I was studying them, attempting to discern their meaning, although it is laborious, and suddenly there was a brightness, and that is all I know.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Very cryptic.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Pjorg arcana check. boom.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The runes he was studying are supposed to keep him awake, so it's really weird he fell asleep afterwards. they definitely don't have anything to do with inducing soporificness. which is like terrificness, but sleepier.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg has drawn their copies, and people can see his actual runes carved into his armor and weapons. The dust is transcribed into a runic journal.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; INT kl. nat 20.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick can tell that these don't look like the runes on his weapons. As Drav suspects, they look like they are part of a grammatical language. It's not a language she knows. Is it a language Pjorg knows? Yes, it's very close to one ... he knows.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg's runes are like sigils. The runes contain the essence of the thing that's being written, and that's what allows the thing to be ...&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick commands the Rope of Climbing to wend its way up and knot itself to an outcropping on ground level. It takes about a minute. Flick, a good climber, lifts the part members up to the rope.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>FLick turns to Jaap: Do you have business in this cave? What were you doing today?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap: whatever you're doing sounds like a cool adventure. Flick: We're going to get back a salamander from some con artists and see where the day takes us.</p>\n<p>Pjorg: Is this a normal day for you small ones?</p>\n<p>Flick: Kind of ?</p>\n<p>Jaap: and sandford is our destination?</p>\n<p>Flick: yep</p>\n<p>Jaap: Oh, I'd love to come with.</p>\n<p>Flick: We're a party of little people</p>\n<p>Pjorg: Indeed, save one.</p>\n<p>Drav: Isn't there a weight limit for this thing?</p>\n<p>Flick: I don't know, DRAV, is there?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick thinks about daisy-chaining, then realizes she'll be holding everyone's weight, so jumps down and then agrees people should just get boosted up the rope.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Where is Mule? As Jaap was tipped into the chasm, he saw across the way a contented Mule chomping at some sedge grass. The ponies nodded knowingly at it. Did it have a weird nose? Yes, it looked vaguely humanoid. Very vaguely. Shortened nose, humany-lips, a human soul poking out from its eyes. Oh, that must be another gnome (illusion?) then.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: Not a lot of people know this, but that Mule came rocketing out of a pool of greasy wrestling oil at us, and we invited it along on our quest. You, Jaap, might crack the top three for strangeness of circumstances&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg: I believe this is a rather DRAV (drab?) day&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav: I think the slime unicorn is top of the list.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>At the mention of a slime unicorn, Jaap perks up, as it sounds a lot like the strange unicorn Jan was telling him about. \"Oh, what about this unicorn, did you encounter it?</p>\n<p>Flick: Encounter it? we killed it</p>\n<p>Jaap: were there any virgins around at the time?</p>\n<p>Flick looks at Jean-Luc. \"Maybeee?\"</p>\n<p>JL: mmmmmmmmm (voice cracks) could happen</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick never attracted any interest from her age group and thinks of herself. \"Yeah ... there were some virgins around.\"</p>\n<p>Jaapn: So the unicorn was there for a reason then.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Everyone is clinging successfully, even Pjorg, for whom the rope is too large a gauge. he used a smaller rope to tie to the bigger rope.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The rope apparently responds to french: e lev tois (sp?) . and it pulls them up as it coils itself around the rock. They get their feet up the cliff and they kind of shuffle upwards without banging ; DRav and the smaller creatures can't quite make contact; Drav's feet are stabbing Vengeance in the face and shoulders as she basically stands on top of him.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sandford is south of them, on the western side of the river. They head south and look for a crossing.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap can't think of any secret crossings.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Though Roxfallanah is on the other side of teh river, Vengeance casts himself down and acts as though she's crushing him in the chest with her hooves.</p>\n<p>Flick: Hey Vengeance, let's get you over and make sure you can really do that.</p>\n<p>Pjorg: Tell me more of this brotherhood of oxidation.</p>\n<p>Vengeance: I am really doing it. Do I still have to whisper.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick just summons Gerd to ferry them all across, and keeps concentrating on her for the 40 minutes it takes to get to Sandford. Flick uses her like a surveillance drone on the Hat Baskets. Jaap: Yeah, and we can see if there are any more wagons coming out of the sky.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Nissi had taken a less explored route south on the east of the river.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick turns to Jean-Luc. \"Based on what you know of these folks, would we be able to find the Hat Baskets based on where they were last night?\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Is Jean-Luc familiar with the Demerast Saga? (It bears the same relation to real thieves that Law&amp;Order does to actually being a homicide detective. It \"has the trappings of authenticity but is deeply ridiculous\") Yes, but it didn't bear any relation to why he chose thieves' work. (He's a romantic, but not like that. Jean-Luc would have read Demerast because it would have given him something to talk about with the women in his classes)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The things about meetings in safe-houses is that, even if HB aren't actively using it, they are keeping an eye on it. JL thinks if they go there, because of the chaos, and explosion, it would \"bring up a lot of bad memories\" -- this is how the HB choose their safe houses. Also if Tishara has a lot of money to burn, she'd be in favor of conspicuous consumption, but there's a chance that some of their agents are still hanging around there.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; How expensive is real estate in Sandford? Flick: Looking at your character sheet it doesn't look like you're proficient in commercial real estate. Michael: Yeah that was a tough choice. Mick: You could always work that into the character attributes. If the HB want to be close to the ports, there is a great deal of turnover in those properties, but it's also in high demand, so they could move outwards to the north-east; but it's a matter of meeting their requirements for accessibility, secrecy, and ostentation.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL: Because they expect us to do a job for them, and/or set us up, we won't have to find them, they will probably find us. Flick: Fair enough, but I don't like being \"found\" in this context. Should we start from the former safehouse and see if there are breadcrumbs for us to follow? Are these crumb-bums careless enough? JL: I think they're capable, and security-conscious, enough that because this is their town, we will alert them if we go looking for them. We can't avoid hitting their trip wires. DM: They were pretty good at finding you initially, and it may also be that they're operating in an environment where they don't have any considerable enemies.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Flick: like the dodo, and we're the Portuguese. On the list of crimes, #1: Brazil. #2: the dodo.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: there are two things we can do: try to track them down, or ready ourselves and conspicuously ask around for them. JL: we have one advantage, which is that we weren't accompanied by a goblin and a kobold. JAAP: excuse me! (Jean-Luc doesn't know what race they are, and doesn't care. \"I don't see kobold\").</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL: we can use ourselves as bait and let our friends hide in the shadoes.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: I like that a lot; Pjorg is very adept at hiding, so I think this plan is great (presumably irony?)</p>\n<p>JL: if we go around looking for them, that will be suspicious. If we present ourselves openly</p>\n<p>Flick: We could pretend we did the job.</p>\n<p>JL: Yeah, the ledger wouldn't be too hard to forge.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: We could find some leather-bound book at some bookstore. Drav -- you probably even have something on hand.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav: We should probably try to match what it looks like</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; they roll a 100 on 1d100 luck check for how well they remeber what it looks like.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It looks like a large, weathered, leather-bound tome with brass bindings.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>They look for an antiquarian bookstore.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Montage music.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: What if Pjorg and Jaap are sent into the bookstores? If we're being watched that might make most sense. JL: I want to believe I can convincingly lie about why I'm in a bookstore to other thieves. Flick: These are the people we had to fold their frickin map around a dagger. JL: it feels more like ornamentation rather than actual security. Pjorg: I have seen a hydra, and they are tremendous in their size. Jaap: it's a good idea; we probably don't want to be seen with the rest of the gang, then. Flick: This is getting very complicated. I think maybe we should just get the book, and JL will talk us out of it if we're caught. Drav: there's probably other materials we'd need too, wouldn't there be? Flick: we;ll need some filigree and carbolic acid to weather the pages.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Carbolic acid, or phenol, is present in coal tar (from where it's primarily extracted), but also from the temporal glands of elephants in musth, and beaver castoreum, which is a great addition to anyone's cabinet of curiosities.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vengeance: I've heard of phenols and carbolic acids mentioned in conjunction with the Order of Rust.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: You're still on that, huh?</p>\n<p>Vengeance: How not? It's what my childhood enemy devoted himself to.</p>\n<p>Flick fails in trying to convince vengeance to leave on a quest.</p>\n<p>Vengeance: Flick, your reverse psychology attempt to get me to stay has worked, I do declare.</p>\n<p>Pjorg: &lt;some nonsense&gt;</p>\n<p>Vengeance: If the Order of Rust is about disintegration, then I want to integrate with you all by staying</p>\n<p>Pjorg: Isn't the order of rust very fiendish?</p>\n<p>Vengeance: Ok ... true ...</p>\n<p>Pjorg: then wouldn't they have already planned for this?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vengeance: They're fiendish, but they aren't all that smart</p>\n<p>Pjorg: or maybe they want you to think that.</p>\n<p>Vengeance: I don't know i've played mind games with them.</p>\n<p>Pjorg: They've bee doing that the whole time.</p>\n<p>Vengeance: Do you want to come with me?</p>\n<p>PJorg. Yes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Deception KH.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vengeance: ok, so as long as you come with me?</p>\n<p>Pjorg: absolutely. here's the plan, let's split up.</p>\n<p>Vengeance: already going back to the Order of Rust structure of disintegration.</p>\n<p>Pjorg: I'm coming with you, but we're splitting up.</p>\n<p>Vengeance: Where should I be going ?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[57::]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Vengeance lives with Roxfallanah</p>\n<p>- Everyone thinks he gave up way too easily, maybe.</p>\n<p>- Ledger, and what they need</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Drav arcana (11)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Drav knows that there's an arcane fingerprint to the tome, but she's not positive that she can replicate it.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Flick: we just really need to get in the same room as them</p>\n<p>- JL is upset most by why _they_ are being involved</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If they were able to make text appear on it in real time, as though it were coming from the captains, it would do a lot to sell the illusion.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Jaap: I think I have a cantrip for that. Minor illusion?&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Flick: Jaap, you're already pulling your weight.=</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick goes to bookstore since she got best look at book. JL to bar to act like he did the job.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick remembers passing Poor Souls' Salvation (book store, among other things); Fountain of Elegance. Flick heads there. (Another water feature like the caves)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; JL Performance/Deception check KH</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pjorg is hiding; doesn't know how well goblins will be received. Flick thinks they should do the buddy system. Drav is also interested in what the Fountain would sell. Jaap goes to look around town; he's never been in a town like this before, just underground warrens.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Jaap Investigation nat 20.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sandford is a small town, only a mile in diameter. Bigger than anything he's seen; a curious distinction between social classes. Larger estates, crummy houses near docks; warehouse districts; open plazas. people milling about; there are quite a few strangers to town. it's in the middle of a fishing competition/contest/holiday .&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Ian: is there a weighstation to see what's the biggest one? DM: Yes, one of the plazas set off specifically for sizing and weighing competition. Officiants with giant white moustaches that reach to their knees, and ancient rulers; metreticians to weigh them magically, and people expounding on symbolic and religious fishy values. Some fish are in ice; some people have brought giant aquariums.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Magnificent Sandford Menagerie Fishing Jostle</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap is into trickery, as a gnome, but hasn't used this spell all this often with strangers, and ends up shouting \"Hey buddy, watch it there\" and he can't sell the ventriloquism. Everyone looks at Jaap. The fish catcher: I am taking care of him; i'm gonna throw him back later. Jaap: Uhhhh ... well done, yes. Other guy: Look, there's funnel cakes and spun sugar. I'm sure that's good for a toddler like you. Jaap, embarrassed, moves away.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>With Nat 20, he sees these creatures that meet one of Nissi's description. Local pirates, maybe even raiders or slavers. If he didn't know better he'd think they were part fish. Their skin is thick, pale, and wet, almost like skin kept in wet boots for too long. They are ghouls, or ghasts, though, and live in the Sea of Kohsht. They make excursions up to Marshbout and teh Honeied sea, and take goods and valuables from religious institutions; they have slaves to build their ships, and cut wood, and sew sails, etc. This could have been one of the routes for his sister being taken. It's unusual she would have disappeared without a trace, since they usually do a lot of damage, and there are a few on the outskirts of one of the plazas; maybe they have an SEP around them.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; There are no police in Sandford, per se. Gnomes don't have police. There was a bailiff or constable, maybe, but no \"bureaucrats with guns\" .&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaap pops into a wholegoods store and pokes out from behind a barrel full of olives. a customer looks at him quizzically but assumes him to be an employee. He casts Disguise Self to change his apperance.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[Cut to]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick and Drav in Fountain of Elegance; there is a fountain in the middle of the room, and through some gaudy magic there are rhetorical phrases being spewed out of the fountain, where it speaks the phrases as the water forms the shape of the words. The store is far too large for the few shelves it has, and there are even fewer books per shelf. Dispite all the room, the books are spine out, and it's clear they are going for some kind of arcane minimalism.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[:: back to full transcript]]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>There's no counter or desk, there's just a retail space.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: Is this just a front? This doesn't look like a business meant to do business.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Nat 20 (from before)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>She's pretty sure that's exactly what's going on, and because it's so twee she's pretty sure it's the Hat Baskets too. \"Drav! This isn't a real bookstore, I think it's a front for the Hat Baskets\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As she looks around, she sees that the back wall, in the silhouette of a person, starts to become liquid, and out of it emerges a figure (reminding her slightly of the naiad), a polished greenish-blue skin, completely bald, piercing golden-brown eyes, wearing a well-tailored white dress, simple sandals. she comes forward.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: mam, do you happen to be responsible for this establishment.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Oriax: Yes, this is my bookstore. We sell all sorts of rare artefacts here. 9She looks at both of them). You're not my typical clientelle.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: I was wondering. If you not only sold volumes but took them on consignment or trade. I happen to have a biography detailing the lives of certain captains of industry by an author D. L. Ledger and I haven't had much luck getting it appraised.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>(Flick has to restrain herself from tapping her nose, like the thieves stereotypes cliches).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&gt; Deception check? 18 (I should have done something like ... they both roll intelligence or Insight and the scores have to add up to a certain number?)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Oriax looks at Flick. Oh, DL Ledger. I was going to tell you that consignment here is -- I've hardly ever spoken the word. And emits a beautiful, bell-like laugh. Neither Drav nor Flick can tell what species she is, but she does seem humanoid. \"How many 'a's are at the start of your name?\" My name is Oriax.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick lapses into fey and speaks a fey idiom \"~ you never know what rock the golden worm will be under.\" She looks at Flick and laughs, \"Indeed!\" She has no idea what Flick has just said.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick papers over that \"party foul\". \"I unfortunately don't have it with me; I left it in my rooms, but after your obligations are finished here perhaps you and whoever is interested in acquiring it could meet me at (she pulls out her map and points conspicuously at the dagger hole ) \" right here, for instance.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Though the store is empty, Oriax looks around and pushes the map down out of sight. \"There's no need for that here -- I don't think that a tawdry meeting like that ; perhaps just keep it with you and you'll be found this evening.\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick: Marvellous, that's actually what I was hoping for all along.</p>\n<p>Oriax: In the meantime can I interest you in any of the wares I do sell. It looks like you travel in more elevated circles than I immediately assumed.</p>\n<p>Flick: The rarest of the rare, you have no idea. Drav, is the grimoire you're looking for among this selection?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav: I've not seen it, but thank you.</p>\n<p>Flick (in fey): &lt;bad pun on farewell&gt; Dos vidanya, don't get any on ya'.</p>\n<p>Oriax looks haughtily baffled; oh, you elves and your wordplay</p>\n<p>Flick: let's get out of here, Drav.</p>"}
{"_id":"NGVUw2vypYm6qXo9","name":"Sheldrake Baggs","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"wf40lADkdvhEIKuG","sort":1400000,"flags":{},"content":"<div>aka Drake, Shelby, bags</div>\n<div>- a dragon</div>\n<div>- really old</div>\n<div>- megatherium</div>\n<div>- the bag dragon / bar tender / bar itself</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- has a milk robot (Turr and TMK connection)</div>"}
{"_id":"NYsi23BQuqTAdi7z","name":"Amabelle","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"wf40lADkdvhEIKuG","sort":200000,"flags":{},"content":"<ul>\n<li>The dwarven sorceress who transformed Roxfallanah into Mule.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Vengeance remembers her as being very stylish, wearing a top hat and statement glasses, a lot of tattoos and a cool braided beard.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>- Star: did you say amabelle? well she used to run with the fiend; she was a tatoo artist and she did his first tats, and they started running together. she&rsquo;s a real legend in the biz; her tattoos could do pretty much anything. stuff as far as healing people, or giving them really big appetites, just a huge puff of some sweeet grass; she could eliminate a hangover if she wanted.</li>\n<li>? God of Asceticism</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->"}
{"_id":"NYvtq0Av2tBn3Jkf","name":"Lum Gorbelly","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"wf40lADkdvhEIKuG","sort":1500000,"flags":{},"content":"<h1 dir=\"ltr\">Lum Gorbelly</h1>\n<div><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-6dd199ba-7fff-0044-e42a-8f4786dd9979\"></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">gnoll (weregnoll?)</div>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">stodgy</div>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">maybe in the mid-5 feets</div>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">looks like a teddy bear (but a cute jackal version)</div>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">had wanted to go into public office, but even the S&amp;B thought he was too uncharismatic, so they didn&rsquo;t even use him as a pawn</div>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">kind of pessimistic (oh goodness, i hope that never happens&hellip;)</div>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">(a futilitarian, too?)</div>\n</li>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">maybe this is part of what makes him a bad politician hopeful</div>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">despite this, he&rsquo;s always trying to recruit new members (or, just &hellip; friends)</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">always full or complaining about being full</div>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">pact with Raul?</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Lum gets garbled &amp; incomplete messages from Raul's life, essentially, because neither really understands the other. This is slowly driving him mad, and can look like Bogshosh, but is not.</li>\n</ul>"}
{"_id":"NmtPt8bB0bOvvEWF","name":"buggshosh","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"srmjxCv4QHqVw5AK","sort":1200001,"flags":{},"content":"<h1 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Proxima Nova',sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bugg-Shash</span></h1>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Black One</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Filler of Space</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">He Who Comes in the Dark</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">a gelatinous creature with innumerable human-like eyes and mouths within its black mass. It attacks human victims by wrapping its mass around them and drowning them in slime, often attacking several individuals at once. Once dead, the victim(s) can be controlled, puppet-like, to perform a task where there is light, something which Bugg-Shash cannot endure.&nbsp;</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-indent: 36pt; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Proxima Nova',sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">twinning horror</span></h2>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 36pt;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bugg-Shash can appear to a susceptible victim as their clone or twin. &hellip; wake up cold, with ice crystals on nose, mouth, eyes</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-f0aa2275-7fff-f8bd-ea76-68e2075fef2e\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Proxima Nova',sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bugg-Shash cultists</span></h2>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0.3pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Marshbout &ldquo;chapter&rdquo;</span></h3>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Proxima Nova',sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Thistlemilk Kids</span></h2>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">a front organization for The Bugg-Shash cultists near Marshbout&nbsp;</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Proxima Nova',sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Stagger &amp; Bellows</span></h2>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">something to do with legality ?</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">counter-intelligence unit (because Cultists are pretty fucking stupid)</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-indent: 36pt; margin-top: 5pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Preston Girnel aka Remy Flitch</span></h4>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 36pt;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Joan&rsquo;s handler</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0.3pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Turnquist</span></h3>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 36pt;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bragg&rsquo;s handler</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 36pt;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">doesn&rsquo;t &lsquo;pose&rsquo; as anything</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0.3pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Adriana Quence</span></h3>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 36pt;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Cambria,serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">married to Lum&rsquo;s sister</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br /><br /></p>"}
{"_id":"OXrrziC98jd97ZAi","name":"Teallach Gormflaith","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"srmjxCv4QHqVw5AK","sort":2700001,"flags":{},"content":"<div>ghouls / ghasts - heroic oral celtic culture</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- more like vikings than pirates; but isn't this where we get some of our ideas about pirates?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>two creatures that look like avatar or githyanki</div>\n<div>dressed in hides that don't conform well to bodies</div>\n<div>carrying large metal staves, hoooked at end, with barbed points</div>\n<div>talking about supposed to meet kinsmen coming in on placid beast, and worried about not having seen them</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>metal staves are made with red alloy</div>\n<div>[ when he got to throttlebottom, he gave arlan the metal they picked up from the warehouse]</div>\n<div>\"how did you come by those staves ; they are very interesting\"</div>\n<div>[i hand steve the &hellip; lady logo]</div>\n<div>staffs are symbol of becoming a sailor</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>recently we've been trading for this metal (scintillating, never rust, hard and keep a fine point).&nbsp;</div>\n<div>we were coming here also to get more of these weapons (metal)</div>\n<div>a good weapon is worth more than its weight in gold</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<h2>NPCS</h2>\n<div>one is female, one male</div>\n<div>vishara, and yvonna</div>\n<div>were supposed to meet kinsmen traveling on placid beast from up north; heard that ship went down it was supposed to dock in marshbout</div>\n<div>- Farog Vell</div>"}
{"_id":"OhS6CiVehAqLBA7P","name":"Palchin","permission":{"default":0,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3},"folder":"wf40lADkdvhEIKuG","sort":900000,"flags":{},"content":"<h2>Conversation with Vengeance</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Vengeance: Jean-Luc, why don't you let me handle this. I think this matter requires a bit of delicacy. Palchin, if you don't tell us what you're up to, we're going to burn your house down and kill everybody that you love. I take that back &hellip; Palchin, what monastery did you happen to study in. You seem like you might follow the ways of the Tranquil monks.</li>\n<li>Palchin: How did you know?</li>\n<li>Vengeance: I guess you could say that I'm a \"weirdo\" like yourself.</li>\n<li>Palchin: I wasn't going to say that, but &hellip; that's up to you. But yes -- I'm a monk of the Ivory Empire. But that was decades, if not almost a hundred years ago.</li>\n<li>Vengeance: I seem to recall we used to play that Monastery in stickball.</li>\n<li>Palchin: Stickball, yes! It's been quite a while. It certainly does bring back the memories. Some of our fellow monks were lucky enough to have their limbs amputated and replaced with sticks so as to play the game in its purest form.</li>\n<li>Vengeance: The game has changed a lot since then. These days everyone seems to be \"stick-doping\". It's sort of lost its lustre.</li>\n<li>Palchin: Stick-doping?</li>\n<li>Vengeance: No, like replacing their limbs with sticks. It's kind of unfair, don't you think.</li>\n<li>Palchin: well i think it's unfair in a religious sense, but maybe not in a physiomechanical sense. but of course, the religious sense is the most important. we're agreed there.</li>\n<li>Vengeance: given that the purpose of stick-ball is to be as much like a stick as you can</li>\n<li>Palchin: That's interesting, our monastery always had a different take on it, which was it's important to be as much like a ball impaled by a stick as possible.</li>\n</ul>"}
