{"_id":"VFQbjTlZnh65HjBH","name":"The Dirty-Milk War","permission":{"default":0,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3},"folder":"IahJpr0JiteucCD5","sort":200000,"flags":{},"content":"<ul>\n<li>[a note i had in prepping for 20201206]</li>\n<li>part of what's going on with Snav trying to siphon off energy of qi.&nbsp;\n<ul>\n<li>maybe a similar kind of thing to the water of the valley in the Uprooted book(s) or whatever those titles were, where people are kind of mildly magical because they imbibe the milk.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>there are a few main milk-producing regions:\n<ul>\n<li>Turr in the Sjosthern steppes</li>\n<li>Cattle in the Olmak Valley and connected valleys of the Akran Peninsula</li>\n<li>Ground-milk of the Biely Unik</li>\n<li>Troll milk of Thuridan and perhaps other Firbolgs</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>"}
{"_id":"VaD07WPJjYTFCG7O","name":"Jan Jansen","permission":{"default":0,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3},"folder":"wf40lADkdvhEIKuG","sort":2000000,"flags":{},"content":"<div>Jaap Jansen's Uncle from Athkatla in Faer&ucirc;n.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<h1>disguises</h1>\n<h2>Nissi Whistle-Pummleaf</h2>\n<div>&nbsp;Jaap met up with a gnome named&nbsp;Nissi&nbsp;Whistle-Pummleaf with three stout ponies leading a large wagon labeled somewhat cumbersomely \"The Mobile Toyshop --- Owner, Proprietor, Landlord, Tenant, Customer, Patron, Litigator, Heir, and all Other Things Apparent being one&nbsp;Nissi&nbsp;Whistle-Pummleaf, Gnome, Of No Certain Provenance, So Don't Bother Asking, Have a Good Day Thank You and Hello.\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>You've been traveling with this unplaceably&nbsp;familiar figure but have not been allowed to step foot in the wagon; instead&nbsp;Nissi&nbsp;has set up bedrolls for both of you at night and provided fresh meals from within.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Despite the sign's admonition, he's been doing nothing but describing the land of his home, a place he calls Anuparktos, and all the unbelievably wild things which go on there, none of which you're inclined to believe, but which you feel might hold some odd glimpse or glimmer of truth. As this particular day dawns, you both rise, break your fast, and head south along the western edge of the Braided Mountains (he calls the closest ridge the \"Arm of the Pig\") and towards the port town of Sandford, at which destination you believe you'll be confident and safe enough to ask questions of some more worldly people than the inlanders you've been seeing so far.</div>"}
