{"_id":"XmRidnsXl9hlKmWn","name":"009. Sap, sugar, butter, flour (nightmare remix)","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"7FU7CCEBg8xZrzdi","sort":500000,"flags":{},"content":"<div dir=\"ltr\">Session 009 Sap, sugar, butter, flour (nightmare remix)</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Played</strong>:&nbsp;December 21, 2019 (2019-12-21)</div>\n<div><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-1eda0cfa-7fff-9e22-1931-ce5b601b3de2\"></span></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Day 3 (cont.)</strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Level 3</strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><hr /></div>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">Recap</h2>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3db8e2cd-7fff-877d-9246-702af2550e39\">Polive and the other three gnomes (Riult, Woon, and Foldorf) brought the adventurers to the Candy Lab &mdash; a marvellously lit space containing an imposing bulbous oven, vats filled with a dimly glowing purple liquid, four shilvery^ cleanroom suits, and hardly any candy to be seen &mdash; whereupon Flick promptly declared her intention to nap. While Paros futzed about with a draconic alarm clock, the wood elf deferred her doze upon detecting some curious odors emanating from the hob. Polive walked Joan to a worktable in the back where she fitted the adventuresome dragonborn with the promised prototype of \"septum gear,\" a twin of the one seen in situ on Nexnag resembling a boiler's pressure release valve and provided brief instruction in its use and maintenance. Meanwhile our resident planar warrior, much like an astronomien^ secluded deep within a transcolating <em>beorh&thorn;^</em> to detect nought but the unmistakable issels^ of an eludent cosmocaust, was a bit \"weirded out;\" the familiar traces of Thuridan's feybubble, Baba Jezda's fading portalian aura were soon outshadowed by&nbsp; a curious notch in the worldgrain some few hundred yards to her left. Notorious maverick Drav inquisitively stuck her head into the oven while Domonkos, having succumbed to Paros's exhortation to accompany them, skeptically bit into a bloodcake (one of Polive's confectionaries), whose ingrediential^ provenance posed him cause for concern.</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-14c7cd10-7fff-6aa1-8078-3b9799bfec02\"></span></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\"><strong>&mdash; Guck-iin-zehr-Luft</strong></h4>\n<hr />\n<div><strong>shilvery</strong>:&nbsp;(perh.) <em>Moir&eacute; metallique</em>.</div>\n<div><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ce0333f7-7fff-9b13-242c-bb13474d2e90\"><strong>astronomien</strong>: Astronaut.</span></div>\n<div><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-897653e9-7fff-f67a-b56e-19de1ac02b5b\"><strong>beorh&thorn;</strong>: </span>(perh.) Planetary mass?</div>\n<div><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-1226ef03-7fff-5b97-19c3-76a87167989c\"><strong>issels</strong>: Sparks.</span></div>\n<div><strong>ingrediential</strong>: &nbsp;Pertaining to ingredients; compositous.</div>\n<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\n<h2>Transcript</h2>\n<p>[n/a]</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>home session 9_1_1_0_polive_leads_into_factory</p>\n<p>==============================================</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[...]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;lights string between columns (oil and magical lamps)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] people wearing bunny suits (donnie darko)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick isn't all that interested in touring the candy lab</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;can I set up in a corner and take a [SR]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;sits in the oven-adjacent corner</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros prepares action to prestidigitation-slap flick if something seems amiss [x] technically you can't slap someone with prestidigitate</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick [PERC 14] - complexity of odors coming out of the oven. not just candy and cake.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros: are there work gnomes around ?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;no, just these four</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive: purply glowy stuff is natural features of cave. like breweries that boast of clean water.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;before trancing, flick looks at hob surface.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;jake: \"who's good at smells?\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] DON'T FORGET PAROS SMELL SPELLS</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;drav: can joan smell?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;debi rolls ...&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;nothing on hob itself, but pans are ready for use.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: how glowy is the purple ?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fairly dim, but purplish</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive says \"i promised two of you one thing each\";&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;goes back to shelves&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[7]</p>\n<p>===</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick weirded out at planar warrior abilities</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;will feel around for nearby portals</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;one mile sphere</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;trace of firbolg's bubble&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;nighthunter's fading aura - portal that it is</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"portalian\"; \"portalesque\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;ian: \"almost like walking around with her eyes closed; she can see stuff \"in between\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;700 ft. \"left\" of candy lab, same depth below surface (&frac14; mile)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick is off meditating.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;drav looking in ovens</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick thinks that's what she was smelling</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive offers Domonkos a bloodcake. he sniffs it, quizzical look, eats it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros detects that Domonkos is a little peeved that D caved to P's request to come to the candy lab and he's putting a mental barrier up between the two.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;D. looks like the bloodcake might not be pleasing him.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;but to polive \"very tasty, very sophisticated\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive: \"and now for the dragonborn\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive gives joan the septum gear, but it glints in the purple light and joan's sparks. it's one nostril in, one nostril release valve or flange</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;door at the back opens to cooling area.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;opens a sliver, a face pops out; human-sized; face is round and greenish-white, and frozen in a smile with huge chiclet-style teeth</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;drav strolls to&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] that's drav, playing it cool</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>home session 9_1_1_1</p>\n<p>====================</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[0]&nbsp;</p>\n<p>====</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;describing juniper as spirited away greenish with chiclet teeth, sausage appendages</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;jake: are they chiclets because we're in a candy factory?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;dm: you don't know.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;drav, arcane check (18). dm: they might be a magic user, but no spells in the area</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[3]</p>\n<p>===</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;domonkos comes over to paros: what do you think a bloodcake should have in it?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros: probably a lot of blood</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;domonkos: what kind of blood?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros: (using messaging) Domonkos: there's definitely blood in there; i'm worried it might be too close to your species for you not to be concerned.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[3-]</p>\n<p>====</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;setting positions on map</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;no other workers.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;matt finishes up transferring the map</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[6]</p>\n<p>===</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;rihhilt and foldulf communing with the vat</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[&lt;7m]</p>\n<p>=====</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive done distributing presents, asks if anyone wants a demonstration</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos (jenny) asks if he can have candy candy (as present)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive offers to make her fresh candy</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;WUUN (jake) \"loves it when they make the candy\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[10]</p>\n<p>====</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick sees the rest of sausage-link Juniper (segments that bend, rather than bone articulations) , normal eyes, wearing a loose burlap sack. human in size. Ethel the baby gray render comes out (only 10-12 ft). keeping up with Juniper.&nbsp; Very playful.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;would know that refrigerated unit goes back (but perpendicular to the direction flick detected the weird portally thing)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;the four elements (sap, sugar, butter, flour)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;juniper the \"Death doctor\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[16]</p>\n<p>====</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;i tell flick there's no monstrosities back in the refrigerated area, now that ethel came out</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;domonkos tells paros: this has something to do with the baron.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;the bloodcake has a distinctly humanoid blood, and with the hair on the oven -- would be canine humanoid; werejackal; or gnoll</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>home session 9_1_1_2</p>\n<p>====================</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick perception check with advantage -- hears muffled cries, and then she flips down next to joan</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;her&nbsp; acrobatic expertise (aptitude, adroitness) leads polive to ask if flick can help fix something above the vents&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick tries to see into refrigerator door, but it was closed behind them.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros messages flick and says \"hey i think they're killing gnolls\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;drav has sidled casually up to carlos</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"Dwarves being dwarves, hanging out in entryways\" . drav asks carlos \"how are those rocks?\" carlos: \"rocks look great!\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez is trying to figure out where the four elements are within the room</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;hasn't had a sweet in 4 &frac12; years (just hard-tack)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez tries to fix the sink when I say that investigation check revealed it to be backed up</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive \"she ship is like a big toilet\" -- then tries to grab plunger</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez wrests away (20 dex), and poilve buys his explanation</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] fez: \"i'm pretty good at most things in life\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[7]</p>\n<p>---</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;Wuun tries to show Flick how it's done after Flick gets (6) PERFormance on jumping up out of the hole. (and DM says: \"either athletics or acrobatics; ACRO will determine how balletic / elegantly / harmonious ?/ lissomely / nimbly /&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;WUUN tries a backhandspring after walking down the steps (two-level)]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;makes it to ceiling of refrigerated area, then goes down butt first (tried two back-handsprings)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;WUUn is looking for FLICK (who's hiding) so WUUn can do a high-five, because she thinks they are both awesome</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[10]</p>\n<p>----</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez wants to know if anything about the water is changing. (dm: industrial strength; 10 ft. wide), 2 levels ; can't see behind to plumbing.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;brutalist / minimalist sink, with steel wool whorls&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive tries to get fez to come back over for the demo.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez does flourish with plunger to hand it like a sword</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;juniper is trying to get ethel to do tricks and not destroy everything</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] ethel trying to bury something? (or recover something?) from rock floor</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: \"is a death doctor the same thing as a forensic pathologist?\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos (jenny) shouts that they should make their way back</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] flick&nbsp; is worried about THAZ</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;trying to figure out if gnolls are inherently evil</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive spoons out sap into casting trays and takes them to purification oven , after which they'll work with it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;ethel and juniper make their way over to the entrance</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;vats are chest-level</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>home session 9_1_1_3</p>\n<p>====================</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[0]</p>\n<p>---</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] paros has HEIGHTENED SPELL and EMPOWERED SPELL @ third level&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros tries detect thoughts on Polive ?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros wondering if they will pay attention to the demo</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez is super into it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] fez: confidence outruns his abilities</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[X] CONFIDENCE</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros goes over to oven and turns it on max</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;INT controls = ok</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;STEALTH 19&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;ethel is whining and trying to get out into the tunnel</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;juniper \"in the three schools we have to co-seat with an Ethel. i do like her, but i'm tied to her at the hip\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;joan hears pained noises coming from the refrigerated area. tries to RIP IT OPEN.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;rip the metal door open -- everyone notices</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;ethel takes off to get to JOAN</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;PAROS uses his old reaction to slap FLICK.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[9]</p>\n<p>---</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[X] FLICK gets her goodberries from forest nightmare candy factories (wilderness proficiency)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[11] initiative</p>\n<p>---------------</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick readies action</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos can choose shape of weapon</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;uses Bless as a level 1 (3 creatures)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;ian \"domonkos catches on fire because he's a fucking vampire\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;PAROS, CARLOS, DRAV</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;FOLDULF dives into vat and disappears</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[vats allow them to pop up anywhere; something different will come up out of vat; or some kind of healing/bless]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>home session 9_1_1_4</p>\n<p>====================</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick:&nbsp; uses planar warrior and hits Ethel with his reaction, and ETHEL gets a reaction attack</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick: \"the real doing the most damage was the friends we made along the way\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[3]</p>\n<p>---</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: hearing carlos's blessing; \"seas be with me\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;doesn't know that he did that; doesn't know what happened</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;religion check, 11, calms down (goddess of tranquil sea), and +1 to next wisdom check</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros tells domonkos to get on his side of the oven</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;casts ray of frost on vat, turns it into a bit of a slushy</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;domonkos says: \"no, help, don't freeze these stupid vats. what's with you and fire and ice.\" just because all the things worked on back-mogh doesn't mean it will here</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez : \"can't prove it won't\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;joan: \"they are really cute\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive thinks : \"two of the sea ones?\" / deities</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: \"seaward just means 'towards the sea' \"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;RIHHILT has ian's glasses on. - hits Fez with a fire sphere&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[13]</p>\n<p>----</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;i go to bathroom</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;they start calling FOLDULF fol-dorf</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[15]</p>\n<p>----</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] JUNIPER casts mage armor \"flatuling blue shield of armor\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;casts magic missile (9 force) at Paros.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[17]</p>\n<p>----</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;joan's turn. she doesn't want to hurt ethel.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;she can see the two tied figures inside the fridge.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>home session 9_1_1_5</p>\n<p>====================</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;joan goes into a rage and uses her trident.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] background : gear head [5] dm \"oh, it might work!\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;nope, doesn't go into rage, lightning breath blasts out of free nostril, and tea kettle steam out of the release valve</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;ethel's \"Fragile, doglike, monster body\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;joan has betrayed her trust, even though she was coming to murder you</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;joan: \"i can't handle that, why are you doing this to me\"; just feel neutral and that like you've hurt her.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;Domonkos goes after Ethel with \"both his fangs\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez :\"instead of the usual one-fang attack vampires are known for\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] asymmetry is the name of the game</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;POLIVE turns towards Fez&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: \"doubt it!\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;polive hits him with a thunderwave or something (4 thunder), pushed 10 ft. back</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos tries to SHATTER the vats</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;thick viscous liquid spills out of broken vats. difficult terrain&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: \"is it grape?!\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] salted grape jerky</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: \"it's like drinking a raisin\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;rihhilt smashes up against the fall and falls down unconscious</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;drav sees that there's a giant drain at the bottom of the vat</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;massive plunger at the bottom of the vat</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;WUUN is pissed that Drav spilled the candy.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;runs over to DRAV</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;ECKS swoops down and starts attacking Ethel -- skin too think (2 inches)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] creature with hippo incisors</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[16]</p>\n<p>====</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;back to flick (2nd round of combat)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"for the record, fez looks confident\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"i ride the rippling (earth) waves; some of them i ride, some push me back\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] relate everything about fez to the sea</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick gets within 30 ft. of polive and marks for force damage</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>home session 9_1_1_6</p>\n<p>====================</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick his polive for 16 force damage -- smashes her into table, slumps onto ground, and pulls self up barely.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;carlos swings at WUUN.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;(can't heal them from this distance). 3+2 = 5 damage.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;WUUN: wondering if protecting the candy vats is worth it</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;terrifying that it's either \"protect the candy, or ... nothing\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;now that the candy is gone, defend its memory</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;Ethel tries to rip domonkos off her head</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;both get natural ones. collapse in greco-roman wrestling. covered in vat goo.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;Paros : readies action to BURNING HANDS juniper if she comes within view</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;gets 2 more sorcery points, so can cast it as empowered possibly.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] fez: sorcerers are like bank tellers, exchanging things</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] magic nickels like real nickels - if you melt down, worth less than nickel. (or ... more?)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;Juniper fires off more magic missiles at Drav (9 d)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;then goes roughing towards Ethel, gets hit by burning hands</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;smells like sausage cooked with pine chips</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;joan: sees LUM and (ripped white skullcap); female gnoll is attractive (and not even for a gnoll, just absolutely).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;joan: \"i don't want to talk to these people\" / swipe left</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"yes, there's stuff happening, are you good fighters?\" \"there's no one to help us recover\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;have been living off candy (LUM and CORATASH) - lum passes out</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;joan returns to the fight.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;sees that there is a tunnel leading further back</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;DOMONKOS licked some of fluid off; attacks ETHEL</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez takes 9 fire damage (from polive?)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>home session 9_1_1_7</p>\n<p>====================</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;drav tries magic missile -- like a cowards shoots them into juniper's back, who dies, slides up to ETHEL , who sees her dead person in front of her.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: \"burn spelled with a G?\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;WUUN (jake): considered RIHHILT and POLIVE more than siblings; FOLDULF is ?? ; you're feeling alone; ethel is getting massacred by domonkos and ecks. the thought of protecting the area is secondary to this kind of confusion.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick: \"you'll have to go through my force arrows unless you want to drop your weapons!\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] WUUN: \"it didn't have to be this way, we could have communed as candy and snackers!\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] carlos: \"i just wanted candy!\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;WUUN disengages and runs for drainage hole in vat; fez almost accidentally hits him with rapier (8 d); WUUN feels self surrounded by purplish black liquid; feel self carried away down claustrophobic (physically and emotionally) pipeline; the taste of it is comforting; you see these very flat flipper-like long, come up and grab you, and it feels like joining your family; they wrap around you and pull you deeper into the tunnel, and you black out.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;[x] i confirm that this isn't what Carlos saw coming up from a sandstone tunnel</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;ETHEL only one left up. still prone.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick goes up to stick the tiny, 12 foot beast . advantage.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"singular, punctuated squish sounds\" 14 damage.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;ETHEL attacked from the back.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[8]</p>\n<p>---</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;Carlos: prayer of healing (10 m ritual casting time)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;figure of FOLDULF climbs out of the drain, reaches out at fez, and flings some of the vat liquid.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;into medicine supply kit, bursts salve, grows out of it is huge fish, and then coalesces into human-fish form (ghostly white flat fins instead of hands, red streaks) -- recognize as figure of Cpt. Juna Marigold. staring with vacant eyes, double-blinks,&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"fez, is that you?\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: we ended on \"good\" terms (but shipwreck)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: \"juna is that you\"? \"you look terrible, you look like a fish\" : \"I suppose this is real bad carp-ma\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez: \"how do we fix? you always had the plans for this stuff\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;juna: \"been floating around like this, without memory\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;i had images of these fins in the blackness</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;staggers back and falls onto the ground</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;FOLDORF (now renamed) is passed out. \"what the foldulf\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick backs off ETHEL; e. is looking at dead body of juniper. DOMONKOS \"she seems distracted now; we could probably put her in a safe state of mind\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;animal handling: ETHEL leans up into Joan, and looks distraught; you think she might be trying to form another bond with you.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;two gnolls come out of the back:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;\"help us kill gnomes?\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;joan: \"flick, this sounds like a you thing\"\\</p>\n<p>home session 9_1_1_8</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;flick heads to RIHILT (\"rye-ull\")&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;paros samples things (purple liquid, sap)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez tries to use ointments (4 points) -- use it go get RIHHILT up -- look back at jar; the one that you knew was most efficacious was juna's. this salve is helpful, but not the main one that expertise has been structured around.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;fez religion check (4) : \"i must be great at making any kind of salve i set my mind to\"</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;get a job at a local hospital or infirmary&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[3] - session ends.</p>\n<p>-------------------</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp;nexnag was in a little pen the whole time.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>[10] - listened up through here</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>10-14 - skipped</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>14-end : me and debi talking</p>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"XpLK7ljzwJZBWyop","name":"Jaap Jansen","permission":{"default":0,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3},"folder":"HnsRctNEFA19GYLE","sort":400001,"flags":{},"content":"<div>For a point of origin, Sedlo forest sounds good to me. My gnome only has little strides and can't have gotten much further than 100 mi yet =)</div>\n<h2>Inner Conflict</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>If Garl is LG, are there conflicts with Jaap with being Chaotic Good?</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Garl Glittergold&nbsp;</h2>\n<div><strong>Symbol:&nbsp;</strong>gold nugget</div>\n<div><strong>Aspects:&nbsp;</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Concerning my interaction with my god, I have not thought this out superhard yet, but no time as the present. As a cleric of Garl in a forest, I don't think there should exist a big structure to Garl in the community; instead we honor him by living by his code of conduct.</li>\n<li>In terms of interaction with Garl, Jaap would automatically have responded to kobold raids on his turf, but seeking them out in their own caves was directed by Garl in a vision (not a dream) around sunrise.</li>\n<li>For some reason, Garl has not been able to help Jaap much with the search for his sister, Jantien.</li>\n<li>Jaap has been using Augury to figure out very generally where to travel to, but has not found any clues yet. The divination spell doesn't quite fit his purpose much I think, and Jaap tried Locate Person once, but did not get any direction. I guess Jaap could have 'Auguried' his way to a predestined meeting with the rest of the party; this might be a start of figuring out how to get Jaap connected to the party.</li>\n</ul>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>"}
{"_id":"Y70RWpRzhOKFVakF","name":"052. He's a man of refinement.","permission":{"default":0,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3,"9Z2Zfs8yQYNI02Bm":3},"folder":"nEIZOAbBi8YZmJDe","sort":1100000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Jean-Luc</h2>\n<p>Jean-Luc, slightly trailing his companions as they marched towards the Triggered Beta inn, found himself enticed by a spicy nostalgic scent -- Kriobolitan sausages! It had been weeks since he had any real taste of home, and though enjoying the adventure and happy to be running from the troubles of Kreabolois, the southern contents of Marshbout really ought to take some cooking lessons. He approached the food cart from which the odor seemed to be wafting, and, after bragging about his mother's culinary expertise to the vendor and expressing his eagerness for the day his mother's secret recipe for the meaty delicacies would be passed down to him, he gladly purchased one and took a hearty bite. The sausage was spiced well, if a bit undercooked, but as the remnants of his bite traveled down his throat a faint metallic aftertaste lingered on his tongue. Within moments, a powerful narcotic washed over his body. He became faintly aware of three figures wearing decidedly quaint masks advancing on him and though he turned to confront them they moved too quickly. His balance failed him and he was quickly restrained. Jean-Luc attempted to alert his adventuring companions; even though he could feel the effort of his shouts, however, no sounds issued from his mouth. Just before his vision went black, he saw the food cart proprietor grip the trolley and toddle frantically back into a dim alleyway.</p>\n<p>He awoke feeling as though years had passed, having been beset in the interim by claustrophobic dreams in which he prowled around a strangely familiar city (Kreepolopas? Krabopolis?). He wandered through dim, labyrinthine streets populated by figures from his childhood -- a baker who'd always had a sweet bun ready for him; a friendly councilwoman of the ward who vouched his mother for a loan; one of his charter-school chums from whom he'd first begun to learn lock-picking; a witty, troublesome redheaded daughter of a shopkeeper -- none of whose names he could recall. That girl, though, she had been something special to him. What was her name? Laura? Lara? Laria? Alara? Alaria? Elaria? Pelaria? The name stuck fast in his mind: he couldn't think of any other name, any other word, any other world. Just Pelaria. Pelaria. Pelaria.</p>\n<p>\"Good. You're up.\" Jean-Luc looked around, but the smell hit him first. Horse. He was in a stable. In a stall. There was still some horse shit on the fresh straw covering the floor, so he knew that his \"accommodations\" had been made up somewhat hastily. Or someone had a very particular idea about discomfort. As his eyes adjusted to the dim light, he suspected that both suppositions could be true: at a glance, the tack on the wall looked to be quite expensive: the saddle alone would fetch almost 100 gp from a generous fence. The rest of the accoutrements screamed show horse rather than a working beast. The fog from the narcotic lingered, without any of the pleasant afterglow he would have expected if it had been one of the ones he&rsquo;d take willingly. Absent any other options he focused again on the saddle; there was a monogram on it, and he didn't need some magic darkvision (some of his companions had that right? Where was that elf when he needed her?) to guess that it started with a \"T\" and ended with a \"V.\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Indeed, as his mind raced through all the possible meanings of those initials, he noticed a flash of light coming from a reflective surface at about eye level by the frame of the stall door. The object was immediately retracted, and Tishara Vernix, purported head of the Hat Baskets, casually slotting a jointed mirror into a loop on her middle belt, stepped into view. Her forest-green, almost satiny hair created an eerie moir&eacute; effect in the shadowy stable and hung in a thick braid over a well-starched, ruffed-neck white blouse and a dark brown riding jacket. The jacket, and her riding pants, were embroidered in the same, clashing green, blue, and white beadwork he'd seen on the guild's dagger. The pants looked rumpled, and he suspected that she'd just rode in, probably urgently. Whether that had to do with just him was anyone's guess.</p>\n<p>\"I let it be known to your ... consociates ... that the longer we go without the Ledger of Pathytus, the more they'll have to learn to do their own accounting. Of your body parts.\" Her delivery left something to be desired, and Jean-Luc noticed, before she could hide it, disappointment with herself, and perhaps a touch of a distracted mind.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Ugh. Amateurs&rdquo; Jean Luc thought.&nbsp; He hated taking hostages. It was almost always a small child for maximum leverage. You needed to communicate with the family, arrange a drop off and in the interim you had a blubbering, and loud, quarry to contend with. In addition while the noble class deserved to be separated from their wealth, children ought to be off limits.&nbsp; Even if you were successful the family usually sent mercenaries after you in an understandable act of retribution. &ldquo;Far easier to just steal the payment directly&rdquo;, he thought wistfully as he settled in and waited to see if his new companions were as loyal as he hoped.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"YoIybo3s6BETOYNC","name":"Commentary on the Diaschizdein Glaucous","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"Cec7aiKp7sFrzQHB","sort":200000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>How the sap angels are able to split from the zorbwood and their relation to the symbol of seven winged eyes. It's possible for the wood to act as a teleportation circle into the material plane for someone who otherwise wouldn't be able to get into that plane.</p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-e573132c-7fff-62f7-3930-98637ff2a355\"></span></p>\n<h4 id=\"hfwylmott\">— H.F. Wylmott</h4>\n<p>First appeared: s.17</p>"}
