{"_id":"cz2OkQ4KPeqpQxdg","name":"thoughts","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"NdtTfwZe9YTsCoFv","sort":600000,"flags":{},"content":"<div><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-5a727226-7fff-4da3-8c6c-b3f19f57b149\"></span></div>\n<h2>regular</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>people named after the gods or heroes or emperors, like you'd see in greece or something</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>dream</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">grollowers</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">petting grouth</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">tropical possell pits</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>creatures</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>lol, a David-litch -- flick: is shoemaker a druid-litch. is that his phylactery?</li>\n<li>creatures born on treestumps\n<ul>\n<li>- becoming a mighty oak (\"the mighty elk\" of Fez!)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>- Flick believes Snav to be a functionary that has unsavory ties, like Molotov (Snav Snifter)</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- --><!-- --><!-- -->\n<h1 id=\"necromancerandgraal\">necromancer and graal</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Joan wants to</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>have a lot of degrees</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>but have her not know anything</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>also she is very strong</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>be able to meet a cardi b-type earnest lady</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Joan should be able to deal with this necromancer, but can't. but she's so strong - her certifications: Indiana Jones Ancestor -</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;!-- --&gt;\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>somehow flick ports them somewhere?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>FACTION: Fang of the Besh'ti (the ancient Girallon guardians) - Graal's arm eaten by Oklmuk didn't heal correctly, and she came to this necromancer on her way back to the homeland.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>FENIENDUM: what is her deal? oh yeah, part of the fang of the besh'ti. collecting these zombies to use them (fang is just a metonym : they want the whole body) - background: her sister Gaduul married her ex-lover Hautesse, and now their mother, (Leathan \"Knottybones\"), dotes on Gauduul and her new psychic twins (Mamonas and Nychtbouris)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Nugget was discovered in one of the archaeological sites being dug by the Seomra archaeologists, but abandoned after being forced out by FENIENDUM.&nbsp;</p>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Drav: spell ink from Rotrude or Hiero's blue boils</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: [INT] shipwreck happened at night, so how does he remember seeing Abz&ucirc;</div>\n<div>- Fez: [INT] can remember something about the Teallacht mentioned by Abz&ucirc;</div>\n<div>- learns the Deep Undersea language from Abz&ucirc;, not Ulimara</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick: foil ranger (super laid back; never strings bow; always wants to slow things down and look around)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: spells like Befuddlement</div>\n<div>- unerring strike</div>\n<div>- confounding strike</div>\n<div>- more people that want to torture with him but present an obstacle in some way.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc: spell Blacksteel</div>\n<div>- Rogue: Perished features since interaction with Marjorie</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<h2 id=\"futureideas\">future ideas</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>- they actually go to an \"Undead Horror Show\" (how Fez described Undead Rotrude)</li>\n<li>- in-universe rapper \"tood arts\" (from 2Dartz)</li>\n<li>- Carlos: genie warlock -- tobolux / or great old one warlock</li>\n<li>- Unseen Servant</li>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d77ce6c0-7fff-61d3-c0dd-d31ff8ba9439\">background &rarr; rapid and unexpected change in habits for the</span><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d77ce6c0-7fff-61d3-c0dd-d31ff8ba9439\">&nbsp;worse</span></li>\n<li>Drav never examined the finishing stones on the ancient walls around Sandford: what do those rocks hold in, and what do they keep out?</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->"}
{"_id":"dgQ8uxoLK60LRyGF","name":"Bench of the Two Otters","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"vefgbkd0YcstUxkK","sort":200000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>On this bench sit the abstract forms of two otters, carved from local sandstone, leaning protectively towards one another. It appears that the empty sockets of their eyes once held gems or rare stones.</p>"}
{"_id":"e2KLy5BcyoYJwryN","name":"Nerch","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"wf40lADkdvhEIKuG","sort":300000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>nerch’s deal is that she was part of a cult, so she can connect to vengeance through that, only they were never able to take the torture into their own hands, and nerch was a “mundane” child (unlike the mutants like Urek, which were thought of as conduits to the gods, and for this they were punished) and they would have to isolate themselves during periods of the month? when their magic seeped out of them and they couldn’t control it or do magic with it (and then she learns that that helps define her, but isn’t essential, to the definition, of a magician) . but the leader of the cult was — it was a baphomet type; or at least the twisted one (maybe it was the twisted one).</p>"}
