{"_id":"eCHxw4Y9C5XzlqWf","name":"031. Thereby, smoke","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"3raMqXjxKE8cvKwn","sort":433229,"flags":{},"content":"<h1>alternate titles</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>\"Which one is ... 'shithead'\"&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<h1 id=\"recap\">Recap</h1>\n<div>[not available]</div>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h1 id=\"transcript\">Transcript</h1>\n<div>- Shoemaker dumps a double-handful of goodberries onto the ground, walks to the nearest table and puts the vase full of earth there.</div>\n<div>- Meanwhile, Flick is rolling around on the ground, trying to put out a fire.</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: I thought that, being a wood-elf, you would have been circumspect enough to look around for the source of your magic. You just thought it was coming to you from nowhere in particular?</div>\n<div>- Flick: I don&rsquo;t know what you want me to say; that&rsquo;s kind of how magic works.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: Well maybe for wizards, but not for plane-walkers like you. You&rsquo;re going to have to reconcile yourself to this.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- (As Shoemaker has a hard time getting both Flick and Fez in the circumference of the vase's effect) Flick: my flailing around has paid off!</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- The jar of earth starts to tremble and soil spills over the top, down the table, and starts to engulf Shoemaker. She dissolves into a hilly lump of flesh. Resonating out of the jar: &lt;&lt;Return to what you are&gt;&gt; Fez for a moment feels himself start to collapse into a fleshmound, but he shakes his head and steels himself and the vision disappears.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- (Flick remembers that Onfalon told her a long time ago that Shoemaker had spirits in her basement which people came to pray to.)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-Luc goes to stab Shoemaker.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: why are you going after me? My concern is with this spoiled ranger who keeps grabbing things as if from a void.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-Luc: as weird as they are, these people are my friends.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: So you&rsquo;re a little thief too?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-Luc: Little? I&rsquo;d like to think I'm 'medium' to 'renowned'.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: Are we talking about height or notoriety?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-Luc: Why not both?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: why does it always have to be about height?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-Luc: semantically arguing with a demon-bear is not one of the things I imagined doing.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: your extra-little cleric friend over here could tell you that.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick: she&rsquo;s talking about Carlos.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: Yeah, the dwarf. Compared to you, Fez, he&rsquo;s a giant. With that robe, it&rsquo;s hard to tell gender, in case I used the wrong one right there.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: You&rsquo;ve been backpedalling like this since you got here.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: TBH this isn&rsquo;t my natural habitat. I&rsquo;m used to the woods.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: You still have to be better.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: I do my best. What are you saying I don&rsquo;t do well enough? You all are the ones with privilege. Ganging up on me in a dungeon. This feels like a zoo enclosure.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: YOU came in HERE. &hellip; This is going to get GRIZZLY.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: I&rsquo;m not a black, polar, or grizzly bear. Are you another cleric? You don&rsquo;t appear to have a deity you dedicate yourself to?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: That&rsquo;s a solid maybe. But this fight is going to be a LOSS for you. You came to talk about goodberries, but we&rsquo;re going to say goodbye. Also you&rsquo;re a metaphysical construct that doesn&rsquo;t exist outside this dungeon.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: Aren&rsquo;t we all? When before have you disappeared into an ineluctable dungeon with the face of a god on the floor.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hieronymus takes a flying leap onto Shoemaker&rsquo;s back and attacks with his Karbunqle staff. He smashes his hand against the kettle-pot after smashing her over the head with his staff. Hieronymus skips out of there, but Shoemaker catches him in the heel with her greataxe.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: So many of you are in robes. It&rsquo;s hard to tell with the body ends and the robe starts. I don&rsquo;t wear clothes so it&rsquo;s difficult to figure out the geometry.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hieronymus: I plan on wearing your pelt when we kill you.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: Be careful my pelt doesn&rsquo;t wear &hellip; you &hellip; after you put it on.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hieronymus: Well I&rsquo;ve always wanted a good hair-shirt.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: Definitely don&rsquo;t take my helmet! It&rsquo;s just here for decoration. And it even looks stupid!</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick [Insight 18] Shoemaker doesn&rsquo;t want you to take the helmet.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-Luc continues to debate what kind of 12-dimensional kettlepot bear chess Shoemaker is playing.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick intuits that this helmet has something to do with the fire suppression compulsion, and her ability to invoke the soil spirit.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez knows that the helmet needs to come off. For no reason.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick: &ldquo;Since the dawn of time, bears have not worn helmets on their heads.&rdquo;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez remembers Ponderous bears, Lugubrious bears, (halflings consider themselves so entertaining that other entities that couldn&rsquo;t speak common were considered boring); Insipid bears (all from childhood books about bears)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- it is speaking to you, and with the accent of the lead singer of a band, so as a halfling you might even feel a little affiliation with them.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Drav shoots a ray of frost that misses Shoemaker, but adorns the vat of earth with some frosty tips.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: Will it take us to Flavortown? [investigation explosion of 2]: Flavortown will commence shortly.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- the raw smell of city earth when construction crews have dug up a sub basement.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick has &ldquo;put out the fire&rdquo;, nor is she obsessed with kindling. Flick remembers knocking over Drav and shouting at her&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick [perception 16] can tell there is something odd about the active radius around the vat of earth.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez is slightly spacey to start with, thinking about how clever he is most of the time; he might have sneezed at the melty-flesh vision.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick avoids using planar warrior; throws a hunters mark at Shoemaker. &ldquo;You made a mistake that&rsquo;s just the first in a long line of mistakes!&rdquo;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: I&rsquo;m here as a warning to you! (Flick shoots her twice; nocks a third arrow)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick: &ldquo;You can fuck off, or we can keep doing this.&rdquo;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: I don&rsquo;t know why you&rsquo;re so resistant to being helped, as far as your only true powers are concerned.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick narrows her eyes.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker turns to Fez: And what did YOU just say? (presumably about flavor town). Frazzled by Flick&rsquo;s arrows, she&rsquo;s unable to swing her axe properly. However, she&rsquo;s close enough to the vase to shake it like a delicate maraca in Fez&rsquo;s direction. Closer to the epicenter, Fez feels his body start to come unglued, and then snaps back into stability.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-Luc successfully puts together a Snav Snifter (red dragon burp, gremlo&rsquo;s indigestion? gremlo&rsquo;s heartburn? bigby&rsquo;s &ldquo;i ate too many spicy wings [spicy wings are angel wings torn off in hell and eaten by demons]&rdquo;), which he finishes and shouts: &ldquo;Fez, get out of the way!&rdquo;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: when you say &ldquo;Watch out&rdquo; i can hear that too.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez attacks with whip, hits, runs and hops up on the bar.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick: &ldquo;when i&rsquo;m not rolling around &hellip;&rdquo;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: &ldquo;Oh yeah, why don&rsquo;t you feel a bit warm right now?&rdquo;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick: &ldquo;No, as a wood elf I know when things are on fire. and i&rsquo;m not on fire in the middle of a damp dungeon underground.&rdquo;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: Haven&rsquo;t you ever heard of coal-mine fires? In any case, you should still feel guilt about the way you abuse your magic.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick: I&rsquo;m gonna take all your Goodberries after we explode your corpse.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: There&rsquo;s not a finite supply.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick: Then why are you mad about it?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: because you open yourself up to retaliation each time you grab one from elsewhere. You don&rsquo;t remain safe when you use your portal spells. &mdash; no snappy retort, eh?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hieronymus does what he thinks is whisper telepathically to his friends. &ldquo;Guys, I know this bear&rsquo;s weakness. If I take her kettle off, her brains will be exposed underneath.&rdquo; &mdash; He takes out his bagpipes and thinks back to the first song he learned in the monastery: the bare bear-plains national anthem. (which is the only song he can play). there&rsquo;s a heavily orchestrated version ; but hieronymus is playing the hot cross buns learner&rsquo;s version. he starts to play and looks over to see if Shoemaker is reacting in any way, like taking her helmet off (out of respect)&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- He plays really terribly but realizes that no one else can hear his telepathy; it might be that tapping into the whisper walls is using all his telepathic energy, or nobody heard him (not getting service down here). but he still thinks he&rsquo;s telepathic. He plays so badly that it angers Shoemaker.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: this is like the sounds of the elks mating in the winter. which i hate. everything else mating, though, i love.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude (shouting) : did i hear that it was damp up there? it is quite wet down here as well; we should consider uniting the spaces in an aquatic park of entertainment. and murder.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: I would love send you to sea world.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: to see which world?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: the world in which you don&rsquo;t exist.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: I feel like that is a logical contradiction. yes they never did teach you logic at the monastery, did they? that&rsquo;s reserved for those 200 years old or older.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: but i&rsquo;m like&hellip; at least 300.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: I thought I was at least 300. But &hellip; then why didn&rsquo;t you ever take logic classes?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: oh that&rsquo;s right, because we&rsquo;re twins.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Yes, indeed, we are born of the same mother</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: yes, like all elves at the monastery. don&rsquo;t you remember when we all hatched at the same time?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: of course; elves hatch from eggs. you made sure you use my hypertrophied fingernails and toenails to chip open the egg for yourself. it&rsquo;s where my obsession with manicures comes from. i never want to be instrumentalized again. but you have no problem instrumentalizing others.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: i seem to be having a bit of a problem with my instrument. once it&rsquo;s fixed &hellip; things are going to go down.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: did i hear the bare bear-plain national anthem?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: i was, yes</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: i must tell you that the bears have overthrown their nationalist ambitions, and since have joined together as a consensus-based democracy of bears.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: well if you know so much, why don&rsquo;t you come up here and play it yourself?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: is that an invitation which aims to dispel the fact that i have been turned from the doughty cleric up there?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: yeah, it&rsquo;s like &hellip; a detente.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Ok well i will see you shortly.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: i definitely can wait, because i hate you.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: did someone say Snav? he&rsquo;s well-known around here.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick thinks back to Joan, and wonders if she made it back to Marshbout or Cressida.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Drav (Angela has left; through Ian) casts &hellip; ? fire bolt.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker, a fire-retardant creature, only takes 1/2 damage. -- Perhaps on a ponderous bear that might have worked, but some of us spend our entire lives putting out fires in the woods.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Eldar goes to re-tag Drav to start the game up again, doing a bunch of damage. \"Drav, don&rsquo;t you remember? we were never supposed to tell your new parents about me. I was one of the reasons that you were forced out of your birth home. doesn&rsquo;t this ring a bell?\"</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick reaches out and envelops Shoemaker in an energy field, and tries to explode it in a point. for damage.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- retreats out to table, and then tries a called shot to try to knock the kettle off her head.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- The kettle falls off Shoemaker&rsquo;s head and clangs against the floor.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: I gave you a lot to think about, eh?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez, standing on the bar, gets his legs cut out from under him as Shoemaker rushes up with her great axe.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: I&rsquo;m too tired to go back and get my helmet. unrelated, my ass, with its callouses, is the toughest part of my body.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-Luc repositions himself and throws a Snav&rsquo;s Snifter, which explodes on Shoemaker. Jean-Luc sprints over and picks up the kettle. &ldquo;Got your stupid helmet motherfucker!&rdquo;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: you&rsquo;re right &mdash; so you should just leave it where it is. if you&rsquo;re carrying something stupid that makes you a stupid.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-Luc [intimidation 15] (&ldquo;what&rsquo;s the equivalent of giving the bear the middle finger?&rdquo;) attempts to goad Shoemaker</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: &ldquo;I wouldn&rsquo;t put that on if I were you; but i&rsquo;m gonna be over there in a second anyway and there&rsquo;s not much you can do about it&rdquo;. Jean-Luc pantomimes huge jaw hands like &ldquo;blah blah blah&rdquo;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-Luc hears behind him the soft sifting noise of dirt behind him; the vase is erupting with soil and covers his boots and climbs up his body in a mound. he turns into a creature of pure physical flesh; a gelatinous pyramid; as the dirt recedes ; (from the outside he looks normal).&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- afraid for at least 1 minute with a DC 17 Charisma throw.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez heals himself.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: I bet you too think that ability to heal yourself comes from nowhere?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: pass. you&rsquo;re talking nonsense.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: i wanted to have a sophisticated conversation about your belief system. &mdash; shoemaker bites Fez, and he doesn&rsquo;t slip on goo. but her saliva looks like normal saliva, not marjorie&rsquo;s greenish-white saliva.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: i want to play one of my favorite bear games. i killed a bear when i was only 3. and he takes out darts to shoot them.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: hieronymus, i knew you were a murderer: you&rsquo;ve been killing bears and bars and elves. and fish.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: well obviously i didn&rsquo;t kill a bear when i was three; i was still in the egg-womb with you.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: I was under the impression we counted ages after we hatched. i would rather not have to think about abortions, which are an egg-layer&rsquo;s right to choose.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: not in Marshbout it&rsquo;s not.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude (getting frazzled for some reason): well &mdash; marshbout is a large place &mdash; and &mdash; has a diversity of opinions (perhaps she&rsquo;s been wrestling with her pro-choice views after growing up as a monk)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: we can talk politics later. i&rsquo;m not exactly sure where you are at the moment.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: i&rsquo;m downstairs; i was just speaking with Eldar. a very very powerful little lady. i&rsquo;m not sure you know the extent of her hidden powers.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: there is no escape.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: well, i _have_ made my way out of the monastery. or we can see each other in a moment up there?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: no, i have &hellip; an appointment.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: oh, and it&rsquo;s covered? what is it for?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: no, dental is not.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: probably all the rich fatty and sugary urban fare you&rsquo;ve been eating. if you adhered to the dietary restrictions of the monastery it would just be grasses and natural plants and fruits.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: if you had any sense, you would know that i&rsquo;m going to get my teeth drilled. because i desire the pain.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: well have you considered dilettantes, because it would be more torturesome?</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: but the professional knows exactly where to poke and prod</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: i suppose the difficulty is when they get so wrapped up in their technique&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: my dentist is a true maniac. he has no scruples whatsoever.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude. a rare combination indeed. i must offer you all the worst, then.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: if you&rsquo;ll excuse me, i&rsquo;m in the middle of a game of darts now</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: by all means, throw the darts as hard as you may into your own extremities, as we play darts.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- both of Hiero&rsquo;s darts hit the bear; &mdash; Bear&rsquo;s eye! and he shoots directly for her eyes.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Shoemaker: sometimes it&rsquo;s important to see what&rsquo;s hidden, but this really hurts.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero kills her very slowly. He hops onto her, and presses the darts deeper and deeper into her brain through her eyes. (thinking he&rsquo;s using time-manipulating magic) -- everyone else sees him shoot the darts, which go into random parts of her body (shoulder and ribs) but Hiero runs up anyway and smashes her eyes with his open palms. &ldquo;Time-Manipulating Magic!&rdquo;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez and Hieronymus [DC 17 charisma check] . Hieronymus also turns into a flesh mound. might actually be one of his dreams as a flagellant, to be nothing but exposed nerves and muscles; unable to move.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Eldar&rsquo;s creepy whispers to Drav don&rsquo;t go unnoticed, and Drav shrieks in pain as Eldar reaches out to grab her hand again.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Eldar: If you wouldn&rsquo;t try to keep me hidden inside of you, I can promise that it wouldn&rsquo;t be so painful when I emerge. &mdash; the putrid rot of drav&rsquo;s flesh is evident.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Drav disengages and runs back behind Carlos.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick takes the opportunity to shoot at Eldar, this poor little dwarf spirit. Eldar becomes transparent and disappears as she whispers to Drav &ldquo;don&rsquo;t allow them to keep suppressed within you what is your greatest power!&rdquo;&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick tries to shatter the vase with a regular arrow. the arrow pings harmlessly off it, despite its appearing to be made of glass.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Drav: i think it has some kind of magical protection on it. Carlos is my best friend. (Drav and Carlos hug each other). We may need to cast dispel magic on it.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude shouts: Which one is &hellip; &ldquo;shithead&rdquo; ?</div>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"egapeyslkcUY0EaC","name":"006. [Untitled]","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"7FU7CCEBg8xZrzdi","sort":300000,"flags":{},"content":"<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Session</strong>: &sect;006&nbsp;</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Played</strong>: November 23, 2019 (2019-11-23)</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Day 2 (cont.)</strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Level 2</strong></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><hr /></div>\n<h1 dir=\"ltr\">Recap</h1>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-0ddf54f9-7fff-565e-67a1-56dc440dee52\"></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">a chat with Forlig &mdash; towards Kulgmark &mdash; extracting Fez &mdash; into the caves&mdash; Paros heads the other way &mdash; sounds of distress &mdash; the chamber &mdash; a long slog &mdash; possession! &mdash; victory &mdash;Domonkos makes a plea</p>\n<h1 dir=\"ltr\">Transcript</h1>\n<p>[n/a]</p>\n<section>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">[1:36 - 2:10]</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">forlig has been rescued, shouting to save Fez (doesn&rsquo;t know who it is) ; everyone jumping down the hole, dealing with BLACKNESS,&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">[2:10]</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">in the midst of fighting the surn, surn-dwarves, and seeing that vampire is barely conscious</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Carlos leaves early and Ian takes over</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</section>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"enEUbqqwDyTurklC","name":"033. [Untitled]","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"3raMqXjxKE8cvKwn","sort":433278,"flags":{},"content":"<div>2020-06-21 (June 21, 2020)</div>\n<div>very end of Day 9, long rest, Day 10 to early afternoon</div>\n<div>level 7</div>\n<div><hr></div>\n<h1 id=\"recap\">Recap</h1>\n<div>Long rest under Xanthuc Temple. A deal with Vek. Fez can't fake it. Cyrowan, the reluctantly silent squire. Up into the sunlight and towards the Big Hedge. Absquatulating with Aphelia? Shut in by Seomra.</div>\n<div></div>\n<h1 id=\"transcript\">Transcript</h1>\n<div><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Flick’s apology meant quite a lot to me.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Vek, do you remember a younger me when you knew Shoemaker.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Shoemaker was more like the curator of a museum with a lot of travelling exhibits. Occasionally we’d get spirits from overseas. There were elves that came through there, sometimes druids; we did get a lot of creatures, hermits, ascetics. As an elf you’re …</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: I’m 75. (So, a young adult)</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: I don’t remember you coming into that basement, and I’m fairly sure we’ve not interacted before this.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Do you remember (Lupenna’s description) [Bad Persuasion role]</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: I certainly do get a lot of werecreatures ,lycanthropes and things. It’s rumored that I can cure that disease. It takes more than the power I have, because that’s an agreement made with the natural cycles — almost behind the creature’s back. I largely allow people to look inside themselves. I can offer certain remediations to an unwilling shapechanger. It is possible.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: You may be with us longer than you intend to be.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Just any place outside should do to dump me in! And a glassblower with 50-60 years of training in order to properly break down the vase.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Was this part of the agreement, guys?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Jean-luc: It seems like a thing we’d agree to.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Do you remember when we were trying to liberate Aphelia from Seomra so we could return the music to the Peryton? Where did that end up?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Jean-luc: I’m just along for the ride, baby.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Someone had their abilities sucked out of them? That sounds like precisely what they may have directed you here for. It’s one of my talents to reintegrate the separated flesh and spirit, just as I can separate them.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: What would you need to help us out with this?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: You’re right I don’t do things for free; but as part of the intervention; I could certainly help with Jean-luc’s increasing alcoholism. I don’t know if the whole surprise intervention thing works; he’d have to be a little bit on board.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: I’m not sure that’s a problem that needs solving.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Typically I get to know people so well that I can gain knowledge that is useful to me; it is sufficient , kind of a pay what you will situation. I’m glad to accept donations.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick:We’ve gained a spirit therapist with the voice of A’Leh “The Goon” Kihs</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">When Vek speaks, it unintentionally spits bits of soil out of the lidless vase. Flick covers the lid with the mildly sticky fizzlecyst webbing, forgoing the use of a hammock spied in a backroom. Survival and perception checks indicate to Fez and Flick that there could be an entity in the subbasement’s pool. If it hasn’t come up by now it probably won’t. If the door is barred, they should be safe. Flick has lingering anxiety about smoldering wood, and scurries about stamping out any charred pieces of wood.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">[Long Rest commences]</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Jean-luc thinks to himself that he enjoys a good drink, and maybe hits the bottle harder than others, but recently he’s started to doubt whether or not he’s a verified alcoholic.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Fez [Wis save] Abzu had mentioned something about the Talleacht; while dreaming, these tall pale humanoid creatures, known from childhood stories describing ghouls or ghasts; look like they have gills and webbing. A nightmare of a few of these creatures wandering up from the sub basement pool (still green pool with algae on top), algae covers them like strands; they make their way up the stairs and come stand before you.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Talleacht. Fez! Why aren’t you coming for us? Why aren’t you saving us?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: I don’t know who you are.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Talleacht: Fez! Seek out the Talleacht. We are the Gormflaith. Why have you abandoned your fellow sailors?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">Fez startles awake, and they disappear.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Vengeance [Con save fail] CON and CHA decrease by three due to the Boils spreading. He wakes up in the middle of the night shivering from a fever; the neuropathy is worse; the boils have started to spread across his body; and he’s having trouble breaking.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I think i know what the problem is. I have to go downstairs and take a dip. I used to swim every day in the icy ponds of Cromfldldor; that’s how I felt my best self; and I haven’t felt my best self since then. I just need a nice refreshing swim, so I’m going to pop down there and do a few laps if you fellas don’t mind.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Well don’t let me stop you.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Before you go some of those boils look pretty — uhf. Do you mind if I put a salve on them?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Well, they do hurt. it’d be nice if you could pop them like a bubble wrap.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: It’s going to burn a little (but it actually burns a lot)</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Bring it on, brother.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Fez brings out a primarily alcohol-based salve and then “heals disease.” The boils subside somewhat, and the delicious warm feeling of burning alcohol spreads throughout the wound, and he regains 1 points each of CON and CHA.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Well perhaps I don’t need that swim after all.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: It’s an excellent salve; I made it myself</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Could you give me the recipe?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: I think I remember what it was, but it requires a still and the necessary amount of sailor’s grog.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: That I'm afraid I don’t have. I’d have to ask Jean-luc, our drunkard friend.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: He does know how to put it away, doesn’t he.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I’m not sure he “knows how”</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Jean-luc is over in the corner sleeping soundly. Fez [makes DC 15 wisdom check with nat 20?], while applying the salve, his fingers feel strange and rubbery for a minute, but as he continues to rub it into the gross boils, he explains it to himself as having to do with how disgusting Vengeance’s skin is.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: On second thought, maybe I’ll dip my toe in the water and see how it feels.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Vengeance makes his way downstairs, Flick quietly tracking him, while the sounds of a flute issue from the bar. Vengeance plays a horrible screwing racket on his bagpipes. Vengeance makes it to the pool which emits a lurid and noxious green light. The pool is almost 100 feet long, and the room is entirely visible due to the glow. As Vengeance gets down to the pool, he sees, standing 30 feet away, a figure of a teenage boy, wearing a dark green robe over tattered hide armor.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: I’m looking for Sir Master Fezziwig Hornswoggle!</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Vengeance plays his mournful nightswimming theme on his bagpipes. [nat 20?] .&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Are you saying he’s dead? Your bagpipe playing conveys so much, even your name!</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I was hoping to take a solitary swim, and you’re harshing my buzz, so if you could kind of scram, little boy.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Yes, I’ve been told I’m always getting in the way of people. Is the body of Lord Fez somewhere that I could still view it?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Since when did he become a lord?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: I’m not sure of his title, but I know that he’s renowned throughout the world?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I think he’s just upstairs.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: How should I prepare myself to see him? Is he in a casket, or a mausoleum?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I think he’s just having a drink up there in the bar. He’s definitely still alive.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: why were you playing such a sad dirge for him.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: That was just for my swimming ritual.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: OHHH! Well can i sidle past you here?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I’ve already changed into my bathing costume made of sharp and spiny hair.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Why do you have the hairs pointing inwards towards yourself?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I sometimes like to do it that way; it provides better insulation.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: And what’s going on with your hands? It looks like a dead person’s skin.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: No, that’s just my normal hands…</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: I’m sorry, I shouldn’t be so judgmental. I’ll get out of your way — the water’s quite tepid.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Vengeance dips his toe in to discover the water is room temperature.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Little boy, do you know any freezing spells, something to take the water temperature down a bit?</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Cyrowan’s eyes roll back in his head.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: [deep voice] Ye [regular voice] s I do have something like that. What would you like frozen?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Maybe a swimming lane?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: It’s really just a cube this big.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: FINE I’ll just paddle around in circles.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Vengeance [Arcana fail] is distracted by a rebar pole in the wall; meanwhile Cyrowan creates a five foot cube of ice just under Vengeance’s feet floating in the pool.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Will this do for you? If you give me a minute or so I could cover more of a line for you?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Ok, here goes.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Vengeance puts on his splintery wooden goggles and jumps into the pool. The water chills quickly near to the ice cube; it does get satisfactorily cold within a few minutes. Meanwhile, Cyrowan, making his way up the stairs fitfully, sneaks surreptitious glances back at Vengeance.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Come on in everybody, the water’s terrible?</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Vengeance’s voice is so quiet that it doesn’t even reverberate back to him — has his larynx frozen up, as had been his intent? Flick makes it back to the room before Cyrowan. Carlos is praying fervently, and Jean-luc is slumped over the table.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Sorry to wake you up, bud.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Did you make breakfast?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Not yet, but something came out of the radiant pool downstairs and is asking about you. I would bet it’s the same kind of creature as the ones disguised as people from our past. Fez leaps up, grabbing weapons and armor. Without waking the dwarves, Flick moves the upturned table on which Drav and Carlos are sleeping. Flick positions herself behind Fez but in the limits of his aura. Jean-luc is still sleeping behind the bar, as far as possible from the door, in the hammock.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">They see the pale, tow-headed figure, black-eyebrowed, unarmed figure of Cyrowan, in tattered leather armor, poke his head around the door frame.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan (taking a knee and bowing his head in front of Fez): Lord Sir Fezziwig Hornswoggle, it’s such an honor to meet you!</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Just call me ‘Sir Fezziwig Hornswoggle’</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Yes, whatever you desire, of course!</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: And what is your name?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: My name? It’s hardly worth mentioning. The name of one so lowly as myself …</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Nice to meet you, ‘It’s-Hardly-Worth-Mentioning’</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Oh, sir, quite a wit on you! It’s one of the reasons I’ve sought you out over the land, high low east west top bottom</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: But your name…</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: It’s Cyrowan sir c-y-r-o-w-a-n</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: I have very little use for letters</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Oh yes, a lack of need for letters is one of the signs of a great knight, how could I forget?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Why have you sought me out, as great as I am.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: I wish to become your squire. Precisely because of your reputation. I wish to become one who’s skilled in the martial arts like yourself and do wonderful things.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: What skills do you have? Any skills with a sword?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Yes, I can swing a sword capably.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez (tossing him a rapier): Show me what you got. This is a job interview.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: that’s very kind sir but I want more than a job. I want to train with you and be an apprentice! I don’t require any pay.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez (to the open room): Is ‘apprentice’ a job?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick (hiding): —</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Drav, Carlos, back me up here. Apprentice is a job, right?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: From what I’ve seen, an apprenticeship is more like a station in life rather than a job.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Are the mechanics of getting it similar?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Typically families send someone to a higher-status family. It’s sort of a take it or leave it. The higher status people are always looking for servants, essentially.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: What if I’m … not.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: I guess you have to tell him to piss off.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez; Ok, well, scary dirt monster says you have to piss off.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Who, sir? I heard that bag talking.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: That’s some kind of weird potted plant. I’m not sure of the details. He … came in with a giant bear. He suggests that if I’m not looking for a servant, that you should “piss off”</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Please sir I’ll do anything to be your apprentice, doing whatever you bid.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: that does seem like a very useful service. Unfortunately staffing needs … in this economy. And our alcohol budget is going to go through the roof. I’m not sure we have the resources, know-how, elbow-grease.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Sir in fact I provide my own way and even provide for you.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: In that case you’re hired. I teach you how to be great. The first: be luckier. Two: Every morning I will work on sparring with you and teach you how to fight. Three: A vow of silence. All of my apprentices take a vow of silence.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: Yes I’ve heard of this. In fact I think I saw a monk downstairs. He was talking, but … we could still talk during the training? That sounds good to me, sir.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Fez reaches out his hand. He and Cyrowan narrow down the terms of the vow of silence.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: You don’t think I’m weird, do you sir?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Absolutely not.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: I can still write things down?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Yes. And the vow is also an expression of silence.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan: So clever sir, I wouldn’t let anyone tell me you’re not the cleverest man on the planet.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Cyrowan begins being silent. Fez, without alerting Cyrowan, uses Divine Sense. He doesn’t detect celestials, fiends, or undead. Flick comes out from behind the table and begins trancing. Downstairs, Vengeance, feeling refreshed, jumps out of the pool and uses the piece of rebar to comb his few strands of hair while viewing his reflection in the pool. “Alright Vengeance, you can do this,” and adopts a karate pose. The laceration on his side splits open at this, bursting boils along the laceration and spreading the diseased tissue outwards from the center. Little piranha-like fish jumps from the pool and gobble up the exploding liquid. A frothy whirlpool appears as they go crazy.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I thought I wanted to freeze, but I guess I needed to BOIL, popping some boils and collecting the liquid in a vial.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">He runs upstairs to show his friends the vial, and asks if they’d wish to go into business opening an apothecary with him.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Hey, the guy from before!</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Yes, my squire: he has taken the customary vow of silence. It’s great for building character and absorbing what the world has to offer.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: That’s probably for the best — his voice was a little distracting.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: That’s definitely not why he took the vow.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Why was it then? He seemed to really like you.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: I’m trying to be a good teacher — I have to make a personal sacrifice because it’s necessary for the learning process.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Vengeance, did you ever take a vow of silence?&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I did take such a vow; however, I did eventually have to break it, mostly because I was screaming so hard during one particularly rigorous tortue sessions, so I figured, screw it, I don't need to keep this up.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: So you thought that committing to a vow would prevent you from screaming? It had to be an external reinforcement?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Unfortunately I haven’t been very good at sticking to my decisions, but from now on I’m going to. I’m set on completing my quest.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: We did make quite a breakthrough! You wanted to become an oak tree, I said you had to become a grub first, then you were going to seek out a woman who transformed your beloved into a mule. I know I’m gonna find something in you, and I promise you can find something in me.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: You seem like a really cool spirit.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Yeah, me and this little wet dude are pretty cool together. we could be our own little sub-group.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Wet dude</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Yeah, … the Cyrowan guy.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Oh I thought you said “Rotrude” and I got wistful.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: You must have had quite the on-again off-again&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Sometimes I think about her and wonder what could have been.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Vengeance expresses sympathy for soil being paved over.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: Yeah I used to have a brother: Sek. He could manifest as soil too. That’s what happened to him. Somebody poured him on some farmland, and covered it over. He’s still stuck there to this day. Maybe your dwarf friends could help with that. I haven’t heard from him in millenia.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Vek begins to describe his multi-container claustrophobia, and how he needs to contract out a shaman to de-contain him if he’s contained three times. Then he “goes to the bathroom.”</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">[Long Rest actually completes]</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick (to Vengeance): Was there a way further into the structure in the pool downstairs?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I didn’t see exits, but I didn’t dive down. I have to imagine that this dungeon goes down infinitely to the depths of hell. It just seems like that kind of place.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Yeah, even just one level down has proven very strange. I was to get back to Seomra and see if we can get Aphelia to come with us.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I’m ready to get out of here as well.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick (to Jean-luc): You ready to go?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Jean-luc: Yeah, thanks for the hammock. (Looks around) Did we pick up a new companion while I was out?&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">The rocks that Xanthu had used to block the exit are again crumbled on the floor. In the temple, Slugg and Balgarius are curled up sleeping together. Vengeance, existing the basement, and in combination with the Hairshirt and the ameliorative effects of the pool, the boils have subsided and all that remains is the healing laceration and the boil scars.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: I told you that salve would work.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Allow me to present you with this vial of pus. It’s quite potent.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: Please hand it to my new squire, who keeps all of my noxious boil materials.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Cool, so we’re just going to be going through him now?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Cyrowan nods officiously. Not able to find a bag, he wraps the vial in his tattered clothing.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: We’ll find you a bag.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">The group heads back to Seomra and the music room there. Only about a day and a half has passed. Empty leave plates with crumbs and fruits are scattered about; pitcher-plants hold various enticing liquids. Flick walks in, acting like she belongs in the place, but not owns the place, and casually sets Vek’s container on a nearby projection.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick (whispering): Vek, can you sense anything “off” about Aphelia. (Pointing out Aphelia)</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Flick [fails Intimidation] sees a number of the women run up to help her; Vek’s vase is closed so no dirt closes.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Oh, if you can make sure that’s not too close to the edge.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- long silver haired elf: Why are you here? I don’t think I’ve seen you before.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick (pulling out her flute): I feel like Aphelia and I connected yesterday and I wanted to see if she had anything else to teach me.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Flick remembers that she had been starting to understand or translate Aphelia’s sonic communications. She gives a quick flourish with the flute. Aphelia looks up and over at you. She glances quizzically at the vase. Flick holds out her hand in a placatory manner .</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- FLick (to Vek): She’s who we’re here to see. Does anything seem missing about her?&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: There are odd vibrations in this room.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Are they coming from her or someone else?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Eth: oh, YOU! I thought you were already taken care of by the Simurgh.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">“here . time . now . is . preference “ (while disguising as casual noodling) [nat 20]”</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">A smile creeps across her face. She plays deep bass notes, and any hair that hasn’t fallen off by now does so; everyone returns to their original level of hairiness. she gets up and places a hand on Eth’s shoulder. aphelia comes over and adopts a cross-legged style, which flick mirrors. she pushes flick’s flute aside. I explain to her why we’re there and impress upon her the daily horror that the gnolls are living under. I’m not asking her to come with; we’re going to fight the Peryton and bring it back.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Is she willing to entertain that being reintegrated with the Peryton (calliope) would end her existence as she knows it.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Last time she’d said that she had amnesia and couldn’t remember a prior life. But communicating through music she did indicate that she remembered the musical feeling of that time, and that it was something she longed for. (also, all this music stuff … ?)</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick (to Vek): could you effect this reunification in the wild?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: I’d have to see the flesh; there’s so much missing here; i don’t know that i’ve ever seen a creature separated from its spirit outside my embrace. but the wild is, to me, just like an interior, except for all that claustrophobia stuff.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Aphelia isn’t making a noise, but she’s putting her hands over her ears and screaming.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Fez: this is kinda out of my element.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Well, nothing to do but forge ahead.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Eth: what are you doing to her? She's very sensitive to vibrations. I don’t know that anyone would like the sounds coming out of that vase. What have you got in there?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: where are you putting me?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Eth: make sure you cinch the bag!</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Flick puts Vek in the key pocket of the bag of holding.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vek: This is even more restrictive!</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Eth: Thank you! Now what are you trying to get from Aphelia? She already said that she would go with you.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: It looks from the outside like we are a band of crazy people and — we are</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Jean-luc: but we mean well?</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Aphelia connects eyes with Cyrowan and touches his lips. Cyrowan mimes being a squire for Fez. (Fez had asked for rabbits, and laughed at Cyrowan when he’d fallen down on the way over).</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Jean-luc remembers a dream in which by putting the kettle on his head he is able to transform into a bear. Was Shoemaker under this spell? But she had stayed a bearlike creature after death. He did not sense anything malevolent during the dream. Vengeance meanwhile traverses the room to the piano, places Rotrude’s handskin on the piano, saying, “Ok, sister, one more time?” and takes out his bagpipe to play. The gloves not animating themselves, Vengeance puts his hands inside and begins to play.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- What are you touching our piano with?&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: It’s normal, it’s just me and my dead sister playing a duet.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Sister? You’re just holding decaying matter in your hands.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: How dare you!&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">One of the druids grapples the monk to the ground while another grabs his bagpipe.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- What are these things? This is something you’re wearing? Who are you?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Vengeance? is my name? — why are you harassing me like this?&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Certainly you can play the piano, but why would you want to make it so disgusting?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: I don’t really have the time to explain this to you, and really you should educate yourself. This seems to be a bit anti-undead. [persuasion 16]</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">The druids still look suspicious, but a little calmer.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Yeah, we’ve been called that before, and I recognize how that could come off as bigotted. But we still ask that the undead clean up after themselves, the entrails and other body parts that fall off. Seomra has enough to deal with on her own.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Let me give you this book, it’s called human Fragility, and we don’t realize the privileges that we have as humans — i’m half-elf, so I can talk about this stuff. There’s a workbook with some exercises you can do.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Is the workbook separate?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: no , that’s something you can mail in for.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Cyrowan shuffles forward with the brochures he and Vengeance had made on their way north. One of the druids looks at it cursorily.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- I think we’re pretty good as far as educating ourselves goes. we have access to most of the knowledge in the known universe.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: It’s this arrogance I’m talking about . You need to know what you don’t know before you know anything.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- I’m going to pity you and borrow your book.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: great, the answers come pre-filled in. other workbooks come blank, but mine are already filled in.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- So the answer key is there, you just want us to do the reading. there’s no grading service?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: no, there is. there’s … you send me some money and then I send you an A.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- And the cert is good for what?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: It’s really a self-betterment thing. the work that you do to earn the money to spend on the book.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Our money is basically this (she pulls out a leave with bones and a worm on it). it’s primarily the leave, but sometimes we put a little spice on our currency. What’s really dangerous is if you try to pull my hair out, without pulling it up.</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Flick tries to “read the room” in order to see how much distraction is going on. And Vengeance has been employing Qi-Xotic Confusion. Flick’s goal, getting Aphelia out of the room without being seen. So they are so engaged with Vengeance that they can’t move or take actions. Vengeance takes out his three nut shells , “Hey anybody want to play a quick game? It’s really fun,” yanking one of his teeth out and putting it under the shells. Instead of playing, they scream and pack gauze and phellem into his mouth. One of them is trying to get the gloves off his hands without touching them.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Vengeance: Watch yourself!</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick (whispers to Aphelia): Come with me now!</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">[Mick leaves]</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Aphelia resists ineffectually, and with Eth distracted, Flick drags the personified Kiss backwards into the stairwell, promising inwardly to explain everything to her. The stairway begins to collapse on the two fleeing figures [insight 12], and pull back upwards, which seems intentional.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick (to Aphelia): Have you ever ‘gone between’ ?</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Flick grabs her closely and does a dance spin to open the portal and catch both of them. [Arcana 8] . That doesn’t work, so flick grabs her by the waist and dives off the stairway , using her climbing glove to hang onto the end and jerk a vine free that will swing them down to the ground. It goes so well that Flick is even able to manage a flavor-triple-spin and land lightly and gracefully on her feet with Amalia in her off-arm. A few leaves scatter picturesquely.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick (whispering): I’m really sorry!</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Aphelia’s nausea appears to worsen. Flick grabs her and pulls her towards the entrance. As they run past some other elves in there , as she made quite an entrance, she sees that Seomra’s door is beginning to close. The doors close before Flick can get there and takes some bludgeoning damage.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: The biggest wound is to my pride!&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Get off of her! (five other elves that have gathered around)</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Upstairs, Eth sees that Aphelia has gone missing. She looks at Jean-Luc, and beneath her the floor opens up and she drops down a slide made of leaves to the floor below. Jean-luc hurries down the stairs.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: I’m very dangerous! But against five, we’ll see!&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">[DM tries to figure out the map system]</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">The elves are not wielding weapons.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick (in elvish): Brothers and sisters, I’m glad you can bear witness to the way I saved this young woman from the staircase malfunction. I know you’re very impressed by that. We were going to go on a walk by the Alldrink; if you could back away we’d very much appreciate it. Flick, addressing the elf who called back her unsuspecting companion, Ephlalphl, who (he) has his name embroidered on his leaf toga.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Efphalphl: the tree can clearly see that you’re attempting to make your egress with no good business at hand; you’ve taken this young lady here hostage?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Why would you trust its judgment more than mire?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- The tree has an ability to read intentions; how else could it open paths for you</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: but surely it doesn’t have access to the objective rightness or wrongness of any course of action. . why would you defer to it blindly?&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Efphalphl: Well, you know, it _might_, as a possibly immortal vegetal entity. so who knows how close its connection is to true and false. but in any case it can see that one who’s lived here her whole life seems to be in danger.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: I assure you she’s in no danger. i don’t know if you noticed, but i saved her … very impressively I might add.&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Ef: is that where you decided to jump off the stairs?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: we were both being prevented from using a slightly less convenient door. I see you’re not going to be any help!&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Dlapholph here! you want me to tell my friends what to do? I feel like that’s commanding another.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: Ok, i’m just going to turn around and find the handle that’s on this door and be on my way.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Flick [Intimidation 17] notices that Aphelia is clinging closer to Flick just because of Flick’s proximity and her confusion. Flick again commits herself to explaining all this to Aphelia later. She glances behind her to see that there are two side entrances which opened when the primary door closed. Flick thinks it would be great if the elves started arguing amongst each other over who has the most authority. “We’re no better than the tyrants we oppose if we detain her,” Flick, in self-righteous haste, imagines she hears. Aphelia gestures at her hands and Flick sees that her dulcimer is no longer there. Flick gives her the flute to play.&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">[Initiative is rolled.]</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">- Flick: You have exactly six seconds to let me leave or shit is going to get ugly. I’m not going to pretend that you have any right to keep me here. [Intimidation 16].&nbsp;</p><br><p dir=\"ltr\">Two of the elves back off and join Dalpholf. “She’s got a point, I’m going to let Seomra deal with it.” But two others remain committed to keeping the sketchy Flick from leaving.&nbsp;</p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-cd299809-7fff-d32a-fb85-45573f094c1d\"></span></div>"}
