{"_id":"i0mwLxdkmNds47Lv","name":"046: αὐτὰρ ἐπεὶ παύσαντο πόνου τετύκοντό τε δαῖτα, δαίνυντ᾿, οὐδέ τι θυμὸς ἐδεύετο δαιτὸς ἐΐσης·","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"nEIZOAbBi8YZmJDe","sort":700000,"flags":{},"content":"<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Session </strong><strong>&sect;046 &alpha;ὐ&tau;ὰ&rho; ἐ&pi;&epsilon;ὶ &pi;&alpha;ύ&sigma;&alpha;&nu;&tau;&omicron; &pi;ό&nu;&omicron;&upsilon; &tau;&epsilon;&tau;ύ&kappa;&omicron;&nu;&tau;ό &tau;&epsilon; &delta;&alpha;ῖ&tau;&alpha;, &delta;&alpha;ί&nu;&upsilon;&nu;&tau;᾿, &omicron;ὐ&delta;έ &tau;&iota; &theta;&upsilon;&mu;ὸ&sigmaf; ἐ&delta;&epsilon;ύ&epsilon;&tau;&omicron; &delta;&alpha;&iota;&tau;ὸ&sigmaf; ἐΐ&sigma;&eta;&sigmaf;&middot;</strong></div>\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Played </span>November 7, 2020 (2020-11-07)</strong></div>\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong>Evening Day 13 to wee hours Day 14</strong></div>\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Level</strong>&nbsp;<strong>8</strong></div>\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" /></div>\n<h1 id=\"sister-light-sister-dark\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-line=\"20\">Recap</h1>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Proving quite hearty, Scunner remains standing long enough to be rescued by Breg, a salt-and-pepper dwarven geomancer who begins to throttle Jean-Luc with a massive granite hand that rises from the floor. A temporary truce is called, and on Scunner's thiefly word, and the gang's almost complete disavowel of the Hat Baskets, they are allowed further into the caves, where are situated a giant salamander, a lizardfolk shaman and about half a dozen similarly dressed humans. They appear to be engaged in mining a muted blue crystalline ore, but before the adventurers can enter, the oldest human, Fundi, runs over and prevents the group from entering the ritual mining space -- for such it is -- until they've passed a bevy of personal questions. The mining team deliver their own side of the \"stolen logbook\" story, which is that the Hat Baskets stole the giant salamander's baby mandling and they hoped for a hostage exchange by stealing the book, whose power Breg believes too great to leave in Hat Basket hands. The adventurers immediately back this new horse and plan to retrace their steps to recover \"Nubbs.\" Everyone gets drunk and goes to sleep.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h1 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">Transcript</h1>\n<p>JL is surprised that Scunner isn't dead.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Flick makes a Perception check to judge the distance of the others down the tunnel. 15.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>She thinks they are close enough to get there this round or next round if they dash. Flick, not wanting to be the first thing they see, moves and calls out to Jean-Luc, \"You're going to want to duck!\" and force-shoots Scunner.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>23 force damage.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Scunner twists and puts the column between himself and the arrow, but it's clear he's in bad shape: JL's thrust to the armpit is bleeding copiously. Gerd flies on in ...</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Ian informs the team that summoning Gerd scales with spell level.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>... and mauls the rogue, but it's still too lumbering to hit him. Gerd's momentum carries it over to the other side, licking the salt crystals there for a moment before turning back to face the adversary.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Galen arrives.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Vengeance admires the 'water feature,' a tasteful and well-appointed pond with a different species of fish inhabiting each step of the pool, arranged by color of the rainbow. Flick sees that the first person to round the corner is a dwarf, clad in thick woolen grey robes. She has a grey-white bears obscuring her face and a beretlike cap. She carries in her hands a staff carved out of a pure white crystal. As she casts&nbsp;Maximillian's Earthen Grasp, the rocky floor erupts into the shape of a hand which secures Jean-Luc in its grasp and squeezes tight. JL starts gasping for air. \"What ... the fuck...\"</p>\n<p>Vengeance recalls that the spell is named after Maximillian, a man who was killed by falling into an open mine, and then named for a chess move where one of the pieces goes forward a great number of spaces , sacrificing itself. As Vengeance communicates this history to JL he begins to lose consciousness.</p>\n<p>Flick bets dollars to donuts that this is a concentration spell.</p>\n<div>Breg: Parlay with us, or your friend is crushed. I know what you've come for -- it's the book you want, isn't it?</div>\n<div>JL: Parlay sounds good!</div>\n<div>Flick: Can we at least kill Scunner?</div>\n<div>Breg: No, Scunner's with me, as different as our ways of life are.</div>\n<div>Flick: It was worth a shot.</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Vengeance, intending to use his Quixotic Qonfusion ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>... says, \"release our friend here and we will do anything you wish.\" Flick: We'll put down our weapons Vengeance: One wish Breg: You can cast the wish spell? Flick [undecipherable] Breg: What? you broke up there in the lava static. Vengeance: There's lava in here? Breg: Well, as a geomancer I'm in touch with all the rocks and uh, the lava is distant but it does contribute to my signal-to-noise ratio. Flick: I said i'm pretty adept at the misty step. that's impressed people in the past. Breg: But not a wish spell. Vengeance: Yes, by \"wish\" i basically meant that we would perform one dance for you, and it would be the misty step. Breg: How interesting. You've certainly made different overtures than other members of the Hat Baskets. Is it -- does this spell attempt to work some kind of charm over us? V: The Hat Baskets are really upping their game, as you probably know, and they've been hiring better and better actors, and so we're part of the latest crop. Breg: You really hit the nail on the head saying \"actors.\" They merely play-act at this game that the rest of us have been involved in our entire lives, for actual stakes. V: Is it a game to you? Breg: No! Are you saying you're a performer? V: No. Breg: Then why are you so interested in this dance? What's going on here?</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Somehow Vengeance has gotten around to Confusing her, allowing him to make a good-faith Persuasion check. 18.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Jean-Luc has been doing some kind of self-anti-boa constricting.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breg: We do appear to be at a standoff. Perhaps a dance would allow us to reset ourselves. Vengeance: Well, Flick, it's up to you, now.</p>\n<p>Flick tries her best to improvize \"Misty Step\" -- there were barn dances and such. She spent a fair amount of time moving rhythmically with other young people. Plus she's very light on her feet, and can make things look pretty good to someone standing 70 feet away. Flick, raised by humans foster parents. They weren't kind, but neither were they abusive and isolating. She can do a bastardized jig for a few minutes.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Flick gets to make the performance check with her Dexterity modifier.&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Breg looks like she's getting into it; she's one of the stouter dwarves, and Flick is flitting around the column; she may be put in mind of tales of the elves and dwarves having huge shared feasts together. She turns back and shouts. \"It's ok, we've brokered a sort of truce here. I'm sure we can sort this out. You'll love what this elf is doing, by the way.\"</p>\n<p>Flick pauses to stare daggers at Vengeance, who's openly weeping at the beauty of the dance. Vengeance turns to Jean-Luc, \"Now I know why they call it the misty step.\"</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>DK points out Vengeance is not close enough, and JL is constrained by the giant rock hand.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>JL: Very nice, still stuck in an earthen grip here.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Scunner puts a hand up to his eye to wipe away a tear, which becomes an ice droplet and shatters on the ground. Breg lets the spell drop, and the hand crumbles back into the floor of the cave.</p>\n<p>JL: So we've agreed to a parlay, yes? Breg: Yes. If you wish to come back here, it's a little more hospitable, and we can talk about our mutual needs.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick and JL think that they really need to keep the Gaol Maidens from finding out who he is. However, he's not sure if these people know who he is.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>JL Investigation&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The distance of Kriobolis from Marshbout is around 500 miles, so it's fairly unlikely they would have received information about a hit on you, since that's pretty specific and they are stationed here, and in fact if few people know they are here at all (!).</p>\n<p>JL flashes a hand signal to indicate that he comes in peace, and Scunner meets his eyes and shakily returns the hand signal; Breg doesn't appear to notice. Flick walks over and hands a goodberry to the Gaol Maiden</p>\n<p>Your mercy is as meaningful as your hostility, elf. What do I call you.</p>\n<p>Flick: My name is Flick. Scunner: The full name's Blad Schillaber, but everyone calls me Scunner. Blad has all those connotations these days. He eats the goodberry and looks quite full. \"I thought those roast meats had filled me up, but I guess I didn't all the corners. You're ohhhhhhhh,\" and he passes out. Gerd moves forward and begins to lick his wound. JL suggests to Vengeance that he tend to JL. Vengeance comes over and joins in the licking. It's clear Scunner hasn't had a fight like this in quite sometime. He wakes up to pontificate: \"I still don't know how I missed you with that first swipe. I mean, I know you're a fellow Maiden, but what kind of training have you had?\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL: I imagine we come from the same school. You know how it is: you see a glint of steel and your instincts kick in. Scunner: You're right, I've probably been staring into the flames for too long. I'm not used to being underground. JL: Preaching to the quite. Scunner: Uh, huh. Sure. You don't happen to have any drink on you?</p>\n<p>JL offers him a swig from the Tepplin bottle.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Would Flick have noticed the Thieves' cant hand signal? DM says no.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Scunner sees the brewer's mark on the bottle. \"Ah, right on for you, did you steal this from some high-flying elites? Well done.\" JL: I don't know its provenance. I came across it under somewhat unusual circumstances which I'll have to relate later. Scunner: \"Well, you must know -- the Tepplin distilleries provide all the priests in Kriopolis with their sacramental wines and their religious drinks.\" It's clear that Scunner, with the loss of blood, the goodberry, being licked by Gerd and Vengeance, and a few shots of liquor have loosened his tongue. \"I hear that somebody's making a play for their Star. I think they want to brand beers for the common man with the Star so they can sell 'elite' drinks at higher prices.\" He goes on to criticize commodity branding and the sheeple that buy into it. JL: I miss the days when the lower classes brewed their own beer and had a good time doing it. Scunner: That's right! Brewing their own beer, leavening their own bread. Now they have to get it from whoever's ... JL: \"And the leases!\" He goes on a rant about the economy&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Persuasion check</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It's clear that JL's bourgeoisie education start creeping into the way he's talking about things. Scunner, \"Ok, I see eye to eye with you. As I've said, I'm Scunner\" JL: Jean-Luc.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>DM establishes that, from the rolls, he doesn't know about a bounty on your head.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Scunner looks like the name reminds him of something. \"It's an odd name for Kriopolis ... maybe you're from southern Albland? I know a few Jean-Lucs from there\" Vengeance: He spells it J-A-A-A-N L-U-K-E like a fun unconventional spelling. Such were JL's parents, I guess.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>JL insight check.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>JL detects that Scunner's eyes lit up when Jean-Luc said his name, and this business about other Jean-Lucs is clearly covering for something. He doesn't know about the bounty, but he's heard of you, or heard the name and now has a face. JL plays along, so Scunner doesn't know that JL knows that Scunner knows.</p>\n<p>Flick calls Gerd over, \"Flit over by that column and keep an eye on the Geomancer, and tell me what she does and says.\"&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Gerd is Gerd-sexual.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Gerd communicates to you that there are a bunch of people chilling back in the tunnel. It holds up most of its hands (each with 3 claws) to indicate the number of people. Flick wants to know if they are holding weapons. It holds up one claw, and puffs his cheek up, and mimes doing a really large creature. One claw. Then he mimes smoking. 3 claws.</p>\n<p>Flick: So it's either a really fat guy, or an ogre. and someone toking.</p>\n<p>Breg: I hope you've brought more to parlay with than just that dance, unless we have to recommence hostilities, but why not come back here?</p>\n<p>Flick: we need to be ready to act or think fast because we're not fooling anyone at this point. JL: \"Scunner's assured me of safe passage. Unless things go totally sideways\" and he looks over to Vengeance. JL helps Scunner to his feet. \"I can tell you're not like the Hat Baskets; one of them has aim like you wouldn't believe, but you seem much more grounded than whatever's going on with that group. I'm still curious. None of us want to die&nbsp;too&nbsp;prematurely.</p>\n<p>By the time they round the corner he's a little more steady on his feet. They see a few humans hanging out in the corner and smoking.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Insight checks.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>All except Jean-Luc recognize quickly that this is an extended family unit, unlike what those unfamiliar with thieves groups might have expected, which would have been individual ne'er-do-wells with secretive backgrounds. In addition, they see a very large creature, 12-15 feet long, looking like a scaled-up newt, emitting a yellowish-red light which they identify as the cove light. Next to the salamander is a lizardfolk who appears to be the creature's handler. The salamander is facing a heaping pile of ore, and near its butt a smaller pile of bright-blue cylindrical gems. The family looks like they were the ones mining.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drav's 'wizard' part suddenly realizes this is a gemstone known as Azurite. It's a blue mineral which will slowly lose its vibrancy over time, and indeed there appears to be a kind of oily rectal mucus swaddling the crystals. Drav knows that it's used as a spell component for high-level spells that try to diminish the power of other things.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Like Jorgensen's Blue Balls, Ian suggests. The DM clarifies that it's more likely to be The Inverse of Jorgensen's Blue Balls, which are being crushed by Maximillians' Eearthen Hand. There is a famous statue on the North Strictland of that exact thing, marking the entrance into the Val&ouml;r Pass. The 'balls' part of the statue is made of a stable blue mineral, rather than Azurite.&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Everyone looks pretty relaxed except for someone who looks like the grandfather; he's spry but has grey hair, and a tetrapod animated boulder which has skeletal arms and legs protruding from it.</p>\n<p>Fundi: Breg says you're hear to parlay, and not to interrupt our mining? JL: We have no reason to stop your mining. Not our bailiwick. Fundi: Well as you can see I've set up this periphery of ribbons; they&nbsp;area traditional part of the goings-on. I must ask you a few questions as you approach the area. Have any of your been infidelitous to your spouses or significant others? Flick: I'm not married. JL turns to the group: Are any of us married? Vengeance: Uh, yeah! But it would take me a few days to figure out how to answer that question truthfully. It depends on so many definitions. Fundi: Can you stay as far away from the mining, then? Since that's going to disrupt the blessing we're trying to impose on this area. Flick: Is azurite oxidized by perverts or something? Fundi: Well, yes, kindof. The ore gets corrupted and it's much more difficult to smelt -- and, furthermore, nasty effects can attend those who don't follow the proper ritual precautions that must be taken. Vengeance: Does it matter, sir, that my Wife happens to be a mule and is, in fact,&nbsp;not&nbsp;manogamous. Fundi: Is she here? With you? Vengeance: No. Fundi: Well ... I've already asked you to stay as far away as possible. But let me ask. Nyuka! I have a theological question for you! Nyuka, the lizardfolk handler of the salamander. \"Yes, what's your question.\" Fundi repeats what Vengeance has told him. Nyuka: No, as long as she stays far away it shouldn't have any effect. Fundi: Ok, then you may enter, but for a number of reasons, some of which are merely the general unpleasantness of being in close proximity to you, I ask that you keep your distance from the mining. Vengeance: Yes, that will do, thank you.</p>\n<p>Vengeance takes a look at some of these ribbons comprising the perimeter fence. Fundi says they are fabrics of some rarity, originating likely from the \"Acha Bashoor\" continent to the southwest.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>History or religion check to determine legitimacy of the pomp. Ian declines to roll, as Flick would not quibble with Fundi's explanations. Most roll a 10.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Many practices that concern extracting rare earth materials do involve a great deal of magic and ritual. Depending on where you fall on the religion/spirituality spectrum, you might believe the necessity more or less. Depending on Drav's increasing contact with Eldar, she may develop more respect for it. But they may regard it as \"hooey\" even if they don't believe in it themselves, but you wouldn't tell someone not to go to church.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jean-Luc knows that Acha Bashoor is south of Kriobolis, which is on the isthmus dividing Ys from Bashoor. There are beautiful textiles and port cities which export the same. Flick is only vaguely aware that there are even other landmasses. She's pretty provincial, but commits to play along with their ribbon-dance games. She is also romantically inexperienced, so finds Fundi's prodding somewhat offputting. Of course, a kiss and cuddle happened at the barn dances, but she watched most of her peers die. She outlived her foster parents while she was an \"adolescent\" -- she saw several generations of her environs live, marry, and die, while she looked the same. Other people know that she's not part of the dating pool.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The DM relates that the world does abide by plate techtonics where possible. But he does admit that the ecosystems don't make as much sense as they might. The DM also pictures Flick as Jack Nicholson showing up in time cycles at the Shining, returning to ask who's going to be at the next barn dance.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Flick was found as an infant, is 75 now. Recently it occured to Ian that she outlived her foster parents and is late adolescent relative to elf life cycles, and a little damaged in being raised by faster-living humans. It can be a big or small a part of the campaign as desired. Her life in that town must have been pretty weird. Imagine a human raised by a series of their pets.&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Breg approaches Drav; she's a fairly old Dwarf, probably 400 years old. All her hair is grey and white. Her face looks literally chiseled from rock, which appears to have infused the character of her face. Drav gets a vibe that she's pretty intuitive about this kind of stuff. \"I can tell that you've recently been dabbling in the ways in which dwarves can communicate with rocks and mold rocks to their will.\" Drav: That's absolutely correct. I didn't grow up with much exposure to that. My parents are elves, they loved me very much, but and I didn't learn much about this stonework.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breg: that's very interesting, and now you find yourself drawn to it. Have you found any expertise or instruction on your travels? Or doing your own research? Drav: I've done a lot of reading, but it's not the same as practicacl experience. We seem to get distracted by many things along our journey. Breg: If you were to practically engage, how would you envision doing so? Drav: The way you seem to be able to read the rock and stone, and mold and shape it, that's not something I've ever done myself, or seen done. Breg: What you've seen so far are almost parlor tricks of the geomancer. These are commonplace spells for magically inclined dwarves. I myself am too old to take on an apprentice, but there are areas in the world that would love to take on a dwarf of your inquisitive nature to learn of the living rock.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>She scribbles down a small map of the area, and identifies some mountains to the east: there's a well renowned teacher here, her name is Obnovenie Sveta. she's unique in a number of ways, one of which is eschewing the traditional dwarven habit of taken a last name that's a noun compound; she said that the name was given to her by one of the earth elementals. I think you would be perfect precisely because of your knowledge of the written word. She teaches dwarves to learn the powers of the earth through runes that are inscribed into the rocks themselves, and it acts as a mediating, plastic medium for those who have the power within themselves but just need a channel through which to direct that power.</p>\n<p>But in the meantime I can certainly teach you the rudiments of the spell I was able to cast on your roguish friend. She takes Drav's hand, spits onto the wall behind her, rubs the stylus in the stone ink, and inscribes the text of the spell into her spellbook, holding drav's hand under hers</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Maximillian's Earthen Guuuuurrrrrrrrasp</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Drav hugs Breg, who hugs her back. They are both strong. In this instance Drav expresses deference to her elder, and Breg gives her a rib cracking hug, that feels warm, parental, strengthening, all in one.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Inspiration point.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Fundi gets up on the turnbuckle and presses down the ribbons and motions to everyone to come in. Breg turns to Flick, \"are you acting as an agent for the hat baskets. scunner seems to think you're not quite of their ilk.\"</p>\n<p>Flick, \"I didn't even know the hatpins from adama before i arrived here. the way i help friends is by shooting things, and I'm sorry we had to cross paths in that way. no hard feelings.\"</p>\n<p>Breg: you'd have to take that up with scunner -- we did post him as a guard. all things being equal, i'd say put it in the past</p>\n<p>Scunner: i think it was a fight well met and well returned. there are no hard feelings here. I've seen it go worse so many times. his lower lip starts to tremble as he stares into space. JL pours some fortifying liquor into his mouth.</p>\n<p>JL: we seem to have found ourselves in a dispute that we're not sure we're a part of. we have almost literally, and definitely figuratively, stumbled in here.</p>\n<p>Breg: so what was it that did bring you here?</p>\n<p>JL: you guys are a cell, outfit, or extension of the gaol maidens?</p>\n<p>Breg: The Ruhu family here would think of themselves as a self-contained family unit within the GM, i'm not sure if they see themselves as an extension. Fundi: We were able to claim this mining spot for ourselves, and that has to be honored by the GMs JL: So it's a franchise opportunity. Fundi: In a way. JL: I had some dealings with the GM back in Krobopolis, then we were approached by the Hat baskets who were trying to wind us up to send us after you because of whatever turf war you two are in. But we have no interest in either side of that dispute. Flick: There was the matter of the aethereal firebomb. JL: Yeah, was that you?</p>\n<p>Nyaka perks up. \"Did you say there was an explosion?\" Flick: A very strange one. (and, unguardedly, describes what it looked like from the aethereal plane.).&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Insight checks all around. Drav is still beaming after hugging Breg and notices nothing. Flick and JL do well.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>JL notices -- he used to know the name of his city; the fact that he doesn't know how to pronounce it anymore is worrisome; something mystical might be going on. Flick notices something similar, a little ameliorated, but she hasn't seen anyone (except maybe when her original foster parents got dementia) thinks JL might be under a localized aphasia. She knows of a legend that Gonfalon told her, of a dark wood, when people would live within the shadow of the wood, they couldn't remember anything that had happened during that period of time. She's been noticing this since she's known JL.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vengeance: JL, why don't you just call it C-town, or the Big C. that's what I do with my monastery.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>JL intelligence check</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Flick does know of a Kriobolis.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL can't remember if it's spelled with a K or a C.</p>\n<p>Flick hears \"kribopolis\" and asks to be excused by the dwarves, hops over the club ribbon, and walks to JL. Can you repeat after me: Kree-ah-bo-lis . JL repeats it fine, no problem. \"Sorry, dwarves, a bit of house keeping.\"</p>\n<p>\"I hate to get involved in this sort of thing, but, well, ...\" Flick: by all means, everyone's up in our shit. \"I'm gonna let Nyaka ask you about the explosive device while I pontificate\"</p>\n<p>Nyaka comes over: \"it sounds like ... describe to me more this explosion.\" Flick does her best. they smelled smoke and JL saw an ingot under vengeance's crate. \"I'm able to step into neighboring planes. it was a bright radiation in the ethereal plane.\" Nyaka: you may need to speak with the elves. I don't know what this is. Flick: mother -- you don't think i'm a vampire too, do you? Nyaka: no, elves. Lhaska keeps me warm no matter what the temperature; we have quite a bond between us. As a warmblood, you wouldn't understand. It also sounds like you weren't told that we were working a joint venture with the hat baskets to mine the iridium flick: that sounds expensive Nyaka: it is, a very rare metal. if we'd had our way, we would have been the only ones taking the ore. but the hatbaskets had managed to maneuver into a position of negotiation, and we were forced to split with them. flick: they didn't tell us about this. the explosion went off, -- no one died, but they were very hurt, and they immediately pointed us your way.</p>\n<p>Drav, at the time, noticed that the explosion was an iridium-like material. It's very rare on the crust of the planet. in order to find a vein is almost unheard of. (Iridium is completely resistant to rust.)</p>\n<p>Nyaka: i'm not the first to say this, but those naive idiots probably didn't know the danger of the material; all our sources tell us that they're trading with the Gormflaith in the Sea of Kosht.</p>\n<p>Fez had mentioned the Gormflaith as being on the Majestic Elf -- sea pirates that live in marshy areas, interested in iridium as it's rust resistant and an elite high-value material for weapons.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Nyaka: I don't know what would cause it to explode like&nbsp;that, though. was the ... mandling they took from us nearby it at the time? the salamander child? (-- the creature underneath the bench. the bench was close to vengeance's seat. (they recall that it was about 5 or 6 feet away). )</p>\n<p>Nyaka: it's possible that an immature mandling, unable to control its heat, could have caused an explosion, but i think something else could have been going on. but in any case, you say that they do still have the lizard child</p>\n<p>vengenace: the lizard child!</p>\n<p>nyaka: i don't know why the hatbaskets are so vicious, but they stole lhaska's baby and refused to give it back, and we had no choice but to take the log book. JL: do you think they'll make that trade? Nyaka: they haven't shown any indication so far. Vengeance: Nyackha! Nyaka: You pronounced my name in the ancient way! Vengeance: No i had a great joke. Nyaka: ok, go ahead Vengeance: I was going to compare our \"common beef\" to the handsome jean-luc, who is a peasant, and thus also, \"common beef\" Nyaka: Very good&nbsp;</p>\n<p>behind Lhaska , there is a spit on which an entire roasting sheet is rotating, and from which parts have been eaten.</p>\n<p>Fundi has some markings on his face that look like they could have been blood.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vengeance: well now i'm really distracted: is that sheep for your salamander? Nyaka: you really don't know what the salamander eats? V: nnnnnnnoo Nyaka: we feed it the ore, and inside its body, it performs the smelting, and excretes the pur mineral, the azurite. V: that's the way my favorite coffee is made. well i was going to offer a trade. perhaps we could kill a few hat baskets, and in exchange we can take this fine lizard. Nyaka: we've refrained from killing as much as possible. they're just annoying rich people; if we could have made this ransom exchange it would have been the preferred outcome. and also, i would never give up Lhaska. we are almost as Lovers, in your hot blooded terms. V: everything must have its price Nyaka: no, that seems like a capitalist perspective. here we're largely family or clan or lineage-based system of thief traders V: i would sell my wife for fifty ... dubloons?</p>\n<p>Breg: Is that because you've been infidelitous? Out of the ribbon area. GET. HIM. OUT.</p>\n<p>Fundi approaches Vengeance adn Scunner bats him back. V: Not you too, scunner Scunner. i gotta listen to Breg, man. She can literally make the rocks swallow me.</p>\n<p>JL: the HB stole your salamander, you stole their logbook, they're unwilling to make the trade, do we know what they want with your salamander?&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Nyaka: as you can see, salamanders are capable of almost elemental feats with minerals. I expect that's their intention. Breg: what Nyaka told you is not the whole truth. we took their logbook because it's of a magnitude of power far beyond what they can control, for quite petty reasons, so they know when their captains arrive in port. they don't even know that the corresponding logs the captains possess will corrupt them over time, and that this log can't be controlled but rather is something which controls you over time. i think -- we are not willing to give it back to them, i must admit, even if they did want to.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL: i remember why i left the theives' guild now. all these internal squabbles.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breg: we would like to think we're on the right side of things JL: it's what everybody thinks Breg: I guess you have a point. JL: why do you think the log book is corrupting them?</p>\n<p>Breg: it's because they've portrayed it to you as just a log book. the magician who originally created it, pathytus, he was a magician ... from beyond the stars, and his magic when applied here, could only do harm to the consciousnesses native to this planet, and the areas from where he came, the consciousnesses were merged into a single field , undifferentiatable, and i believe that this logbook, were it allowed to propagate its influence, would bring about the same on this planet. creating a sort of horde or swarm of ethically divested intellect.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>is this bullshit?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>vengeance remembers training at the monastery, reading a text that concerned the synchronization of the rotation of the celestial sphers. he rememberes that the sphere in which this planet is inscribed was believed to intersect with the other sphere every thousand years, intersecting twice once every thousand years looking like bike spokes -- this other sphere was thought to be inhabited by the kind of collective intelligence that the geomancer is describing.</p>\n<p>vengeance: yeah, it's just a mcguffin guys flick has read enough of the demerast saga that she knows what a mcguffin is.</p>\n<p>flick: if the whole point is to get this from point a to point b, should we take it, or can we ask nicely?&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Insight check from JL for battle intelligence on their odds in this fight</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Vengeance: but, if we want a salamander, assuming the child has the same properties as this one, we need only go back to the hat baskets, and steal from them because they are clearly incompetent; so I say we go and steal that lizard. we definitely want to steal the lizard, right?</p>\n<p>JL: Seems worth asking: are we sure we want to be involved in this conflict? We do have those gnolls to save. And I was only investigating this to see if we're connected. If Yolandar does have a price on my head, it hasn't reached marshbout yet.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>JL: How dangerous is it if the hat baskets have the baby salamander? What level of malfeasance are we talking about? (he asks...) Nyaka: How dangerous is it if the hatbaskets have your child? JL: In the grand scheme of things, I'd be devastated. Nyaka yes, it's devastating; emotionally and psychologically it takes quite a toll. we will have to ... make a run to free it, i believe, soon. Flick: so that salamander that was drying our asses, that belongs to these people? well then we have to help them. these guys stole this log book, but that's a living creature that has to stare at people's assess all day. we're not going to let that happen, right? Drav: I agree with flick. JL: let's go make another enemy. Flick: i have plenty of notches ... left? on my belt? for enemies. Nyuka: You'll help? Flick: we're going to get back your -- JL: -- don't give them guarantees! Nyuka: well in that case, why don't you join us in the feast. We have to eat this entire sheep before we can proceed with the mining. As long as none of you are infidelitous. JL: what if you've caused&nbsp;others&nbsp;to be infidelitous? Breg: What do you mean exactly? JL: So, I'm not married, but I've had several affairs with married men and women. Breg: And none of them believed it to be exclusive? JL: No...? You know how it is. Breg: An interesting blind spot in this practice. We must convene.</p>\n<p>Breg, Nyaka, and Fundi come over and knock heads. They talk for a few moments. They all look very happy.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This is even better than we thought! It explodes our conceptual notions of what constitutes fidelity, obligation, and responsibility. Even your weird half-elf friend is welcome into the circle.</p>\n<p>Flick: Wow, let's have some roast.</p>\n<p>JL intuits that they might have gotten things wrong here, and it might affect the success of this operation and the future luck of anyone who participates.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>How does he know that?&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>JL motions to Fundi: when was the last time the original text was reviewed? Fundi: Well this is a tradition that's been passed down orally over generations, so I wouldn't say there's an original text. It largely involves getting involved with our family spirit Ruhu, which may have been mentioned before. JL: and when was that? Fundi: when we sacrificed the sheep, that was to Ruhu, and we spread the blood over our faces, and eating the sheep, in order to placate Ruhu with the magnitude of the ceremony.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vengeance has a daydream where his face is smeared with blood and he's eating a leg of mutton? \"Come over here and let me shotgun you some meat.\" He takes JL's head in his hands in order to -- he jolts alert.</p>\n<p>JL thinks that they are so excited by what's going on, that they are overlooking any ritual specifics. Since he doesn't believe in the metaphysical nature of this anyway, (like someone misreading a starchart of astrology) he doesn't care and starts to eat.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>They bring out roasted flatbreads and beer; they ask you to pass around the Starr liquor. They fill their bellies and no man lacked his share of the feast. the annoying younger brother Haigi says that, and JL thinks to himself: did this idiot also have to study heroic poems? are they still teaching that?</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Charisma check.&nbsp;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Fundi approaches V. \"You know, i could tell you wanted this little boomerang to return to your hand\" and goes to grab at V's crotch. \"I'm afraid that one won't come back to you.\" - \"But, I expose myself; there's -- when I was growing up, one of my schoolmates went on to become an artificer, he went on to infuse weapons with spells. There's a spell which I believe is called ... I'm sure an artificer would be able to tell you. it allows your weapon to return to your hand, with just the action of the mind. If you were able to find an artificer with this spell you could ahve the weapon you desire.\" - Vengeance: \"i'll just write down my address for you.\"</p>\n<p>Flick: Peglini's Plenty Persuasive Plea to Return.</p>\n<p>\"Look it's returning weapon, yes.\" - Vengeance: Flick, you knew all along? I'm going to kill you.</p>\n<p>Fundi sits back to watch drama: oh is there a disagreement between you two, oh yes? Vengeance: who even are you? Fundi: I'm just an old man who knows his rocks, who knows how to get his rocks off. Flick: We sure can pick 'em guys. V: I guess he's a part of the group now.</p>\n<p>Nyaka comes over to JL; she's also affected by the beer. She and Lhaska have been swooning on each other; she's high on passion and drink. Nyaka: As a lover, I can see that you hold two items that wish they were more united than they are now. (and she points to his daggers). I have the privilege of a rare love magic that allows me to unite even inanimate objects. Could I see them?&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is this an innuendo? he rolls badly, so thinks it is.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Vengeance: No, she wants you to cut her! JL: Oh (dejectedly) she probably did just want the daggers.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Nyaka wanders over to Lhaska, basking in her own heat. both of the lizards hold their tongues out, which she cuts with the daggers, which she coats in the blood which is then absorbed into the daggers, kind of like the iruvian metal. You'll find that these should perform much better when you wield them together.&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>For these daggers, you have the Two Weapon Fighting feat.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Many thanks! and he offers her a celebratory lift of his glass. Nyaka: yes, this elixer has done quite the job on my reptilian brain.&nbsp;wink&nbsp;If you ever develop a cloaca, you should come and see us. JL: given how my last couple dates have gone, that is not out of the question. Nyaka: You're very charming for a human. (SHe goes and nuzzles up next to Lhaska and falls asleep.)</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>intended Long Rest begins</p>\n<p>End of session</p>\n</blockquote>"}
{"_id":"iQXQvmvK8M8iwy2F","name":"Dark Song (ship)","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"srmjxCv4QHqVw5AK","sort":900001,"flags":{},"content":"<p dir=\"ltr\">client/target: occult collector</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">work: perform/stop ritual</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">twist: The job furthers a city official&rsquo;s secret agenda</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">connected to: city notable, and (my) rival</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">methods (ours or theirs?): espionage, arcane</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">my take on this:</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Turns out that The Dark Song (a leviathan hunter) is owned by Lord Strangford.&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">The woman Sallender was rumored to have it's map-book. She was being chased down by the Rail Jacks (presumably for the Ministry, who wishes to take over the leviathan hunting fleets)&nbsp;</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">perhaps (by coincidence) the leviathan map book taken by Sallender is being taken to Odrienne (see below)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Perform a ritual:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">one with a connection to Ruka through the Church of Ecstasy.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Or we have to perform a ritual in conjunction with Orion's discovery: (\"I'm thinking we could use leviathan blood as a carrier/medium to make bound in darkness work:process the blood halfway, then mix our own blood into it\")</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">twist:&nbsp; this furthers Strangford's secret agenda</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">occult collector who we have to talk to or spy on is my (gob's) rival (Odrienne Welker, a woman).</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We also might learn that Lord Strangford wants the remaining Investigators working on his case killed (see Strangford's entry in the Blades book for info on this). And we want to prevent that for ourselves (or for someone else paying money) or offer to do that for money.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 dir=\"ltr\">Odrienne:</h1>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;she's slim, stooped, disfigured / maimed; her goals are chaos/destruction &amp; love; and she has connections with gondolier and a/the treasurer (maybe the treasurer for the CoE)</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">place of business in The Six Towers. (A formerly rich district, now worn down and dilapidated.)</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">she's Arrogant, and takes pleasure in Fine clothes, jewelry, furs. She inherited her position. May not deserve / want it.</p>\n<p><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">bluecoats/inspectors</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">grey cloaks</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;&nbsp;-A crew of former Bluecoats turned to crime after being framed and expelled from the City Watch.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;Nessa (leader, scrupulous, daring). Hutch (second, brash, fierce).</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">(so they burned evidence for&nbsp; strangford ? otherwise, why would strangford be their enemy. strangford would pay well too &hellip; kill the inspectors who still know about the evidence?&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;The Gray Cloaks are all former Bluecoats who were framed for a crime committed by their Watch station commander. Sure, they were skimming from the city coffers and taking bribes like everyone else, but they didn&rsquo;t burn down the Watch station and destroy the evidence in the case against Lord Strangford (of the Leviathan Hunters). Several inspectors who were working the case know the truth but can&rsquo;t prove anything&mdash;yet. Lord Strangford would pay well to have these loose ends removed permanently.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">the Inspectors (aka &ldquo;Constables&rdquo;) investigate crimes and present evidence for warrants and trials. Inspectors are appointed by the Lord Governor of the city. Inspectors are often foreigners, with no close ties within Duskwall.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Lord Strangford. Operates one of the largest leviathan hunter fleets, serves on the City Council and is a high-ranking member of the secret order within the Church of Ecstasy. (Secretive, Calculating, Arrogant)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Turns out that The Dark Song is owned by Lord Strangford.&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Connection to Ruka through the Church of Ecstasy.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Or the ritual is the one we have to perform that Orion mentioned with the leviathan blood.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">twist:&nbsp; this furthers Strangford's secret agenda</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">occult collector is my rival (Odrienne Welker, a woman)</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">slim, stooped, disfigured / maimed</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">goals: chaos/destruction &amp; love</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">has connections with gondolier and a/the treasurer (maybe the treasurer for the CoE)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Arrogant</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Fine clothes, jewelry, furs</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Inherited their position. May not deserve / want it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">methods: espionage, arcane</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"iR6Mkt3SUxHQFeYa","name":"019. [interlude] The power tie of our discord","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"gNDm5xMcEMxCyTVb","sort":-49999,"flags":{},"content":"<p>2020-03-14</p>\n<p>Level 5</p>\n<p>Day 7</p>\n<hr />\n<h1 id=\"recap\">Recap</h1>\n<p>This was an interlude session helping Curculio find her friend Wodden.</p>\n<h3 id=\"curculio\"><strong>Curculio</strong></h3>\n<p>Flick, Carlos and Joan returned to&nbsp;An Sr&aacute;idbhaile&nbsp;with Thaz in order to plead with the gnolls to accept her back into their clan. Meanwhile, Curculio approached Drav, Fez and Paros about a message she had been sent by her friend Wodden just after he escaped the confines of a magic lake. Curculio believed that playful flowerfolk were known to swarm to the lake's bittersweet magic and, if seen, could serve as guides. Paros worried that Baphomet posed a serious threat to the flowerfolk. Fez unhelpfully misheard Baphomet as \"Bear Vomit.\"</p>\n<p>Paros went on to insult human-fox news in front of Curculio, and admitted that sourced his own news from the psychic manifestation of an evil entity known as Veenock. Curculio mentioned another friend of hers, Zadee (a competent [^verb runt], which Fez believed unlikely until told of the logically rigorous 63-letter alphabet employed by many canids.</p>\n<p>Curculio, took a moment to size up Turtle's gastronomical potential, proceeding to describe her home cuisine of [^schilpad stoofpot]. Fez declared himself \"His Seaness\" -- a necessary ego boost before the kitsune maligned a halfling language orthography for consisting of only \"bowls and sticks.\" Fez was put in mind of Doodril Frogwart's&nbsp;Bowls and Sticks: a Confusing language for a Charming people; an Abecedarium or alphabetical Primer&nbsp;published through Doodle's Toodles, an \"young readers\" imprint of Frogwart's primary publisher. Curculio mentioned Doodril Frogwart's Secular Healing Clinic in Marshbout, the not-unsuspicious vanguard of a series of similar clinics popping up in the major cities, and the primary distributor of the&nbsp;Secular Ministrations, a copy of which Paros lifted from the Castle Karn library. Drav was able to confirm that Frogwart was not only prolific, but prolithic, as he had penned a few flimflammminy articles on healing crystals. Paros unsuccessfully attempted to recall the method for extracting malt sugar (maltose) from barley, disappearing into one of his familiar reveries and dreaming about the fancypencils he used at the castle. Out of nowhere, Fez, determined to save the face of his people, declared that \"in our world, flowers are the children's money.\"</p>\n<h3 id=\"theghostinthewoods\"><strong>The ghost in the woods</strong></h3>\n<p>Continuing south through the forest, the group came across an innocuous ghost trapped in what appeared to be an ghostly, evolving maze. When Fez approached, he was recognized by the spirit, which resolved into the likeness of of Cpt. Merrigold. Juna revealed that the death of Von Veen released her from her piscine hybrid form; however, before she could arrive at the ultimate destination on her postmortem journey, she was redirected into the limitless maze in which she now found herself. With Baphomet's influence in play, Drav thought it highly likely that an entity enjoying a boon of Baphomet, allowing one to encase people or spirits in demiplanar mazes, might be siphoning life energy from Juna.</p>\n<p>As Fez retreated into the [^seomra crann] to clear his head and bladder, Paros, Curculio, and Drav notioned using Turtle as merely a catalyst and seasoning for a \"turtle bath stew.\" Informing Fez of this upon his return, the overconfident halfling opined on the fox fur stew so favored by halfling-kind. Curculio slashed Fez across the face for this insult, interjecting that her mother had died in the Foxpelt Wars, but then apologized when Fez clarified that the fur in the stew was merely shorn from willing foxes rather than made of their pelts. Paros forgot the difference between the words \"hasty\" and \"tasty\" before trying to work out with Fez the mathematics of a hypothesized interdimensional snail for which every journey was \"an hour and 50 miles.\"</p>\n<h3 id=\"tusternoof\"><strong>Tusternoof</strong></h3>\n<p>At that point, the gang witnessed Juna's form torn apart like curtains being drawn open as an entish creature with a motile deerskull for a head, vines and leaves streaming off its body like a tattered cloak, stepped through the opening. Announcing itself as \"Tusternoof\" or \"The twisted one,\" it attempted to imprison the adventurers in mazes like that restraining Juna. After a debate on the competing merits of halfing, grenlich, and tusternoofian land husbandry, The twisted one provided a possible clue to locating the mirror lake. Paros, realizing the unmined potential of Tusternoof's knowledge, sank deep into its mind as Fez found himself sucked into a mindmaze. Tusternoof unwittingly revealed the 'org chart' of Baphomet's followers (of which he confirmed himself a boon'd lieutenant), including a shadowy cult of [^urush mekh] handling intricate metalwork skullcaps made of a reddish-gold alloy.</p>\n<p>Fez harnessed the incredible power of his mind-thoughts and collapsed the carceral psychic construct, appearing back on the material plan in a series of thin slices which coalesced into his physical form -- an event which would certainly not have any future effect on him. Drav and Paros summarily defeated Tusternoof with well-placed blobs of pure elemental energy.</p>\n<h3 id=\"flowerfolk\"><strong>Flowerfolk</strong></h3>\n<p>With the monster dead, the forest sprang to life, and Fez was drawn to a member of the Flowerfolk (or&nbsp;bloemenwet) in a nearby tree. The creature, named Ashtai, resembled a domestic rabbit comprised entirely of pale red and violet flower petals, and declared itself in the midst of its vacation. Paros shattered the tranquility of its aestivation by warning Ashtai of Baphomet's plans to absorb the power of the Flowerfolk. Using Ashtai as a signal booster, Paros harness his bracer to telepathically premonish the bloemenwet on the Slubber, receiving in return nothing but visions of holocaust. Unsure as to whether this was an oracle or had already transpired, Paros communicated his anxiety to the party. Drav recalled reading the minutes of a colloquendo conducted by dwarven geomancers: they had discussed an ancient earth spirit, Mogesh, which was reputed to guard and protect the Slubber. Drav suggested that perhaps Mogesh could be convinced to extend its aegis to the bloemenwet.</p>\n<p>The group pondered what step to take next.</p>\n<p><strong>&mdash; Artemis Tapples</strong></p>\n<hr />\n<p>[^verb runt] stenographer; amanuensis; scribe&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a title=\"show-mrah crown\" href=\"http://localhost:8080/recap/pr\">^seomra crann</a>: bathroom; lit. \"tree room\" in halfling</p>\n<p>[^schilpad stoofpot] turtle-and-rosepetal stew made customarily from auroch-bladder-sized turtles found in seaside collections of nearly frictionless stones sliding back and forth with the tide along thin trenches</p>\n<p>[^urush mekh] whatever dang creature Tusternoof is</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h1 id=\"transcript\">Transcript</h1>\n<p>all just defeated kolmy thaz being talked into returning to village by flick</p>\n<p>Curculio message brought to me by raven ; one of the clues might indicate that might friend might be somwhere around here. they had mentioned something about a lake. after they had been trapped in this area by a lake they couldn&rsquo;t get out of. wodden (friend) somehow managed to break the spell and get out of the vicinity. and i heard there is a lake nearby like that. it moves around and it difficult to locate. if you know the area well we might be able to</p>\n<p>fez intrigued by idea of a body of water that&rsquo;s not always in the same place. rides over on Turtle.</p>\n<p>curculio: riding or eating: fez: mostly riding; it does eat things tho</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the turtle will bite or eat, but won&rsquo;t be bitten or eaten C: the ones we ate looked like big beach balls. only nominally turtles fez: ball-based C: discovered them near rocks rounded by action of ocean; slide around almost frictionlesssly in trenches. you do have a bit of the sea to you. fez is &ldquo;his sea-ness&rdquo;; john sea-nuh</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>halfling is a language, and written infrequently, and fez speaks it dm: language is just the bottom half of the alphabet &ldquo;bowls and sticks: a confusing language for a charming people; an abecedarium or alphabetical primer&rdquo; published by doodle&rsquo;s toodle&rsquo;s Doodril Frogwart&rsquo;s juvenile imprint. has these suspicious clinics that pop up . Doodril Frogwarts secular healing clinic in marshbout.</p>\n<p>paros already picked up the secular ministrations</p>\n<p>fez: is he really prolific? dm: he&rsquo;s pro-lithic. drav has read some of his rock-based essays</p>\n<ul>\n<li>doodril is a [rock symbol in shape of a g] + nome . his letters are shorter than halfling letters.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>paros tries to remember how to make sugar. from malt?</p>\n<p>drav recalls she read something by doodril about rocks. and healing (basically healing crystals) . you don&rsquo;t need the powers of the gods or magical powers. thought to be somewhat of a crank or weirdo. techniques reminded you of what foldorf was able to do.</p>\n<p>i remind angela who foldorf was</p>\n<p>drav: let&rsquo;s go &hellip; find this lake i guess</p>\n<p>paros falls out of the sugar reverie and can move his limbs. starts day-dreaming about a sweet fancy pencil he was using at castle karn. couldn&rsquo;t use pens.</p>\n<p>drav: curculio, do you have any idea how to find this lake?</p>\n<p>curculio: it&rsquo;s south of Thubudder forest, and i was coming from up north; if you go too far south you hit the coast. i guess we can find someone who knows once we get into that area drav: the lake is not invisible? curculio: yeah, you can see it, but it can trap you within its borders, or move around,</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the lake is &ldquo;fair&rdquo; &mdash; a knowledge of judicial rationing. it&rsquo;s fair skinned and around an amusement park (near lake were strange, overly-playful flower children; little animals made out of flowers) if we can find them, we might be able to locate the lake paros: i&rsquo;ve heard about flower people fez: the flowers are the children&rsquo;s money. in our world, (halflings) flowers equal dollars paros: there&rsquo;s a serious threat on the horizon to the FP C: why exhibiting such levity? P: well i heard about it through alternate channels fez: (whispers) &ldquo;the grapevine&rdquo; C &gt; insight check.</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>[54] paros: well it&rsquo;s not like fox news C: what&rsquo;s wrong with my news?! P: i have a strong suspicion that the person telling me is evil. have you ever heard of veenock? C: no. P: this veenock talks to me sometimes &hellip; C looks to D and F. drav shrugs. Fez: seems like there&rsquo;s a lot of that going around these days. not being fully conscious. having strange visions. P: there&rsquo;s something called Baphomet trying to kill the flower people. C: there&rsquo;s BAphomet. sometimes people get confused. fez: ohhh, not THE VOMIT ?</p>\n<p>dm: i should set sadie up as court stenographer fez: i don&rsquo;t think she could do it dm: i am offended &mdash; the letters are a paw, and you leave out one or more of the foot pads</p>\n<p>C: baphomet is one of the demons. [also something called DEMONTS because i mistyped?] P: i think B just wants to eat them C: yeah we would put rose petals in turtle stew back in the home country. i don&rsquo;t know that i&rsquo;d try to escape hell to try to do that. P: they could be really good F: [bemused] [tries to contain laughter] absolutely not C: i&rsquo;m assuming B hasn&rsquo;t been seen on this plane &hellip; ?</p>\n<p>I give everyone an inspiration point for figuring out 4-way video</p>\n<p>curculio is going to head there now D: i&rsquo;m in P: sounds interesting C: you may want to work through your psych problems. i&rsquo;ve heard of this great guy who does non-religious healing. Doodril P: oh yeah C: he used to write all sorts of tracts, but now he&rsquo;s a commercial enterprise and v/h integrate.</p>\n<pre>matt: natural light is wonderful\nmick: negative\n</pre>\n<p>they start walking in the forest see a ghostly presence in the forest 3-4 feet tall; shorter than drav it&rsquo;s in the underbrush; about 40 ft away looks more like a very worldly halfling</p>\n<p>** fez is great at everything (lie)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>good at persuasion (CHA); athletics (+1); insight (so, wisdom)</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>f having trouble telling difference between ghost and moderately sized spiderwebs outside they get shit stealth making quite a bit of noise as they head over looks like it&rsquo;s trapped in a rectangular space like a roomba that&rsquo;s moving rooms / cycles through fixed boundaries</p>\n<p>ghost: how did you get in here? in this maze with me? i&rsquo;ve been trapped in this gigantic hedge maze, but i can&rsquo;t do anything to them C: are you a revenant? do we have to solve a problem? ghost: no, i&rsquo;m trapped here for some reason. fez: no&hellip; ghost: a revenant wants to complete its goal in life ghost: that voice sounds so familiar to me fez: juna?! juna: fez, i&rsquo;m really getting put through the ringer here fez: what happened at the end? june: the baron was keeping me coherent, and i dissipated, and my understanding is now totally upturned. my spirit was going somewhere, and on the way i was captured and put into this space, an infinite maze. i can&rsquo;t tell how long i&rsquo;ve been here.</p>\n<p>drav: you know that some of baphomet&rsquo;s lieutenants have this power. while the people are there, power / life force can be sapped from them. their anxiety and mental struggle generates arcane and religious energy. might be a sign that baphomet&rsquo;s making stronger roots in the area.</p>\n<p>fez: we have to plan an aMAZEing rescue juna: i haven&rsquo;t seen anyone else; as a mariner, this is a little bit beyond my knowledge C: traveling minstrel, almost fez goes to the bathroom C goes over to the turtle and pokes at it to see if it&rsquo;s tasty meat =&mdash; are you sure he doesn&rsquo;t eat these?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>a little less meaty than i&rsquo;d expect</li>\n<li>turtle bath stew? through the turtle out with the bathwater fez gets back C: using turtle maybe as a catalyst for a stew fez: i haven&rsquo;t had fox fur stew &mdash; favored among halflings</li>\n<li>she claw-slaps fez &mdash; give him a clawmark paros: we could make a turtle-fox-bath stew</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>my mother died in the fox-pelt wars. fez and you won&rsquo;t eat my turtle! and we just shave the hair ? C: oh, ok, i guess I over-reacted P; did you say hasty or tasty</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>tuesday thursday friday matt works from home &gt;&gt; he did it for a whole year once ; he used to not leave the house for a whole week &gt;&gt;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;an hour and 50 miles&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&ldquo;it&rsquo;s like travelling on the back of an interdimensional snail&rdquo; &ldquo;because the distance isn&rsquo;t necessarily a constant&rdquo;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>catching angela up</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>fez can understand the turtle but they can&rsquo;t communicate yet ? it already has a name fez doesn&rsquo;t know what it is: it has said it to him, but he doesn&rsquo;t know what it is (in sound) we can understand each other, but i can&rsquo;t speak his language yet just says &ldquo;the turtle&rdquo;</p>\n<p>fez rubs his cheek and uses 15 HP NOT what doodril is writing about. it&rsquo;s absent-minded for fez</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>\"i'm not in charge of your eurekas&rdquo;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>P: like a baby snake. they dump all their venom.</p>\n<p>standing there, attempting to communicate with Juna fez used the tree room contributes to green house effect: slap on an explicit label</p>\n<p>fez: how are we going to rescue juna paros: i have a rope, and i toss it to juna merrigold</p>\n<p>creature like small ent, but instead of weird ent head, it has a deer skull, and humanoid limbs that are living tree. small living tree with deerskull face, and streaming off of it like a tattered cloak are vines and leaves and vegetative matter.</p>\n<p>Tusternoof: no getting your friend out of there; but you&rsquo;re welcome to find your own ways own Paros: we&rsquo;re not in there, silly creature</p>\n<p>rolling initiative T: &ldquo;names have no power. mortals like you call me &lsquo;the twisted one&rsquo;&rdquo; P: let&rsquo;s get that Tosser n00b F: can you spell it? T: stick. stick. little bowl. are you getting it?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>no, i&rsquo;m not gonna spell it for you. look it up in your stupid books fez: how much does &ldquo;tossernoob&rdquo; suck T: i suck nutrients up from the soil and stuff paros: why can&rsquo;t we be friends? t: you want to be friends: come into my house P: sees maze runner / the shining hedge maze paros does 19 fire damage</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- -->\n<p>T: soon you&rsquo;re going ot be so confused by my talking &hellip; it&rsquo;ll be like you&rsquo;re in a maze already fez: [gets turtle to come over and he hops on it] T: what a beautiful riding turtle! (gets hit) I take it back. your turtle sucks. i hope somebody eats him. &lt;&gt; T: stop filling me up with