{"_id":"n76RA7ytTBdFK2AL","name":"Udrek","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"wf40lADkdvhEIKuG","sort":400000,"flags":{},"content":"<ul>\n<li><p>vivarium (bf/gf trapped in other dimension to raise an alien)</p></li>\n<li><p>Or, from kid’s perspective, he’s raised by creatures he despises while also meeting with his “real” parents. - interesting for Udrek — the issue is, in real brood mimickry, they think it’s theirs - so who was he raised by? (ooh, maybe Thuridan and other evil firbolgs do this kind of changeling work with intelligence trolls / trollkin)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>or, even, these trolls essentially have their intelligence stolen and are 'reduced' to trollkin to be herded.</li></ul>\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->\n<!-- --></li>\n<li><p>Charles II of Spain died childless in 1700, but he left no children. Thus the discussion started who had the right to own the lands he left. So Udrek was a compromise between x and y</p></li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->\n<h2 id=\"appearance\">appearance</h2>\n<p>The huge hobgoblin looks like it’s been carved from wood, and has terrifying white eyes (a hobgolem if you will, says Flick, bragging of her intelligence)</p>\n<h2 id=\"habits\">habits</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>does not drink (or, by extension, use depressants)</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->\n<!-- -->"}
{"_id":"nDd5duRXiH8MKAL0","name":".factions","permission":{"default":0,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3},"folder":"srmjxCv4QHqVw5AK","sort":2000001,"flags":{},"content":"<ul>\n<li>Pigs of cheese</li>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-6575f9da-7fff-0790-2c59-6e125e2523cb\">the Society of the Water with the Sun</span></li>\n<li>\"the hounds of love\" exist in this world - trudy</li>\n<li>Defectors</li>\n<li>Iron-Headed Hounds (could also be actual hound that have metal horns or something growing out of their heads)</li>\n<li>Felicity &amp; Innocence</li>\n<li>Redintegration of the World</li>\n<li>Misoneists (haters of innovation)</li>\n<li>Girouettists (changing opinion based on literally weather)</li>\n<li><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">The countenance of selfless mercy&nbsp; (where?)</span></li>\n<li>The Hyperplastics vs. the Hypertrophics</li>\n<li>The Ring of Infinite Light</li>\n<li>Hug of the Tarnisher</li>\n<li>The true kleptos / Hlifan (thieves)</li>\n<li>Creatures born in the old crown</li>\n<li>[they love] Old Blood</li>\n<li>The abscess/absinthe/absence&nbsp; formerly known as wax</li>\n<li>Epiphanoids</li>\n</ul>"}
{"_id":"nU20PoOeMgaaOLxv","name":"Session 22 (Riding the Neightmare: it will be blood — Enix Bretcock)","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"Tbev7nPs0FJzqZih","sort":0,"flags":{},"content":"<p>Saturday, April 4, 2020</p>\n<p>Level 5</p>\n<p>Day 8</p>\n<h1 id=\"recap\">Recap</h1>\n<h2 id=\"thebattlecontinues\">the battle continues</h2>\n<p>Flick suffered a run of bad luck, first in attempting a coolly unimpressive waddle between a pair of rocks, and then in getting Scrobs'd by a effluxion of sticky sweat. Exuviae thought she saw a true convert in Fez, but upon anointing him with holy chrism (chunky style) the thriste<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/recap/8#fn1\">[1]</a>&nbsp;halfling resisted the compulsion to wrestle naked in honor of the leprechaunic horse. Exuviae admitted that she enjoyed being a member of the bourgeois-leisure class insofar as she was able to provide a similar service&nbsp;gratis&nbsp;to interested members of the burgher demographic. She then turned a scatological imprecation into a confession, revealing that the ring of realistic genital molds kept her trapped in this ring. Carlos attempted to sell out Jean-Luc's jewels (or their negative image), before agreeing with Flick's idea to destroy the integrity of the procreant<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/recap/8#fn2\">[2]</a>&nbsp;ring, a task to which they committed themselves once assured of Scrobs's neutrality by the wacky equine. Scrobs, despite the detente, remained a chip off the old block, and danced around the wood elf provocatively in hopes of eliciting a wrestling match.</p>\n<h2 id=\"smashandstab\">smash and stab</h2>\n<p>Drav, cautious of the possibly toxic genital dust pluming from Carlos's maddened swings, drew into herself, and recalled learning that rituals with similar terrestrial geometry, in the absence of a transcendental power, typically conjured their objects in pairs according to the most powerful axis of polarization: in this case, good and evil (or so she thought). Paros, spaced out for reasons altogether unrelated to his proximal physical environment recalled an ecological text which contended that the natural products of certain ancient worms had the tendency to appear differently to surface dwellers. Drav's suspicions aroused, she began further examining the rocks, and quickly determined that the igneous layer was a mere shell over a viscous brown substance.</p>\n<p>As Flick went to inform everyone of the 'planar anomalies' caused by boggle teleportations, the image of Daealla appeared to her through a Scrobs puddle and enjoined Flick to cease destroying the protective genital ring. As Flick remained unable to tear Daealla from the mirror world for a tete-a-tete, and Drav considered the implications of ancient earth-moving entities, Fez noticed that Exuviae had become transfixed by Daealla's genitals, transformed into a shining vector of pure radiant light visible in the nearest puddle.</p>\n<p>Stuck in this stalemate, Daealla confessed that the peryton raiding the gnolls had once been a fey succubus named Calliope, whose draining Kiss had been extracted into a literal and symbolic daughter named Aphelia to reduce the number of enucleated men pledging themselves to the ancient horrors. Attending to the matters at hand, the gang took a moment to catch their collective breath and then precipitously lit all the collected genitals on fire in one of the oil pits, occasioning the transformation of one of the larger rock benches into the malicious form of Gedhtathgon, a totally metal black knight, at whose beck and call Exuviae transformed into Hengest the Violent, the Neightmare of renown.</p>\n<hr />\n<section>\n<ol>\n<li id=\"fn1\">\n<p>Bold, daring; audacious, presumptuous.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/recap/8#fnref1\">↩︎</a></p>\n</li>\n<li id=\"fn2\">\n<div>Of, relating to, or enabling procreation.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/recap/8#fnref2\">↩︎</a></div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h1>Transcript</h1>\n<p>flick: unimpressive \"acrobatics\" to waddle between the rocks.</p>\n<p>orange, but purple veins in it the color of scrobs' body. dc-18 strenght saving throw or be restrained (oh, scrob's restraint puddle)</p>\n<p>exuviae does cream-cheese oil all over fez (i give him advantage because he's protected from good and evil) -- but also it's a charm spell and he's immune to charm</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>fez still covered in oil</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>fez tries to make it seem like it's not the grossest thing ever.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>exuviae: you like it! is this part of your normal morning routine.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>sect of halflings somewhere that does this to themselves.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>performed \"Traditional halfling ablutions\" on you -- for nothing. how's that a waste?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>exuviae gets others to do things for it, and likes being a member of the leisure class</p>\n<ul>\n<li>misses hoof attack on fez</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick: fuck you!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>exuviae: if would make it easier to fuck me with a copy of your genitals</p>\n<ul>\n<li>it's the main reason i'm trapped here.</li>\n<li>druids try to keep themselves in wrestling salad days.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick insight[20] -- not lying about being trapped here. when it's on this plane, it has to come to this area. (i'm giving a lot for a 20)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>would you not being fighting us to the death now?</li>\n<li>exuviae : with the druids in me, hard to resist. but also pissed about druids getting firebombed. half and half. we really just wanted copies of this cool blonde-haired dude's genitals.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick: could you break out of this thing?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>you're not who we came here to deal with. i want to stop this if we can.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>carlos: can jean-luc just give up his genitals.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>exuviae: the models are what keep me here.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>could try to destroy them all. i can't touch them myself.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick: can you call off scrobs?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>scrobs: yeah i'll stand down.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick gets knives and carlos gets hammer to destroy genitals</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>scrobs tries to get flick to wrestle him.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>exuv: not sure how much destroying them will be complete effect.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>drav: the intent is to bind something evil from the hells; if they are too powerful, they have to bind one of each to balance them off (OR if they don't have enough to ... sacrifice)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>paros: formation of molds, through the action of words, with observations on their habits</p>\n<ul>\n<li>certain ancient worms. underneath the surface, their excretions end up looking like different things above ground.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>drav: stonework check [25]: these rocks aren't carrying vibrations or sounds. almost like they're not the same composition all the way through.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>carlos smashing genitals; genital dust getting everywhere.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>drav chips away at the rock; \"it will be blood\"</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick tells them how fucked up planarly the circle is.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick sees daealla in mirror image.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\"you have to stop that\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick: make me an offer</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>daealla: we have her trapped for a reason. if exuviae gets out, then her nightmare twin gets out at the same time.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick: can i pull you out of the oil plane?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>daealla: i am where you see me, but things look different down here.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick smacks the circle of the oil pool with his planar force</p>\n<ul>\n<li>should i have done something different here?</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>drav: think it has something to do with ancient earth-moving entities who could turn rocks into blood and work with the fundamental constituents of the universe. it's value-neutral.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>exuviae transfixed by the opposite of a black bar: a white cylinder. poking out at you. over genitals of daealla. image.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>daealla: the nightmare has a black coat and fiery red mane; bright red eyes. hooves made of obsidian.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>carlos: i think we need to let the nightmare out and separate these things.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>maybe there will be a purely good unicorn to fight on our side; and the druids.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>asking daealla about calliope</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>we do tend to get ourselves in straits trying to fix problems</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>peryton was a fey creature whose name was calliope.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>was a succubus. \"sexomancy\"</li>\n<li>she wasn't as voracious as a fiend from hell or something like that would have been; but what she was doing became a problem - those she had fed off of ; weren't reduced to husks, but they became susceptible to recruitment by some of the more dangerous cults in the area. esp. ones connected to creatures that have existed before even some of the gods. tried to extract this power.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>in this form she's compelled to try to bring back this power in the form of a child.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>tantegorisch created by trying to order a pizza ?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>calliope was turned 5 or 10 years ago.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick: we might have to kill the peryton. calliope doesn't sound great.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>how would we revert her to fey form? (my magic is more sort of intuitive)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>daealla: something to do with breaking that cycle ?</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>aphelia</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>daealla: the kiss ended up becoming a person.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>carlos: i can't aphelia, i hardly know ya'</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick [20 history]:</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>paros thinks it's the&nbsp;aphelion&nbsp;: furthest part of orbit from sun</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>carlos wants to fight the neightmare</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>paros agrees with carlos: we've solved all of our other problems with violence</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>drav: let's see who aphelia is</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>would aphelia know what she, aphelia, is.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flick: that guy Onfalon: one of the things you learned from him was how to trap certain animals; before you parted that he hinted to you that trapping formed the structural architecture for a lot of the abilities he was able to do as a druid</p>\n<ul>\n<li>or maybe they know something we don't (doubt it) -- to druids, something about basically create of matter and anti-matter spontaneously from the vacuum.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\"short halfling word\" -- if you can finish it before someone finishes their second breakfast.</p>\n<h2>short rest</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>flick wants to make poison.\n<ul>\n<li>survival check, divide by 4, round up</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>paros has:\n<ul>\n<li>naphula ashes</li>\n<li>zarachiel sap</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>carlos has P's sap-wood chunk</li>\n<li>paros can't quite figure out how to make sugar\n<ul>\n<li>takes bread, rubs it around in the oil, and casts fire on it.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>burning genitals</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>flick and carlos: throw all of them in an oil pit and set it alight.\n<ul>\n<li>paros wants to create ray of frost to make them shatter ???</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>set the grease pit on fire with all the genitals in it. (which grease pit: the one exuviae is still staring into)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>set the pit on fire.\n<ul>\n<li>fez [24 perception; nat 20]: the rock with height, dark red liquid starts bubbling out from underneath, and cracks start to form in the outside of the rock. the cracks get wider; material oozes out from cracks. start splitting up like an ice float. soon it's just a bubbling pillar of dark red blood; coming out what look like brains. brainal matter.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\"scrotum: the hanging brains\"</li>\n<li>looks like the blood is cascading from a well armored knight wearing all black plate mail, and as the blood drains off his helmet and his shoulders, he says: Hengest, to Me!!! Exuviae lights on fire, and it's still burning the but the fire rises up from mane and tail, body is pitch black, blows fire out its mouth -- and he pulls himself onto the horse.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\"ride the nightmare\"</p>\n<p>initiative: flick, 23 fez: 6 paros: 15, carlos: drav: 17</p>\n</section>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"nXHcfmxaCj7VSfuf","name":"000 Day by day","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"YQonjgXSLBnFUZ2O","sort":100000,"flags":{},"content":"<h1>Day 1</h1>\n<p><strong>&sect;001. Marshboutwards. September 21, 2019. Level 1. (Swaddlington P. Footh)&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>Flick and Joan travel south from Cressida to Marshbout. They inquire of Perchmaster Buddock the goings-on, and are directed to Norman Barrelchest, one of the town's current constables. Meanwhile, Drav and Carlos hitch a ride with a cloud giant from the east and by chance head straight for the armory as well.</p>\n<p><strong>&sect;002.&nbsp;&nbsp;Love at first lightning sparks.&nbsp; October 5, 2019. Level 1. (Purdie I. Rademacher)</strong></p>\n<p>Unfortunately, Norman was pulled out of the building by a group of rowdy rownsfolk demanding redress about something or other. Carlos stole some supplies from the medical cabinet with Joan's help while Flick extracted the location of one 'Lupenna' (who she hoped held an answer to the mystery of her birth and the figurine given to her then) from the remaining staff. These four newly met sojourners agreed to proceed together for a variety of reasons we won't look at too closely. Passing through Thubutter Farest on their way to Castle Karn (where Lupenna was rumored to be holed up) they survived an attack by dogs corrupted by evil vegetative magic.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>&sect;003. A satisfying rom-vom. October 12, 2019. (Ludmilla Sperski)</strong></p>\n<p>More isolated inhabitants of the creepy 'Farest' made themselves known to the group, including squipiderlings, chondric mushroom fetuses, shy but mechanically-savvy trickster bears, and a human sorcerer going by the name Paros. Soon, however, the trappings of civilization appeared and, after a few impermanent martial understandings, the group, defeating an <em>immor</em> ^ with the help of their new friend and a few witherlings, were welcomed into a gnoll village.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>&sect;004. Small potatoes. October 26, 2019. (</strong><strong>Hingleburt Tauncelledonque, esq.)</strong></p>\n<p>They traded tales with the gnolls, who suspected that a gnoll named Grenlich was responsible for the fetus mushrooms and perhaps the plant-dogs.&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Day 2</h1>\n<p>Everyone slept in an abandoned house and woke the next morning to the screams of the townsfolk as one of their number was brought in&nbsp;<em>sans</em> heart. The adventurers and the gnolls repelled an attack by flying mushroms-heads. Lorekeeper Shortpaw informed them that many of these attacks had been occurring, and she suspected they were being perpetrated by a peryton residing in the Goblinsmite Peaks.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>&sect;005. A warm sense of nostalgia for the wordplay of half-elves. November 16, 2019. (Ludmilla Sperski)</strong></p>\n<p>Flick and Joan returned to Marshbout to collect Drav, who had returned the previous day to study up at the Famasta Monastery's well-stocked Doodril Library. On the way back all three were waylaid by Thuridan, a suspicious firbolg who provided information about a potentially helpful group of druids in the northwest of the Farest. Thuridan's magic bubble deposited them close to the gnoll village, where Carlos continued to work his healing trade. Since the trail of the flying mushrooms had gone cold, and the peryton was nowhere to be seen, Flick, Joan, Carlos, Paros and Drav set out for the Grey Tongue and Castle Karn. As night began to fall they entered a portentous abbey surrounded by wooden crosses.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>&sect;006. [Untitled]. November 23, 2019. ([unauthored])</strong></p>\n<h1>Day 3</h1>\n<p><strong>&sect;007.&nbsp;</strong><strong>My divine inspiration is from me.</strong><strong>&nbsp;December 07, 2019 (Melinda Pentelow)</strong></p>\n<p>Under questioning, Domonkos revealed he knew of Lupenna and her father Raul, a client of Tantegorische. Suddenly, they were attacked by a gigantic squidlike creature Domonkos referred to cryptically as Mogh. With the help of the Kulgmarkers, they defeated the beast without severe injury to themselves. Unexpectedly, its death allowed the trapped spirit of Domonkos to escape and merge with his body. He let everyone out of the cave by a secret back route. The Kulgmark dwarves trotted back to their kingdom and Flick quickly put it together that Paros had been charmed by the vampire.&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>&sect;008 Blue dragon, candy, an accounting. December&nbsp;14, 2019. (J. McClintock)</strong></p>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Unbeknownst to them, they had been trailed by a sap demon since slicing the mysterious wooden pole in the woods, and it emerged to claim vengeance just as Baba Jezda, a nighthunter guardian, emerged to imprison Domonkos once more. To complicate matters, a baby Mogh grew from Domonkos's back, and a group of gnomes let by Polive Pittlans helped them defeat the demon and temporarily banish Baba Jezda.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>&sect;009. Sap, sugar, butter, flour (nightmare remix). December 21, 2019. (Guck-iin-zehr-Luft)</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">They accompany the gnoes back to their Candy Lab, whereupon they all begin to suspect some evil afoot. Flick detects a new portal.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>&sect;010. The day the skeletons came to life. January 4, 2019. ([?])</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">[?]</p>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</div>\n<h1 dir=\"ltr\">Day 4</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[...]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>(i think i added a day by accident. Day 13 should be 12, and Day 14 should be 13?) - will have to fix in episode-by-episode too.</p>\n<h1>Day 13&nbsp;</h1>\n<p><strong>&sect;<span style=\"color: #191813;\">045: Sister light, sister dark</span></strong></p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Explosion and figuring things out.&nbsp;</p>\n</section>\n<p>Jean-Luc easily brushed aside a dumb twee riddle employing the nonconsensual labor of a Zorbo, and the gang exited the below-stairs. They traveled north to the Gaol Maiden's supposed headquarters in the seacoveson the other side of the Strigge River: Flick summoned Gerd to fly everyone across the river, and they made their way as cautiously as possible to the mouth of the cave and towards a mysterious glowing light. Unfortunately, suffering possibly from residual air sickness, even the stealthy passage of Jean-Luc was noticed, and they were immediately set upon by a veteran snaphance or thief arrant.</p>\n<p>&gt;&gt;&gt; not tense edited</p>\n<p><strong>&sect;046: &alpha;ὐ&tau;ὰ&rho; ἐ&pi;&epsilon;ὶ &pi;&alpha;ύ&sigma;&alpha;&nu;&tau;&omicron; &pi;ό&nu;&omicron;&upsilon; &tau;&epsilon;&tau;ύ&kappa;&omicron;&nu;&tau;ό &tau;&epsilon; &delta;&alpha;ῖ&tau;&alpha;, &delta;&alpha;ί&nu;&upsilon;&nu;&tau;᾿, &omicron;ὐ&delta;έ &tau;&iota; &theta;&upsilon;&mu;ὸ&sigmaf; ἐ&delta;&epsilon;ύ&epsilon;&tau;&omicron; &delta;&alpha;&iota;&tau;ὸ&sigmaf; ἐΐ&sigma;&eta;&sigmaf;&middot;</strong></p>\n<p>Proving quite hardy, the&nbsp;ceathairneach&nbsp;Scunner remains standing long enough to be rescued by Breg, a salt-and-pepper dwarven geomancer who begins to throttle Jean-Luc with a massive granite hand that rises from the floor. A temporary truce is called, and on Scunner's thiefly word, and the gang's almost complete disavowel of the Hat Baskets, they are allowed further into the caves, where are situated a giant salamander, a lizardfolk shaman and about half a dozen similarly dressed humans. They appear to be engaged in mining a muted blue crystalline ore, but before the adventurers can enter, the oldest human, Fundi, runs over and prevents the group from entering the ritual mining space -- for such it is -- until they've passed a bevy of personal questions. The mining team deliver their own side of the \"stolen logbook\" story, which is that the Hat Baskets stole the giant salamander's baby mandling and they hoped for a hostage exchange by stealing the book, whose power Breg believes too great to leave in Hat Basket hands. The adventurers immediately back this new horse and plan to retrace their steps to recover \"Nubbs.\" Everyone gets drunk and goes to sleep.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Day 14</h1>\n<em>&raquo; Day of the Snaking Waters</em>\n<p><strong>&sect;046 [cont.]</strong></p>\n<p>The adventurers continue to party and pass out in the caves.</p>\n<p><strong>&sect;047: The Order of Rust</strong></p>\n<p>Flick emerges from her elven trance with worrisome gaps in her memory from the previous evening; suspecting foul play, she wakes Jean-Luc to check Nyuaka's bag for poisons and narcotics, but they come up empty-handed. Nyuaka's nightmares and their conspiratorial whispering wake Drav and, as yet unbeknownst to the crew, a goblin rune knight named Pjorg (the) Tallhearted down the hall, who had lost consciousness after consuming light exploded from archaic symbols he was studying. As Pjorg creeps towards the encampment, Vengeance is awoken by qi with the urge to swallow and steal as many of the azurite prisms as possible, only to become distracted by the curious pendants worn by the Ruhu family which Vengeance believes an emblem of The Order of Rust. With Eldar's help, Drav blends mystically into the rock floor as Pjorg bursts into the cave; Jean-Luc and Flick disappear into the shadows. Vengeance bagpipes nearly everyone awake, but Pjorg is so conspicuous in his clanging shiny plate armor that all attention focuses on him. After a bit of parlay, everyone decides he means no harm. Nevertheless, the main crew, suspicious of the possibly amnesiogenic azurite after hearing it called the \"Forgetting Stone,\" pick up their bedrolls and return to their landing above the Strigge River.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>&sect;048: This is not for this</strong></p>\n<p>Pjorg translates some runes &bull; Waking up in the caves &bull; Jaap Jansen \"drops\" in &bull; Up and across the river&nbsp; (Gerd redux) &bull; The Fountain of Eloquence &bull; Jean-Luc indulges his alcoholism &bull; Pjorg sets Vengeance off on a wild rust chase &bull; Jaap sees some Gormflaith &bull; Oriax promises a meet-up</p>\n<p><strong>&sect;049:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n</div>"}
{"_id":"nwO42CukD0sTp3BW","name":"032. For a brief moment I have both again","permission":{"default":2,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"3raMqXjxKE8cvKwn","sort":433253,"flags":{},"content":"<div>session date: 2020-06-21 (June 21, 2020)</div>\n<div>game day:&nbsp;</div>\n<div>player level: 6</div>\n<div><hr></div>\n<h1 id=\"recap\">Recap</h1>\n<div>Vek pushes its flesh agenda on Hiero and Jean-luc. Fez refutes Abzû. Amalia, unturned, is killed. Rotrude gives the gift of boils and her handskin. Vek makes a plea for its life. Jean-luc finally gets a star.</div>\n<h1 id=\"transcript\">Transcript</h1>\n<div>Jean-luc, operating under the impression that he is an unmoving puddle of flesh, attempts to gather himself up again using his own dissolving form. Through his lo-res eyespots he is able to locate himself vaguely in the room; occupying the site of the soil on the bar table is a nebulous swirling cloud of dirt and starlight mineral sparkles.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Vek: You have a lot of anxiety. Perhaps just relax into your new form. Why are you resisting this after just having invoked my powers?</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>This rumbling spirit voice can be heard only by Jean-luc and Hieronymus. Hieronymus goes to pour his liquid self into the vase to become one with the spirit.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Vek: Yes, you are already quite of the flesh. I can tell that you, Hieronymus, know the relationship that transpires here.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Jean-luc thinks that the process can be interrupted if he lets the spirit know what is actually going on. More panicked than anything, he attempts to move towards the bar. The intense training he's done over the years is not available to him, and he only slides about ten feet forwards. It feels to him as though he's rolling a fleshball.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Vek: You won't be able to take advantage of what I have to offer if you resist like this.</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc: I'm kind of a fan of having bones.</div>\n<div>- Vek: Why did you even come here, then?</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc: It's a long story. I'm just along for the ride. You may have gotten the wrong idea. I ... didn't mean to offer myself.</div>\n<div>- Vek: Have no doubt you will get your bones back. I can see that already you are intellectualizing this experience, whereas the point is to retreat into yourself, and 'lose' your bones.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc: I'm not quite sure I understand what you mean.</div>\n<div>- Flick: Who would seek out such an experience?</div>\n<div>- Vek: I can hear your friend, but I cannot talk to her unless she becomes one with my network.</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc: That's a hard pass.</div>\n<div>- Vek: One more step closer and I can offer that to her.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Fez, experiencing a lot of new things with his friends around, goes to push over the vase, [Athletics 12], really putting his \"fish-man\" scale-mailed shoulder into it. As he does so, the room rotates around him, the vase, and the table (on a horizontal axis) in the opposite direction that he's pushing. Flick sees that Fez is falling backwards to the floor after initially touching the vase. Fez, desirous of resetting the room, stops pushing the vase and comes to, prone on the ground. Fez notices that his carrying bag is beginning to undulate gently. Upon looking inside, he sees that the conch shell found on the sand after the shipwreck of the Majestic Elk is overflowing with dirt, and that thick green (in between nature and evil) tentacles are emerging from the dirt, like a hermit crab's claws. He takes the conch from the top and places it on the ground.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Abzu: Fez, come to collect on our pact, have you.</div>\n<div>- Fez: New phone, who dis.</div>\n<div>- Abzu: My name is Abzu; it's \"short\" for Adzub. It is likely that your weak half human frame was too discombobulated at the time the pact was made to remember the finer details.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>A rapid-fire clarification of the orthography of the creature's name takes place. Suddenly, the inimitable voice seems to trigger a memory in Fez. ... is it a boomerang? No. It's a \"memory boomerang\" from the sea. As the Majestic Elk was destroyed, and he was dragged under the surface of the ocean, the cries of the sailors of \"Kraken!\" reverberated in his mind, and he found himself wrapped in massive, thick tentacles. His eyes regained focus to find himself staring into huge expressionless eyes, churning like a hurricane. For one of the few times in his life, his self-confidence and ego were subsumed beneath a desperate plea for his life. (This couldn't be right, Fez thinks. I'd never do that.) In the memory, Abzu, for that was the kraken, let him live, as long as he committed to a pact: when it was requested, he would act in service of the beast. Some time later he found himself cast up onto the shore with the conch.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Fez remembers seeing it. The fact that he wasn't confident at the time couldn't be right, but it does seem like it happened to him. Unable to process something like this, he tries to turn away from the months of depression he thought might ensue.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Abzu: There's no need to be depressed. The power I'm willing to give you will compensate for any transient emotional distress.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: It doesn't sound like a great deal, and it conflicts with my visions of more benevolent sea monsters.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Abzu: What is there about me that's not benevolent?</div>\n<div>- Fez: Your creepy voice, your tentacles, and the destruction of a ship.</div>\n<div>- Abzu: Well that ship was in my waters -- and many of those aboard were enemies of the Krakens.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: Why?</div>\n<div>- Abzu: They are a coastal people and have animosity towards those who wish to share the sea with them.</div>\n<div>- Fez: It doesn't seem like you're sharing the sea with them at all -- you were the aggressor.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Abzu: After they demonstrated they were xenophobic, I decided to trade them an eye for an eye.</div>\n<div>- Fez: So the things people did to you, you did back to them. That's not benevolent.</div>\n<div>- Abzu: I protect the sea creatures.</div>\n<div>- Fez: What do you eat?</div>\n<div>- Abzu: Algae.</div>\n<div>- Fez: You sure?</div>\n<div>- Abzu: That's it.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Fez is pretty sure that algae and plankton go towards its diet.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Abzu: The blue whale is even larger than I am, and it's sustained on krill.</div>\n<div>- Fez: Yeah but it's a mammal.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Abzu: Right, so its metabolism is even higher.</div>\n<div>- Fez: So you're saying it's worse than you?</div>\n<div>- Abzu: Is a tortoise worse than a mouse?</div>\n<div>- Fez: Yes.</div>\n<div>- Abzu: You were only recently riding on a turtle.</div>\n<div>- Fez: How do you know that?</div>\n<div>- Abzu: You made a pact with me!</div>\n<div>- Fez: That doesn't sound right. Can you show me where I signed?</div>\n<div>- Abzu: It's not my fault that mortal memory is so easily destroyed.</div>\n<div>- Fez: None of this adds up correctly.</div>\n<div>- Abzu: Fine, if you don't believe me, the next time you go to swipe at one of these many enemies -- attend to what occurs, and it will be clear that I provide your power to you.</div>\n<div>- Fez: Even if that's true, what were the terms of the pact?</div>\n<div>- Abzu: When I need you, you will be there to serve me. A war is brewing, and even these minor excursions by the Teallacht could be dissuaded with your involvement.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: Why are you talking to me now?</div>\n<div>- Abzu: Something about the way you lost life after we made our pact rendered our continued conversations impossible. Through the influence of Vek, you are reduced to what is fundamental about your body, and that has allowed me to talk to you again.</div>\n<div>- Fez: Can we return to our previous relationship? Where you shut the fuck up and I go on my way?</div>\n<div>- Abzu: If you wish</div>\n<div>- Fez: Great -- so be it. And a reminder that this is the first pact I've made with you.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>A discussion of bags, shells, and halfling racism ensues as Fez and Abzu attempt to hang up on one another.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Flick: Yeah -- our adventuring team only has one famous hobbit!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>(From the outside room)</div>\n<div>- Amalia: Carlos!!</div>\n<div>- Flick: What the fuck was that?</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>With Flick's superior elven hearing she can determine that Amalia is still quite far down the hallway. Hieronymus meanwhile slides into Vek's DMs in an attempt to pour himself into the vase.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Hieronymus: Yes, spirit, let us commune. Let me absorb your nutrients and grow into the mighty oak that I have always longed to be.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Vek: Before you become the oak, you must become a grub.</div>\n<div>- Hieronymus: I thought if anything I'd have to become an acorn first.</div>\n<div>- Vek: Acorns are much tougher and resilient than those who come to me wish to be. But you may crawl towards me slowly, little grub.</div>\n<div>- Hieronymus: Uh..... ok!</div>\n<div>- Vek: When you mortify yourself, do you know about the energy that ... flows through the universe.</div>\n<div>- Hieronymus: ... what? Yes, I know all about that. Am I not talking to myself?</div>\n<div>- Vek: This is Vek. Victor. Echo. Karate.</div>\n<div>- Hieronymus: Well, Mr. Vik, I agree, I'd like to become part of you. May we commune in a beautiful fusion of flesh and soil?&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Vek: Yes, I'm glad I don't have to convince you like I do Jean-luc.</div>\n<div>- Heiro: Yes, he's just an old fuddy-duddy who never wants to do anything fun.</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc (nodding): Yeah, both of you enjoy your blood orgy.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Fez [Con 5], hearing Vek's low-decibel, extra-low-frequency whispers, hurls chunks all over the place.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Hiero: I quite like this \"Not having any bones\" thing. Bones, as it turns out, were an unnecessary luxury. Life is a lot simpler this way. I can't wait to harvest this divine energy so I become even more powerful.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Vek: The way to the divine energy is to let go of your bones. To become nothing but flesh.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hiero: So, mission accomplished!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Hieronymus then passes out. Void. Small elven boy. Equally as weird looking. At the horizon of his tunnel his parents are fishing. Instead of physical forms he sees their ki. But looking down at himself he just sees his body: the body of a child. His parents turn to look back at him; as they do he feels an intense, direct hostility coming from them. Then they are yanked out of his vision, and he's left there with no one to protect him.&nbsp;</div>\n<div> - Kid Hiero: Mommy, daddy! Why are you gone before I got a chance to tip your boat over and drown you?!</div>\n<div> - Mom: Heiro, you were always such a rascal. We don't know where you got it from, but it's too much for us, and we're done with you.</div>\n<div> - Kid Hiero: Ohh. Where will I find my ki now? My ky. The key to my existence.</div>\n<div> - Mom: If only you would stop looking -- perhaps then, it will emerge from within you, rather than always stay out of your grasp.</div>\n<div> - Kid Hiero: Stop looking, you say.</div>\n<div> - Mom: Indeed.</div>\n<div>The sky appears to wink, and Kid Heiro takes a whittled wooden dagger and stabs them into his eyes, just like the darts into Shoemaker Byte's eyes. As he does that, he suddenly sees, even eyeless, the pure representation of ki across the night sky. He then wakes up, on the floor of the bar.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Hiero: All has been revealed to me. From this day forward, I shall have a new name: VENGEANCE.</div>\n<div>- Vek: Everyone doooooes experience it differently.</div>\n<div>- Fez: Maybe we need to overload the dirt with non-dirt.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Carlos: Curse this backwards! Curse your curse nuts!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Carlos calls down the divine energy of Aulë to rend the vase apart, but the vase merely jiggles excitedly and settles back on the table.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Carlos: My Hammer! Shatter this perverted symbol of vulgarity!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>The hammer courses towards the glass container and smashes against it. A crack running from base to rim forms, and soil begins to drain out of the vase. Jean-luc for a brief moment senses his cool sturdy bones. He rises to his feet, throwing off the hallucination like a blanket, confident in his sprightly frame. He grabs the kettle and goes to wing it at the vase.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Rotrude: I can finally come up there! Perhaps we can make our way to your dental appointment together.</div>\n<div>- Hiero: I am a changed man, now. I wish to make up with you and go fishing and huckleberry'ing as we once did.</div>\n<div>- Flick: Don't be a simp, Heironymus!</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: That sounds wonderful. Perhaps this time we might bring a chaperone in case one of us needs resuscitation.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Heiro: Well, we're adults. I think we can handle ourselves.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: I certainly believe that you can handle yourself, but I think I might need assistance. I don't know if you were able to drag me from the depths as quickly as I'd like.</div>\n<div>- Heiro: I'm kind of like ... the most powerful person in the world now. I don't have time to explain.</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Have you been off on one of your meditative journeys again? And what is this fascinating energy coming from the room you're in.</div>\n<div>- Heiro: That is the dirt spirit.</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Well I will be right up, and perhaps we do find a chaperone.</div>\n<div>- Heiro: Well, Jean-luc here looks up to me as a mentor and is a good friend, and might fit the bill.</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc: I do not look up to you as a mentor, you crazy asshole!</div>\n<div>- Heiro: Well then Jean-luc perhaps you would like to be the first to jump into the swirling dirt here.</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Your friend sounds audibly disgusted! There is quite a lot of dry-heaving coming from that room.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Flick, encouraged by the crack in the vase, leaps ten feet towards the table on which it rests. She sees Rotrude, dressed in simple blacks and greys and dripping with brackish water, through the open door. She fires a force-arrow at it, but it wraps around the vase like light bending in water. Forgoing a sharpshoot opportunity, she looses a regular arrow, quickly retreating out of the proximity of the vase. Fez, having had a moment to strategize, lashes his whip towards the vase in the hopes of dragging it off the table; the heavy vase smashes against the floor, the lid smashing but the vase remaining upright, still spilling dirt.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Vek: There's no need to destroy me. I was only being invited into your minds by Shoemaker. People usually come to me of their own volition.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Fez recognizes the possible truth of this plea.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Fez: If you want \"Live and let live,\" can you ... go dormant? And we can just leave you?</div>\n<div>- Vek: I wouldn't mind if you deposited my soil in a local ... heap ... of soil.</div>\n<div>- Fez: I, Fezziwig Hornswoggle, (making the 2nd pact of my life) --</div>\n<div>- Abzu: &lt;Would you like to renew our pact?&gt;</div>\n<div>- Fez: No!</div>\n<div>- Vek: Was that a benevolent kraken talking to you?</div>\n<div>- Fez: It was a non-benevolent kraken.</div>\n<div>- Vek: I know of no such thing.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: You're literally dirt.</div>\n<div>- Vek: Dirt is only the vessel through which I can become manifest.</div>\n<div>- Fez: Then how do you know about water creatures?</div>\n<div>- Vek: I don't understand the question.</div>\n<div>- Fez: You retreat your presence into your soil; we will take you out to an inviting spot and deposit you there.</div>\n<div>- Flick (embarrassed at having missed a stationary pot): I agree wholeheartedly</div>\n<div>- Hiero: I agree as well, as long as you allow me to become the seed I have always wanted to be, and implant myself into the soil so that I may become a mighty oak.</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc: Anything that lets me keep my bones is ok with me.</div>\n<div>- Vek: The bones always come back after a time.</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc: Not good enough.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Vek: Heiro, since when have you taken such an interest in plant-life. I thought you were more of a poison guy.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Heiro: Well yes, poison comes from plants. When I was a boy, all I ever wanted to be was a tree.</div>\n<div>- Vek: This is fascinating. and you were aware of this before today's visions?</div>\n<div>- Heiro: Yes, I was. But now -- I have a renewed purpose. Like when you come back from a year abroad. I know now that I cannot simply be a tree (altho I would like to try that at some point). I have to find the sorceress and give her a good wallop after I am powerful enough to do so.</div>\n<div>- Vek: As a plea for my continued accompaniment, if you look inwards towards yourself you will see that our interaction has renewed your connection with Ki. [Heiro recovers 6 ki points.]</div>\n<div>- Fez: If I wanted to dispose of a seashell and have it decompose in the dirt. And the malevolent presence inside it.</div>\n<div>- Vek: Yes, it could work. There is a risk that it could escape from the physical constraint. A pretty high risk. I don't like to overestimate my skills.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: Is it like a minimal effort for you? Or you and Hieronymus could co-exist with that power.</div>\n<div>- Vek: If it's a shell, I'm not sure I would be up to the task. It's hard to convince a shell to return to its fleshy blob state.</div>\n<div>- Fez: What about a kraken?</div>\n<div>- Vek: A little tadpole kraken?</div>\n<div>- Fez: Yeah ... he fits in this shell.</div>\n<div>- Vek: Then possibly.</div>\n<div>- Fez: Well what if it happens to be a small version of a larger kraken.</div>\n<div>- Vek: I am good at suppressing spirits if they can be isolated from their physical forms. It's rare for krakens to be spirits, though.</div>\n<div>- Fez: Can they communicate at a distance?</div>\n<div>- Vek: If you made a pact with them. The Quacken.</div>\n<div>- Fez: I'm not typically in the business of not honoring my pacts, so I'll just keep it.</div>\n<div>- Vek: You're the kind of guy who, no matter what he's doing, _thinks_ he's honoring a pact.</div>\n<div>- Fez: That is deeply true. Because of tautology.</div>\n<div>- Vek: This explains a lot, really.</div>\n<div>- Fez: Are you and Hieronymus going to become a tree together?</div>\n<div>- Vek: Hieronymus may have misunderstood what the soil component of me is for.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Hieronymus: All I wanted was to soil myself. I don't understand why that's so hard</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: We can soil one another together once I get up there!</div>\n<div>- Hiero: I know I said we could be friends again, but that was a passing mood, so I don't want to see you.</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: So you want a 'two-hurls-one-monk' situation?</div>\n<div>- Hiero: No. No.</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Why not? If you don't desire me, what do you wish for?</div>\n<div>- Heiro: I can take care of it. Just please retreat to your dungeons or your catacombs, wherever you came from. [Fails a persuasion check]</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Oh, I can tell you're just kidding. I'll be right up.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Jean-luc moves as far as he can from Vek and upturns a bottle of disgusting, yet effective, hard spirits. The liquid is quite murky. Fez notices that one of his whip tassles is poking out of Vek's soil, and he goes to wiggle it free, but comes up with just a root.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Vek: I do love a good head massage. Whatever you want to call it.</div>\n<div>- Fez: My apologies.</div>\n<div>- Vek: Yes, you are coming to know yourself through my intervention.</div>\n<div>- Fez: NOW who's overly confident?</div>\n<div>- Vek: I'm a spirit. I'm allowed to be.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Fez and Vek discuss the notion of an entity's right to be overconfident. Turns out, The Best The First Halfling said \"Freedom is a right of all living beings.\" Fez agrees to 'companion' his friends to help Vek back onto the table. Amalia runs into the room, past the dissipated vapors of Eldar.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Amalia: Carlos, I can't be held responsible for what I'm about to do after you abandoned me in that cave-in only to come in here for a drink. ... Like I said, no one could blame me for not being able to hit.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Amalia hits him with a crossbow bolt which retains a tenebrous tether to her, which throbs with stolen life energy.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Amalia: I'll take from you the life that you denied to me!</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Do I hear the pitter-patter of my dear Hiero's feet.</div>\n<div>- Hiero: I just want to live my life, MAN!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Displacing his anger onto this new arrival, Hieronymus batters Amalia with his Karbunqlestaph. Hieronymus slides down his staff, sliced by the protruding thorns and lubricating it with blood. While being drained, Carlos, not his usual self, wiffs with his battleaxe and coughs unhelpfully. Then Rotrude comes in!&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Rotrude: We can finally tussle like we're used to. Just get those little hammy fists up, let me see what we can do!</div>\n<div>- Hiero: Hammy?&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>With her jagged, shredded nails she claws into Hieronymus, and where she slashes the monk his skin begins to bubble with blueish blisters, and a mild neuropathy settles into his limbs.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Rotrude: I hope you like this bit of torture I've devised. It allows for a bit more pain during our sparring.</div>\n<div>- Hiero: A touch of hurt, you say?</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Hiero squeezes a boil and a thick, blue liquid jets out and into Rotrude's eye, which immediately swells and takes on the cast of one of the boils themselves.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Rotrude: What have you done? This isn't what I agreed to!</div>\n<div>- Hiero: I'm sorry but it seems as though you broke the rules, and the gloves are off.</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: How interesting that you should say that!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Rotrude pulls off the skin of her hands up to the elbows, like gloves.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Rotrude: A duel it is, then!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Flick, worried about Carlos and attempting to suppress the revulsion at what she witnessed with Rotrude, closes to within two rods, shatters the very fabric of Amalia's being, and then shoots an arrow into Rotrude.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Is this part of the new techniques you mentioned?</div>\n<div>- Hiero: Stay still while I make a portrait of you!</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: You should use some fluid from the boils on your arm!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Jean-luc skips into the fray and delivers another deep wound.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Distance fighters look to be your main companions now?</div>\n<div>- Hiero: These are my followers; they haven't learned how to fight yet.</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc and Flick: Don't lump us in with him!</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Given the distance between all of you: we already have a strong friendship foundation; yet you all treat each other as the same pole on a magnet.</div>\n<div>- Fez (after a long delay): what's a magnet?</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: What about the concept of magnetism?</div>\n<div>- Fez: What? The compass points the direction. North.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Fez then \"applies\" a whipping.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Rotrude: I thought you said you were going to give me a solid whipping, not a one-and-done.</div>\n<div>- Fez: I genuinely thought you couldn't take another hit and felt pity for you.</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: I doubt that this human frame can withstand much more. In the monastery we are taught many ways to consider the human form.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: Yeah, well, to me, you look like an undead horror show.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Hieronymus, utterly fed up, tears the undead monk to pieces.</div>\n<div>- Hiero: Perhaps we shall meet again.</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Yes, we will always be twins, circling one another, like two halves of a symbolon.</div>\n<div>- Hiero: I'm not sure I would go that far.</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Would you go to the ends of the earth for me?</div>\n<div>- Hiero: Well, that's not that far.</div>\n<div>- Rotrude: Yes, the monastery taught us we live on a very very small, two-dimensional planet. Goodbye my hairy mouse!</div>\n<div>- Hiero: Goodbye my lovely serpent sister.</div>\n<div>- Flick (After a beat): Enough of that pervert shit.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>The gang listens intently for footsteps; Fez, glancing around the room, casts his eyes over Shoemaker, her greataxe, the skin of Rotrude's de-gloved hands. Flick dances sprightly over to Carlos and tries to draw any evil out of him and into the void.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Carlos: I think I just need to sleep for a long time -- regain my ruddy dwarven complexion -- and this will all go away like a bad dream.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Flick hands him a goodberry, and he chokes it down despite his nausea and Shoemaker's warnings. The wood elf then trips over to Shoemaker's body, determining for good that she's a bear only with opposable thumbs and the ability to walk upright with ease. Flick remembers that ordinary folks think of these things as ursothropes, but there doesn't appear to be any shapechanging going on, as such creatures are supposed to return to their \"default\" state at death.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Flick: What am I supposed to make of this!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>She's not a werecreature, and this is probably just her species, a kind of permanently hybrid species. [Int 1] She is from an ancient line of humans, from which druids \"evolved.\" Flick picks up 39 uncrushed goodberries which dropped out of Shoemaker's paws upon her earlier entrance. They are vines, like grapes -- not like the individual and separate berries she typically receives; they clearly grow somewhere, which she would never have guessed before. The one rotten goodberry that appeared at Castle Karn had really freaked her out.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Flick (mumbling to herself): Yes, the humans I know _are_ pretty hairy. I don't want to skin a sapient creature.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Her hand briefly touches some of the soil.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Vek: The berries, they grow around Shoemaker's house.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick: Sorry about trying to break your vase. Sorry about that.</div>\n<div>- Vek: That means a lot.</div>\n<div>- Flick: How did you get here? I had always heard that she lived near where I grew up. Did you take some kind of portal here?</div>\n<div>- Vek: My jar is in Shoemaker's basement. I'm not just waiting in there, though. People have to come by and invoke me. I'm always popping up all over the place.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Flick: so Shoemaker summoned you once she had tracked me down. If we were to scatter your soil, you'd be able to unbind and return whence you came.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Vek: Unbinding isn't a problem but I don't like to have unnecessary duplicates of myself hanging around.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Flick finagles the vase into the bag of holding, while Jean-luc notices that the kettle radiates indeterminate magic.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Carlos: Aule seems to think this is more druid magic rather than anything arcane.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Fez: Hey, I bet I know what that thing does. You take crabs, and boil them -- then the shells go all soft and you can get into the meat.</div>\n<div>- Jean-luc: I do enjoy a good seafood feast.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Jean-luc grabs some clarified alcohol in a distinctive bottle bearing a silver eight-pointed star etched into the bottle. Hiero goes over to Jean-luc, puts a chair behind him.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Hiero: Jean-luc, why don't you sit down for a second, there's something we have to talk about. [Jean-luc remains standing] I know that you think we came down here to fight some undead creatures, but actually this is an intervention. I'd like you to give me your bottles; i'll keep them safe. To make headway we need you at 100%, and you weren't really all that much help in the last bottle.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Jean-luc walks away stoically.&nbsp;</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>- Heiro: Suit yourself. If you ever want to talk, I'll be here.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Flick throws the departing rogue a goodberry. After eating the berry, Jean-luc's desire for drinking increases. Poking around behind the bar, he finds 70 gold in the till. Jean-luc, not looking to take money from a hardworking establishment underground in a creepy temple, leaves the gold. But, lying right in his line of sight, he sees a star matching the one on the bottle exactly, and he pockets it.</div>\n<div></div>"}
