{"_id":"pETxNBRjz3gdCeFm","name":"fake foreshadowing","permission":{"default":0,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3},"folder":"NdtTfwZe9YTsCoFv","sort":0,"flags":{},"content":"<h1 id=\"fakeforeshadowing\">fake foreshadowing ?</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>so that I may expose your true identity :: as a coward!</li>\n</ul>"}
{"_id":"pQ1lZ8p2yhC97ErE","name":"001. Marshboutwards","permission":{"default":2,"r4bmbG4VWpj9A47k":3},"folder":"czpWrAnwoEB0zrc0","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"<p><em>[Editor's note: Summaries contained herein have been faxed by Sun of Jupiter Publications (Bergillias branch) and converted with Ow!Crom-97Restore text recognition software to digital format before manual review and upload.]</em></p>\n<div><strong>Session: </strong>&sect;001 Marshboutwards</div>\n<div><strong>Played</strong>: September 21, 2019</div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-8f8e6d46-7fff-e346-4a37-0be41a6696d2\"></span></div>\n<div><strong>Day</strong>: Day 1</div>\n<div><strong>Level</strong>: Level 1</div>\n<div><hr /></div>\n<h1 id=\"recap\">Recap</h1>\n<p>In the city of Cressida, wood elf Flick approached Remy Flitch, a well-known crew leader, for information about an enigmatic statuette she&rsquo;d been carrying with her since adoption. Remy&rsquo;s thaumaturge Snav, after inspecting the artifact, grotesquely directed her to a &lsquo;Lupenna&rsquo; near the town of Marshbout. Remy, though annoyed by Flick&rsquo;s importunity, dispatched Joan &mdash; travelling to Marshbout on her own assignment &mdash; as a chaperone.</p>\n<p>They both made their way south without issue until their passage over a stone bridge was impeded by a deceptively adorable bearcublike creature sporting a single spiral horn on its forehead. Joan&rsquo;s attempts to platonically embrace the creature were misinterpreted as aggression, and she allowed herself to be flung to the side so as to spare it any embarrassment. Flick, evincing her trademark uncircumspect insistency, presented the creature with her onyx figurine. The Zorbo, upon touching the object, began to take on its material attributes (for such, they surmised, is the way of Zorbon), only to be afflicted by something far more powerful, and collapsed. They administered to the cub as best they were able, but only time and physical contact with its fieldstone home could help the cutie, so they proceeded apace to Marshbout.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, Drav, a dwarf wizard raised by elves in Forest Ogrelodge, adventured westward in order not just to meet more of, and learn the ways of, her race, but also to expand the ambit of her academic knowledge. At the foothills of the Steeple Peak Mountains, she was introduced to Carlos the Dwarf, a cleric about to travel to Marshbout to donate his healing expertise to the beleaguered community there.</p>\n<p>They were offered a ride by the stormless cloud giant Rufus Skyflume. After a day in his makeshift wagon surrounded by longhaired cloud cattle and a shorthaired favorite named Priscilla, they parted ways at Balach Pass when Rufus headed north to visit a family member. What should have been a half-a-day&rsquo;s march to town elongated somewhat when they passed by Mirror Lake, whose strange magic required that they swap some possessions before escaping its spatio-temporal loop. They arrived in Marshbout later that afternoon, and, while making their way to the Perch Office to send messenger owls with letters of safe arrival to their families, Drav sighted an enormous cat. When they inquired of the loquacious Perchmaster General Buddock as to any events or conditions requiring clerical ministration, he mentioned a few instances of exploding bodies and zombified cats, but could not comment as to the &lsquo;pig-sized&rsquo; feline of Drav&rsquo;s report. He was able to point them towards Norman Barrelchest, one of the town&rsquo;s constables (in charge of the armamentarium and responsible for ensuring the safety of the nearby highways).</p>\n<p><strong>&mdash; Swaddlington P. Footh</strong></p>\n<h1 id=\"transcript\">Transcript</h1>\n<p>[n/a]</p>"}
{"_id":"pVNGhMxLLwJbfLah","name":"mysteries","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"NdtTfwZe9YTsCoFv","sort":1000000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>where did all the goblins go?</p>"}
{"_id":"pemAz7hmioBCmifq","name":"page from ...","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"Cec7aiKp7sFrzQHB","sort":500000,"flags":{},"content":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">I returned to northeast Nicklefurrow (lit.: woodpecker furrow), where the thief, Bergna, by all accounts a greatly disfigured creature, stooped and scarred, was last seen. Prostrating myself in ritual abnegation, I dove into the seething whirlwind of </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">jukas</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">, the roiling signs left by the unsatisfied spirits who had passed by. A jagged promontory stabbed upwards out of the otherwise placid web; unmistakably, this was the chasm which that splinter of Sirmgalv </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">the Earthroot) carved through the tapestry of ghostly mundanity. Its frantic outline led unerringly south, seeking the great </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">leuqline </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(roughly: ley line) which unites the islands and makes landfall in Nicklefurrow. Near the north-west elbow of the </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">leuqline </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">the spear's fulgurous spoor sunk precipitously into the ground and out of sight. Confident I could mirror its path, I released myself from the ritual's grasp, but the sere afterimage of that ungodly weapon marched across my vision, and I took slow and uncertain steps south.</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-34b1cf7b-7fff-2227-e03b-1283bcecccb8\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">After a few hundred yards my sight cleared, and I began to stride as confidently as my tense frame would allow. Then, suddenly, I was pitched sideways into a greasy darkness, and felt tendrils of </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">drūzma </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(ghostflesh) wrap around my form. These wisps of spirit were angry, and raged impotently against a recent </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">blödveipr </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(trauma, lit.: blood scarf). Using what I had learned of the arts of </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">atraidīth </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(a discipline which effects the transfer of tranquility and pleasure to spirits) I calmed the frenzied host. — What ails you, </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">draught </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(roughly</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">:</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> (slang) ghost</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">-</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Georgia; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">friend)? Its answer came in fits and starts, but I learned that it was in life a young boy, disembodied only a few days previous, and made, in details I choose not to recount, to serve a demonic agenda of one it called Khelfaraz. If only this name had been strange to me, but alas, I had become well-acquainted with it over the last few weeks.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: right; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">— Lord Nydia Moenn, </span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">A Veridical and Truthful Ephemerides of the Adventures of Provisioners, Venturelings, Bonaventors, and Pieds Poudreux as recollected to the author</span><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">. Cressida: printed for the author by N. Culverkayes</span></p>"}
