{"_id":"sszIEE5BvOoDMhEx","name":"foodstuffs, herbs, medicine","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"NdtTfwZe9YTsCoFv","sort":800000,"flags":{},"content":"<ul>\n<li>pearmains</li>\n<li>pippins</li>\n<li>fitches</li>\n<li>verjuice</li>\n<li>perry (pear cider)</li>\n<li>something <strong>qualified </strong>(cooked) with oil</li>\n<li>a crapula (resin or drug producing intoxication and hangover)</li>\n<li>cicuta (water hemlock, very poisonous, not the 'hemlock' people usually mean when they refer to hemlock)</li>\n<li>aconitum (aeh cone EYE tum): a preparation or extract from root fo aconite, used as drug, medicine, or poison\n<ul>\n<li>\"aconitum is useful in catarrhs caused by exposure to a sharp and keen dry wind\"</li>\n<li>\"a dose of aconitum was administered, and soon afterwards Belladonna, in solution\"</li>\n<li>\"aconitum when the eyes are gritty and swollen\"</li>\n<li>\"someone has plundered his aftershave, spilled his bayberry, stolen his aconitum, and rummaged through his wardrobe\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>bayberry (fruit of the bay tree; like cloves); also called wax-myrtle, candleberry; similar to the sweet-gale\n<ul>\n<li>bayberry tallow: a fragrant green wax yielded by boiling berries in water, used for candlemaking</li>\n<li>leaves yield an \"agreeable perfume\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>hellebore: a plant valued for \"strong purgative properties\"\n<ul>\n<li>\"a good purgation for phrenticke [frantic; lunatic] heads\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>a costive: something that makes one constipated</li>\n<li>clyster: Also&nbsp;<strong>glister:</strong>&nbsp;an enema or suppository\n<ul>\n<li>\"to purge their black jaundice with a glister of ink\"</li>\n<li>\"for the last ten days of his life he was supported [alimented] by broth clysters\"</li>\n<li>\"clysters of the smoke of tobacco\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>fuliginous (adj): designating a noxious sooty vapor formed within the body by compused, of the humour melancholy, and excreted in breath or poors\n<ul>\n<li>\"tis not amisse to bore the skull with an instrument to let ou the fuliginous vapors\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>fomentation: putting warm flannels or other warm, soft medicinal substance, soaked in hot water and possibly medidcated, to the skin. also&nbsp;<strong>dry fomentation&nbsp;</strong>if it's dry.</li>\n<li>acopon: a remedy for waeriness or pain, typically a paste or oil\n<ul>\n<li>\"likewise young mice are employed to the same purpose, being brayed in a mortar with old wine to the consistence of those medicines which becalled acopa, and prepared to dissolve lassitudes\"</li>\n<li>\"old oil boiled to the temper and thickness of an Acopon, helpeth all vices of the nerves, and pain\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>copos: weariness or lassitude</li>\n<li>exagitate: to stir up (the humors, spitits) ; to quicken (the breathing); to set in motion (the blood) ; to excite\n<ul>\n<li>\"Business has exagitated my complexion to that exorbitancy of vermeille [red]\"&nbsp;</li>\n<li>of disease or pain: to torment, worry (\"exagitated with this same sore\")</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>exalgyn: an anodyne (ex + algos)</li>\n<li>chloral hydrate [anachronism note: not discovered until 1832]. produced by a chlorination reaction on ethanol. used as a knockout medication in asylums, clearing agent for chitin and fibers, ingredient in mounting mediums ro slides</li>\n<li>fluid aliments, such as broth and soops\n<ul>\n<li>\"true and improving aliments\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>quotes&nbsp;</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>at admission he was&nbsp;<strong>stuporose&nbsp;</strong>[numb; having impaired consciousness], somnolent, disoriented, and febrile</li>\n</ul>"}
{"_id":"tDso6IfGEGIWCsBr","name":"Iridium, Meteorite, Azurite","permission":{"default":0,"akeJDKtMsE0KHFKm":3},"folder":"srmjxCv4QHqVw5AK","sort":1700001,"flags":{},"content":"<ul>\n<li>\n<div>Vengeance's qi (and the influence of the salamander) is what set off the iridium ingot\n<ul>\n<li>this way we can relate his qi to the story</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>there are fossils in the sea coves that show the same kind of mutations seen in gorph? but mostly the fish that had begun dying in Uugeet's cave.</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>flick experiences more vampirism in the ethereal plane around the left-over iridium / meteorite traces (how would there be any left, though)</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Breg the geomancer weighs in</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Drav hears from Eldar&nbsp;</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Azurite</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>the Fading Stone</li>\n<li>Ruhu family were the ones who noticed it when they were mining the Iridium for the Gaol Maidens, so they claimed the first rights&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Breg is there as a ... ? independent observer? monitor? not quite sure -- wouldn't her \"mining\" things make it go a lot faster?&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Why is a lizardfolk shaman working with the Gaol Maidens and a human family (why don't they have their own shaman?)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Ruhu</h2>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">probably a mother &amp; father, grandparent (Fundi) , kids Aba and Haigy, and the dad's cousin or something</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Mother's grandmother Fundi</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Father</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Mother</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">daughter Aba</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">brother Haigy</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">dad's cousin (kid's cousin once removed)&nbsp; / spirit person Nyakatagara</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">lizardfolk handler</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">salamander</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3d681741-7fff-aba2-622e-7ec816a9c005\">why are they mining at night?</span><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3d681741-7fff-aba2-622e-7ec816a9c005\">technically it's the town's mines ? getting some kind of ore</span><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3d681741-7fff-aba2-622e-7ec816a9c005\">-- are they working with / against the druid archeologists?</span><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3d681741-7fff-aba2-622e-7ec816a9c005\">- maybe one of the archaeologists is trading with them unbeknownst to the others</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Nyuka</h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">one of the diviners he used lost their connection with their connection to the divine and is giving bad (corrupt) information</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">reversal : and now that diviner is sad, so is giving people really bad news (because of some kind of sadness &ldquo;mist&rdquo; over their eyes)</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">have to rekindle the connection between them and themselves as a vessel</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">why did connection to the divine get disrupted ?</p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d8475968-7fff-4a96-d311-3c0e70a6830b\"></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&hellip; part of the larger thing (it's more difficult here -- getting a lot of interference)</p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">Breg</h2>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Breg thinks the interference is from the lava, but it's from this iridium, which even hides its own source (oh -- the combined effect of the fading stone and the iridium)</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">- which means Laska is super forgetful now if Flick beast senses her</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3d681741-7fff-aba2-622e-7ec816a9c005\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3d681741-7fff-aba2-622e-7ec816a9c005\"></span></p>"}
